P_HTM[2013]="*‘appassādā, āvuso, kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo.**‘Reverend, the Buddha says that sensual pleasures give little gratification and much suffering and distress, and they are all the more full of drawbacks.*";
P_HTM[2014]="*Aṭṭhikaṅkalūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo.**With the simile of a skeleton …*";
P_HTM[2015]="*Maṃsapesūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … pe … tiṇukkūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … aṅgārakāsūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … supinakūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … yācitakūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … rukkhaphalūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … asisūnūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … sattisūlūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … sappasirūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo.**a lump of meat … a grass torch … a pit of glowing coals … a dream … borrowed goods … fruit on a tree … a butcher’s knife and chopping block … a staking sword … a snake’s head, the Buddha says that sensual pleasures give little gratification and much suffering and distress, and they are all the more full of drawbacks.*";
P_HTM[2016]="*Abhiramatāyasmā brahmacariye;**Be happy with the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[2017]="*māyasmā sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattī’ti.**Venerable, please don’t declare your inability to continue training, reject it and return to a lesser life.’*";
P_HTM[2018]="*So sabrahmacārīhi evaṃ ovadiyamāno evaṃ anusāsiyamāno evamāha:**When thus advised and instructed by his spiritual companions, he says:*";
P_HTM[2019]="*‘ussahissāmi, āvuso, vāyamissāmi, āvuso, abhiramissāmi, āvuso.**‘I’ll try, reverends, I’ll struggle, I’ll be happy.*";
P_HTM[2020]="*Na dānāhaṃ, āvuso, sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattissāmī’ti.**I won’t now declare my inability to continue training, reject it and return to a lesser life.’*";
P_HTM[2021]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, yodhājīvo asicammaṃ gahetvā dhanukalāpaṃ sannayhitvā viyūḷhaṃ saṅgāmaṃ otarati, so tasmiṃ saṅgāme ussahati vāyamati, tamenaṃ ussahantaṃ vāyamantaṃ pare upalikkhanti, tamenaṃ apanenti; apanetvā ñātakānaṃ nenti, tamenaṃ ñātakā upaṭṭhahanti paricaranti. So ñātakehi upaṭṭhahiyamāno paricariyamāno vuṭṭhāti tamhā ābādhā; tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.**I say that this person is like the warrior who recovers from his injuries while in the care of his relatives.*";
P_HTM[2022]="*Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo hoti.**Some people are like that.*";
P_HTM[2023]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho yodhājīvūpamo puggalo santo saṃvijjamāno bhikkhūsu.**This is the fourth person similar to a warrior found among the monks.*";
P_HTM[2024]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā upanissāya viharati.**Furthermore, a mendicant lives supported by a town or village.*";
P_HTM[2025]="*So pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya tameva gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya pavisati rakkhiteneva kāyena rakkhitāya vācāya rakkhitena cittena upaṭṭhitāya satiyā saṃvutehi indriyehi.**He robes up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, enters a village or town, guarding body, speech, and mind, establishing mindfulness, and restraining the sense faculties.*";
P_HTM[2026]="*So cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī.**Seeing a sight with his eyes, he doesn’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[2027]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati; rakkhati cakkhundriyaṃ; cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of sight were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, he practices restraint, protecting the faculty of sight, and achieving restraint over it.*";
P_HTM[2028]="*Sotena saddaṃ sutvā …**Hearing a sound with his ears …*";
P_HTM[2029]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …**Smelling an odor with his nose …*";
P_HTM[2030]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …**Tasting a flavor with his tongue …*";
P_HTM[2031]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …**Feeling a touch with his body …*";
P_HTM[2032]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī.**Knowing a thought with his mind, he doesn’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[2033]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati; rakkhati manindriyaṃ; manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of mind were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, he practices restraint, protecting the faculty of mind, and achieving restraint over it.*";
P_HTM[2034]="*So pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto**Then after the meal, on his return from alms-round,*";
P_HTM[2035]="*vivittaṃ senāsanaṃ bhajati araññaṃ rukkhamūlaṃ pabbataṃ kandaraṃ giriguhaṃ susānaṃ vanapatthaṃ abbhokāsaṃ palālapuñjaṃ.**he frequents a secluded lodging—a wilderness, the root of a tree, a hill, a ravine, a mountain cave, a charnel ground, a forest, the open air, a heap of straw.*";
P_HTM[2036]="*So araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**Gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut, he sits down cross-legged, with his body straight, and establishes mindfulness right there.*";
P_HTM[2037]="*So abhijjhaṃ loke pahāya … pe … so ime pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe**He gives up these five hindrances, corruptions of the heart that weaken wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2038]="*vivicceva kāmehi … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**Then, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, he enters and remains in the first absorption … second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption.*";
P_HTM[2039]="*So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti.**When his mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—he extends it toward knowledge of the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[2040]="*So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāti.**He truly understands: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’. He truly understands: ‘These are defilements’ … ‘This is the origin of defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of defilements’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of defilements’. Knowing and seeing like this, his mind is freed from the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance. When freed, he knows ‘it is freed’. He understands: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’*";
P_HTM[2041]="*Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, yodhājīvo asicammaṃ gahetvā dhanukalāpaṃ sannayhitvā viyūḷhaṃ saṅgāmaṃ otarati, so taṃ saṅgāmaṃ abhivijinitvā vijitasaṅgāmo tameva saṅgāmasīsaṃ ajjhāvasati; tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.**I say that this person is like the warrior who dons his sword and shield, fastens his bow and arrows, and plunges into the thick of battle. He wins victory in battle, establishing himself as foremost in battle.*";
P_HTM[2042]="*Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo hoti.**Some people are like that.*";
P_HTM[2043]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo yodhājīvūpamo puggalo santo saṃvijjamāno bhikkhūsu.**This is the fifth person similar to a warrior found among the monks.*";
P_HTM[2044]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca yodhājīvūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā bhikkhūsū”ti.**These five people similar to warriors are found among the monks.”*";
P_HTM[2045]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2046]="*7. Paṭhamaanāgatabhayasuttaṃ**Future Perils (1st)*";
P_HTM[2047]="*“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, anāgatabhayāni sampassamānena alameva āraññikena bhikkhunā appamattena ātāpinā pahitattena viharituṃ appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya.**“Mendicants, seeing these five future perils is quite enough for a wilderness mendicant to meditate diligently, keenly, and resolutely for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized.*";
P_HTM[2048]="*Katamāni pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2049]="*Idha, bhikkhave, āraññiko bhikkhu iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Firstly, a wilderness mendicant reflects:*";
P_HTM[2050]="*‘ahaṃ kho etarahi ekako araññe viharāmi.**‘Currently I’m living alone in a wilderness.*";
P_HTM[2051]="*Ekakaṃ kho pana maṃ araññe viharantaṃ ahi vā maṃ ḍaṃseyya, vicchiko vā maṃ ḍaṃseyya, satapadī vā maṃ ḍaṃseyya, tena me assa kālaṃkiriyā, so mamassa antarāyo;**While living here alone I might get bitten by a snake, a scorpion, or a centipede. That’d kill me, which would stop my practice.*";
P_HTM[2052]="*handāhaṃ vīriyaṃ ārabhāmi appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāyā’ti.**I’d better rouse up energy for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized.’*";
P_HTM[2053]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamaṃ anāgatabhayaṃ sampassamānena alameva āraññikena bhikkhunā appamattena ātāpinā pahitattena viharituṃ appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya.**This is the first future peril …*";
P_HTM[2054]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, āraññiko bhikkhu iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Furthermore, a wilderness mendicant reflects:*";
P_HTM[2055]="*‘ahaṃ kho etarahi ekako araññe viharāmi.**‘Currently I’m living alone in a wilderness.*";
P_HTM[2056]="*Ekako kho panāhaṃ araññe viharanto upakkhalitvā vā papateyyaṃ, bhattaṃ vā bhuttaṃ me byāpajjeyya, pittaṃ vā me kuppeyya, semhaṃ vā me kuppeyya, satthakā vā me vātā kuppeyyuṃ, tena me assa kālaṅkiriyā, so mamassa antarāyo;**While living here alone I might stumble and fall, or get food poisoning, or my bile or phlegm or stabbing wind might get upset. That’d kill me, which would stop my practice.*";
P_HTM[2057]="*handāhaṃ vīriyaṃ ārabhāmi appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāyā’ti.**I’d better rouse up energy for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized.’*";
P_HTM[2058]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyaṃ anāgatabhayaṃ sampassamānena alameva āraññikena bhikkhunā appamattena ātāpinā pahitattena viharituṃ appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya.**This is the second future peril …*";
P_HTM[2059]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, āraññiko bhikkhu iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Furthermore, a wilderness mendicant reflects:*";
P_HTM[2060]="*‘ahaṃ kho etarahi ekako araññe viharāmi.**‘Currently I’m living alone in a wilderness.*";
P_HTM[2061]="*Ekako kho panāhaṃ araññe viharanto vāḷehi samāgaccheyyaṃ, sīhena vā byagghena vā dīpinā vā acchena vā taracchena vā, te maṃ jīvitā voropeyyuṃ, tena me assa kālaṅkiriyā, so mamassa antarāyo;**While living here alone I might encounter wild beasts—a lion, a tiger, a leopard, a bear, or a hyena—which might take my life. That’d kill me, which would stop my practice.*";
P_HTM[2062]="*handāhaṃ vīriyaṃ ārabhāmi appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāyā’ti.**I’d better rouse up energy for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized.’*";
P_HTM[2063]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyaṃ anāgatabhayaṃ sampassamānena alameva āraññikena bhikkhunā appamattena ātāpinā pahitattena viharituṃ appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya.**This is the third future peril …*";
P_HTM[2064]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, āraññiko bhikkhu iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Furthermore, a wilderness mendicant reflects:*";
P_HTM[2065]="*‘ahaṃ kho etarahi ekako araññe viharāmi.**‘Currently I’m living alone in a wilderness.*";
P_HTM[2066]="*Ekako kho panāhaṃ araññe viharanto māṇavehi samāgaccheyyaṃ katakammehi vā akatakammehi vā, te maṃ jīvitā voropeyyuṃ, tena me assa kālaṅkiriyā, so mamassa antarāyo;**While living here alone I might encounter youths escaping a crime or on their way to commit one, and they might take my life. That’d kill me, which would stop my practice.*";
P_HTM[2067]="*handāhaṃ vīriyaṃ ārabhāmi appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāyā’ti.**I’d better rouse up energy for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized.’*";
P_HTM[2068]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, catutthaṃ anāgatabhayaṃ sampassamānena alameva āraññikena bhikkhunā appamattena ātāpinā pahitattena viharituṃ appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya.**This is the fourth future peril …*";
P_HTM[2069]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, āraññiko bhikkhu iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Furthermore, a wilderness mendicant reflects:*";
P_HTM[2070]="*‘ahaṃ kho etarahi ekako araññe viharāmi.**‘Currently I’m living alone in a wilderness.*";
P_HTM[2071]="*Santi kho panāraññe vāḷā amanussā, te maṃ jīvitā voropeyyuṃ, tena me assa kālaṃkiriyā, so mamassa antarāyo;**But in a wilderness there are savage monsters who might take my life. That’d kill me, which would stop my practice.*";
P_HTM[2072]="*handāhaṃ vīriyaṃ ārabhāmi appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāyā’ti.**I’d better rouse up energy for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized.’*";
P_HTM[2073]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamaṃ anāgatabhayaṃ sampassamānena alameva āraññikena bhikkhunā appamattena ātāpinā pahitattena viharituṃ appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya.**This is the fifth future peril …*";
P_HTM[2074]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca anāgatabhayāni sampassamānena alameva āraññikena bhikkhunā appamattena ātāpinā pahitattena viharituṃ appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāyā”ti.**These are the five future perils, seeing which is quite enough for a wilderness mendicant to meditate diligently, keenly, and resolutely for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized.”*";
P_HTM[2075]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2076]="*8. Dutiyaanāgatabhayasuttaṃ**Future Perils (2nd)*";
P_HTM[2077]="*“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, anāgatabhayāni sampassamānena alameva bhikkhunā appamattena ātāpinā pahitattena viharituṃ appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya.**“Mendicants, seeing these five future perils is quite enough for a wilderness mendicant to meditate diligently, keenly, and resolutely for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized.*";
P_HTM[2078]="*Katamāni pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2079]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu iti paṭisañcikkhati:**An offending mendicant reflects:*";
P_HTM[2080]="*‘ahaṃ kho etarahi daharo yuvā susukāḷakeso bhadrena yobbanena samannāgato paṭhamena vayasā.**‘Currently I’m a youth, young, black-haired, blessed with youth, in the prime of life.*";
P_HTM[2081]="*Hoti kho pana so samayo yaṃ imaṃ kāyaṃ jarā phusati.**But there will come a time when this body is struck with old age.*";
P_HTM[2082]="*Jiṇṇena kho pana jarāya abhibhūtena na sukaraṃ buddhānaṃ sāsanaṃ manasi kātuṃ, na sukarāni araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevituṃ.**When you’re old, overcome by old age, it’s not easy to focus on the instructions of the Buddhas, and it’s not easy to frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.*";
P_HTM[2083]="*Purā maṃ so dhammo āgacchati aniṭṭho akanto amanāpo;**Before that unlikable, undesirable, and disagreeable thing happens,*";
P_HTM[2084]="*handāhaṃ paṭikacceva vīriyaṃ ārabhāmi appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya, yenāhaṃ dhammena samannāgato jiṇṇakopi phāsuṃ viharissāmī’ti.**I’d better preempt it by rousing up energy for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized. That way, when it happens, I’ll live comfortably even though I’m old.’*";
P_HTM[2085]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamaṃ anāgatabhayaṃ sampassamānena alameva bhikkhunā appamattena ātāpinā pahitattena viharituṃ appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya.**This is the first future peril …*";
P_HTM[2086]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Furthermore, a wilderness mendicant reflects:*";
P_HTM[2087]="*‘ahaṃ kho etarahi appābādho appātaṅko samavepākiniyā gahaṇiyā samannāgato nātisītāya nāccuṇhāya majjhimāya padhānakkhamāya.**‘Currently, I’m rarely ill or unwell. My stomach digests well, being neither too hot nor too cold, but just right, and fit for meditation.*";
P_HTM[2088]="*Hoti kho pana so samayo yaṃ imaṃ kāyaṃ byādhi phusati.**But there will come a time when this body is struck with sickness.*";
P_HTM[2089]="*Byādhitena kho pana byādhinā abhibhūtena na sukaraṃ buddhānaṃ sāsanaṃ manasi kātuṃ, na sukarāni araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevituṃ.**When you’re sick, overcome by sickness, it’s not easy to focus on the instructions of the Buddhas, and it’s not easy to frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.*";
P_HTM[2090]="*Purā maṃ so dhammo āgacchati aniṭṭho akanto amanāpo;**Before that unlikable, undesirable, and disagreeable thing happens,*";
P_HTM[2091]="*handāhaṃ paṭikacceva vīriyaṃ ārabhāmi appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya, yenāhaṃ dhammena samannāgato byādhitopi phāsuṃ viharissāmī’ti.**I’d better preempt it by rousing up energy for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized. That way, when it happens, I’ll live comfortably even though I’m sick.’*";
P_HTM[2092]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyaṃ anāgatabhayaṃ sampassamānena alameva bhikkhunā appamattena ātāpinā pahitattena viharituṃ appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya.**This is the second future peril …*";
P_HTM[2093]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Furthermore, a wilderness mendicant reflects:*";
P_HTM[2094]="*‘etarahi kho subhikkhaṃ susassaṃ sulabhapiṇḍaṃ, sukaraṃ uñchena paggahena yāpetuṃ.**‘Currently, there’s plenty of food, a good harvest, so it’s easy to get alms-food, and easy to keep going by collecting alms.*";
P_HTM[2095]="*Hoti kho pana so samayo yaṃ dubbhikkhaṃ hoti dussassaṃ dullabhapiṇḍaṃ, na sukaraṃ uñchena paggahena yāpetuṃ.**But there will come a time of famine, a bad harvest, when it’s hard to get alms-food, and not easy to keep going by collecting alms.*";
P_HTM[2096]="*Dubbhikkhe kho pana manussā yena subhikkhaṃ tena saṅkamanti.**In a time of famine, people move to where there’s plenty of food,*";
P_HTM[2097]="*Tattha saṅgaṇikavihāro hoti ākiṇṇavihāro.**where they live crowded and cramped together.*";
P_HTM[2098]="*Saṅgaṇikavihāre kho pana sati ākiṇṇavihāre na sukaraṃ buddhānaṃ sāsanaṃ manasi kātuṃ, na sukarāni araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevituṃ.**When you live crowded and cramped together, it’s not easy to focus on the instructions of the Buddhas, and it’s not easy to frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.*";
P_HTM[2099]="*Purā maṃ so dhammo āgacchati aniṭṭho akanto amanāpo;**Before that unlikable, undesirable, and disagreeable thing happens,*";
P_HTM[2100]="*handāhaṃ paṭikacceva vīriyaṃ ārabhāmi appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya, yenāhaṃ dhammena samannāgato dubbhikkhepi phāsu viharissāmī’ti.**I’d better preempt it by rousing up energy for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized. That way, when it happens, I’ll live comfortably even though there’s a famine.’*";
P_HTM[2101]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyaṃ anāgatabhayaṃ sampassamānena alameva bhikkhunā appamattena ātāpinā pahitattena viharituṃ appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya.**This is the third future peril …*";
P_HTM[2102]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Furthermore, a wilderness mendicant reflects:*";
P_HTM[2103]="*‘etarahi kho manussā samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā khīrodakībhūtā aññamaññaṃ piyacakkhūhi sampassantā viharanti.**‘Currently, people live in harmony, appreciating each other, without quarreling, blending like milk and water, and regarding each other with kindly eyes.*";
P_HTM[2104]="*Hoti kho pana so samayo yaṃ bhayaṃ hoti aṭavisaṅkopo, cakkasamārūḷhā jānapadā pariyāyanti.**But there will come a time of peril from wild savages, when the countryfolk mount their vehicles and flee everywhere.*";
P_HTM[2105]="*Bhaye kho pana sati manussā yena khemaṃ tena saṅkamanti.**In a time of peril, people move to where there’s sanctuary,*";
P_HTM[2106]="*Tattha saṅgaṇikavihāro hoti ākiṇṇavihāro.**where they live crowded and cramped together.*";
P_HTM[2107]="*Saṅgaṇikavihāre kho pana sati ākiṇṇavihāre na sukaraṃ buddhānaṃ sāsanaṃ manasi kātuṃ, na sukarāni araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevituṃ.**When you live crowded and cramped together, it’s not easy to focus on the instructions of the Buddhas, and it’s not easy to frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.*";
P_HTM[2108]="*Purā maṃ so dhammo āgacchati aniṭṭho akanto amanāpo;**Before that unlikable, undesirable, and disagreeable thing happens,*";
P_HTM[2109]="*handāhaṃ paṭikacceva vīriyaṃ ārabhāmi appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya, yenāhaṃ dhammena samannāgato bhayepi phāsuṃ viharissāmī’ti.**I’d better preempt it by rousing up energy for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized. That way, when it happens, I’ll live comfortably even in a time of peril.’*";
P_HTM[2110]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, catutthaṃ anāgatabhayaṃ sampassamānena alameva bhikkhunā appamattena ātāpinā pahitattena viharituṃ appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya.**This is the fourth future peril …*";
P_HTM[2111]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu iti paṭisañcikkhati:**Furthermore, a wilderness mendicant reflects:*";
P_HTM[2112]="*‘etarahi kho saṅgho samaggo sammodamāno avivadamāno ekuddeso phāsu viharati.**‘Currently, the Saṅgha lives comfortably, in harmony, appreciating each other, without quarreling, with one recitation.*";
P_HTM[2113]="*Hoti kho pana so samayo yaṃ saṅgho bhijjati.**But there will come a time of schism in the Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[2114]="*Saṅghe kho pana bhinne na sukaraṃ buddhānaṃ sāsanaṃ manasi kātuṃ, na sukarāni araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevituṃ.**When there is schism in the Saṅgha, it’s not easy to focus on the instructions of the Buddhas, and it’s not easy to frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.*";
P_HTM[2115]="*Purā maṃ so dhammo āgacchati aniṭṭho akanto amanāpo;**Before that unlikable, undesirable, and disagreeable thing happens,*";
P_HTM[2116]="*handāhaṃ paṭikacceva vīriyaṃ ārabhāmi appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya, yenāhaṃ dhammena samannāgato bhinnepi saṅghe phāsuṃ viharissāmī’ti.**I’d better preempt it by rousing up energy for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized. That way, when it happens, I’ll live comfortably even though there’s schism in the Saṅgha.’*";
P_HTM[2117]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamaṃ anāgatabhayaṃ sampassamānena alameva bhikkhunā appamattena ātāpinā pahitattena viharituṃ appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya.**This is the fifth future peril …*";
P_HTM[2118]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca anāgatabhayāni sampassamānena alameva bhikkhunā appamattena ātāpinā pahitattena viharituṃ appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāyā”ti.**These are the five future perils, seeing which is quite enough for a wilderness mendicant to meditate diligently, keenly, and resolutely for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized.”*";
P_HTM[2119]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2120]="*9. Tatiyaanāgatabhayasuttaṃ**Future Perils (3rd)*";
P_HTM[2121]="*“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, anāgatabhayāni etarahi asamuppannāni āyatiṃ samuppajjissanti.**“Mendicants, these five future perils have not currently arisen, but they will arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[2122]="*Tāni vo paṭibujjhitabbāni;**You should look out for them*";
P_HTM[2123]="*paṭibujjhitvā ca tesaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.**and try to give them up.*";
P_HTM[2124]="*Katamāni pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2125]="*Bhavissanti, bhikkhave, bhikkhū anāgatamaddhānaṃ abhāvitakāyā abhāvitasīlā abhāvitacittā abhāvitapaññā.**In a future time there will be mendicants who have not developed their physical endurance, ethics, mind, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2126]="*Te abhāvitakāyā samānā abhāvitasīlā abhāvitacittā abhāvitapaññā aññe upasampādessanti.**They will ordain others,*";
P_HTM[2127]="*Tepi na sakkhissanti vinetuṃ adhisīle adhicitte adhipaññāya.**but be unable to guide them in the higher ethics, mind, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2128]="*Tepi bhavissanti abhāvitakāyā abhāvitasīlā abhāvitacittā abhāvitapaññā.**They too will not develop their physical endurance, ethics, mind, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2129]="*Te abhāvitakāyā samānā abhāvitasīlā abhāvitacittā abhāvitapaññā aññe upasampādessanti.**They too will ordain others,*";
P_HTM[2130]="*Tepi na sakkhissanti vinetuṃ adhisīle adhicitte adhipaññāya.**but be unable to guide them in the higher ethics, mind, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2131]="*Tepi bhavissanti abhāvitakāyā abhāvitasīlā abhāvitacittā abhāvitapaññā.**They too will not develop their physical endurance, ethics, mind, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2132]="*Iti kho, bhikkhave, dhammasandosā vinayasandoso;**And that is how corrupt training comes from corrupt teachings,*";
P_HTM[2133]="*vinayasandosā dhammasandoso.**and corrupt teachings come from corrupt training.*";
P_HTM[2134]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamaṃ anāgatabhayaṃ etarahi asamuppannaṃ āyatiṃ samuppajjissati.**This is the first future peril that has not currently arisen, but will arise in the future …*";
P_HTM[2135]="*Taṃ vo paṭibujjhitabbaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2136]="*paṭibujjhitvā ca tassa pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2137]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhavissanti bhikkhū anāgatamaddhānaṃ abhāvitakāyā abhāvitasīlā abhāvitacittā abhāvitapaññā.**Furthermore, in a future time there will be mendicants who have not developed their physical endurance, ethics, mind, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2138]="*Te abhāvitakāyā samānā abhāvitasīlā abhāvitacittā abhāvitapaññā aññesaṃ nissayaṃ dassanti.**They will give dependence to others,*";
P_HTM[2139]="*Tepi na sakkhissanti vinetuṃ adhisīle adhicitte adhipaññāya.**but be unable to guide them in the higher ethics, mind, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2140]="*Tepi bhavissanti abhāvitakāyā abhāvitasīlā abhāvitacittā abhāvitapaññā.**They too will not develop their physical endurance, ethics, mind, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2141]="*Te abhāvitakāyā samānā abhāvitasīlā abhāvitacittā abhāvitapaññā aññesaṃ nissayaṃ dassanti.**They too will give dependence to others,*";
P_HTM[2142]="*Tepi na sakkhissanti vinetuṃ adhisīle adhicitte adhipaññāya.**but be unable to guide them in the higher ethics, mind, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2143]="*Tepi bhavissanti abhāvitakāyā abhāvitasīlā abhāvitacittā abhāvitapaññā.**They too will not develop their physical endurance, ethics, mind, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2144]="*Iti kho, bhikkhave, dhammasandosā vinayasandoso;**And that is how corrupt training comes from corrupt teachings,*";
P_HTM[2145]="*vinayasandosā dhammasandoso.**and corrupt teachings come from corrupt training.*";
P_HTM[2146]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyaṃ anāgatabhayaṃ etarahi asamuppannaṃ āyatiṃ samuppajjissati.**This is the second future peril that has not currently arisen, but will arise in the future …*";
P_HTM[2147]="*Taṃ vo paṭibujjhitabbaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2148]="*paṭibujjhitvā ca tassa pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2149]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhavissanti bhikkhū anāgatamaddhānaṃ abhāvitakāyā abhāvitasīlā abhāvitacittā abhāvitapaññā.**Furthermore, in a future time there will be mendicants who have not developed their physical endurance, ethics, mind, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2150]="*Te abhāvitakāyā samānā abhāvitasīlā abhāvitacittā abhāvitapaññā abhidhammakathaṃ vedallakathaṃ kathentā kaṇhadhammaṃ okkamamānā na bujjhissanti.**In discussion about the teachings and classifications they’ll fall into dark ideas without realizing it.*";
P_HTM[2151]="*Iti kho, bhikkhave, dhammasandosā vinayasandoso;**And that is how corrupt training comes from corrupt teachings,*";
P_HTM[2152]="*vinayasandosā dhammasandoso.**and corrupt teachings come from corrupt training.*";
P_HTM[2153]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyaṃ anāgatabhayaṃ etarahi asamuppannaṃ āyatiṃ samuppajjissati.**This is the third future peril that has not currently arisen, but will arise in the future …*";
P_HTM[2154]="*Taṃ vo paṭibujjhitabbaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2155]="*paṭibujjhitvā ca tassa pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2156]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhavissanti bhikkhū anāgatamaddhānaṃ abhāvitakāyā abhāvitasīlā abhāvitacittā abhāvitapaññā.**Furthermore, in a future time there will be mendicants who have not developed their physical endurance, ethics, mind, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2157]="*Te abhāvitakāyā samānā abhāvitasīlā abhāvitacittā abhāvitapaññā ye te suttantā tathāgatabhāsitā gambhīrā gambhīratthā lokuttarā suññatāppaṭisaṃyuttā, tesu bhaññamānesu na sussūsissanti, na sotaṃ odahissanti, na aññā cittaṃ upaṭṭhapessanti, na ca te dhamme uggahetabbaṃ pariyāpuṇitabbaṃ maññissanti.**When discourses spoken by the Realized One—deep, profound, transcendent, dealing with emptiness—are being recited they won’t want to listen. They won’t pay attention or apply their minds to understand them, nor will they think those teachings are worth learning and memorizing.*";
P_HTM[2158]="*Ye pana te suttantā kavitā kāveyyā cittakkharā cittabyañjanā bāhirakā sāvakabhāsitā, tesu bhaññamānesu sussūsissanti, sotaṃ odahissanti, aññā cittaṃ upaṭṭhapessanti, te ca dhamme uggahetabbaṃ pariyāpuṇitabbaṃ maññissanti.**But when discourses composed by poets—poetry, with fancy words and phrases, composed by outsiders or spoken by disciples—are being recited they will want to listen. They’ll pay attention and apply their minds to understand them, and they’ll think those teachings are worth learning and memorizing.*";
P_HTM[2159]="*Iti kho, bhikkhave, dhammasandosā vinayasandoso;**And that is how corrupt training comes from corrupt teachings,*";
P_HTM[2160]="*vinayasandosā dhammasandoso.**and corrupt teachings come from corrupt training.*";
P_HTM[2161]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, catutthaṃ anāgatabhayaṃ etarahi asamuppannaṃ āyatiṃ samuppajjissati.**This is the fourth future peril that has not currently arisen, but will arise in the future …*";
P_HTM[2162]="*Taṃ vo paṭibujjhitabbaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2163]="*paṭibujjhitvā ca tassa pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2164]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhavissanti bhikkhū anāgatamaddhānaṃ abhāvitakāyā abhāvitasīlā abhāvitacittā abhāvitapaññā.**Furthermore, in a future time there will be mendicants who have not developed their physical endurance, ethics, mind, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2165]="*Te abhāvitakāyā samānā abhāvitasīlā abhāvitacittā abhāvitapaññā therā bhikkhū bāhulikā bhavissanti sāthalikā okkamane pubbaṅgamā paviveke nikkhittadhurā, na vīriyaṃ ārabhissanti appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya.**The senior mendicants will be indulgent and slack, leaders in backsliding, neglecting seclusion, not rousing energy for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized.*";
P_HTM[2166]="*Tesaṃ pacchimā janatā diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjissati.**Those who come after them will follow their example.*";
P_HTM[2167]="*Sāpi bhavissati bāhulikā sāthalikā okkamane pubbaṅgamā paviveke nikkhittadhurā, na vīriyaṃ ārabhissati appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya.**They too will become indulgent and slack, leaders in backsliding, neglecting seclusion, not rousing energy for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized.*";
P_HTM[2168]="*Iti kho, bhikkhave, dhammasandosā vinayasandoso;**And that is how corrupt training comes from corrupt teachings,*";
P_HTM[2169]="*vinayasandosā dhammasandoso.**and corrupt teachings come from corrupt training.*";
P_HTM[2170]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamaṃ anāgatabhayaṃ etarahi asamuppannaṃ āyatiṃ samuppajjissati.**This is the fifth future peril that has not currently arisen, but will arise in the future …*";
P_HTM[2171]="*Taṃ vo paṭibujjhitabbaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2172]="*paṭibujjhitvā ca tassa pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2173]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca anāgatabhayāni etarahi asamuppannāni āyatiṃ samuppajjissanti.**These are the five future perils that have not currently arisen, but will arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[2174]="*Tāni vo paṭibujjhitabbāni;**You should look out for them,*";
P_HTM[2175]="*paṭibujjhitvā ca tesaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabban”ti.**and try to give them up.”*";
P_HTM[2176]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2177]="*10. Catutthaanāgatabhayasuttaṃ**Future Perils (4th)*";
P_HTM[2178]="*“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, anāgatabhayāni etarahi asamuppannāni āyatiṃ samuppajjissanti.**“Mendicants, these five future perils have not currently arisen, but they will arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[2179]="*Tāni vo paṭibujjhitabbāni;**You should look out for them*";
P_HTM[2180]="*paṭibujjhitvā ca tesaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.**and try to give them up.*";
P_HTM[2181]="*Katamāni pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2182]="*Bhavissanti, bhikkhave, bhikkhū anāgatamaddhānaṃ cīvare kalyāṇakāmā.**In a future time there will be mendicants who like nice robes.*";
P_HTM[2183]="*Te cīvare kalyāṇakāmā samānā riñcissanti paṃsukūlikattaṃ, riñcissanti araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni;**They will neglect the practice of wearing rag robes and the practice of frequenting remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.*";
P_HTM[2184]="*gāmanigamarājadhānīsu osaritvā vāsaṃ kappessanti, cīvarahetu ca anekavihitaṃ anesanaṃ appatirūpaṃ āpajjissanti.**They will come down to the villages, towns, and capital cities and make their homes there. And they will try to get robes in many kinds of wrong and inappropriate ways.*";
P_HTM[2185]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamaṃ anāgatabhayaṃ etarahi asamuppannaṃ āyatiṃ samuppajjissati.**This is the first future peril that has not currently arisen, but will arise in the future …*";
P_HTM[2186]="*Taṃ vo paṭibujjhitabbaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2187]="*paṭibujjhitvā ca tassa pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2188]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhavissanti bhikkhū anāgatamaddhānaṃ piṇḍapāte kalyāṇakāmā.**Furthermore, in a future time there will be mendicants who like nice alms-food.*";
P_HTM[2189]="*Te piṇḍapāte kalyāṇakāmā samānā riñcissanti piṇḍapātikattaṃ, riñcissanti araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni;**They will neglect the practice of walking for alms-food and the practice of frequenting remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.*";
P_HTM[2190]="*gāmanigamarājadhānīsu osaritvā vāsaṃ kappessanti jivhaggena rasaggāni pariyesamānā, piṇḍapātahetu ca anekavihitaṃ anesanaṃ appatirūpaṃ āpajjissanti.**They will come down to the villages, towns, and capital cities and make their homes there. And they will try to get alms-food in many kinds of wrong and inappropriate ways.*";
P_HTM[2191]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyaṃ anāgatabhayaṃ etarahi asamuppannaṃ āyatiṃ samuppajjissati.**This is the second future peril that has not currently arisen, but will arise in the future …*";
P_HTM[2192]="*Taṃ vo paṭibujjhitabbaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2193]="*paṭibujjhitvā ca tassa pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2194]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhavissanti bhikkhū anāgatamaddhānaṃ senāsane kalyāṇakāmā.**Furthermore, in a future time there will be mendicants who like nice lodgings.*";
P_HTM[2195]="*Te senāsane kalyāṇakāmā samānā riñcissanti rukkhamūlikattaṃ, riñcissanti araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni;**They will neglect the practice of staying at the root of a tree and the practice of frequenting remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.*";
P_HTM[2196]="*gāmanigamarājadhānīsu osaritvā vāsaṃ kappessanti, senāsanahetu ca anekavihitaṃ anesanaṃ appatirūpaṃ āpajjissanti.**They will come down to the villages, towns, and capital cities and make their homes there. And they will try to get lodgings in many kinds of wrong and inappropriate ways.*";
P_HTM[2197]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyaṃ anāgatabhayaṃ etarahi asamuppannaṃ āyatiṃ samuppajjissati.**This is the third future peril that has not currently arisen, but will arise in the future …*";
P_HTM[2198]="*Taṃ vo paṭibujjhitabbaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2199]="*paṭibujjhitvā ca tassa pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2200]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhavissanti bhikkhū anāgatamaddhānaṃ bhikkhunīsikkhamānāsamaṇuddesehi saṃsaṭṭhā viharissanti.**Furthermore, in a future time there will be mendicants who mix closely with nuns, trainee nuns, and novice nuns.*";
P_HTM[2201]="*Bhikkhunīsikkhamānāsamaṇuddesehi saṃsagge kho pana, bhikkhave, sati etaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ:**In such conditions, it can be expected that*";
P_HTM[2202]="*‘anabhiratā vā brahmacariyaṃ carissanti, aññataraṃ vā saṅkiliṭṭhaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjissanti, sikkhaṃ vā paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattissanti’.**they will live the spiritual life dissatisfied, or commit one of the corrupt offenses, or reject the training and return to a lesser life.*";
P_HTM[2203]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, catutthaṃ anāgatabhayaṃ etarahi asamuppannaṃ āyatiṃ samuppajjissati.**This is the fourth future peril that has not currently arisen, but will arise in the future …*";
P_HTM[2204]="*Taṃ vo paṭibujjhitabbaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2205]="*paṭibujjhitvā ca tassa pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2206]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhavissanti bhikkhū anāgatamaddhānaṃ ārāmikasamaṇuddesehi saṃsaṭṭhā viharissanti.**Furthermore, in a future time there will be mendicants who mix closely with monastery attendants and novices.*";
P_HTM[2207]="*Ārāmikasamaṇuddesehi saṃsagge kho pana, bhikkhave, sati etaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ:**In such conditions it can be expected that*";
P_HTM[2208]="*‘anekavihitaṃ sannidhikāraparibhogaṃ anuyuttā viharissanti, oḷārikampi nimittaṃ karissanti, pathaviyāpi haritaggepi’.**they will engage in storing up goods for their own use, and making obvious hints about digging the earth and cutting plants.*";
P_HTM[2209]="*Idaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamaṃ anāgatabhayaṃ etarahi asamuppannaṃ āyatiṃ samuppajjissati.**This is the fifth future peril that has not currently arisen, but will arise in the future …*";
P_HTM[2210]="*Taṃ vo paṭibujjhitabbaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2211]="*paṭibujjhitvā ca tassa pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2212]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca anāgatabhayāni etarahi asamuppannāni āyatiṃ samuppajjissanti.**These are the five future perils that have not currently arisen, but will arise in the future.*";
P_HTM[2213]="*Tāni vo paṭibujjhitabbāni;**You should look out for them*";
P_HTM[2214]="*paṭibujjhitvā ca tesaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabban”ti.**and try to give them up.”*";
P_HTM[2215]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2216]="*Yodhājīvavaggo tatiyo.* **";
P_HTM[2217]="*Dve cetovimuttiphalā,* **";
P_HTM[2218]="*dve ca dhammavihārino;* **";
P_HTM[2219]="*Yodhājīvā ca dve vuttā,* **";
P_HTM[2220]="*cattāro ca anāgatāti.* **";
P_HTM[2221]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**Senior Mendicants*";
P_HTM[2222]="*1. Rajanīyasuttaṃ**Desirable*";
P_HTM[2223]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ appiyo ca hoti amanāpo ca agaru ca abhāvanīyo ca.**“Mendicants, a senior mendicant with five qualities is unlikable and unlovable to their spiritual companions, not respected or admired.*";
P_HTM[2224]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2225]="*Rajanīye rajjati, dussanīye dussati, mohanīye muyhati, kuppanīye kuppati, madanīye majjati—**They desire the desirable, they hate the hateful, they’re deluded by the delusory, they’re annoyed by the annoying, and they’re intoxicated by the intoxicating.*";
P_HTM[2226]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ appiyo ca hoti amanāpo ca agaru ca abhāvanīyo ca.**A senior mendicant with these five qualities is unlikable and unlovable by their spiritual companions, not respected or admired.*";
P_HTM[2227]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo ca.**A senior mendicant with five qualities is dear and beloved to their spiritual companions, respected and admired.*";
P_HTM[2228]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2229]="*Rajanīye na rajjati, dussanīye na dussati, mohanīye na muyhati, kuppanīye na kuppati, madanīye na majjati—**They don’t desire the desirable, they don’t hate the hateful, they’re not deluded by the delusory, they’re not annoyed by the annoying, and they’re not intoxicated by the intoxicating.*";
P_HTM[2230]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo cā”ti.**A senior mendicant with these five qualities is dear and beloved to their spiritual companions, respected and admired.”*";
P_HTM[2231]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2232]="*2. Vītarāgasuttaṃ**Free of Greed*";
P_HTM[2233]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ appiyo ca hoti amanāpo ca agaru ca abhāvanīyo ca.**“Mendicants, a senior mendicant with five qualities is unlikable and unlovable to their spiritual companions, not respected or admired.*";
P_HTM[2234]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2235]="*Avītarāgo hoti, avītadoso hoti, avītamoho hoti, makkhī ca, paḷāsī ca—**They’re not free of greed, hate, and delusion; they are offensive and contemptuous.*";
P_HTM[2236]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ appiyo ca hoti amanāpo ca agaru ca abhāvanīyo ca.**A senior mendicant with these five qualities is unlikable and unlovable to their spiritual companions, not respected or admired.*";
P_HTM[2237]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo ca.**A senior mendicant with five qualities is dear and beloved to their spiritual companions, respected and admired.*";
P_HTM[2238]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2239]="*Vītarāgo hoti, vītadoso hoti, vītamoho hoti, amakkhī ca, apaḷāsī ca—**They’re free of greed, hate, and delusion; they’re not offensive and contemptuous.*";
P_HTM[2240]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo cā”ti.**A senior mendicant with these five qualities is dear and beloved to their spiritual companions, respected and admired.”*";
P_HTM[2241]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2242]="*3. Kuhakasuttaṃ**Deceiver*";
P_HTM[2243]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ appiyo ca hoti amanāpo ca agaru ca abhāvanīyo ca.**“Mendicants, a senior mendicant with five qualities is unlikable and unlovable to their spiritual companions, not respected or admired.*";
P_HTM[2244]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2245]="*Kuhako ca hoti, lapako ca, nemittiko ca, nippesiko ca, lābhena ca lābhaṃ nijigīsitā—**They use deceit, flattery, hinting, and belittling, and they use material possessions to pursue other material possessions.*";
P_HTM[2246]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ appiyo ca hoti amanāpo ca agaru ca abhāvanīyo ca.**A senior mendicant with these five qualities is unlikable and unlovable to their spiritual companions, not respected or admired.*";
P_HTM[2247]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo ca.**A senior mendicant with five qualities is dear and beloved to their spiritual companions, respected and admired.*";
P_HTM[2248]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2249]="*Na ca kuhako hoti, na ca lapako, na ca nemittiko, na ca nippesiko, na ca lābhena lābhaṃ nijigīsitā—**They don’t use deceit, flattery, hinting, or belittling, and they don’t use material possessions to pursue other material possessions.*";
P_HTM[2250]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo cā”ti.**A senior mendicant with these five qualities is dear and beloved to their spiritual companions, respected and admired.”*";
P_HTM[2251]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2252]="*4. Assaddhasuttaṃ**Faithless*";
P_HTM[2253]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ appiyo ca hoti, amanāpo ca agaru ca abhāvanīyo ca.**“Mendicants, a senior mendicant with five qualities is unlikable and unlovable to their spiritual companions, not respected or admired.*";
P_HTM[2254]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2255]="*Assaddho hoti, ahiriko hoti, anottappī hoti, kusīto hoti, duppañño hoti—**They’re faithless, shameless, imprudent, lazy, and witless.*";
P_HTM[2256]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ appiyo ca hoti amanāpo ca agaru ca abhāvanīyo ca.**A senior mendicant with these five qualities is unlikable and unlovable to their spiritual companions, not respected or admired.*";
P_HTM[2257]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo ca.**A senior mendicant with five qualities is dear and beloved to their spiritual companions, respected and admired.*";
P_HTM[2258]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2259]="*Saddho hoti, hirīmā hoti, ottappī hoti, āraddhavīriyo hoti, paññavā hoti—**They’re faithful, conscientious, prudent, energetic, and wise.*";
P_HTM[2260]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo cā”ti.**A senior mendicant with these five qualities is dear and beloved to their spiritual companions, respected and admired.”*";
P_HTM[2261]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2262]="*5. Akkhamasuttaṃ**Cannot Endure*";
P_HTM[2263]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ appiyo ca hoti amanāpo ca agaru ca abhāvanīyo ca.**“Mendicants, a senior mendicant with five qualities is unlikable and unlovable to their spiritual companions, not respected or admired.*";
P_HTM[2264]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2265]="*Akkhamo hoti rūpānaṃ, akkhamo saddānaṃ, akkhamo gandhānaṃ, akkhamo rasānaṃ, akkhamo phoṭṭhabbānaṃ—**They can’t endure sights, sounds, smells, tastes, and touches.*";
P_HTM[2266]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ appiyo ca hoti amanāpo ca agaru ca abhāvanīyo ca.**A senior mendicant with these five qualities is unlikable and unlovable to their spiritual companions, not respected or admired.*";
P_HTM[2267]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo ca.**A senior mendicant with five qualities is dear and beloved to their spiritual companions, respected and admired.*";
P_HTM[2268]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2269]="*Khamo hoti rūpānaṃ, khamo saddānaṃ, khamo gandhānaṃ, khamo rasānaṃ, khamo phoṭṭhabbānaṃ—**They can endure sights, sounds, smells, tastes, and touches.*";
P_HTM[2270]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo cā”ti.**A senior mendicant with these five qualities is dear and beloved to their spiritual companions, respected and admired.”*";
P_HTM[2271]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2272]="*6. Paṭisambhidāpattasuttaṃ**Attaining the Methods of Textual Analysis*";
P_HTM[2273]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo ca.**“A senior mendicant with five qualities is dear and beloved to their spiritual companions, respected and admired.*";
P_HTM[2274]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2275]="*Atthapaṭisambhidāpatto hoti, dhammapaṭisambhidāpatto hoti, niruttipaṭisambhidāpatto hoti, paṭibhānapaṭisambhidāpatto hoti,**They have attained the textual analysis of meaning, text, terminology, and eloquence.*";
P_HTM[2276]="*yāni tāni sabrahmacārīnaṃ uccāvacāni kiṃkaraṇīyāni tattha dakkho hoti analaso tatrupāyāya vīmaṃsāya samannāgato alaṃ kātuṃ alaṃ saṃvidhātuṃ—**And they are skilled and tireless in a diverse spectrum of duties for their spiritual companions, understanding how to go about things in order to complete and organize the work.*";
P_HTM[2277]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo cā”ti.**A senior mendicant with these five qualities is dear and beloved to their spiritual companions, respected and admired.”*";
P_HTM[2278]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2279]="*7. Sīlavantasuttaṃ**Ethical*";
P_HTM[2280]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo ca.**“A senior mendicant with five qualities is dear and beloved to their spiritual companions, respected and admired.*";
P_HTM[2281]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2282]="*Sīlavā hoti, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati. Ācāragocarasampanno aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu;**They’re ethical, restrained in the monastic code, conducting themselves well and seeking alms in suitable places. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken.*";
P_HTM[2283]="*bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo, ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpāssa dhammā bahussutā honti dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā;**They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering them, reinforcing them by recitation, mentally scrutinizing them, and comprehending them theoretically.*";
P_HTM[2284]="*kalyāṇavāco hoti kalyāṇavākkaraṇo poriyā vācāya samannāgato vissaṭṭhāya anelagaḷāya atthassa viññāpaniyā;**They’re a good speaker, with a polished, clear, and articulate voice that expresses the meaning.*";
P_HTM[2285]="*catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī;**They get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that belong to the higher mind—when they want, without trouble or difficulty.*";
P_HTM[2286]="*āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati.**They realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[2287]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo cā”ti.**A senior mendicant with these five qualities is dear and beloved to their spiritual companions, respected and admired.”*";
P_HTM[2288]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2289]="*8. Therasuttaṃ**Senior Mendicants*";
P_HTM[2290]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu bahujanaahitāya paṭipanno hoti bahujanaasukhāya bahuno janassa anatthāya ahitāya dukkhāya devamanussānaṃ.**“Mendicants, a senior mendicant who has five qualities is acting for the hurt and unhappiness of the people, for the harm, hurt, and suffering of gods and humans.*";
P_HTM[2291]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2292]="*Thero hoti rattaññū cirapabbajito;**They are senior and have long gone forth.*";
P_HTM[2293]="*ñāto hoti yasassī sagahaṭṭhapabbajitānaṃ bahujanaparivāro;**They’re well-known, famous, with a large following that includes both laypeople and renunciates.*";
P_HTM[2294]="*lābhī hoti cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ;**They receive robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick.*";
P_HTM[2295]="*bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo, ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpāssa dhammā bahussutā honti dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā appaṭividdhā;**They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering them, reinforcing them by recitation, mentally scrutinizing them, and understanding them with view.*";
P_HTM[2296]="*micchādiṭṭhiko hoti viparītadassano, so bahujanaṃ saddhammā vuṭṭhāpetvā asaddhamme patiṭṭhāpeti.**But they have wrong view and distorted perspective. They draw many people away from the true teaching and establish them in false teachings.*";
P_HTM[2297]="*Thero bhikkhu rattaññū cirapabbajito itipissa diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjanti, ñāto thero bhikkhu yasassī sagahaṭṭhapabbajitānaṃ bahujanaparivāro itipissa diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjanti, lābhī thero bhikkhu cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ itipissa diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjanti, bahussuto thero bhikkhu sutadharo sutasannicayo itipissa diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjanti.**People follow their example, thinking that the senior mendicant is senior and has long gone forth. Or that they’re well-known, famous, with a large following that includes both laypeople and renunciates. Or that they receive robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick. Or that they’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned.*";
P_HTM[2298]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu bahujanaahitāya paṭipanno hoti bahujanaasukhāya bahuno janassa anatthāya ahitāya dukkhāya devamanussānaṃ.**A senior mendicant who has these five qualities is acting for the hurt and unhappiness of the people, for the harm, hurt, and suffering of gods and humans.*";
P_HTM[2299]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu bahujanahitāya paṭipanno hoti bahujanasukhāya bahuno janassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānaṃ.**A senior mendicant who has five qualities is acting for the welfare and happiness of the people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans.*";
P_HTM[2300]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2301]="*Thero hoti rattaññū cirapabbajito;**They are senior and have long gone forth.*";
P_HTM[2302]="*ñāto hoti yasassī sagahaṭṭhapabbajitānaṃ bahujanaparivāro;**They’re well-known, famous, with a large following, including both laypeople and renunciates.*";
P_HTM[2303]="*lābhī hoti cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ;**They receive robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick.*";
P_HTM[2304]="*bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo, ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpāssa dhammā bahussutā honti dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā;**They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering them, reinforcing them by recitation, mentally scrutinizing them, and comprehending them theoretically.*";
P_HTM[2305]="*sammādiṭṭhiko hoti aviparītadassano, so bahujanaṃ asaddhammā vuṭṭhāpetvā saddhamme patiṭṭhāpeti.**And they have right view and an undistorted perspective. They draw many people away from false teachings and establish them in the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[2306]="*Thero bhikkhu rattaññū cirapabbajito itipissa diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjanti, ñāto thero bhikkhu yasassī sagahaṭṭhapabbajitānaṃ bahujanaparivāro itipissa diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjanti, lābhī thero bhikkhu cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ itipissa diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjanti, bahussuto thero bhikkhu sutadharo sutasannicayo itipissa diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjanti.**People follow their example, thinking that the senior mendicant is senior and has long gone forth. Or that they’re well-known, famous, with a large following that includes both laypeople and renunciates. Or that they receive robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick. Or that they’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned.*";
P_HTM[2307]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu bahujanahitāya paṭipanno hoti bahujanasukhāya bahuno janassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānan”ti.**A senior mendicant who has these five qualities is acting for the welfare and happiness of the people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans.”*";
P_HTM[2308]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2309]="*9. Paṭhamasekhasuttaṃ**A Trainee (1st)*";
P_HTM[2310]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhammā sekhassa bhikkhuno parihānāya saṃvattanti.**“These five things lead to the decline of a mendicant trainee.*";
P_HTM[2311]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2312]="*Kammārāmatā, bhassārāmatā, niddārāmatā, saṅgaṇikārāmatā, yathāvimuttaṃ cittaṃ na paccavekkhati—**They relish work, talk, sleep, and company. And they don’t review the extent of their mind’s freedom.*";
P_HTM[2313]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhammā sekhassa bhikkhuno parihānāya saṃvattanti.**These five things lead to the decline of a mendicant trainee.*";
P_HTM[2314]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhammā sekhassa bhikkhuno aparihānāya saṃvattanti.**These five things don’t lead to the decline of a mendicant trainee.*";
P_HTM[2315]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2316]="*Na kammārāmatā, na bhassārāmatā, na niddārāmatā, na saṅgaṇikārāmatā, yathāvimuttaṃ cittaṃ paccavekkhati—**They don’t relish work, talk, sleep, and company. And they review the extent of their mind’s freedom.*";
P_HTM[2317]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhammā sekhassa bhikkhuno aparihānāya saṃvattantī”ti.**These five things don’t lead to the decline of a mendicant trainee.”*";
P_HTM[2318]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2319]="*10. Dutiyasekhasuttaṃ**A Trainee (2nd)*";
P_HTM[2320]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhammā sekhassa bhikkhuno parihānāya saṃvattanti.**“These five things lead to the decline of a mendicant trainee.*";
P_HTM[2321]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2322]="*Idha, bhikkhave, sekho bhikkhu bahukicco hoti bahukaraṇīyo viyatto kiṅkaraṇīyesu;**Firstly, a mendicant trainee has many duties and responsibilities, and is competent in many tasks.*";
P_HTM[2323]="*riñcati paṭisallānaṃ, nānuyuñjati ajjhattaṃ cetosamathaṃ.**They neglect retreat, and are not committed to internal serenity of heart.*";
P_HTM[2324]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo dhammo sekhassa bhikkhuno parihānāya saṃvattati.**This is the first thing that leads to the decline of a mendicant trainee.*";
P_HTM[2325]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sekho bhikkhu appamattakena kammena divasaṃ atināmeti;**Furthermore, a mendicant trainee spends their day doing trivial work.*";
P_HTM[2326]="*riñcati paṭisallānaṃ, nānuyuñjati ajjhattaṃ cetosamathaṃ.**They neglect retreat, and are not committed to internal serenity of heart.*";
P_HTM[2327]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo dhammo sekhassa bhikkhuno parihānāya saṃvattati.**This is the second thing that leads to the decline of a mendicant trainee.*";
P_HTM[2328]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sekho bhikkhu saṃsaṭṭho viharati gahaṭṭhapabbajitehi ananulomikena gihisaṃsaggena;**Furthermore, a mendicant trainee mixes closely with laypeople and renunciates, socializing inappropriately like a layperson.*";
P_HTM[2329]="*riñcati paṭisallānaṃ, nānuyuñjati ajjhattaṃ cetosamathaṃ.**They neglect retreat, and are not committed to internal serenity of heart.*";
P_HTM[2330]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo dhammo sekhassa bhikkhuno parihānāya saṃvattati.**This is the third thing that leads to the decline of a mendicant trainee.*";
P_HTM[2331]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sekho bhikkhu akālena gāmaṃ pavisati, atidivā paṭikkamati;**Furthermore, a mendicant trainee enters the town at the wrong time, and returns too late in the day.*";
P_HTM[2332]="*riñcati paṭisallānaṃ, nānuyuñjati ajjhattaṃ cetosamathaṃ.**They neglect retreat, and are not committed to internal serenity of heart.*";
P_HTM[2333]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho dhammo sekhassa bhikkhuno parihānāya saṃvattati.**This is the fourth thing that leads to the decline of a mendicant trainee.*";
P_HTM[2334]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sekho bhikkhu yāyaṃ kathā ābhisallekhikā cetovivaraṇasappāyā, seyyathidaṃ—**Furthermore, a mendicant trainee doesn’t get to take part in talk about self-effacement that helps open the heart, when they want, without trouble or difficulty. That is,*";
P_HTM[2335]="*appicchakathā santuṭṭhikathā pavivekakathā asaṃsaggakathā vīriyārambhakathā sīlakathā samādhikathā paññākathā vimuttikathā vimuttiñāṇadassanakathā, evarūpiyā kathāya na nikāmalābhī hoti na akicchalābhī na akasiralābhī;**talk about fewness of wishes, contentment, seclusion, aloofness, arousing energy, ethics, immersion, wisdom, freedom, and the knowledge and vision of freedom.*";
P_HTM[2336]="*riñcati paṭisallānaṃ, nānuyuñjati ajjhattaṃ cetosamathaṃ.**They neglect retreat, and are not committed to internal serenity of heart.*";
P_HTM[2337]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo dhammo sekhassa bhikkhuno parihānāya saṃvattati.**This is the fifth thing that leads to the decline of a mendicant trainee.*";
P_HTM[2338]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhammā sekhassa bhikkhuno parihānāya saṃvattanti.**These five things lead to the decline of a mendicant trainee.*";
P_HTM[2339]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhammā sekhassa bhikkhuno aparihānāya saṃvattanti.**These five things don’t lead to the decline of a mendicant trainee.*";
P_HTM[2340]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2341]="*Idha, bhikkhave, sekho bhikkhu na bahukicco hoti na bahukaraṇīyo viyatto kiṅkaraṇīyesu;**Firstly, a mendicant trainee doesn’t have many duties and responsibilities, even though they are competent in many tasks.*";
P_HTM[2342]="*na riñcati paṭisallānaṃ, anuyuñjati ajjhattaṃ cetosamathaṃ.**They don’t neglect retreat, and are committed to internal serenity of heart.*";
P_HTM[2343]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo dhammo sekhassa bhikkhuno aparihānāya saṃvattati.**This is the first thing that doesn’t lead to the decline of a mendicant trainee.*";
P_HTM[2344]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sekho bhikkhu na appamattakena kammena divasaṃ atināmeti;**Furthermore, a mendicant trainee doesn’t spend their day doing trivial work.*";
P_HTM[2345]="*na riñcati paṭisallānaṃ, anuyuñjati ajjhattaṃ cetosamathaṃ.**They don’t neglect retreat, and are committed to internal serenity of heart.*";
P_HTM[2346]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo dhammo sekhassa bhikkhuno aparihānāya saṃvattati.**This is the second thing that doesn’t lead to the decline of a mendicant trainee.*";
P_HTM[2347]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sekho bhikkhu asaṃsaṭṭho viharati gahaṭṭhapabbajitehi ananulomikena gihisaṃsaggena;**Furthermore, a mendicant trainee doesn’t mix closely with laypeople and renunciates, socializing inappropriately like a layperson.*";
P_HTM[2348]="*na riñcati paṭisallānaṃ, anuyuñjati ajjhattaṃ cetosamathaṃ.**They don’t neglect retreat, and are committed to internal serenity of heart.*";
P_HTM[2349]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo dhammo sekhassa bhikkhuno aparihānāya saṃvattati.**This is the third thing that doesn’t lead to the decline of a mendicant trainee.*";
P_HTM[2350]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sekho bhikkhu na atikālena gāmaṃ pavisati, nātidivā paṭikkamati;**Furthermore, a mendicant trainee doesn’t enter the village too early or return too late in the day.*";
P_HTM[2351]="*na riñcati paṭisallānaṃ, anuyuñjati ajjhattaṃ cetosamathaṃ.**They don’t neglect retreat, and are committed to internal serenity of heart.*";
P_HTM[2352]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho dhammo sekhassa bhikkhuno aparihānāya saṃvattati.**This is the fourth thing that doesn’t lead to the decline of a mendicant trainee.*";
P_HTM[2353]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sekho bhikkhu yāyaṃ kathā ābhisallekhikā cetovivaraṇasappāyā, seyyathidaṃ—**Furthermore, a mendicant trainee gets to take part in talk about self-effacement that helps open the heart, when they want, without trouble or difficulty. That is,*";
P_HTM[2354]="*appicchakathā santuṭṭhikathā pavivekakathā asaṃsaggakathā vīriyārambhakathā sīlakathā samādhikathā paññākathā vimuttikathā vimuttiñāṇadassanakathā, evarūpiyā kathāya nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī;**talk about fewness of wishes, contentment, seclusion, aloofness, arousing energy, ethics, immersion, wisdom, freedom, and the knowledge and vision of freedom.*";
P_HTM[2355]="*na riñcati paṭisallānaṃ, anuyuñjati ajjhattaṃ cetosamathaṃ.**They don’t neglect retreat, and are committed to internal serenity of heart.*";
P_HTM[2356]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo dhammo sekhassa bhikkhuno aparihānāya saṃvattati.**This is the fifth thing that doesn't lead to the decline of a mendicant trainee.*";
P_HTM[2357]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhammā sekhassa bhikkhuno aparihānāya saṃvattantī”ti.**These five things don’t lead to the decline of a mendicant trainee.”*";
P_HTM[2358]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2359]="*Theravaggo catuttho.* **";
P_HTM[2360]="*Rajanīyo vītarāgo,* **";
P_HTM[2361]="*kuhakāssaddhaakkhamā;* **";
P_HTM[2362]="*Paṭisambhidā ca sīlena,* **";
P_HTM[2363]="*thero sekhā pare duveti.* **";
P_HTM[2364]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**With Kakudha*";
P_HTM[2365]="*1. Paṭhamasampadāsuttaṃ**Accomplishments (1st)*";
P_HTM[2366]="*“Pañcimā, bhikkhave, sampadā.**“Mendicants, there are five accomplishments.*";
P_HTM[2367]="*Katamā pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2368]="*Saddhāsampadā, sīlasampadā, sutasampadā, cāgasampadā, paññāsampadā—**Accomplishment in faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2369]="*imā kho, bhikkhave, pañca sampadā”ti.**These are the five accomplishments.”*";
P_HTM[2370]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2371]="*2. Dutiyasampadāsuttaṃ**Accomplishment (2nd)*";
P_HTM[2372]="*“Pañcimā, bhikkhave, sampadā.**“Mendicants, there are five accomplishments.*";
P_HTM[2373]="*Katamā pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2374]="*Sīlasampadā, samādhisampadā, paññāsampadā, vimuttisampadā, vimuttiñāṇadassanasampadā—**Accomplishment in ethics, immersion, wisdom, freedom, and the knowledge and vision of freedom.*";
P_HTM[2375]="*imā kho, bhikkhave, pañca sampadā”ti.**These are the five accomplishments.”*";
P_HTM[2376]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2377]="*3. Byākaraṇasuttaṃ**Declarations*";
P_HTM[2378]="*“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, aññābyākaraṇāni.**“Mendicants, there are five ways of declaring enlightenment.*";
P_HTM[2379]="*Katamāni pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2380]="*Mandattā momūhattā aññaṃ byākaroti;**One declares enlightenment out of stupidity and folly.*";
P_HTM[2381]="*pāpiccho icchāpakato aññaṃ byākaroti;**Or because of wicked desires, being naturally full of desires.*";
P_HTM[2382]="*ummādā cittakkhepā aññaṃ byākaroti;**Or because of madness and mental disorder.*";
P_HTM[2383]="*adhimānena aññaṃ byākaroti;**Or out of overestimation.*";
P_HTM[2384]="*sammadeva aññaṃ byākaroti.**Or one declares enlightenment rightly.*";
P_HTM[2385]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca aññābyākaraṇānī”ti.**These are the five ways of declaring enlightenment.”*";
P_HTM[2386]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2387]="*4. Phāsuvihārasuttaṃ**Living Comfortably*";
P_HTM[2388]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, phāsuvihārā.**“Mendicants, there are these five ways of living comfortably.*";
P_HTM[2389]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2390]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati;**It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[2391]="*vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati;**As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter and remain in the second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption …*";
P_HTM[2392]="*āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati.**They realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[2393]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca phāsuvihārā”ti.**These are the five ways of living comfortably.”*";
P_HTM[2394]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2395]="*5. Akuppasuttaṃ**Unshakable*";
P_HTM[2396]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu nacirasseva akuppaṃ paṭivijjhati.**“Mendicants, a mendicant who has five things will soon penetrate the unshakable.*";
P_HTM[2397]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2398]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu atthapaṭisambhidāpatto hoti, dhammapaṭisambhidāpatto hoti, niruttipaṭisambhidāpatto hoti, paṭibhānapaṭisambhidāpatto hoti, yathāvimuttaṃ cittaṃ paccavekkhati.**It’s when a mendicant has attained the textual analysis of meaning, text, terminology, and eloquence, and they review the extent of their mind’s freedom.*";
P_HTM[2399]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu nacirasseva akuppaṃ paṭivijjhatī”ti.**A mendicant who has these five things will soon penetrate the unshakable.”*";
P_HTM[2400]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2401]="*6. Sutadharasuttaṃ**Remembering What You’ve Learned*";
P_HTM[2402]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu ānāpānassatiṃ āsevanto nacirasseva akuppaṃ paṭivijjhati.**“Mendicants, a mendicant cultivating mindfulness of breathing who has five things will soon penetrate the unshakable.*";
P_HTM[2403]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2404]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu appaṭṭho hoti appakicco subharo susantoso jīvitaparikkhāresu;**It’s when a mendicant has few requirements and duties, and is easily looked after and contented with life’s necessities.*";
P_HTM[2405]="*appāhāro hoti anodarikattaṃ anuyutto;**They eat little, not devoted to filling their stomach.*";
P_HTM[2406]="*appamiddho hoti jāgariyaṃ anuyutto;**They are rarely drowsy, and are dedicated to wakefulness.*";
P_HTM[2407]="*bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo, ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpāssa dhammā bahussutā honti dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā;**They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering them, reinforcing them by recitation, mentally scrutinizing them, and comprehending them theoretically.*";
P_HTM[2408]="*yathāvimuttaṃ cittaṃ paccavekkhati.**They review the extent of their mind’s freedom.*";
P_HTM[2409]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu ānāpānassatiṃ āsevanto nacirasseva akuppaṃ paṭivijjhatī”ti.**A mendicant cultivating mindfulness of breathing who has these five things will soon penetrate the unshakable.”*";
P_HTM[2410]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2411]="*7. Kathāsuttaṃ**Talk*";
P_HTM[2412]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu ānāpānassatiṃ bhāvento nacirasseva akuppaṃ paṭivijjhati.**“Mendicants, a mendicant developing mindfulness of breathing who has five things will soon penetrate the unshakable.*";
P_HTM[2413]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2414]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu appaṭṭho hoti appakicco subharo susantoso jīvitaparikkhāresu;**It’s when a mendicant has few requirements and duties, and is easily looked after and contented with life’s necessities.*";
P_HTM[2415]="*appāhāro hoti anodarikattaṃ anuyutto;**They eat little, not devoted to filling their stomach.*";
P_HTM[2416]="*appamiddho hoti jāgariyaṃ anuyutto;**They are rarely drowsy, and are dedicated to wakefulness.*";
P_HTM[2417]="*yāyaṃ kathā ābhisallekhikā cetovivaraṇasappāyā, seyyathidaṃ—**They get to take part in talk about self-effacement that helps open the heart, when they want, without trouble or difficulty. That is,*";
P_HTM[2418]="*appicchakathā … pe … vimuttiñāṇadassanakathā, evarūpiyā kathāya nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī;**talk about fewness of wishes, contentment, seclusion, keeping your distance, arousing energy, ethics, immersion, wisdom, freedom, and the knowledge and vision of freedom.*";
P_HTM[2419]="*yathāvimuttaṃ cittaṃ paccavekkhati.**They review the extent of their mind’s freedom.*";
P_HTM[2420]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu ānāpānassatiṃ bhāvento nacirasseva akuppaṃ paṭivijjhatī”ti.**A mendicant developing mindfulness of breathing who has these five things will soon penetrate the unshakable.”*";
P_HTM[2421]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2422]="*8. Āraññakasuttaṃ**In the Wilderness*";
P_HTM[2423]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu ānāpānassatiṃ bahulīkaronto nacirasseva akuppaṃ paṭivijjhati.**“Mendicants, a mendicant practicing mindfulness of breathing who has five things will soon penetrate the unshakable.*";
P_HTM[2424]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2425]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu appaṭṭho hoti appakicco subharo susantoso jīvitaparikkhāresu;**It’s when a mendicant has few requirements and duties, and is easily looked after and contented with life’s necessities.*";
P_HTM[2426]="*appāhāro hoti anodarikattaṃ anuyutto;**They eat little, not devoted to filling their stomach.*";
P_HTM[2427]="*appamiddho hoti jāgariyaṃ anuyutto;**They are rarely drowsy, and are dedicated to wakefulness.*";
P_HTM[2428]="*āraññako hoti pantasenāsano;**They live in the wilderness, in remote lodgings.*";
P_HTM[2429]="*yathāvimuttaṃ cittaṃ paccavekkhati.**They review the extent of their mind’s freedom.*";
P_HTM[2430]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu ānāpānassatiṃ bahulīkaronto nacirasseva akuppaṃ paṭivijjhatī”ti.**A mendicant practicing mindfulness of breathing who has these five things will soon penetrate the unshakable.”*";
P_HTM[2431]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2432]="*9. Sīhasuttaṃ**The Lion*";
P_HTM[2433]="*“Sīho, bhikkhave, migarājā sāyanhasamayaṃ āsayā nikkhamati;**“Mendicants, towards evening the lion, king of beasts, emerges from his den,*";
P_HTM[2434]="*āsayā nikkhamitvā vijambhati;**yawns,*";
P_HTM[2435]="*vijambhitvā samantā catuddisaṃ anuviloketi;**looks all around the four directions,*";
P_HTM[2436]="*samantā catuddisaṃ anuviloketvā tikkhattuṃ sīhanādaṃ nadati;**and roars his lion’s roar three times.*";
P_HTM[2437]="*tikkhattuṃ sīhanādaṃ naditvā gocarāya pakkamati.**Then he sets out on the hunt.*";
P_HTM[2438]="*So hatthissa cepi pahāraṃ deti, sakkaccaññeva pahāraṃ deti, no asakkaccaṃ;**If he strikes an elephant, he does it carefully, not carelessly.*";
P_HTM[2439]="*mahiṃsassa cepi pahāraṃ deti, sakkaccaññeva pahāraṃ deti, no asakkaccaṃ;**If he strikes a buffalo …*";
P_HTM[2440]="*gavassa cepi pahāraṃ deti, sakkaccaññeva pahāraṃ deti, no asakkaccaṃ;**a cow …*";
P_HTM[2441]="*dīpissa cepi pahāraṃ deti, sakkaccaññeva pahāraṃ deti, no asakkaccaṃ;**a leopard …*";
P_HTM[2442]="*khuddakānañcepi pāṇānaṃ pahāraṃ deti antamaso sasabiḷārānampi, sakkaccaññeva pahāraṃ deti, no asakkaccaṃ.**or any smaller creatures—even a hare or a cat—he does it carefully, not carelessly.*";
P_HTM[2443]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[2444]="*‘Mā me yoggapatho nassā’ti.**Thinking: ‘May I not lose my way.’*";
P_HTM[2445]="*Sīhoti kho, bhikkhave, tathāgatassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa.**‘Lion’ is a term for the Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2446]="*Yaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tathāgato parisāya dhammaṃ deseti, idamassa hoti sīhanādasmiṃ.**When the Realized One teaches Dhamma to an assembly, this is his lion’s roar.*";
P_HTM[2447]="*Bhikkhūnañcepi, bhikkhave, tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti, sakkaccaññeva tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti, no asakkaccaṃ;**When the Realized One teaches the monks …*";
P_HTM[2448]="*bhikkhunīnañcepi, bhikkhave, tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti, sakkaccaññeva tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti, no asakkaccaṃ;**nuns …*";
P_HTM[2449]="*upāsakānañcepi, bhikkhave, tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti, sakkaccaññeva tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti, no asakkaccaṃ;**laymen …*";
P_HTM[2450]="*upāsikānañcepi, bhikkhave, tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti, sakkaccaññeva tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti, no asakkaccaṃ;**laywomen …*";
P_HTM[2451]="*puthujjanānañcepi, bhikkhave, tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti antamaso annabhāranesādānampi, sakkaccaññeva tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti, no asakkaccaṃ.**or ordinary people—even food-carriers and hunters—he teaches them carefully, not carelessly.*";
P_HTM[2452]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[2453]="*Dhammagaru, bhikkhave, tathāgato dhammagāravo”ti.**Because the Realized One has respect and reverence for the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[2454]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2455]="*10. Kakudhatherasuttaṃ**With Kakudha*";
P_HTM[2456]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[2457]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[2458]="*Tena kho pana samayena kakudho nāma koliyaputto āyasmato mahāmoggallānassa upaṭṭhāko adhunākālaṅkato aññataraṃ manomayaṃ kāyaṃ upapanno.**At that time the Koliyan named Kakudha—Venerable Mahāmoggallāna’s attendant—had recently passed away and been reborn in a certain host of mind-made gods.*";
P_HTM[2459]="*Tassa evarūpo attabhāvapaṭilābho hoti—seyyathāpi nāma dve vā tīṇi vā māgadhakāni gāmakkhettāni.**He was reincarnated in a life-form that was two or three times the size of a Magadhan village with its fields.*";
P_HTM[2460]="*So tena attabhāvapaṭilābhena neva attānaṃ no paraṃ byābādheti.**But with that life-form he didn’t obstruct himself or others.*";
P_HTM[2461]="*Atha kho kakudho devaputto yenāyasmā mahāmoggallāno tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho kakudho devaputto āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ etadavoca:**Then the god Kakudha went up to Venerable Mahāmoggallāna, bowed, stood to one side. and said to him,*";
P_HTM[2462]="*“devadattassa, bhante, evarūpaṃ icchāgataṃ uppajji:**“Sir, this fixed desire arose in Devadatta:*";
P_HTM[2463]="*‘ahaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ pariharissāmī’ti.**‘I will lead the mendicant Saṅgha.’*";
P_HTM[2464]="*Sahacittuppādā ca, bhante, devadatto tassā iddhiyā parihīno”ti.**And as that thought arose, Devadatta lost that psychic power.”*";
P_HTM[2465]="*Idamavoca kakudho devaputto.**That’s what the god Kakudha said.*";
P_HTM[2466]="*Idaṃ vatvā āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tatthevantaradhāyi.**Then he bowed and respectfully circled Mahāmoggallāna, keeping him on his right side, before vanishing right there.*";
P_HTM[2467]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Mahāmoggallāna went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened.*";
P_HTM[2468]="*“Kakudho nāma, bhante, koliyaputto mamaṃ upaṭṭhāko adhunākālaṅkato aññataraṃ manomayaṃ kāyaṃ upapanno hoti.* **";
P_HTM[2469]="*Tassa evarūpo attabhāvapaṭilābho—seyyathāpi nāma dve vā tīṇi vā māgadhakāni gāmakkhettāni.* **";
P_HTM[2470]="*So tena attabhāvapaṭilābhena neva attānaṃ no paraṃ byābādheti.* **";
P_HTM[2471]="*Atha kho, bhante, kakudho devaputto yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho, bhante, kakudho devaputto maṃ etadavoca:* **";
P_HTM[2472]="*‘devadattassa, bhante, evarūpaṃ icchāgataṃ uppajji—* **";
P_HTM[2473]="*ahaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ pariharissāmīti.* **";
P_HTM[2474]="*Sahacittuppādā ca, bhante, devadatto tassā iddhiyā parihīno’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2475]="*Idamavoca, bhante, kakudho devaputto.* **";
P_HTM[2476]="*Idaṃ vatvā maṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tatthevantaradhāyī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[2477]="*“Kiṃ pana te, moggallāna, kakudho devaputto cetasā ceto paricca vidito:**“But Moggallāna, did you comprehend the god Kakudha’s mind, and know that*";
P_HTM[2478]="*‘yaṃ kiñci kakudho devaputto bhāsati sabbaṃ taṃ tatheva hoti, no aññathā’”ti?**everything he says is correct and not otherwise?”*";
P_HTM[2479]="*“Cetasā ceto paricca vidito me, bhante, kakudho devaputto:**“Indeed I did, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2480]="*‘yaṃ kiñci kakudho devaputto bhāsati sabbaṃ taṃ tatheva hoti, no aññathā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[2481]="*“Rakkhassetaṃ, moggallāna, vācaṃ.**“Mark these words, Moggallāna!*";
P_HTM[2482]="*Rakkhassetaṃ, moggallāna, vācaṃ.**Mark these words!*";
P_HTM[2483]="*Idāni so moghapuriso attanāva attānaṃ pātukarissati.**Now that silly man Devadatta will expose himself by his own deeds.*";
P_HTM[2484]="*Pañcime, moggallāna, satthāro santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**Moggallāna, there are these five teachers found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2485]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2486]="*Idha, moggallāna, ekacco satthā aparisuddhasīlo samāno ‘parisuddhasīlomhī’ti paṭijānāti ‘parisuddhaṃ me sīlaṃ pariyodātaṃ asaṃkiliṭṭhan’ti.**Firstly, some teacher with impure conduct claims: ‘I am pure in ethics. My ethical conduct is pure, bright, uncorrupted.’*";
P_HTM[2487]="*Tamenaṃ sāvakā evaṃ jānanti:**But their disciples know:*";
P_HTM[2488]="*‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ satthā aparisuddhasīlo samāno parisuddhasīlomhī’ti paṭijānāti ‘parisuddhaṃ me sīlaṃ pariyodātaṃ asaṃkiliṭṭhan’ti.**‘This teacher has impure ethical conduct, but claims to be ethically pure.*";
P_HTM[2489]="*Mayañceva kho pana gihīnaṃ āroceyyāma, nāssassa manāpaṃ.**They wouldn’t like it if we were to tell the laypeople.*";
P_HTM[2490]="*Yaṃ kho panassa amanāpaṃ, kathaṃ naṃ mayaṃ tena samudācareyyāma:**And how could we treat them in a way that they don’t like?*";
P_HTM[2491]="*‘sammannati kho pana cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena;**But they consent to robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick.*";
P_HTM[2492]="*yaṃ tumo karissati tumova tena paññāyissatī’ti.**A person will be recognized by their own deeds.’*";
P_HTM[2493]="*Evarūpaṃ kho, moggallāna, satthāraṃ sāvakā sīlato rakkhanti;**The disciples of such a teacher cover up their teacher’s conduct,*";
P_HTM[2494]="*evarūpo ca pana satthā sāvakehi sīlato rakkhaṃ paccāsīsati. (1)**and the teacher expects them to do so.*";
P_HTM[2495]="*Puna caparaṃ, moggallāna, idhekacco satthā aparisuddhājīvo samāno ‘parisuddhājīvomhī’ti paṭijānāti ‘parisuddho me ājīvo pariyodāto asaṅkiliṭṭho’ti.**Furthermore, some teacher with impure livelihood claims: ‘I am pure in livelihood. My livelihood is pure, bright, uncorrupted.’*";
P_HTM[2496]="*Tamenaṃ sāvakā evaṃ jānanti:**But their disciples know:*";
P_HTM[2497]="*‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ satthā aparisuddhājīvo samāno parisuddhājīvomhī’ti paṭijānāti ‘parisuddho me ājīvo pariyodāto asaṅkiliṭṭho’ti.**‘This teacher has impure livelihood, but claims to have pure livelihood.*";
P_HTM[2498]="*Mayañceva kho pana gihīnaṃ āroceyyāma, nāssassa manāpaṃ.**They wouldn’t like it if we were to tell the laypeople.*";
P_HTM[2499]="*Yaṃ kho panassa amanāpaṃ, kathaṃ naṃ mayaṃ tena samudācareyyāma:**And how could we treat them in a way that they don’t like?*";
P_HTM[2500]="*‘sammannati kho pana cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena;**But they consent to robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick.*";
P_HTM[2501]="*yaṃ tumo karissati tumova tena paññāyissatī’ti.**A person will be recognized by their own deeds.’*";
P_HTM[2502]="*Evarūpaṃ kho, moggallāna, satthāraṃ sāvakā ājīvato rakkhanti;**The disciples of such a teacher cover up their teacher’s livelihood,*";
P_HTM[2503]="*evarūpo ca pana satthā sāvakehi ājīvato rakkhaṃ paccāsīsati. (2)**and the teacher expects them to do so.*";
P_HTM[2504]="*Puna caparaṃ, moggallāna, idhekacco satthā aparisuddhadhammadesano samāno ‘parisuddhadhammadesanomhī’ti paṭijānāti ‘parisuddhā me dhammadesanā pariyodātā asaṅkiliṭṭhā’ti.**Furthermore, some teacher with impure teaching claims: ‘I am pure in teaching. My teaching is pure, bright, uncorrupted.’*";
P_HTM[2505]="*Tamenaṃ sāvakā evaṃ jānanti:**But their disciples know:*";
P_HTM[2506]="*‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ satthā aparisuddhadhammadesano samāno parisuddhadhammadesanomhī’ti paṭijānāti ‘parisuddhā me dhammadesanā pariyodātā asaṅkiliṭṭhā’ti.**‘This teacher has impure teaching, but claims to have pure teaching.*";
P_HTM[2507]="*Mayañceva kho pana gihīnaṃ āroceyyāma, nāssassa manāpaṃ.**They wouldn’t like it if we were to tell the laypeople.*";
P_HTM[2508]="*Yaṃ kho panassa amanāpaṃ, kathaṃ naṃ mayaṃ tena samudācareyyāma:**And how could we treat them in a way that they don’t like?*";
P_HTM[2509]="*‘sammannati kho pana cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena;**But they consent to robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick.*";
P_HTM[2510]="*yaṃ tumo karissati tumova tena paññāyissatī’ti.**A person will be recognized by their own deeds.’*";
P_HTM[2511]="*Evarūpaṃ kho, moggallāna, satthāraṃ sāvakā dhammadesanato rakkhanti;**The disciples of such a teacher cover up their teacher’s teaching,*";
P_HTM[2512]="*evarūpo ca pana satthā sāvakehi dhammadesanato rakkhaṃ paccāsīsati. (3)**and the teacher expects them to do so.*";
P_HTM[2513]="*Puna caparaṃ, moggallāna, idhekacco satthā aparisuddhaveyyākaraṇo samāno ‘parisuddhaveyyākaraṇomhī’ti paṭijānāti ‘parisuddhaṃ me veyyākaraṇaṃ pariyodātaṃ asaṅkiliṭṭhan’ti.**Furthermore, some teacher with impure answers claims: ‘I am pure in how I answer. My answers are pure, bright, uncorrupted.’*";
P_HTM[2514]="*Tamenaṃ sāvakā evaṃ jānanti:**But their disciples know:*";
P_HTM[2515]="*‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ satthā aparisuddhaveyyākaraṇo samāno parisuddhaveyyākaraṇomhī’ti paṭijānāti ‘parisuddhaṃ me veyyākaraṇaṃ pariyodātaṃ asaṅkiliṭṭhan’ti.**‘This teacher has impure answers, but claims to have pure answers.*";
P_HTM[2516]="*Mayañceva kho pana gihīnaṃ āroceyyāma, nāssassa manāpaṃ.**They wouldn’t like it if we were to tell the laypeople.*";
P_HTM[2517]="*Yaṃ kho panassa amanāpaṃ, kathaṃ naṃ mayaṃ tena samudācareyyāma:**And how could we treat them in a way that they don’t like?*";
P_HTM[2518]="*‘sammannati kho pana cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena;**But they consent to robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick.*";
P_HTM[2519]="*yaṃ tumo karissati tumova tena paññāyissatī’ti.**A person will be recognized by their own deeds.’*";
P_HTM[2520]="*Evarūpaṃ kho, moggallāna, satthāraṃ sāvakā veyyākaraṇato rakkhanti;**The disciples of such a teacher cover up their teacher’s answers,*";
P_HTM[2521]="*evarūpo ca pana satthā sāvakehi veyyākaraṇato rakkhaṃ paccāsīsati. (4)**and the teacher expects them to do so.*";
P_HTM[2522]="*Puna caparaṃ, moggallāna, idhekacco satthā aparisuddhañāṇadassano samāno ‘parisuddhañāṇadassanomhī’ti paṭijānāti ‘parisuddhaṃ me ñāṇadassanaṃ pariyodātaṃ asaṅkiliṭṭhan’ti.**Furthermore, some teacher with impure knowledge and vision claims: ‘I am pure in knowledge and vision. My knowledge and vision are pure, bright, uncorrupted.’*";
P_HTM[2523]="*Tamenaṃ sāvakā evaṃ jānanti:**But their disciples know:*";
P_HTM[2524]="*‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ satthā aparisuddhañāṇadassano samāno parisuddhañāṇadassanomhī’ti paṭijānāti ‘parisuddhaṃ me ñāṇadassanaṃ pariyodātaṃ asaṅkiliṭṭhan’ti.**‘This teacher has impure knowledge and vision, but claims to have pure knowledge and vision.*";
P_HTM[2525]="*Mayañceva kho pana gihīnaṃ āroceyyāma, nāssassa manāpaṃ.**They wouldn’t like it if we were to tell the laypeople.*";
P_HTM[2526]="*Yaṃ kho panassa amanāpaṃ, kathaṃ naṃ mayaṃ tena samudācareyyāma:**And how could we treat them in a way that they don’t like?*";
P_HTM[2527]="*‘sammannati kho pana cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena;**But they consent to robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick.*";
P_HTM[2528]="*yaṃ tumo karissati tumova tena paññāyissatī’ti.**A person will be recognized by their own deeds.’*";
P_HTM[2529]="*Evarūpaṃ kho, moggallāna, satthāraṃ sāvakā ñāṇadassanato rakkhanti;**The disciples of such a teacher cover up their teacher’s knowledge and vision,*";
P_HTM[2530]="*evarūpo ca pana satthā sāvakehi ñāṇadassanato rakkhaṃ paccāsīsati.**and the teacher expects them to do so.*";
P_HTM[2531]="*Ime kho, moggallāna, pañca satthāro santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ. (5)**These are the five teachers found in the world.*";
P_HTM[2532]="*Ahaṃ kho pana, moggallāna, parisuddhasīlo samāno ‘parisuddhasīlomhī’ti paṭijānāmi ‘parisuddhaṃ me sīlaṃ pariyodātaṃ asaṅkiliṭṭhan’ti.**But Moggallāna, I have pure ethical conduct, and I claim: ‘I am pure in ethical conduct. My ethical conduct is pure, bright, uncorrupted.’*";
P_HTM[2533]="*Na ca maṃ sāvakā sīlato rakkhanti, na cāhaṃ sāvakehi sīlato rakkhaṃ paccāsīsāmi.**My disciples don’t cover up my conduct, and I don’t expect them to.*";
P_HTM[2534]="*Parisuddhājīvo samāno ‘parisuddhājīvomhī’ti paṭijānāmi ‘parisuddho me ājīvo pariyodāto asaṅkiliṭṭho’ti.**I have pure livelihood, and I claim: ‘I am pure in livelihood. My livelihood is pure, bright, uncorrupted.’*";
P_HTM[2535]="*Na ca maṃ sāvakā ājīvato rakkhanti, na cāhaṃ sāvakehi ājīvato rakkhaṃ paccāsīsāmi.**My disciples don’t cover up my livelihood, and I don’t expect them to.*";
P_HTM[2536]="*Parisuddhadhammadesano samāno ‘parisuddhadhammadesanomhī’ti paṭijānāmi ‘parisuddhā me dhammadesanā pariyodātā asaṅkiliṭṭhā’ti.**I have pure teaching, and I claim: ‘I am pure in teaching. My teaching is pure, bright, uncorrupted.’*";
P_HTM[2537]="*Na ca maṃ sāvakā dhammadesanato rakkhanti, na cāhaṃ sāvakehi dhammadesanato rakkhaṃ paccāsīsāmi.**My disciples don’t cover up my teaching, and I don’t expect them to.*";
P_HTM[2538]="*Parisuddhaveyyākaraṇo samāno ‘parisuddhaveyyākaraṇomhī’ti paṭijānāmi ‘parisuddhaṃ me veyyākaraṇaṃ pariyodātaṃ asaṅkiliṭṭhan’ti.**I have pure answers, and I claim: ‘I am pure in how I answer. My answers are pure, bright, uncorrupted.’*";
P_HTM[2539]="*Na ca maṃ sāvakā veyyākaraṇato rakkhanti, na cāhaṃ sāvakehi veyyākaraṇato rakkhaṃ paccāsīsāmi.**My disciples don’t cover up my answers, and I don’t expect them to.*";
P_HTM[2540]="*Parisuddhañāṇadassano samāno ‘parisuddhañāṇadassanomhī’ti paṭijānāmi ‘parisuddhaṃ me ñāṇadassanaṃ pariyodātaṃ asaṅkiliṭṭhan’ti.**I have pure knowledge and vision, and I claim: ‘I am pure in knowledge and vision. My knowledge and vision are pure, bright, uncorrupted.’*";
P_HTM[2541]="*Na ca maṃ sāvakā ñāṇadassanato rakkhanti, na cāhaṃ sāvakehi ñāṇadassanato rakkhaṃ paccāsīsāmī”ti.**My disciples don’t cover up my knowledge and vision, and I don’t expect them to.”*";
P_HTM[2542]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2543]="*Kakudhavaggo pañcamo.* **";
P_HTM[2544]="*Dve sampadā byākaraṇaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[2545]="*phāsu akuppapañcamaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2546]="*Sutaṃ kathā āraññako,* **";
P_HTM[2547]="*sīho ca kakudho dasāti.* **";
P_HTM[2548]="*Dutiyo paṇṇāsako samatto.* **";
P_HTM[2549]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**Living Comfortably*";
P_HTM[2550]="*1. Sārajjasuttaṃ**Assurance*";
P_HTM[2551]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, sekhavesārajjakaraṇā dhammā.**“Mendicants, these five qualities make a trainee assured.*";
P_HTM[2552]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2553]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saddho hoti, sīlavā hoti, bahussuto hoti, āraddhavīriyo hoti, paññavā hoti.**It’s when a mendicant is faithful, ethical, learned, energetic, and wise.*";
P_HTM[2554]="*Yaṃ, bhikkhave, assaddhassa sārajjaṃ hoti, saddhassa taṃ sārajjaṃ na hoti.**A person of faith doesn’t have the insecurities of someone who lacks faith.*";
P_HTM[2555]="*Tasmāyaṃ dhammo sekhavesārajjakaraṇo.**So this quality makes a trainee assured.*";
P_HTM[2556]="*Yaṃ, bhikkhave, dussīlassa sārajjaṃ hoti, sīlavato taṃ sārajjaṃ na hoti.**An ethical person doesn’t have the insecurities of someone who is unethical.*";
P_HTM[2557]="*Tasmāyaṃ dhammo sekhavesārajjakaraṇo.**So this quality makes a trainee assured.*";
P_HTM[2558]="*Yaṃ, bhikkhave, appassutassa sārajjaṃ hoti, bahussutassa taṃ sārajjaṃ na hoti.**A learned person doesn’t have the insecurities of a person of little learning.*";
P_HTM[2559]="*Tasmāyaṃ dhammo sekhavesārajjakaraṇo.**So this quality makes a trainee assured.*";
P_HTM[2560]="*Yaṃ, bhikkhave, kusītassa sārajjaṃ hoti, āraddhavīriyassa taṃ sārajjaṃ na hoti.**An energetic person doesn’t have the insecurities of a lazy person.*";
P_HTM[2561]="*Tasmāyaṃ dhammo sekhavesārajjakaraṇo.**So this quality makes a trainee assured.*";
P_HTM[2562]="*Yaṃ, bhikkhave, duppaññassa sārajjaṃ hoti, paññavato taṃ sārajjaṃ na hoti.**A wise person doesn’t have the insecurities of someone who is witless.*";
P_HTM[2563]="*Tasmāyaṃ dhammo sekhavesārajjakaraṇo.**So this quality makes a trainee assured.*";
P_HTM[2564]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca sekhavesārajjakaraṇā dhammā”ti.**These are the five qualities that make a trainee assured.”*";
P_HTM[2565]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2566]="*2. Ussaṅkitasuttaṃ**Suspected*";
P_HTM[2567]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu ussaṅkitaparisaṅkito hoti pāpabhikkhūti api akuppadhammopi.**“Mendicants, even if a monk is of impeccable character, he might be suspected and distrusted as a ‘bad monk’ for five reasons.*";
P_HTM[2568]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2569]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vesiyāgocaro vā hoti, vidhavāgocaro vā hoti, thullakumārikāgocaro vā hoti, paṇḍakagocaro vā hoti, bhikkhunīgocaro vā hoti.**It’s when a monk frequently collects alms from prostitutes, widows, voluptuous girls, eunuchs, or nuns.*";
P_HTM[2570]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu ussaṅkitaparisaṅkito hoti pāpabhikkhūti api akuppadhammopī”ti.**Even if a monk is of impeccable character, he might be suspected and distrusted as a ‘bad monk’ for these five reasons.”*";
P_HTM[2571]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2572]="*3. Mahācorasuttaṃ**A Master Thief*";
P_HTM[2573]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato mahācoro sandhimpi chindati, nillopampi harati, ekāgārikampi karoti, paripanthepi tiṭṭhati.**“Mendicants, a master thief with five factors breaks into houses, plunders wealth, steals from isolated buildings, and commits highway robbery.*";
P_HTM[2574]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2575]="*Idha, bhikkhave, mahācoro visamanissito ca hoti, gahananissito ca, balavanissito ca, bhogacāgī ca, ekacārī ca.**A master thief relies on rough ground, on thick cover, and on powerful individuals; they pay bribes, and they act alone.*";
P_HTM[2576]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, mahācoro visamanissito hoti?**And how does a master thief rely on rough ground?*";
P_HTM[2577]="*Idha, bhikkhave, mahācoro nadīviduggaṃ vā nissito hoti pabbatavisamaṃ vā.**It’s when a master thief relies on inaccessible riverlands or rugged mountains.*";
P_HTM[2578]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, mahācoro visamanissito hoti.**That’s how a master thief relies on rough ground.*";
P_HTM[2579]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, mahācoro gahananissito hoti?**And how does a master thief rely on thick cover?*";
P_HTM[2580]="*Idha, bhikkhave, mahācoro tiṇagahanaṃ vā nissito hoti rukkhagahanaṃ vā rodhaṃ vā mahāvanasaṇḍaṃ vā.**It’s when a master thief relies on thick grass, thick trees, a ridge, or a large dense wood.*";
P_HTM[2581]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, mahācoro gahananissito hoti.**That’s how a master thief relies on thick cover.*";
P_HTM[2582]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, mahācoro balavanissito hoti?**And how does a master thief rely on powerful individuals?*";
P_HTM[2583]="*Idha, bhikkhave, mahācoro rājānaṃ vā rājamahāmattānaṃ vā nissito hoti.**It’s when a master thief relies on rulers or their ministers.*";
P_HTM[2584]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[2585]="*‘sace maṃ koci kiñci vakkhati, ime me rājāno vā rājamahāmattā vā pariyodhāya atthaṃ bhaṇissantī’ti.**‘If anyone accuses me of anything, these rulers or their ministers will speak in my defense in the case.’*";
P_HTM[2586]="*Sace naṃ koci kiñci āha, tyassa rājāno vā rājamahāmattā vā pariyodhāya atthaṃ bhaṇanti.**And that’s exactly what happens.*";
P_HTM[2587]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, mahācoro balavanissito hoti.**That’s how a master thief relies on powerful individuals.*";
P_HTM[2588]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, mahācoro bhogacāgī hoti?**And how does a master thief pay bribes?*";
P_HTM[2589]="*Idha, bhikkhave, mahācoro aḍḍho hoti mahaddhano mahābhogo.**It’s when a master thief is rich, affluent, and wealthy.*";
P_HTM[2590]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[2591]="*‘sace maṃ koci kiñci vakkhati, ito bhogena paṭisantharissāmī’ti.**‘If anyone accuses me of anything, I’ll settle it with a bribe.’*";
P_HTM[2592]="*Sace naṃ koci kiñci āha, tato bhogena paṭisantharati.**And that’s exactly what happens.*";
P_HTM[2593]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, mahācoro bhogacāgī hoti.**That’s how a master thief pays bribes.*";
P_HTM[2594]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, mahācoro ekacārī hoti?**And how does a master thief act alone?*";
P_HTM[2595]="*Idha, bhikkhave, mahācoro ekakova gahaṇāni kattā hoti.**It’s when a master thief carries out robbery all alone.*";
P_HTM[2596]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[2597]="*‘Mā me guyhamantā bahiddhā sambhedaṃ agamaṃsū’ti.**So that their secret plans are not leaked to others.*";
P_HTM[2598]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, mahācoro ekacārī hoti.**That’s how a master thief acts alone.*";
P_HTM[2599]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato mahācoro sandhimpi chindati nillopampi harati ekāgārikampi karoti paripanthepi tiṭṭhati.**A master thief with these five factors breaks into houses, plunders wealth, steals from isolated buildings, and commits highway robbery.*";
P_HTM[2600]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato pāpabhikkhu khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo viññūnaṃ, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavati.**In the same way, when a bad mendicant has five factors, they keep themselves broken and damaged. They deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much bad karma.*";
P_HTM[2601]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2602]="*Idha, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu visamanissito ca hoti, gahananissito ca, balavanissito ca, bhogacāgī ca, ekacārī ca.**A bad mendicant relies on rough ground, on thick cover, and on powerful individuals; they pay bribes, and they act alone.*";
P_HTM[2603]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu visamanissito hoti?**And how does a bad mendicant rely on rough ground?*";
P_HTM[2604]="*Idha, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu visamena kāyakammena samannāgato hoti, visamena vacīkammena samannāgato hoti, visamena manokammena samannāgato hoti.**It’s when a bad mendicant has unethical conduct by way of body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[2605]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu visamanissito hoti.**That’s how a bad mendicant relies on rough ground.*";
P_HTM[2606]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu gahananissito hoti?**And how does a bad mendicant rely on thick cover?*";
P_HTM[2607]="*Idha, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu micchādiṭṭhiko hoti antaggāhikāya diṭṭhiyā samannāgato.**It’s when a bad mendicant has wrong view, he’s attached to an extremist view.*";
P_HTM[2608]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu gahananissito hoti.**That’s how a bad mendicant relies on thick cover.*";
P_HTM[2609]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu balavanissito hoti?**And how does a bad mendicant rely on powerful individuals?*";
P_HTM[2610]="*Idha, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu rājānaṃ vā rājamahāmattānaṃ vā nissito hoti.**It’s when a bad mendicant relies on rulers or their ministers.*";
P_HTM[2611]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[2612]="*‘sace maṃ koci kiñci vakkhati, ime me rājāno vā rājamahāmattā vā pariyodhāya atthaṃ bhaṇissantī’ti.**‘If anyone accuses me of anything, these rulers or their ministers will speak in my defense in the case.’*";
P_HTM[2613]="*Sace naṃ koci kiñci āha, tyassa rājāno vā rājamahāmattā vā pariyodhāya atthaṃ bhaṇanti.**And that’s exactly what happens.*";
P_HTM[2614]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu balavanissito hoti.**That’s how a bad mendicant relies on powerful individuals.*";
P_HTM[2615]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu bhogacāgī hoti?**And how does a bad mendicant pay bribes?*";
P_HTM[2616]="*Idha, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu lābhī hoti cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ.**It’s when a bad mendicant receives robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick.*";
P_HTM[2617]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[2618]="*‘sace maṃ koci kiñci vakkhati, ito lābhena paṭisantharissāmī’ti.**‘If anyone accuses me of anything, I’ll settle it with a bribe.’*";
P_HTM[2619]="*Sace naṃ koci kiñci āha, tato lābhena paṭisantharati.**And that’s exactly what happens.*";
P_HTM[2620]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu bhogacāgī hoti.**That’s how a bad mendicant pays bribes.*";
P_HTM[2621]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu ekacārī hoti?**And how does a bad mendicant act alone?*";
P_HTM[2622]="*Idha, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu ekakova paccantimesu janapadesu nivāsaṃ kappeti.**It’s when a bad mendicant dwells alone in the borderlands.*";
P_HTM[2623]="*So tattha kulāni upasaṅkamanto lābhaṃ labhati.**They visit families there to get material possessions.*";
P_HTM[2624]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pāpabhikkhu ekacārī hoti.**That’s how a bad mendicant acts alone.*";
P_HTM[2625]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato pāpabhikkhu khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo viññūnaṃ, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavatī”ti.**When a bad mendicant has these five factors, they keep themselves broken and damaged. They deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much bad karma.”*";
P_HTM[2626]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2627]="*4. Samaṇasukhumālasuttaṃ**An Exquisite Ascetic of Ascetics*";
P_HTM[2628]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu samaṇesu samaṇasukhumālo hoti.**“Mendicants, a mendicant with five qualities is an exquisite ascetic of ascetics.*";
P_HTM[2629]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2630]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yācitova bahulaṃ cīvaraṃ paribhuñjati, appaṃ ayācito; yācitova bahulaṃ piṇḍapātaṃ paribhuñjati, appaṃ ayācito; yācitova bahulaṃ senāsanaṃ paribhuñjati, appaṃ ayācito; yācitova bahulaṃ gilānapaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ paribhuñjati, appaṃ ayācito.**It’s when a mendicant usually uses only what they’ve been invited to accept—robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick—rarely using them without invitation.*";
P_HTM[2631]="*Yehi kho pana sabrahmacārīhi saddhiṃ viharati, tyassa manāpeneva bahulaṃ kāyakammena samudācaranti, appaṃ amanāpena; manāpeneva bahulaṃ vacīkammena samudācaranti, appaṃ amanāpena; manāpeneva bahulaṃ manokammena samudācaranti, appaṃ amanāpena;**When living with other spiritual practitioners, they usually treat them agreeably by way of body, speech, and mind, and rarely disagreeably.*";
P_HTM[2632]="*manāpaṃyeva upahāraṃ upaharanti, appaṃ amanāpaṃ.**And they usually present them with agreeable things, rarely with disagreeable ones.*";
P_HTM[2633]="*Yāni kho pana tāni vedayitāni pittasamuṭṭhānāni vā semhasamuṭṭhānāni vā vātasamuṭṭhānāni vā sannipātikāni vā utupariṇāmajāni vā visamaparihārajāni vā opakkamikāni vā kammavipākajāni vā, tānissa na bahudeva uppajjanti.**They’re healthy, so the various unpleasant feelings—stemming from disorders of bile, phlegm, wind, or their conjunction; or caused by change in weather, by not taking care of themselves, by overexertion, or as the result of past deeds—usually don’t come up.*";
P_HTM[2634]="*Appābādho hoti, catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī,**They get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that belong to the higher mind—when they want, without trouble or difficulty.*";
P_HTM[2635]="*āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati.**And they realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[2636]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu samaṇesu samaṇasukhumālo hoti.**A mendicant with these five qualities is an exquisite ascetic of ascetics.*";
P_HTM[2637]="*Yañhi taṃ, bhikkhave, sammā vadamāno vadeyya: ‘samaṇesu samaṇasukhumālo’ti, mameva taṃ, bhikkhave, sammā vadamāno vadeyya: ‘samaṇesu samaṇasukhumālo’ti.**And if anyone should be rightly called an exquisite ascetic of ascetics, it’s me.*";
P_HTM[2638]="*Ahañhi, bhikkhave, yācitova bahulaṃ cīvaraṃ paribhuñjāmi, appaṃ ayācito; yācitova bahulaṃ piṇḍapātaṃ paribhuñjāmi, appaṃ ayācito; yācitova bahulaṃ senāsanaṃ paribhuñjāmi, appaṃ ayācito; yācitova bahulaṃ gilānapaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ paribhuñjāmi, appaṃ ayācito.**For I usually use only what I’ve been invited to accept.*";
P_HTM[2639]="*Yehi kho pana bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ viharāmi, te maṃ manāpeneva bahulaṃ kāyakammena samudācaranti, appaṃ amanāpena; manāpeneva bahulaṃ vacīkammena samudācaranti, appaṃ amanāpena; manāpeneva bahulaṃ manokammena samudācaranti, appaṃ amanāpena;**When living with other spiritual practitioners, I usually treat them agreeably.*";
P_HTM[2640]="*manāpaṃyeva upahāraṃ upaharanti, appaṃ amanāpaṃ.**And I usually present them with agreeable things.*";
P_HTM[2641]="*Yāni kho pana tāni vedayitāni—pittasamuṭṭhānāni vā semhasamuṭṭhānāni vā vātasamuṭṭhānāni vā sannipātikāni vā utupariṇāmajāni vā visamaparihārajāni vā opakkamikāni vā kammavipākajāni vā—tāni me na bahudeva uppajjanti. Appābādhohamasmi.**I’m healthy.*";
P_HTM[2642]="*catunnaṃ kho panasmi jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī akicchalābhī akasiralābhī,**I get the four absorptions when I want, without trouble or difficulty.*";
P_HTM[2643]="*āsavānaṃ khayā … pe … sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmi.**And I’ve realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life.*";
P_HTM[2644]="*Yañhi taṃ, bhikkhave, sammā vadamāno vadeyya: ‘samaṇesu samaṇasukhumālo’ti, mameva taṃ, bhikkhave, sammā vadamāno vadeyya: ‘samaṇesu samaṇasukhumālo’”ti.**So if anyone should be rightly called an exquisite ascetic of ascetics, it’s me.”*";
P_HTM[2645]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2646]="*5. Phāsuvihārasuttaṃ**Living Comfortably*";
P_HTM[2647]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, phāsuvihārā.**“Mendicants, there are these five ways of living comfortably.*";
P_HTM[2648]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2649]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno mettaṃ kāyakammaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti sabrahmacārīsu āvi ceva raho ca, mettaṃ vacīkammaṃ … mettaṃ manokammaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti sabrahmacārīsu āvi ceva raho ca.**It’s when a mendicant consistently treats their spiritual companions with kindness by way of body, speech, and mind, both in public and in private.*";
P_HTM[2650]="*Yāni tāni sīlāni akhaṇḍāni acchiddāni asabalāni akammāsāni bhujissāni viññuppasatthāni aparāmaṭṭhāni samādhisaṃvattanikāni, tathārūpehi sīlehi sīlasāmaññagato viharati sabrahmacārīhi āvi ceva raho ca.**They live according to the precepts shared with their spiritual companions, both in public and in private. Those precepts are unbroken, impeccable, spotless, and unmarred, liberating, praised by sensible people, not mistaken, and leading to immersion.*";
P_HTM[2651]="*Yāyaṃ diṭṭhi ariyā niyyānikā niyyāti takkarassa sammā dukkhakkhayāya, tathārūpāya diṭṭhiyā diṭṭhisāmaññagato viharati sabrahmacārīhi āvi ceva raho ca.**They live according to the view shared with their spiritual companions, both in public and in private. That view is noble and emancipating, and brings one who practices it to the complete ending of suffering.*";
P_HTM[2652]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca phāsuvihārā”ti.**These are the five ways of living comfortably.”*";
P_HTM[2653]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2654]="*6. Ānandasuttaṃ**With Ānanda*";
P_HTM[2655]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[2656]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[2657]="*“Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, bhikkhu saṃghe viharanto phāsuṃ vihareyyā”ti?**“Sir, how could a mendicant live comfortably while staying in a monastic community?”*";
P_HTM[2658]="*“Yato kho, ānanda, bhikkhu attanā sīlasampanno hoti, no paraṃ adhisīle sampavattā;**“It’s when a mendicant is accomplished in their own ethical conduct, but they don’t motivate others to be ethical.*";
P_HTM[2659]="*ettāvatāpi kho, ānanda, bhikkhu saṃghe viharanto phāsuṃ vihareyyā”ti.**That’s how a mendicant could live comfortably while staying in a monastic community.”*";
P_HTM[2660]="*“Siyā pana, bhante, aññopi pariyāyo yathā bhikkhu saṃghe viharanto phāsuṃ vihareyyā”ti?**“But sir, could there be another way for a mendicant to live comfortably while staying in a monastic community?”*";
P_HTM[2661]="*“Siyā, ānanda.**“There could, Ānanda.*";
P_HTM[2662]="*Yato kho, ānanda, bhikkhu attanā sīlasampanno hoti, no paraṃ adhisīle sampavattā;**It’s when a mendicant is accomplished in their own ethical conduct, but they don’t motivate others to be ethical.*";
P_HTM[2663]="*attānupekkhī ca hoti, no parānupekkhī;**And they watch themselves, but don’t watch others.*";
P_HTM[2664]="*ettāvatāpi kho, ānanda, bhikkhu saṃghe viharanto phāsuṃ vihareyyā”ti.**That’s how a mendicant could live comfortably while staying in a monastic community.”*";
P_HTM[2665]="*“Siyā pana, bhante, aññopi pariyāyo yathā bhikkhu saṅghe viharanto phāsuṃ vihareyyā”ti?**“But sir, could there be another way for a mendicant to live comfortably while staying in a monastic community?”*";
P_HTM[2666]="*“Siyā, ānanda.**“There could, Ānanda.*";
P_HTM[2667]="*Yato kho, ānanda, bhikkhu attanā sīlasampanno hoti, no paraṃ adhisīle sampavattā;**It’s when a mendicant is accomplished in their own ethical conduct, but they don’t motivate others to be ethical.*";
P_HTM[2668]="*attānupekkhī ca hoti, no parānupekkhī;**And they watch themselves, but don’t watch others.*";
P_HTM[2669]="*apaññāto ca hoti, tena ca apaññātakena no paritassati;**And they’re not well-known, but aren’t bothered by that.*";
P_HTM[2670]="*ettāvatāpi kho, ānanda, bhikkhu saṅghe viharanto phāsuṃ vihareyyā”ti.**That’s how a mendicant could live comfortably while staying in a monastic community.”*";
P_HTM[2671]="*“Siyā pana, bhante, aññopi pariyāyo yathā bhikkhu saṃghe viharanto phāsuṃ vihareyyā”ti?**“But sir, could there be another way for a mendicant to live comfortably while staying in a monastic community?”*";
P_HTM[2672]="*“Siyā, ānanda.**“There could, Ānanda.*";
P_HTM[2673]="*Yato kho, ānanda, bhikkhu attanā sīlasampanno hoti, no paraṃ adhisīle sampavattā;**It’s when a mendicant is accomplished in their own ethical conduct, but they don’t motivate others to be ethical.*";
P_HTM[2674]="*attānupekkhī ca hoti, no parānupekkhī;**And they watch themselves, but don’t watch others.*";
P_HTM[2675]="*apaññāto ca hoti, tena ca apaññātakena no paritassati;**And they’re not well-known, but aren’t bothered by that.*";
P_HTM[2676]="*catunnañca jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī;**And they get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that belong to the higher mind—when they want, without trouble or difficulty.*";
P_HTM[2677]="*ettāvatāpi kho, ānanda, bhikkhu saṃghe viharanto phāsuṃ vihareyyā”ti.**That’s how a mendicant could live comfortably while staying in a monastic community.”*";
P_HTM[2678]="*“Siyā pana, bhante, aññopi pariyāyo yathā bhikkhu saṃghe viharanto phāsuṃ vihareyyā”ti?**“But sir, might there be another way for a mendicant to live comfortably while staying in a monastic community?”*";
P_HTM[2679]="*“Siyā, ānanda.**“There could, Ānanda.*";
P_HTM[2680]="*Yato kho, ānanda, bhikkhu attanā sīlasampanno hoti, no paraṃ adhisīle sampavattā;**It’s when a mendicant is accomplished in their own ethical conduct, but they don’t motivate others to be ethical.*";
P_HTM[2681]="*attānupekkhī ca hoti, no parānupekkhī;**And they watch themselves, but don’t watch others.*";
P_HTM[2682]="*apaññāto ca hoti, tena ca apaññātakena no paritassati;**And they’re not well-known, but aren’t bothered by that.*";
P_HTM[2683]="*catunnañca jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī;**And they get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that belong to the higher mind—when they want, without trouble or difficulty.*";
P_HTM[2684]="*āsavānañca khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati;**And they realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[2685]="*ettāvatāpi kho, ānanda, bhikkhu saṃghe viharanto phāsuṃ vihareyya.**That’s how a mendicant could live comfortably while staying in a monastic community.*";
P_HTM[2686]="*Imamhā cāhaṃ, ānanda, phāsuvihārā añño phāsuvihāro uttaritaro vā paṇītataro vā natthīti vadāmī”ti.**And I say that there is no better or finer way of living comfortably than this.”*";
P_HTM[2687]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2688]="*7. Sīlasuttaṃ**Ethics*";
P_HTM[2689]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa.**“Mendicants, a mendicant with five factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.*";
P_HTM[2690]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2691]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlasampanno hoti, samādhisampanno hoti, paññāsampanno hoti, vimuttisampanno hoti, vimuttiñāṇadassanasampanno hoti.**It’s when a mendicant is accomplished in ethics, immersion, wisdom, freedom, and the knowledge and vision of freedom.*";
P_HTM[2692]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti.**A mendicant with these five qualities is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.”*";
P_HTM[2693]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2694]="*8. Asekhasuttaṃ**An adept*";
P_HTM[2695]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa.**“Mendicants, a mendicant with five factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.*";
P_HTM[2696]="*Katamehi, pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2697]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu asekhena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekhena samādhikkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekhena paññākkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekhena vimuttikkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekhena vimuttiñāṇadassanakkhandhena samannāgato hoti.**It’s when they have the entire spectrum of the master’s ethics, immersion, wisdom, freedom, and knowledge and vision of freedom.*";
P_HTM[2698]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti.**A mendicant with these five qualities … is the supreme field of merit for the world.”*";
P_HTM[2699]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2700]="*9. Cātuddisasuttaṃ**All Four Directions*";
P_HTM[2701]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu cātuddiso hoti.**“Mendicants, a mendicant with five qualities has all four directions covered.*";
P_HTM[2702]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2703]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati ācāragocarasampanno aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu;**It’s when mendicant is ethical, restrained in the monastic code, conducting themselves well and seeking alms in suitable places. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken.*";
P_HTM[2704]="*bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo, ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpāssa dhammā bahussutā honti dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā;**They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering them, reinforcing them by recitation, mentally scrutinizing them, and comprehending them theoretically.*";
P_HTM[2705]="*santuṭṭho hoti itarītaracīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena;**They’re content with any kind of robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick.*";
P_HTM[2706]="*catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī;**They get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that belong to the higher mind—when they want, without trouble or difficulty.*";
P_HTM[2707]="*āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati.**They realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[2708]="*Imehi, kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu cātuddiso hotī”ti.**A mendicant with these five qualities has all four directions covered.”*";
P_HTM[2709]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2710]="*10. Araññasuttaṃ**Wilderness*";
P_HTM[2711]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevituṃ.**“Mendicants, when a mendicant has five qualities they’re ready to frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.*";
P_HTM[2712]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2713]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti … pe … samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu;**It’s when a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the code of conduct, with good behavior and supporters. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken.*";
P_HTM[2714]="*bahussuto hoti … pe … diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā;**They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s totally full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering them, reciting them, mentally scrutinizing them, and understanding them with right view.*";
P_HTM[2715]="*āraddhavīriyo viharati thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu;**They live with energy roused up for giving up unskillful qualities and gaining skillful qualities. They’re strong, staunchly vigorous, not slacking off when it comes to developing skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[2716]="*catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī;**They get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that belong to the higher mind—when they want, without trouble or difficulty.*";
P_HTM[2717]="*āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati.**They realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[2718]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevitun”ti.**When a mendicant has these five qualities they’re ready to frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.”*";
P_HTM[2719]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2720]="*Phāsuvihāravaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[2721]="*Sārajjaṃ saṅkito coro,* **";
P_HTM[2722]="*Sukhumālaṃ phāsu pañcamaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2723]="*Ānanda sīlāsekhā ca,* **";
P_HTM[2724]="*Cātuddiso araññena cāti.* **";
P_HTM[2725]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**At Andhakavinda*";
P_HTM[2726]="*1. Kulūpakasuttaṃ**Visiting Families*";
P_HTM[2727]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato kulūpako bhikkhu kulesu appiyo ca hoti amanāpo ca agaru ca abhāvanīyo ca.**“Mendicants, a mendicant with five qualities who visits families is unlikable and unlovable, not respected or admired.*";
P_HTM[2728]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2729]="*Asanthavavissāsī ca hoti, anissaravikappī ca, vissaṭṭhupasevī ca, upakaṇṇakajappī ca, atiyācanako ca.**They act as though they're close to people they hardly know. They give away things they don’t own. They over-associate with close friends. They whisper in the ear. And they ask for too much.*";
P_HTM[2730]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato kulūpako bhikkhu kulesu appiyo ca hoti amanāpo ca agaru ca abhāvanīyo ca.**A mendicant with these five qualities who visits families is unlikable and unlovable, not respected or admired.*";
P_HTM[2731]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato kulūpako bhikkhu kulesu piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo ca.**A mendicant with five qualities who visits families is dear and beloved, respected and admired.*";
P_HTM[2732]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2733]="*Na asanthavavissāsī ca hoti, na anissaravikappī ca, na vissaṭṭhupasevī ca, na upakaṇṇakajappī ca, na atiyācanako ca.**They don’t act as though they're close to people they hardly know. They don’t give away things they don’t own. They don’t over-associate with close friends. They don’t whisper in the ear. And they don’t ask for too much.*";
P_HTM[2734]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato kulūpako bhikkhu kulesu piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo cā”ti.**A mendicant with these five qualities who visits families is dear and beloved, respected and admired.”*";
P_HTM[2735]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2736]="*2. Pacchāsamaṇasuttaṃ**An Ascetic to Follow Behind on Almsround*";
P_HTM[2737]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato pacchāsamaṇo na ādātabbo.**“Mendicants, you shouldn’t take an ascetic with five qualities to follow behind on almsround.*";
P_HTM[2738]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2739]="*Atidūre vā gacchati accāsanne vā, na pattapariyāpannaṃ gaṇhati, āpattisāmantā bhaṇamānaṃ na nivāreti, bhaṇamānassa antarantarā kathaṃ opāteti, duppañño hoti jaḷo eḷamūgo.**They walk too far away or too close behind. They don’t take your bowl when it’s full. They don’t warn you when your speech is bordering on an offense. They keep on interrupting while you’re speaking. And they’re witless, dull, and stupid.*";
P_HTM[2740]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato pacchāsamaṇo na ādātabbo.**You shouldn’t take an ascetic with these five qualities to follow behind on almsround.*";
P_HTM[2741]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato pacchāsamaṇo ādātabbo.**You should take an ascetic with five qualities to follow behind on almsround.*";
P_HTM[2742]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2743]="*Nātidūre gacchati na accāsanne, pattapariyāpannaṃ gaṇhati, āpattisāmantā bhaṇamānaṃ nivāreti, bhaṇamānassa na antarantarā kathaṃ opāteti, paññavā hoti ajaḷo aneḷamūgo.**They don’t walk too far away or too close behind. They take your bowl when it is full. They warn you when your speech is bordering on an offense. They don’t interrupt while you’re speaking. And they’re wise, bright, and clever.*";
P_HTM[2744]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato pacchāsamaṇo ādātabbo”ti.**You should take an ascetic with these five qualities to follow behind on almsround.”*";
P_HTM[2745]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2746]="*3. Sammāsamādhisuttaṃ**Right Immersion*";
P_HTM[2747]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu abhabbo sammāsamādhiṃ upasampajja viharituṃ.**“Mendicants, a mendicant who has five qualities can’t enter and remain in right immersion.*";
P_HTM[2748]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2749]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkhamo hoti rūpānaṃ, akkhamo saddānaṃ, akkhamo gandhānaṃ, akkhamo rasānaṃ, akkhamo phoṭṭhabbānaṃ.**It’s when a mendicant can’t endure sights, sounds, smells, tastes, and touches.*";
P_HTM[2750]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu abhabbo sammāsamādhiṃ upasampajja viharituṃ.**A mendicant who has these five qualities can’t enter and remain in right immersion.*";
P_HTM[2751]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu bhabbo sammāsamādhiṃ upasampajja viharituṃ.**A mendicant who has five qualities can enter and remain in right immersion.*";
P_HTM[2752]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2753]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu khamo hoti rūpānaṃ, khamo saddānaṃ, khamo gandhānaṃ, khamo rasānaṃ, khamo phoṭṭhabbānaṃ.**It’s when a mendicant can endure sights, sounds, smells, tastes, and touches.*";
P_HTM[2754]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu bhabbo sammāsamādhiṃ upasampajja viharitun”ti.**A mendicant who has these five qualities can enter and remain in right immersion.”*";
P_HTM[2755]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2756]="*4. Andhakavindasuttaṃ**At Andhakavinda*";
P_HTM[2757]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā magadhesu viharati andhakavinde.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Magadhans at Andhakavinda.*";
P_HTM[2758]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[2759]="*“Ye te, ānanda, bhikkhū navā acirapabbajitā adhunāgatā imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ, te vo, ānanda, bhikkhū pañcasu dhammesu samādapetabbā nivesetabbā patiṭṭhāpetabbā.**“Ānanda, those mendicants who are junior, recently gone forth, newly come to this teaching and training should be encouraged, supported, and established in five things.*";
P_HTM[2760]="*Katamesu pañcasu?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2761]="*‘Etha tumhe, āvuso, sīlavā hotha, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvutā viharatha ācāragocarasampannā aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvino, samādāya sikkhatha sikkhāpadesū’ti—iti pātimokkhasaṃvare samādapetabbā nivesetabbā patiṭṭhāpetabbā.**They should be encouraged, supported, and established in restraint in the monastic code: ‘Reverends, please be ethical. Live restrained in the code of conduct, conducting yourselves well and seeking alms in suitable places. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, keep the rules you’ve undertaken.’*";
P_HTM[2762]="*‘Etha tumhe, āvuso, indriyesu guttadvārā viharatha ārakkhasatino nipakkasatino, sārakkhitamānasā satārakkhena cetasā samannāgatā’ti—iti indriyasaṃvare samādapetabbā nivesetabbā patiṭṭhāpetabbā.**They should be encouraged, supported, and established in sense restraint: ‘Reverends, please live with sense doors guarded, mindfully alert and on guard, with protected mind, having a heart protected by mindfulness.’*";
P_HTM[2763]="*‘Etha tumhe, āvuso, appabhassā hotha, bhasse pariyantakārino’ti—iti bhassapariyante samādapetabbā nivesetabbā patiṭṭhāpetabbā.**They should be encouraged, supported, and established in limiting their speech: ‘Reverends, please speak little. Put a limit on your speech.’*";
P_HTM[2764]="*‘Etha tumhe, āvuso, āraññikā hotha, araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevathā’ti—iti kāyavūpakāse samādapetabbā nivesetabbā patiṭṭhāpetabbā.**They should be encouraged, supported, and established in retreat: ‘Reverends, please live in the wilderness. Frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.’*";
P_HTM[2765]="*‘Etha tumhe, āvuso, sammādiṭṭhikā hotha sammādassanena samannāgatā’ti—iti sammādassane samādapetabbā nivesetabbā patiṭṭhāpetabbā.**They should be encouraged, supported, and established in right perspective: ‘Reverends, please hold right view and have right perspective.’*";
P_HTM[2766]="*Ye te, ānanda, bhikkhū navā acirapabbajitā adhunāgatā imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ, te vo, ānanda, bhikkhū imesu pañcasu dhammesu samādapetabbā nivesetabbā patiṭṭhāpetabbā”ti.**Those mendicants who are junior, recently gone forth, newly come to this teaching and training should be encouraged, supported, and established in these five things.”*";
P_HTM[2767]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2768]="*5. Maccharinīsuttaṃ**Stingy*";
P_HTM[2769]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgatā bhikkhunī yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, a nun with five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[2770]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2771]="*Āvāsamaccharinī hoti, kulamaccharinī hoti, lābhamaccharinī hoti, vaṇṇamaccharinī hoti, dhammamaccharinī hoti.**She is stingy with dwellings, families, material possessions, praise, and the teaching.*";
P_HTM[2772]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgatā bhikkhunī yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ niraye.**A nun with these five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[2773]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgatā bhikkhunī yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ sagge.**A nun with five qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[2774]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2775]="*Na āvāsamaccharinī hoti, na kulamaccharinī hoti, na lābhamaccharinī hoti, na vaṇṇamaccharinī hoti, na dhammamaccharinī hoti.**She is not stingy with dwellings, families, material possessions, praise, or the teaching.*";
P_HTM[2776]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgatā bhikkhunī yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ sagge”ti.**A nun with these five qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[2777]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2778]="*6. Vaṇṇanāsuttaṃ**Praise*";
P_HTM[2779]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgatā bhikkhunī yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, a nun with five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[2780]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2781]="*Ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā avaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati,**Without examining or scrutinizing, she praises those deserving of criticism,*";
P_HTM[2782]="*ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā vaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati,**and criticizes those deserving of praise.*";
P_HTM[2783]="*ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā appasādanīye ṭhāne pasādaṃ upadaṃseti,**She arouses faith in things that are dubious,*";
P_HTM[2784]="*ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā pasādanīye ṭhāne appasādaṃ upadaṃseti,**and doesn’t arouse faith in things that are inspiring.*";
P_HTM[2785]="*saddhādeyyaṃ vinipāteti.**And she wastes gifts given in faith.*";
P_HTM[2786]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgatā bhikkhunī yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ niraye.**A nun with these five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[2787]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgatā bhikkhunī yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ sagge.**A nun with five qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[2788]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2789]="*Anuvicca pariyogāhetvā avaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati,**After examining and scrutinizing, she criticizes those deserving of criticism,*";
P_HTM[2790]="*anuvicca pariyogāhetvā vaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati,**and praises those deserving of praise.*";
P_HTM[2791]="*anuvicca pariyogāhetvā appasādanīye ṭhāne appasādaṃ upadaṃseti,**She doesn’t arouse faith in things that are dubious,*";
P_HTM[2792]="*anuvicca pariyogāhetvā pasādanīye ṭhāne pasādaṃ upadaṃseti,**and does arouse faith in things that are inspiring.*";
P_HTM[2793]="*saddhādeyyaṃ na vinipāteti.**And she doesn’t waste gifts given in faith.*";
P_HTM[2794]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgatā bhikkhunī yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ sagge”ti.**A nun with these five qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[2795]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2796]="*7. Issukinīsuttaṃ**Jealous*";
P_HTM[2797]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgatā bhikkhunī yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, a nun with five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[2798]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2799]="*Ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā avaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati,**Without examining or scrutinizing, she praises those deserving of criticism,*";
P_HTM[2800]="*ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā vaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati,**and criticizes those deserving of praise.*";
P_HTM[2801]="*issukinī ca hoti,**She is jealous,*";
P_HTM[2802]="*maccharinī ca,**stingy,*";
P_HTM[2803]="*saddhādeyyaṃ vinipāteti.**and wastes gifts given in faith.*";
P_HTM[2804]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgatā bhikkhunī yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ niraye.**A nun with these five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[2805]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgatā bhikkhunī yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ sagge.**A nun with five qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[2806]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2807]="*Anuvicca pariyogāhetvā avaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati,**After examining and scrutinizing, she criticizes those deserving of criticism,*";
P_HTM[2808]="*anuvicca pariyogāhetvā vaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati,**and praises those deserving of praise.*";
P_HTM[2809]="*anissukinī ca hoti,**She is not jealous,*";
P_HTM[2810]="*amaccharinī ca,**or stingy,*";
P_HTM[2811]="*saddhādeyyaṃ na vinipāteti.**and doesn’t waste gifts given in faith.*";
P_HTM[2812]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgatā bhikkhunī yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ sagge”ti.**A nun with these five qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[2813]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2814]="*8. Micchādiṭṭhikasuttaṃ**Having Wrong View*";
P_HTM[2815]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgatā bhikkhunī yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, a nun with five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[2816]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2817]="*Ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā avaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati,**Without examining or scrutinizing, she praises those deserving of criticism,*";
P_HTM[2818]="*ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā vaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati,**and criticizes those deserving of praise.*";
P_HTM[2819]="*micchādiṭṭhikā ca hoti,**She has wrong view*";
P_HTM[2820]="*micchāsaṅkappā ca,**and wrong thought,*";
P_HTM[2821]="*saddhādeyyaṃ vinipāteti.**and wastes gifts given in faith.*";
P_HTM[2822]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgatā bhikkhunī yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ niraye.**A nun with these five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[2823]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgatā bhikkhunī yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ sagge.**A nun with five qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[2824]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2825]="*Anuvicca pariyogāhetvā avaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati,**After examining and scrutinizing, she criticizes those deserving of criticism,*";
P_HTM[2826]="*anuvicca pariyogāhetvā vaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati,**and praises those deserving of praise.*";
P_HTM[2827]="*sammādiṭṭhikā ca hoti,**She has right view*";
P_HTM[2828]="*sammāsaṅkappā ca,**and right thought,*";
P_HTM[2829]="*saddhādeyyaṃ na vinipāteti.**and doesn’t waste gifts given in faith.*";
P_HTM[2830]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgatā bhikkhunī yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ sagge”ti.**A nun with these five qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[2831]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2832]="*9. Micchāvācāsuttaṃ**Wrong Speech*";
P_HTM[2833]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgatā bhikkhunī yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, a nun with five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
