P_HTM[2848]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgatā bhikkhunī yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ sagge”ti.**A nun with these five qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[2849]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2850]="*10. Micchāvāyāmasuttaṃ**Wrong Effort*";
P_HTM[2851]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgatā bhikkhunī yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, a nun with five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[2852]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2853]="*Ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā avaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati,**Without examining or scrutinizing, she praises those deserving of criticism,*";
P_HTM[2854]="*ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā vaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati,**and criticizes those deserving of praise.*";
P_HTM[2855]="*micchāvāyāmā ca hoti,**She has wrong effort and*";
P_HTM[2856]="*micchāsatinī ca,**wrong mindfulness,*";
P_HTM[2857]="*saddhādeyyaṃ vinipāteti.**and wastes gifts given in faith.*";
P_HTM[2858]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgatā bhikkhunī yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ niraye.**A nun with these five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[2859]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgatā bhikkhunī yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ sagge.**A nun with five qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[2860]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2861]="*Anuvicca pariyogāhetvā avaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati,**After examining and scrutinizing, she criticizes those deserving of criticism,*";
P_HTM[2862]="*anuvicca pariyogāhetvā vaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati,**and praises those deserving of praise.*";
P_HTM[2863]="*sammāvāyāmā ca hoti,**She has right effort and*";
P_HTM[2864]="*sammāsatinī ca,**right mindfulness,*";
P_HTM[2865]="*saddhādeyyaṃ na vinipāteti.**and doesn’t waste gifts given in faith.*";
P_HTM[2866]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgatā bhikkhunī yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ sagge”ti.**A nun with these five qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[2867]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2868]="*Andhakavindavaggo dutiyo.* **";
P_HTM[2869]="*Kulūpako pacchāsamaṇo,* **";
P_HTM[2870]="*samādhiandhakavindaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[2871]="*Maccharī vaṇṇanā issā,* **";
P_HTM[2872]="*diṭṭhivācāya vāyamāti.* **";
P_HTM[2873]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**Sick*";
P_HTM[2874]="*1. Gilānasuttaṃ**Sick*";
P_HTM[2875]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof.*";
P_HTM[2876]="*Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena gilānasālā tenupasaṅkami.**Then in the late afternoon, the Buddha came out of retreat and went to the infirmary, where*";
P_HTM[2877]="*Addasā kho bhagavā aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ dubbalaṃ gilānakaṃ;**he saw a certain mendicant who was weak and sick.*";
P_HTM[2878]="*disvā paññatte āsane nisīdi.**He sat down on the seat spread out,*";
P_HTM[2879]="*Nisajja kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**and addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[2880]="*“Yaṃ kiñci, bhikkhave, bhikkhuṃ dubbalaṃ gilānakaṃ pañca dhammā na vijahanti, tassetaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ:**“Mendicants, if a weak and sick mendicant does not neglect five things, it can be expected that*";
P_HTM[2881]="*‘nacirasseva āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissatī’ti.**they will soon realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[2882]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2883]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu asubhānupassī kāye viharati, āhāre paṭikūlasaññī, sabbaloke anabhiratasaññī, sabbasaṅkhāresu aniccānupassī, maraṇasaññā kho panassa ajjhattaṃ sūpaṭṭhitā hoti.**It’s when a mendicant meditates observing the ugliness of the body, perceives the repulsiveness of food, perceives dissatisfaction with the whole world, observes the impermanence of all conditions, and has well established the perception of their own death.*";
P_HTM[2884]="*Yaṃ kiñci, bhikkhave, bhikkhuṃ dubbalaṃ gilānakaṃ ime pañca dhammā na vijahanti, tassetaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ:**If a weak and sick mendicant does not neglect these five things, it can be expected that*";
P_HTM[2885]="*‘nacirasseva āsavānaṃ khayā … pe … sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissatī’”ti.**they will soon realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.”*";
P_HTM[2886]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2887]="*2. Satisūpaṭṭhitasuttaṃ**Mindfulness Well Established*";
P_HTM[2888]="*“Yo hi koci, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vā bhikkhunī vā pañca dhamme bhāveti pañca dhamme bahulīkaroti, tassa dvinnaṃ phalānaṃ aññataraṃ phalaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—**“Mendicants, any monk or nun who develops and cultivates five qualities can expect one of two results:*";
P_HTM[2889]="*diṭṭheva dhamme aññā, sati vā upādisese anāgāmitā.**enlightenment in the present life, or if there’s something left over, non-return.*";
P_HTM[2890]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2891]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno ajjhattaññeva sati sūpaṭṭhitā hoti dhammānaṃ udayatthagāminiyā paññāya, asubhānupassī kāye viharati, āhāre paṭikūlasaññī, sabbaloke anabhiratasaññī, sabbasaṅkhāresu aniccānupassī.**It’s when a mendicant has well established mindfulness inside themselves in order to understand the arising and passing away of phenomena, meditates observing the ugliness of the body, perceives the repulsiveness of food, perceives dissatisfaction with the whole world, and observes the impermanence of all conditions.*";
P_HTM[2892]="*Yo hi koci, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vā bhikkhunī vā ime pañca dhamme bhāveti ime pañca dhamme bahulīkaroti, tassa dvinnaṃ phalānaṃ aññataraṃ phalaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—**Any monk or nun who develops and cultivates these five qualities can expect one of two results:*";
P_HTM[2893]="*diṭṭheva dhamme aññā, sati vā upādisese anāgāmitā”ti.**enlightenment in the present life, or if there’s something left over, non-return.”*";
P_HTM[2894]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2895]="*3. Paṭhamaupaṭṭhākasuttaṃ**A Carer (1st)*";
P_HTM[2896]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato gilāno dūpaṭṭhāko hoti.**“Mendicants, a patient with five qualities is hard to care for.*";
P_HTM[2897]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2898]="*Asappāyakārī hoti, sappāye mattaṃ na jānāti, bhesajjaṃ nappaṭisevitā hoti, atthakāmassa gilānupaṭṭhākassa na yathābhūtaṃ ābādhaṃ āvikattā hoti abhikkamantaṃ vā abhikkamatīti paṭikkamantaṃ vā paṭikkamatīti ṭhitaṃ vā ṭhitoti, uppannānaṃ sārīrikānaṃ vedanānaṃ dukkhānaṃ tibbānaṃ kharānaṃ kaṭukānaṃ asātānaṃ amanāpānaṃ pāṇaharānaṃ anadhivāsakajātiko hoti.**They do what is unsuitable. They don’t know moderation in what is suitable. They don’t take their medicine. Though their carer wants what’s best for them, they don’t accurately report their symptoms by saying when they’re getting worse, getting better, or staying the same. And they cannot endure physical pain—sharp, severe, acute, unpleasant, disagreeable, and life-threatening.*";
P_HTM[2899]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato gilāno dūpaṭṭhāko hoti.**A patient with these five qualities is hard to care for.*";
P_HTM[2900]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato gilāno sūpaṭṭhāko hoti.**A patient with five qualities is easy to care for.*";
P_HTM[2901]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2902]="*Sappāyakārī hoti, sappāye mattaṃ jānāti, bhesajjaṃ paṭisevitā hoti, atthakāmassa gilānupaṭṭhākassa yathābhūtaṃ ābādhaṃ āvikattā hoti abhikkamantaṃ vā abhikkamatīti paṭikkamantaṃ vā paṭikkamatīti ṭhitaṃ vā ṭhitoti, uppannānaṃ sārīrikānaṃ vedanānaṃ dukkhānaṃ tibbānaṃ kharānaṃ kaṭukānaṃ asātānaṃ amanāpānaṃ pāṇaharānaṃ adhivāsakajātiko hoti.**They do what is suitable. They know moderation in what is suitable. They take their medicine. Because their carer wants what’s best for them, they accurately report their symptoms by saying when they’re getting worse, getting better, or staying the same. And they can endure physical pain—sharp, severe, acute, unpleasant, disagreeable, and life-threatening.*";
P_HTM[2903]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato gilāno sūpaṭṭhāko hotī”ti.**A patient with these five qualities is easy to care for.”*";
P_HTM[2904]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2905]="*4. Dutiyaupaṭṭhākasuttaṃ**A Carer (2nd)*";
P_HTM[2906]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato gilānupaṭṭhāko nālaṃ gilānaṃ upaṭṭhātuṃ.**“Mendicants, a carer with five qualities is not competent to care for a patient.*";
P_HTM[2907]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2908]="*Nappaṭibalo hoti bhesajjaṃ saṃvidhātuṃ;**They’re unable to prepare medicine.*";
P_HTM[2909]="*sappāyāsappāyaṃ na jānāti, asappāyaṃ upanāmeti, sappāyaṃ apanāmeti;**They don’t know what is suitable and unsuitable, so they supply what is unsuitable and remove what is suitable.*";
P_HTM[2910]="*āmisantaro gilānaṃ upaṭṭhāti, no mettacitto;**They care for the sick for the sake of material benefits, not out of love.*";
P_HTM[2911]="*jegucchī hoti uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā vantaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā nīharituṃ;**They’re disgusted to remove feces, urine, vomit, or spit.*";
P_HTM[2912]="*nappaṭibalo hoti gilānaṃ kālena kālaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassetuṃ samādapetuṃ samuttejetuṃ sampahaṃsetuṃ.**They’re unable to educate, encourage, fire up, and inspire the patient with a Dhamma talk from time to time.*";
P_HTM[2913]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato gilānupaṭṭhāko nālaṃ gilānaṃ upaṭṭhātuṃ.**A carer with these five qualities is not competent to care for a patient.*";
P_HTM[2914]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato gilānupaṭṭhāko alaṃ gilānaṃ upaṭṭhātuṃ.**A carer with five qualities is competent to care for a patient.*";
P_HTM[2915]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2916]="*Paṭibalo hoti bhesajjaṃ saṃvidhātuṃ;**They’re able to prepare medicine.*";
P_HTM[2917]="*sappāyāsappāyaṃ jānāti, asappāyaṃ apanāmeti, sappāyaṃ upanāmeti;**They know what is suitable and unsuitable, so they remove what is unsuitable and supply what is suitable.*";
P_HTM[2918]="*mettacitto gilānaṃ upaṭṭhāti, no āmisantaro;**They care for the sick out of love, not for the sake of material benefits.*";
P_HTM[2919]="*ajegucchī hoti uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā vantaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā nīharituṃ;**They’re not disgusted to remove feces, urine, vomit, or spit.*";
P_HTM[2920]="*paṭibalo hoti gilānaṃ kālena kālaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassetuṃ samādapetuṃ samuttejetuṃ sampahaṃsetuṃ.**They’re able to educate, encourage, fire up, and inspire the patient with a Dhamma talk from time to time.*";
P_HTM[2921]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato gilānupaṭṭhāko alaṃ gilānaṃ upaṭṭhātun”ti.**A carer with these five qualities is competent to care for a patient.”*";
P_HTM[2922]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2923]="*5. Paṭhamaanāyussāsuttaṃ**Longevity (1st)*";
P_HTM[2924]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhammā anāyussā.**“Mendicants, these five things impede longevity.*";
P_HTM[2925]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2926]="*Asappāyakārī hoti, sappāye mattaṃ na jānāti, apariṇatabhojī ca hoti, akālacārī ca hoti, abrahmacārī ca.**Doing what is unsuitable, not knowing moderation in what is suitable, eating food unfit for consumption, activity at unsuitable times, and unchastity.*";
P_HTM[2927]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhammā anāyussā.**These are the five things that impede longevity.*";
P_HTM[2928]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhammā āyussā.**These five things promote longevity.*";
P_HTM[2929]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2930]="*Sappāyakārī hoti, sappāye mattaṃ jānāti, pariṇatabhojī ca hoti, kālacārī ca hoti, brahmacārī ca.**Doing what is suitable, knowing moderation in what is suitable, eating food fit for consumption, activity at suitable times, and celibacy.*";
P_HTM[2931]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhammā āyussā”ti.**These are the five things that promote longevity.”*";
P_HTM[2932]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2933]="*6. Dutiyaanāyussāsuttaṃ**Longevity (2nd)*";
P_HTM[2934]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhammā anāyussā.**“Mendicants, these five things impede longevity.*";
P_HTM[2935]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2936]="*Asappāyakārī hoti, sappāye mattaṃ na jānāti, apariṇatabhojī ca hoti, dussīlo ca, pāpamitto ca.**Doing what is unsuitable, not knowing moderation in what is suitable, eating food unfit for consumption, unethical behavior, and bad friends.*";
P_HTM[2937]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhammā anāyussā.**These are the five things that impede longevity.*";
P_HTM[2938]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhammā āyussā.**These five things promote longevity.*";
P_HTM[2939]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2940]="*Sappāyakārī hoti, sappāye mattaṃ jānāti, pariṇatabhojī ca hoti, sīlavā ca, kalyāṇamitto ca.**Doing what is suitable, knowing moderation in what is suitable, eating food fit for consumption, ethical conduct, and good friends.*";
P_HTM[2941]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhammā āyussā”ti.**These are the five things that promote longevity.”*";
P_HTM[2942]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2943]="*7. Vapakāsasuttaṃ**Living Apart*";
P_HTM[2944]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu nālaṃ saṃghamhā vapakāsituṃ.**“Mendicants, a mendicant with five qualities is not fit to live apart from a Saṅgha community.*";
P_HTM[2945]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2946]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu asantuṭṭho hoti itarītarena cīvarena, asantuṭṭho hoti itarītarena piṇḍapātena, asantuṭṭho hoti itarītarena senāsanena, asantuṭṭho hoti itarītarena gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena, kāmasaṅkappabahulo ca viharati.**It’s when a mendicant is not content with any kind of robe, alms-food, lodging, and medicines and supplies for the sick. And they have a lot of sensual thoughts.*";
P_HTM[2947]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu nālaṃ saṃghamhā vapakāsituṃ.**A mendicant with these five qualities is not fit to live apart from a Saṅgha community.*";
P_HTM[2948]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ saṃghamhā vapakāsituṃ.**A mendicant with five qualities is fit to live apart from a Saṅgha community.*";
P_HTM[2949]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2950]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu santuṭṭho hoti itarītarena cīvarena, santuṭṭho hoti itarītarena piṇḍapātena, santuṭṭho hoti itarītarena senāsanena, santuṭṭho hoti itarītarena gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena, nekkhammasaṅkappabahulo ca viharati.**It’s when a mendicant is content with any kind of robe, alms-food, lodging, and medicines and supplies for the sick. And they think a lot about renunciation.*";
P_HTM[2951]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ saṃghamhā vapakāsitun”ti.**A mendicant with these five qualities is fit to live apart from a Saṅgha community.”*";
P_HTM[2952]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2953]="*8. Samaṇasukhasuttaṃ**An Ascetic’s Happiness*";
P_HTM[2954]="*“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, samaṇadukkhāni.**“Mendicants, there are these five kinds of suffering for an ascetic.*";
P_HTM[2955]="*Katamāni pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2956]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu asantuṭṭho hoti itarītarena cīvarena, asantuṭṭho hoti itarītarena piṇḍapātena, asantuṭṭho hoti itarītarena senāsanena, asantuṭṭho hoti itarītarena gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena, anabhirato ca brahmacariyaṃ carati.**It’s when a mendicant is not content with any kind of robe, alms-food, lodging, and medicines and supplies for the sick. And they live the spiritual life dissatisfied.*";
P_HTM[2957]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca samaṇadukkhāni.**These are five kinds of suffering for an ascetic.*";
P_HTM[2958]="*Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, samaṇasukhāni.**There are these five kinds of happiness for an ascetic.*";
P_HTM[2959]="*Katamāni pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2960]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu santuṭṭho hoti itarītarena cīvarena, santuṭṭho hoti itarītarena piṇḍapātena, santuṭṭho hoti itarītarena senāsanena, santuṭṭho hoti itarītarena gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena, abhirato ca brahmacariyaṃ carati.**It’s when a mendicant is content with any kind of robe, alms-food, lodging, and medicines and supplies for the sick. And they live the spiritual life satisfied.*";
P_HTM[2961]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca samaṇasukhānī”ti.**These are five kinds of happiness for an ascetic.”*";
P_HTM[2962]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2963]="*9. Parikuppasuttaṃ**Fatal Wounds*";
P_HTM[2964]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, āpāyikā nerayikā parikuppā atekicchā.**“Mendicants, these five fatal wounds lead to a place of loss, to hell.*";
P_HTM[2965]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2966]="*Mātā jīvitā voropitā hoti, pitā jīvitā voropito hoti, arahaṃ jīvitā voropito hoti, tathāgatassa duṭṭhena cittena lohitaṃ uppāditaṃ hoti, saṃgho bhinno hoti.**Murdering your mother or father or a perfected one; maliciously shedding the blood of a Realized One; and causing a schism in the Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[2967]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca āpāyikā nerayikā parikuppā atekicchā”ti.**These five fatal wounds lead to a place of loss, to hell.”*";
P_HTM[2968]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2969]="*10. Byasanasuttaṃ**Loss*";
P_HTM[2970]="*“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, byasanāni.**“Mendicants, there are these five losses.*";
P_HTM[2971]="*Katamāni pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2972]="*Ñātibyasanaṃ, bhogabyasanaṃ, rogabyasanaṃ, sīlabyasanaṃ, diṭṭhibyasanaṃ.**Loss of relatives, wealth, health, ethics, and view.*";
P_HTM[2973]="*Na, bhikkhave, sattā ñātibyasanahetu vā bhogabyasanahetu vā rogabyasanahetu vā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti.**It is not because of loss of relatives, wealth, or health that sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[2974]="*Sīlabyasanahetu vā, bhikkhave, sattā diṭṭhibyasanahetu vā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti.**It is because of loss of ethics or view that sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[2975]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca byasanāni.**These are the five losses.*";
P_HTM[2976]="*Pañcimā, bhikkhave, sampadā.**There are these five endowments.*";
P_HTM[2977]="*Katamā pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2978]="*Ñātisampadā, bhogasampadā, ārogyasampadā, sīlasampadā, diṭṭhisampadā.**Endowment with relatives, wealth, health, ethics, and view.*";
P_HTM[2979]="*Na, bhikkhave, sattā ñātisampadāhetu vā bhogasampadāhetu vā ārogyasampadāhetu vā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti.**It is not because of endowment with relatives, wealth, or health that sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[2980]="*Sīlasampadāhetu vā, bhikkhave, sattā diṭṭhisampadāhetu vā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti.**It is because of endowment with ethics or view that sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[2981]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, pañca sampadā”ti.**These are the five endowments.”*";
P_HTM[2982]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2983]="*Gilānavaggo tatiyo.* **";
P_HTM[2984]="*Gilāno satisūpaṭṭhi,* **";
P_HTM[2985]="*Dve upaṭṭhākā duvāyusā;* **";
P_HTM[2986]="*Vapakāsasamaṇasukhā,* **";
P_HTM[2987]="*Parikuppaṃ byasanena cāti.* **";
P_HTM[2988]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**Kings*";
P_HTM[2989]="*1. Paṭhamacakkānuvattanasuttaṃ**Wielding Power (1st)*";
P_HTM[2990]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato rājā cakkavattī dhammeneva cakkaṃ vatteti;**“Mendicants, possessing five factors a wheel-turning monarch wields power only in a principled manner.*";
P_HTM[2991]="*taṃ hoti cakkaṃ appaṭivattiyaṃ kenaci manussabhūtena paccatthikena pāṇinā.**And this power cannot be undermined by any human enemy.*";
P_HTM[2992]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2993]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rājā cakkavattī atthaññū ca hoti, dhammaññū ca, mattaññū ca, kālaññū ca, parisaññū ca.**A wheel-turning monarch knows what is right, knows principle, knows moderation, knows the right time, and knows the assembly.*";
P_HTM[2994]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi aṅgehi samannāgato rājā cakkavattī dhammeneva cakkaṃ pavatteti;**A wheel-turning monarch who possesses these five factors wields power only in a principled manner.*";
P_HTM[2995]="*taṃ hoti cakkaṃ appaṭivattiyaṃ kenaci manussabhūtena paccatthikena pāṇinā.**And this power cannot be undermined by any human enemy.*";
P_HTM[2996]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato tathāgato arahaṃ sammāsambuddho dhammeneva anuttaraṃ dhammacakkaṃ pavatteti;**In the same way, possessing five factors a Realized One, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha rolls forth the supreme Wheel of Dhamma only in a principled manner.*";
P_HTM[2997]="*taṃ hoti cakkaṃ appaṭivattiyaṃ samaṇena vā brāhmaṇena vā devena vā mārena vā brahmunā vā kenaci vā lokasmiṃ.**And that wheel cannot be rolled back by any ascetic or brahmin or god or Māra or Brahmā or by anyone in the world.*";
P_HTM[2998]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[2999]="*Idha, bhikkhave, tathāgato arahaṃ sammāsambuddho atthaññū, dhammaññū, mattaññū, kālaññū, parisaññū.**A Realized One knows what is right, knows principle, knows moderation, knows the right time, and knows the assembly.*";
P_HTM[3000]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato tathāgato arahaṃ sammāsambuddho dhammeneva anuttaraṃ dhammacakkaṃ pavatteti;**Possessing these five factors a Realized One, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha rolls forth the supreme Wheel of Dhamma only in a principled manner.*";
P_HTM[3001]="*taṃ hoti dhammacakkaṃ appaṭivattiyaṃ samaṇena vā brāhmaṇena vā devena vā mārena vā brahmunā vā kenaci vā lokasmin”ti.**And that wheel cannot be rolled back by any ascetic or brahmin or god or Māra or Brahmā or by anyone in the world.”*";
P_HTM[3002]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3003]="*2. Dutiyacakkānuvattanasuttaṃ**Wielding Power (2nd)*";
P_HTM[3004]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato rañño cakkavattissa jeṭṭho putto pitarā pavattitaṃ cakkaṃ dhammeneva anuppavatteti;**“Mendicants, possessing five factors a wheel-turning monarch’s eldest son continues to wield the power set in motion by his father only in a principled manner.*";
P_HTM[3005]="*taṃ hoti cakkaṃ appaṭivattiyaṃ kenaci manussabhūtena paccatthikena pāṇinā.**And this power cannot be undermined by any human enemy.*";
P_HTM[3006]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3007]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño cakkavattissa jeṭṭho putto atthaññū ca hoti, dhammaññū ca, mattaññū ca, kālaññū ca, parisaññū ca.**A wheel-turning monarch’s oldest son knows what is right, knows principle, knows moderation, knows the right time, and knows the assembly.*";
P_HTM[3008]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi aṅgehi samannāgato rañño cakkavattissa jeṭṭho putto pitarā pavattitaṃ cakkaṃ dhammeneva anuppavatteti;**A wheel-turning monarch’s oldest son who possesses these five factors continues to wield the power set in motion by his father only in a principled manner.*";
P_HTM[3009]="*taṃ hoti cakkaṃ appaṭivattiyaṃ kenaci manussabhūtena paccatthikena pāṇinā.**And this power cannot be undermined by any human enemy.*";
P_HTM[3010]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato sāriputto tathāgatena anuttaraṃ dhammacakkaṃ pavattitaṃ sammadeva anuppavatteti;**In the same way, possessing five factors Sāriputta rightly keeps rolling the supreme Wheel of Dhamma that was rolled forth by the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[3011]="*taṃ hoti cakkaṃ appaṭivattiyaṃ samaṇena vā brāhmaṇena vā devena vā mārena vā brahmunā vā kenaci vā lokasmiṃ.**And that wheel cannot be turned back by any ascetic or brahmin or god or Māra or Brahmā or by anyone in the world.*";
P_HTM[3012]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3013]="*Idha, bhikkhave, sāriputto atthaññū, dhammaññū, mattaññū, kālaññū, parisaññū.**Sāriputta knows what is right, knows principle, knows moderation, knows the right time, and knows the assembly.*";
P_HTM[3014]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato sāriputto tathāgatena anuttaraṃ dhammacakkaṃ pavattitaṃ sammadeva anuppavatteti;**Possessing these five factors Sāriputta rightly keeps rolling the supreme Wheel of Dhamma that was rolled forth by the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[3015]="*taṃ hoti cakkaṃ appaṭivattiyaṃ samaṇena vā brāhmaṇena vā devena vā mārena vā brahmunā vā kenaci vā lokasmin”ti.**And that wheel cannot be turned back by any ascetic or brahmin or god or Māra or Brahmā or by anyone in the world.”*";
P_HTM[3016]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3017]="*3. Dhammarājāsuttaṃ**A Principled King*";
P_HTM[3018]="*“Yopi so, bhikkhave, rājā cakkavattī dhammiko dhammarājā, sopi na arājakaṃ cakkaṃ vattetī”ti.**“Mendicants, even a wheel-turning monarch, a just and principled king, does not wield power without having their own king.”*";
P_HTM[3019]="*Evaṃ vutte aññataro bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, one of the mendicants asked the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[3020]="*“ko pana, bhante, rañño cakkavattissa dhammikassa dhammarañño rājā”ti?**“But who is the king of the wheel-turning monarch, the just and principled king?”*";
P_HTM[3021]="*“Dhammo, bhikkhū”ti bhagavā avoca.**“It is principle, monk,” said the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[3022]="*“Idha, bhikkhu, rājā cakkavattī dhammiko dhammarājā dhammaññeva nissāya dhammaṃ sakkaronto dhammaṃ garuṃ karonto dhammaṃ apacāyamāno dhammaddhajo dhammaketu dhammādhipateyyo dhammikaṃ rakkhāvaraṇaguttiṃ saṃvidahati antojanasmiṃ.**“Monk, a wheel-turning monarch provides just protection and security for his court, relying only on principle—honoring, respecting, and venerating principle, having principle as his flag, banner, and authority.*";
P_HTM[3023]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhu, rājā cakkavattī dhammiko dhammarājā dhammaññeva nissāya dhammaṃ sakkaronto dhammaṃ garuṃ karonto dhammaṃ apacāyamāno dhammaddhajo dhammaketu dhammādhipateyyo dhammikaṃ rakkhāvaraṇaguttiṃ saṃvidahati khattiyesu anuyantesu … pe … balakāyasmiṃ brāhmaṇagahapatikesu negamajānapadesu samaṇabrāhmaṇesu migapakkhīsu.**He provides just protection and security for his aristocrats, vassals, troops, brahmins and householders, people of town and country, ascetics and brahmins, beasts and birds.*";
P_HTM[3024]="*Sa kho so, bhikkhu, rājā cakkavattī dhammiko dhammarājā dhammaññeva nissāya dhammaṃ sakkaronto dhammaṃ garuṃ karonto dhammaṃ apacāyamāno dhammaddhajo dhammaketu dhammādhipateyyo dhammikaṃ rakkhāvaraṇaguttiṃ saṃvidahitvā antojanasmiṃ dhammikaṃ rakkhāvaraṇaguttiṃ saṃvidahitvā khattiyesu anuyantesu balakāyasmiṃ brāhmaṇagahapatikesu negamajānapadesu samaṇabrāhmaṇesu migapakkhīsu dhammeneva cakkaṃ pavatteti;**When he has done this, he wields power only in a principled manner.*";
P_HTM[3025]="*taṃ hoti cakkaṃ appaṭivattiyaṃ kenaci manussabhūtena paccatthikena pāṇinā.**And this power cannot be undermined by any human enemy.*";
P_HTM[3026]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhu, tathāgato arahaṃ sammāsambuddho dhammiko dhammarājā dhammaññeva nissāya dhammaṃ sakkaronto dhammaṃ garuṃ karonto dhammaṃ apacāyamāno dhammaddhajo dhammaketu dhammādhipateyyo dhammikaṃ rakkhāvaraṇaguttiṃ saṃvidahati bhikkhūsu:**In the same way, monk, a Realized One, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha, a just and principled king, provides just protection and security for the monks, relying only on principle—honoring, respecting, and venerating principle, having principle as his flag, banner, and authority.*";
P_HTM[3027]="*‘evarūpaṃ kāyakammaṃ sevitabbaṃ, evarūpaṃ kāyakammaṃ na sevitabbaṃ;**‘This kind of bodily action should be cultivated. This kind of bodily action should not be cultivated.*";
P_HTM[3028]="*evarūpaṃ vacīkammaṃ sevitabbaṃ, evarūpaṃ vacīkammaṃ na sevitabbaṃ;**This kind of verbal action should be cultivated. This kind of verbal action should not be cultivated.*";
P_HTM[3029]="*evarūpaṃ manokammaṃ sevitabbaṃ, evarūpaṃ manokammaṃ na sevitabbaṃ;**This kind of mental action should be cultivated. This kind of mental action should not be cultivated.*";
P_HTM[3030]="*evarūpo ājīvo sevitabbo, evarūpo ājīvo na sevitabbo;**This kind of livelihood should be cultivated. This kind of livelihood should not be cultivated.*";
P_HTM[3031]="*evarūpo gāmanigamo sevitabbo, evarūpo gāmanigamo na sevitabbo’ti.**This kind of market town should be cultivated. This kind of market town should not be cultivated.’*";
P_HTM[3032]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhu, tathāgato arahaṃ sammāsambuddho dhammiko dhammarājā dhammaññeva nissāya dhammaṃ sakkaronto dhammaṃ garuṃ karonto dhammaṃ apacāyamāno dhammaddhajo dhammaketu dhammādhipateyyo dhammikaṃ rakkhāvaraṇaguttiṃ saṃvidahati bhikkhunīsu … pe … upāsakesu … pe … upāsikāsu:**In the same way, monk, a Realized One, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha, a just and principled king, provides just protection and security for the nuns … laymen … laywomen, relying only on principle—honoring, respecting, and venerating principle, having principle as his flag, banner, and authority.*";
P_HTM[3033]="*‘evarūpaṃ kāyakammaṃ sevitabbaṃ, evarūpaṃ kāyakammaṃ na sevitabbaṃ;**‘This kind of bodily action should be cultivated. This kind of bodily action should not be cultivated.*";
P_HTM[3034]="*evarūpaṃ vacīkammaṃ sevitabbaṃ, evarūpaṃ vacīkammaṃ na sevitabbaṃ;**This kind of verbal action should be cultivated. This kind of verbal action should not be cultivated.*";
P_HTM[3035]="*evarūpaṃ manokammaṃ sevitabbaṃ, evarūpaṃ manokammaṃ na sevitabbaṃ;**This kind of mental action should be cultivated. This kind of mental action should not be cultivated.*";
P_HTM[3036]="*evarūpo ājīvo sevitabbo, evarūpo ājīvo na sevitabbo;**This kind of livelihood should be cultivated. This kind of livelihood should not be cultivated.*";
P_HTM[3037]="*evarūpo gāmanigamo sevitabbo, evarūpo gāmanigamo na sevitabbo’ti.**This kind of market town should be cultivated. This kind of market town should not be cultivated.’*";
P_HTM[3038]="*Sa kho so, bhikkhu, tathāgato arahaṃ sammāsambuddho dhammiko dhammarājā dhammaññeva nissāya dhammaṃ sakkaronto dhammaṃ garuṃ karonto dhammaṃ apacāyamāno dhammaddhajo dhammaketu dhammādhipateyyo dhammikaṃ rakkhāvaraṇaguttiṃ saṃvidahitvā bhikkhūsu, dhammikaṃ rakkhāvaraṇaguttiṃ saṃvidahitvā bhikkhunīsu, dhammikaṃ rakkhāvaraṇaguttiṃ saṃvidahitvā upāsakesu, dhammikaṃ rakkhāvaraṇaguttiṃ saṃvidahitvā upāsikāsu dhammeneva anuttaraṃ dhammacakkaṃ pavatteti;**When a Realized One, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha has provided just protection and security for the monks, nuns, laymen, and laywomen, he rolls forth the supreme Wheel of Dhamma only in a principled manner.*";
P_HTM[3039]="*taṃ hoti cakkaṃ appaṭivattiyaṃ samaṇena vā brāhmaṇena vā devena vā mārena vā brahmunā vā kenaci vā lokasmin”ti.**And that wheel cannot be rolled back by any ascetic or brahmin or god or Māra or Brahmā or by anyone in the world.”*";
P_HTM[3040]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3041]="*4. Yassaṃdisaṃsuttaṃ**In Whatever Region*";
P_HTM[3042]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato rājā khattiyo muddhāvasitto yassaṃ yassaṃ disāyaṃ viharati, sakasmiṃyeva vijite viharati.**“Mendicants, with five factors an anointed aristocratic king lives in his own realm, no matter what region he lives in.*";
P_HTM[3043]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3044]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rājā khattiyo muddhāvasitto ubhato sujāto hoti mātito ca pitito ca, saṃsuddhagahaṇiko, yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena;**An anointed aristocratic king is well born on both his mother’s and father’s side, of pure descent, irrefutable and impeccable in questions of ancestry back to the seventh paternal generation.*";
P_HTM[3045]="*aḍḍho hoti mahaddhano mahābhogo paripuṇṇakosakoṭṭhāgāro;**He is rich, affluent, and wealthy, with a full treasury and storehouses.*";
P_HTM[3046]="*balavā kho pana hoti caturaṅginiyā senāya samannāgato assavāya ovādapaṭikarāya;**He is powerful, having an army of four divisions that is obedient and carries out instructions.*";
P_HTM[3047]="*pariṇāyako kho panassa hoti paṇḍito viyatto medhāvī paṭibalo atītānāgatapaccuppanne atthe cintetuṃ;**He has a counselor who is astute, competent, and intelligent, able to think issues through as they bear upon the past, future, and present.*";
P_HTM[3048]="*tassime cattāro dhammā yasaṃ paripācenti.**These four things bring his fame to fruition.*";
P_HTM[3049]="*So iminā yasapañcamena dhammena samannāgato yassaṃ yassaṃ disāyaṃ viharati, sakasmiṃyeva vijite viharati.**With these five factors, including fame, an anointed aristocratic king lives in his own realm, no matter what direction he lives in.*";
P_HTM[3050]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3051]="*Evañhetaṃ, bhikkhave, hoti vijitāvīnaṃ.**Because that is how it is for victors.*";
P_HTM[3052]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu yassaṃ yassaṃ disāyaṃ viharati, vimuttacittova viharati.**In the same way, a mendicant with five qualities lives with mind freed, no matter what region they live in.*";
P_HTM[3053]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3054]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati ācāragocarasampanno aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu—**It’s when mendicant is ethical, restrained in the monastic code, conducting themselves well and seeking alms in suitable places. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken.*";
P_HTM[3055]="*rājāva khattiyo muddhāvasitto jātisampanno;**This is like the anointed aristocratic king’s impeccable lineage.*";
P_HTM[3056]="*bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo, ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpāssa dhammā bahussutā honti dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā—**They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering them, reinforcing them by recitation, mentally scrutinizing them, and comprehending them theoretically.*";
P_HTM[3057]="*rājāva khattiyo muddhāvasitto aḍḍho mahaddhano mahābhogo paripuṇṇakosakoṭṭhāgāro;**This is like the anointed aristocratic king being rich, affluent, and wealthy, with full treasury and storehouses.*";
P_HTM[3058]="*āraddhavīriyo viharati akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadāya thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu—**They live with energy roused up for giving up unskillful qualities and embracing skillful qualities. They’re strong, staunchly vigorous, not slacking off when it comes to developing skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[3059]="*rājāva khattiyo muddhāvasitto balasampanno;**This is like the anointed aristocratic king having power.*";
P_HTM[3060]="*paññavā hoti udayatthagāminiyā paññāya samannāgato ariyāya nibbedhikāya sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā—**They’re wise. They have the wisdom of arising and passing away which is noble, penetrative, and leads to the complete ending of suffering.*";
P_HTM[3061]="*rājāva khattiyo muddhāvasitto pariṇāyakasampanno;**This is like the anointed aristocratic king having a counselor.*";
P_HTM[3062]="*tassime cattāro dhammā vimuttiṃ paripācenti.**These four qualities bring their freedom to fruition.*";
P_HTM[3063]="*So iminā vimuttipañcamena dhammena samannāgato yassaṃ yassaṃ disāyaṃ viharati vimuttacittova viharati.**With these five qualities, including freedom, they live in their own realm, no matter what region they live in.*";
P_HTM[3064]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3065]="*Evañhetaṃ, bhikkhave, hoti vimuttacittānan”ti.**Because that is how it is for those whose mind is free.”*";
P_HTM[3066]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3067]="*5. Paṭhamapatthanāsuttaṃ**Aspiration (1st)*";
P_HTM[3068]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato rañño khattiyassa muddhāvasittassa jeṭṭho putto rajjaṃ pattheti.**“Mendicants, an anointed aristocratic king’s eldest son with five factors aspires to kingship.*";
P_HTM[3069]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3070]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño khattiyassa muddhāvasittassa jeṭṭho putto ubhato sujāto hoti mātito ca pitito ca, saṃsuddhagahaṇiko, yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena;**It’s when an anointed aristocratic king’s eldest son is well born on both his mother’s and father’s side, of pure descent, irrefutable and impeccable in questions of ancestry back to the seventh paternal generation.*";
P_HTM[3071]="*abhirūpo hoti dassanīyo pāsādiko paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgato;**He is attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty.*";
P_HTM[3072]="*mātāpitūnaṃ piyo hoti manāpo;**He is dear and beloved to his parents.*";
P_HTM[3073]="*negamajānapadassa piyo hoti manāpo;**He is dear and beloved to the people of town and country.*";
P_HTM[3074]="*yāni tāni raññaṃ khattiyānaṃ muddhāvasittānaṃ sippaṭṭhānāni hatthismiṃ vā assasmiṃ vā rathasmiṃ vā dhanusmiṃ vā tharusmiṃ vā tattha sikkhito hoti anavayo.**He is trained and skilled in the arts of anointed aristocratic kings, such as elephant riding, horse riding, driving a chariot, archery, and swordsmanship.*";
P_HTM[3075]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**He thinks:*";
P_HTM[3076]="*‘ahaṃ khomhi ubhato sujāto mātito ca pitito ca, saṃsuddhagahaṇiko, yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena.**‘I’m well born on both my mother’s and father’s side, of pure descent, irrefutable and impeccable in questions of ancestry back to the seventh paternal generation.*";
P_HTM[3077]="*Kasmāhaṃ rajjaṃ na pattheyyaṃ.**Why shouldn’t I aspire to kingship?*";
P_HTM[3078]="*Ahaṃ khomhi abhirūpo dassanīyo pāsādiko paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgato.**I’m attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty.*";
P_HTM[3079]="*Kasmāhaṃ rajjaṃ na pattheyyaṃ.**Why shouldn’t I aspire to kingship?*";
P_HTM[3080]="*Ahaṃ khomhi mātāpitūnaṃ piyo manāpo.**I’m dear and beloved to my parents.*";
P_HTM[3081]="*Kasmāhaṃ rajjaṃ na pattheyyaṃ.**Why shouldn’t I aspire to kingship?*";
P_HTM[3082]="*Ahaṃ khomhi negamajānapadassa piyo manāpo.**I’m dear and beloved to the people of town and country.*";
P_HTM[3083]="*Kasmāhaṃ rajjaṃ na pattheyyaṃ.**Why shouldn’t I aspire to kingship?*";
P_HTM[3084]="*Ahaṃ khomhi yāni tāni raññaṃ khattiyānaṃ muddhāvasittānaṃ sippaṭṭhānāni hatthismiṃ vā assasmiṃ vā rathasmiṃ vā dhanusmiṃ vā tharusmiṃ vā, tattha sikkhito anavayo.**I’m trained and skilled in the arts of anointed aristocratic kings, such as elephant riding, horse riding, driving a chariot, archery, and swordsmanship.*";
P_HTM[3085]="*Kasmāhaṃ rajjaṃ na pattheyyan’ti.**Why shouldn’t I aspire to kingship?’*";
P_HTM[3086]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi aṅgehi samannāgato rañño khattiyassa muddhāvasittassa jeṭṭho putto rajjaṃ pattheti.**An anointed aristocratic king’s eldest son with these five factors aspires to kingship.*";
P_HTM[3087]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayaṃ pattheti.**In the same way, a mendicant with five qualities aspires to end the defilements.*";
P_HTM[3088]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3089]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saddho hoti, saddahati tathāgatassa bodhiṃ:**It’s when a mendicant has faith in the Realized One’s awakening:*";
P_HTM[3090]="*‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti.**‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’*";
P_HTM[3091]="*Appābādho hoti appātaṅko, samavepākiniyā gahaṇiyā samannāgato nātisītāya nāccuṇhāya majjhimāya padhānakkhamāya;**They are rarely ill or unwell. Their stomach digests well, being neither too hot nor too cold, but just right, and fit for meditation.*";
P_HTM[3092]="*asaṭho hoti amāyāvī, yathābhūtaṃ attānaṃ āvikattā satthari vā viññūsu vā sabrahmacārīsu;**They’re not devious or deceitful. They reveal themselves honestly to the Teacher or sensible spiritual companions.*";
P_HTM[3093]="*āraddhavīriyo viharati akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadāya, thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu;**They live with energy roused up for giving up unskillful qualities and embracing skillful qualities. They’re strong, staunchly vigorous, not slacking off when it comes to developing skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[3094]="*paññavā hoti udayatthagāminiyā paññāya samannāgato ariyāya nibbedhikāya sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā.**They’re wise. They have the wisdom of arising and passing away which is noble, penetrative, and leads to the complete ending of suffering.*";
P_HTM[3095]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[3096]="*‘ahaṃ khomhi saddho, saddahāmi tathāgatassa bodhiṃ:**‘I am a person of faith; I have faith in the Realized One’s awakening …*";
P_HTM[3097]="*“itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3098]="*Kasmāhaṃ āsavānaṃ khayaṃ na pattheyyaṃ.**Why shouldn’t I aspire to end the defilements?*";
P_HTM[3099]="*Ahaṃ khomhi appābādho appātaṅko samavepākiniyā gahaṇiyā samannāgato nātisītāya nāccuṇhāya majjhimāya padhānakkhamāya.**I’m rarely ill or unwell. My stomach digests well, being neither too hot nor too cold, but just right, and fit for meditation.*";
P_HTM[3100]="*Kasmāhaṃ āsavānaṃ khayaṃ na pattheyyaṃ.**Why shouldn’t I aspire to end the defilements?*";
P_HTM[3101]="*Ahaṃ khomhi asaṭho amāyāvī yathābhūtaṃ attānaṃ āvikattā satthari vā viññūsu vā sabrahmacārīsu.**I reveal myself honestly to the Teacher or sensible spiritual companions.*";
P_HTM[3102]="*Kasmāhaṃ āsavānaṃ khayaṃ na pattheyyaṃ.**Why shouldn’t I aspire to end the defilements?*";
P_HTM[3103]="*Ahaṃ khomhi āraddhavīriyo viharāmi akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadāya, thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu.**I live with energy roused up for giving up unskillful qualities and embracing skillful qualities. I’m strong, staunchly vigorous, not slacking off when it comes to developing skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[3104]="*Kasmāhaṃ āsavānaṃ khayaṃ na pattheyyaṃ.**Why shouldn’t I aspire to end the defilements?*";
P_HTM[3105]="*Ahaṃ khomhi paññavā udayatthagāminiyā paññāya samannāgato ariyāya nibbedhikāya sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā.**I’m wise. I have the wisdom of arising and passing away which is noble, penetrative, and leads to the complete ending of suffering.*";
P_HTM[3106]="*Kasmāhaṃ āsavānaṃ khayaṃ na pattheyyan’ti.**Why shouldn’t I aspire to end the defilements?’*";
P_HTM[3107]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayaṃ patthetī”ti.**A mendicant with these five qualities aspires to end the defilements.”*";
P_HTM[3108]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3109]="*6. Dutiyapatthanāsuttaṃ**Aspiration (2nd)*";
P_HTM[3110]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato rañño khattiyassa muddhāvasittassa jeṭṭho putto oparajjaṃ pattheti.**“Mendicants, an anointed aristocratic king’s eldest son with five factors aspires to become a viceroy.*";
P_HTM[3111]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3112]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño khattiyassa muddhāvasittassa jeṭṭho putto ubhato sujāto hoti mātito ca pitito ca, saṃsuddhagahaṇiko, yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena;**It’s when an anointed aristocratic king’s eldest son is well born on both his mother’s and father’s side, of pure descent, irrefutable and impeccable in questions of ancestry back to the seventh paternal generation.*";
P_HTM[3113]="*abhirūpo hoti dassanīyo pāsādiko paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgato;**He is attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty.*";
P_HTM[3114]="*mātāpitūnaṃ piyo hoti manāpo,**He is dear and beloved to his parents.*";
P_HTM[3115]="*balakāyassa piyo hoti manāpo;**He is dear and beloved to the armed forces.*";
P_HTM[3116]="*paṇḍito hoti viyatto medhāvī paṭibalo atītānāgatapaccuppanne atthe cintetuṃ.**He is astute, competent, and intelligent, able to think issues through as they bear upon the past, future, and present.*";
P_HTM[3117]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**He thinks:*";
P_HTM[3118]="*‘ahaṃ khomhi ubhato sujāto mātito ca pitito ca, saṃsuddhagahaṇiko, yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena.**‘I’m well born …*";
P_HTM[3119]="*Kasmāhaṃ oparajjaṃ na pattheyyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3120]="*Ahaṃ khomhi abhirūpo dassanīyo pāsādiko paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgato.**attractive …*";
P_HTM[3121]="*Kasmāhaṃ oparajjaṃ na pattheyyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3122]="*Ahaṃ khomhi mātāpitūnaṃ piyo manāpo.**dear and beloved to my parents …*";
P_HTM[3123]="*Kasmāhaṃ oparajjaṃ na pattheyyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3124]="*Ahaṃ khomhi balakāyassa piyo manāpo.**dear and beloved to the armed forces …*";
P_HTM[3125]="*Kasmāhaṃ oparajjaṃ na pattheyyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3126]="*Ahaṃ khomhi paṇḍito viyatto medhāvī paṭibalo atītānāgatapaccuppanne atthe cintetuṃ.**I’m astute, competent, and intelligent, able to think issues through as they bear upon the past, future, and present.*";
P_HTM[3127]="*Kasmāhaṃ oparajjaṃ na pattheyyan’ti.**Why shouldn’t I aspire to become a viceroy?’*";
P_HTM[3128]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi aṅgehi samannāgato rañño khattiyassa muddhāvasittassa jeṭṭho putto oparajjaṃ pattheti.**An anointed aristocratic king’s eldest son with these five factors aspires to become a viceroy.*";
P_HTM[3129]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayaṃ pattheti.**In the same way, a mendicant with five qualities aspires to end the defilements.*";
P_HTM[3130]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3131]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti … pe … samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu;**It’s when a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the code of conduct, with good behavior and supporters. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken.*";
P_HTM[3132]="*bahussuto hoti … pe … diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā;**They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s totally full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering them, reciting them, mentally scrutinizing them, and understanding them with right view.*";
P_HTM[3133]="*catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacitto hoti;**Their mind is firmly established in the four kinds of mindfulness meditation.*";
P_HTM[3134]="*āraddhavīriyo viharati akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadāya, thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu;**They live with energy roused up for giving up unskillful qualities and embracing skillful qualities. They’re strong, staunchly vigorous, not slacking off when it comes to developing skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[3135]="*paññavā hoti, udayatthagāminiyā paññāya samannāgato ariyāya nibbedhikāya sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā.**They’re wise. They have the wisdom of arising and passing away which is noble, penetrative, and leads to the complete ending of suffering.*";
P_HTM[3136]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[3137]="*‘ahaṃ khomhi sīlavā, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharāmi ācāragocarasampanno aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhāmi sikkhāpadesu.**‘I’m ethical …*";
P_HTM[3138]="*Kasmāhaṃ āsavānaṃ khayaṃ na pattheyyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3139]="*Ahaṃ khomhi bahussuto sutadharo sutasannicayo, ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpā me dhammā bahussutā honti dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā.**learned …*";
P_HTM[3140]="*Kasmāhaṃ āsavānaṃ khayaṃ na pattheyyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3141]="*Ahaṃ khomhi catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacitto.**mindful …*";
P_HTM[3142]="*Kasmāhaṃ āsavānaṃ khayaṃ na pattheyyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3143]="*Ahaṃ khomhi āraddhavīriyo viharāmi akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadāya, thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu.**energetic …*";
P_HTM[3144]="*Kasmāhaṃ āsavānaṃ khayaṃ na pattheyyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3145]="*Ahaṃ khomhi paññavā udayatthagāminiyā paññāya samannāgato ariyāya nibbedhikāya sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā.**wise. I have the wisdom of arising and passing away which is noble, penetrative, and leads to the complete ending of suffering.*";
P_HTM[3146]="*Kasmāhaṃ āsavānaṃ khayaṃ na pattheyyan’ti.**Why shouldn’t I aspire to end the defilements?’*";
P_HTM[3147]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayaṃ patthetī”ti.**A mendicant with these five qualities aspires to end the defilements.”*";
P_HTM[3148]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3149]="*7. Appaṃsupatisuttaṃ**Little Sleep*";
P_HTM[3150]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, appaṃ rattiyā supanti, bahuṃ jagganti.**“Mendicants, these five sleep little at night, staying mostly awake.*";
P_HTM[3151]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3152]="*Itthī, bhikkhave, purisādhippāyā appaṃ rattiyā supati, bahuṃ jaggati.**A woman longing for a man.*";
P_HTM[3153]="*Puriso, bhikkhave, itthādhippāyo appaṃ rattiyā supati, bahuṃ jaggati.**A man longing for a woman.*";
P_HTM[3154]="*Coro, bhikkhave, ādānādhippāyo appaṃ rattiyā supati, bahuṃ jaggati.**A thief longing for their loot.*";
P_HTM[3155]="*Rājā, bhikkhave, rājakaraṇīyesu yutto appaṃ rattiyā supati, bahuṃ jaggati.**A king busy with his duties.*";
P_HTM[3156]="*Bhikkhu, bhikkhave, visaṃyogādhippāyo appaṃ rattiyā supati, bahuṃ jaggati.**A mendicant longing for freedom from attachment.*";
P_HTM[3157]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca appaṃ rattiyā supanti, bahuṃ jaggantī”ti.**These five sleep little at night, staying mostly awake.”*";
P_HTM[3158]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3159]="*8. Bhattādakasuttaṃ**Eating Food*";
P_HTM[3160]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato rañño nāgo bhattādako ca hoti okāsapharaṇo ca laṇḍasāraṇo ca salākaggāhī ca rañño nāgotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**“Mendicants, a royal bull elephant with five factors eats food, takes up space, drops dung, and takes a ticket, yet is still considered to be a royal bull elephant.*";
P_HTM[3161]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3162]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo akkhamo hoti rūpānaṃ, akkhamo saddānaṃ, akkhamo gandhānaṃ, akkhamo rasānaṃ, akkhamo phoṭṭhabbānaṃ.**It’s when a royal bull elephant can’t endure sights, sounds, smells, tastes, and touches.*";
P_HTM[3163]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi aṅgehi samannāgato rañño nāgo bhattādako ca okāsapharaṇo ca laṇḍasāraṇo ca salākaggāhī ca, rañño nāgotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**A royal bull elephant with these five factors eats food, takes up space, drops dung, and takes a ticket, yet is still considered to be a royal bull elephant.*";
P_HTM[3164]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu bhattādako ca hoti, okāsapharaṇo ca mañcapīṭhamaddano ca salākaggāhī ca, bhikkhutveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**In the same way, a mendicant with five qualities eats food, takes up space, tramples beds and chairs, and takes a ticket, yet is still considered to be a mendicant.*";
P_HTM[3165]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3166]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkhamo hoti rūpānaṃ, akkhamo saddānaṃ, akkhamo gandhānaṃ, akkhamo rasānaṃ, akkhamo phoṭṭhabbānaṃ.**It’s when a mendicant can’t endure sights, sounds, smells, tastes, and touches.*";
P_HTM[3167]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu bhattādako ca hoti okāsapharaṇo ca mañcapīṭhamaddano ca salākaggāhī ca, bhikkhutveva saṅkhaṃ gacchatī”ti.**A mendicant with these five qualities eats food, takes up space, tramples beds and chairs, and takes a ticket, yet is still considered to be a mendicant.”*";
P_HTM[3168]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3169]="*9. Akkhamasuttaṃ**Cannot Endure*";
P_HTM[3170]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato rañño nāgo na rājāraho hoti na rājabhoggo, na rañño aṅgaṃtveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**“Mendicants, a royal bull elephant with five factors is not worthy of a king, not fit to serve a king, and is not considered a factor of kingship.*";
P_HTM[3171]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3172]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo akkhamo hoti rūpānaṃ, akkhamo saddānaṃ, akkhamo gandhānaṃ, akkhamo rasānaṃ, akkhamo phoṭṭhabbānaṃ.**It’s when a royal bull elephant can’t endure sights, sounds, smells, tastes, and touches.*";
P_HTM[3173]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo akkhamo hoti rūpānaṃ?**And how is it that a royal bull elephant can’t endure sights?*";
P_HTM[3174]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo saṅgāmagato hatthikāyaṃ vā disvā assakāyaṃ vā disvā rathakāyaṃ vā disvā pattikāyaṃ vā disvā saṃsīdati visīdati, na santhambhati na sakkoti saṅgāmaṃ otarituṃ.**It’s when a royal bull elephant gone to battle falters and founders at the sight of a division of elephants, of cavalry, of chariots, or of infantry. It doesn’t stay firm, and fails to plunge into battle.*";
P_HTM[3175]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo akkhamo hoti rūpānaṃ. (1)**That’s how a royal bull elephant can’t endure sights.*";
P_HTM[3176]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo akkhamo hoti saddānaṃ?**And how is it that a royal bull elephant can’t endure sounds?*";
P_HTM[3177]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo saṅgāmagato hatthisaddaṃ vā sutvā assasaddaṃ vā sutvā rathasaddaṃ vā sutvā pattisaddaṃ vā sutvā bheripaṇavasaṅkhatiṇavaninnādasaddaṃ vā sutvā saṃsīdati visīdati, na santhambhati na sakkoti saṅgāmaṃ otarituṃ.**It’s when a royal bull elephant gone to battle falters and founders at the sound of a division of elephants, of cavalry, of chariots, or of infantry, or the thunder of the drums, kettledrums, horns, and cymbals. It doesn’t stay firm, and fails to plunge into battle.*";
P_HTM[3178]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo akkhamo hoti saddānaṃ. (2)**That’s how a royal bull elephant can’t endure sounds.*";
P_HTM[3179]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo akkhamo hoti gandhānaṃ?**And how is it that a royal bull elephant can’t endure smells?*";
P_HTM[3180]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo saṅgāmagato ye te rañño nāgā abhijātā saṅgāmāvacarā tesaṃ muttakarīsassa gandhaṃ ghāyitvā saṃsīdati visīdati, na santhambhati na sakkoti saṅgāmaṃ otarituṃ.**It’s when a royal bull elephant gone to battle falters and founders when it smells the odor of the feces and urine of battle-hardened, pedigree royal bull elephants. It doesn’t stay firm, and fails to plunge into battle.*";
P_HTM[3181]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo akkhamo hoti gandhānaṃ. (3)**That’s how a royal bull elephant can’t endure smells.*";
P_HTM[3182]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo akkhamo hoti rasānaṃ?**And how is it that a royal bull elephant can’t endure tastes?*";
P_HTM[3183]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo saṅgāmagato ekissā vā tiṇodakadattiyā vimānito dvīhi vā tīhi vā catūhi vā pañcahi vā tiṇodakadattīhi vimānito saṃsīdati visīdati, na santhambhati na sakkoti saṅgāmaṃ otarituṃ.**It’s when a royal bull elephant gone to battle falters and founders when it misses a meal of grass and water, or it misses two, three, four, or five meals. It doesn’t stay firm, and fails to plunge into battle.*";
P_HTM[3184]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo akkhamo hoti rasānaṃ. (4)**That’s how a royal bull elephant can’t endure tastes.*";
P_HTM[3185]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo akkhamo hoti phoṭṭhabbānaṃ?**And how is it that a royal bull elephant can’t endure touches?*";
P_HTM[3186]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo saṅgāmagato ekena vā saravegena viddho, dvīhi vā tīhi vā catūhi vā pañcahi vā saravegehi viddho saṃsīdati visīdati, na santhambhati na sakkoti saṅgāmaṃ otarituṃ.**It’s when a royal bull elephant gone to battle falters and founders when struck by a swift arrow, or by two, three, four, or five swift arrows. It doesn’t stay firm, and fails to plunge into battle.*";
P_HTM[3187]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo akkhamo hoti phoṭṭhabbānaṃ. (5)**That’s how a royal bull elephant can’t endure touches.*";
P_HTM[3188]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi aṅgehi samannāgato rañño nāgo na rājāraho hoti na rājabhoggo na rañño aṅgaṃtveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**A royal bull elephant with these five factors is not worthy of a king, not fit to serve a king, and is not considered a factor of kingship.*";
P_HTM[3189]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi aṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu na āhuneyyo hoti na pāhuneyyo na dakkhiṇeyyo na añjalikaraṇīyo na anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa.**In the same way, a mendicant with five qualities is not worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, not worthy of hospitality, not worthy of a religious donation, not worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is not the supreme field of merit for the world.*";
P_HTM[3190]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3191]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkhamo hoti rūpānaṃ, akkhamo saddānaṃ, akkhamo gandhānaṃ, akkhamo rasānaṃ, akkhamo phoṭṭhabbānaṃ.**It’s when a mendicant can’t endure sights, sounds, smells, tastes, and touches.*";
P_HTM[3192]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkhamo hoti rūpānaṃ?**And how is it that a mendicant can’t endure sights?*";
P_HTM[3193]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā rajanīye rūpe sārajjati, na sakkoti cittaṃ samādahituṃ.**It’s when a mendicant, seeing a sight with their eyes, is aroused by a desirable sight, so is not able to still the mind.*";
P_HTM[3194]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkhamo hoti rūpānaṃ. (1)**That’s how a mendicant can’t endure sights.*";
P_HTM[3195]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkhamo hoti saddānaṃ?**And how is it that a mendicant can’t endure sounds?*";
P_HTM[3196]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sotena saddaṃ sutvā rajanīye sadde sārajjati, na sakkoti cittaṃ samādahituṃ.**It’s when a mendicant, hearing a sound with their ears, is aroused by a desirable sound, so is not able to still the mind.*";
P_HTM[3197]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkhamo hoti saddānaṃ. (2)**That’s how a mendicant can’t endure sounds.*";
P_HTM[3198]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkhamo hoti gandhānaṃ?**And how is it that a mendicant can’t endure smells?*";
P_HTM[3199]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā rajanīye gandhe sārajjati, na sakkoti cittaṃ samādahituṃ.**It’s when a mendicant, smelling an odor with their nose, is aroused by a desirable smell, so is not able to still the mind.*";
P_HTM[3200]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkhamo hoti gandhānaṃ. (3)**That’s how a mendicant can’t endure smells.*";
P_HTM[3201]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkhamo hoti rasānaṃ?**And how is it that a mendicant can’t endure tastes?*";
P_HTM[3202]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā rajanīye rase sārajjati, na sakkoti cittaṃ samādahituṃ.**It’s when a mendicant, tasting a flavor with their tongue, is aroused by desirable tastes, so is not able to still the mind.*";
P_HTM[3203]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkhamo hoti rasānaṃ. (4)**That’s how a mendicant can’t endure tastes.*";
P_HTM[3204]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkhamo hoti phoṭṭhabbānaṃ?**And how is it that a mendicant can’t endure touches?*";
P_HTM[3205]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā rajanīye phoṭṭhabbe sārajjati, na sakkoti cittaṃ samādahituṃ.**It’s when a mendicant, feeling a touch with their body, is aroused by a desirable touch, so is not able to still the mind.*";
P_HTM[3206]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkhamo hoti phoṭṭhabbānaṃ. (5)**That’s how a mendicant can’t endure touches.*";
P_HTM[3207]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu na āhuneyyo hoti na pāhuneyyo na dakkhiṇeyyo na añjalikaraṇīyo na anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa.**A mendicant with these five qualities is not worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, not worthy of hospitality, not worthy of a religious donation, not worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is not the supreme field of merit for the world.*";
P_HTM[3208]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato rañño nāgo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅgaṃtveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**A royal bull elephant with five factors is worthy of a king, fit to serve a king, and is considered a factor of kingship.*";
P_HTM[3209]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3210]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo khamo hoti rūpānaṃ, khamo saddānaṃ, khamo gandhānaṃ, khamo rasānaṃ, khamo phoṭṭhabbānaṃ.**It’s when a royal bull elephant can endure sights, sounds, smells, tastes, and touches.*";
P_HTM[3211]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo khamo hoti rūpānaṃ?**And how is it that a royal bull elephant can endure sights?*";
P_HTM[3212]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo saṅgāmagato hatthikāyaṃ vā disvā assakāyaṃ vā disvā rathakāyaṃ vā disvā pattikāyaṃ vā disvā na saṃsīdati na visīdati, santhambhati sakkoti saṅgāmaṃ otarituṃ.**It’s when a royal bull elephant gone to battle does not falter or founder at the sight of a division of elephants, of cavalry, of chariots, or of infantry. It stays firm, and plunges into battle.*";
P_HTM[3213]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo khamo hoti rūpānaṃ. (1)**That’s how a royal bull elephant can endure sights.*";
P_HTM[3214]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo khamo hoti saddānaṃ?**And how is it that a royal bull elephant can endure sounds?*";
P_HTM[3215]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo saṅgāmagato hatthisaddaṃ vā sutvā assasaddaṃ vā sutvā rathasaddaṃ vā sutvā pattisaddaṃ vā sutvā bheripaṇavasaṅkhatiṇavaninnādasaddaṃ vā sutvā na saṃsīdati na visīdati, santhambhati sakkoti saṅgāmaṃ otarituṃ.**It’s when a royal bull elephant does not falter or founder at the sound of a division of elephants, of cavalry, of chariots, or of infantry, or the thunder of the drums, kettledrums, horns, and cymbals. It stays firm, and plunges into battle.*";
P_HTM[3216]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo khamo hoti saddānaṃ. (2)**That’s how a royal bull elephant can endure sounds.*";
P_HTM[3217]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo khamo hoti gandhānaṃ?**And how is it that a royal bull elephant can endure smells?*";
P_HTM[3218]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo saṅgāmagato ye te rañño nāgā abhijātā saṅgāmāvacarā tesaṃ muttakarīsassa gandhaṃ ghāyitvā na saṃsīdati na visīdati, santhambhati sakkoti saṅgāmaṃ otarituṃ.**It’s when a royal bull elephant gone to battle does not falter or founder when it smells the odor of the feces and urine of battle-hardened, pedigree royal bull elephants. It stays firm, and plunges into battle.*";
P_HTM[3219]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo khamo hoti gandhānaṃ. (3)**That’s how a royal bull elephant can endure smells.*";
P_HTM[3220]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo khamo hoti rasānaṃ?**And how is it that a royal bull elephant can endure tastes?*";
P_HTM[3221]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo saṅgāmagato ekissā vā tiṇodakadattiyā vimānito dvīhi vā tīhi vā catūhi vā pañcahi vā tiṇodakadattīhi vimānito na saṃsīdati na visīdati, santhambhati sakkoti saṅgāmaṃ otarituṃ.**It’s when a royal bull elephant gone to battle does not falter or founder when it misses a meal of grass and water, or it misses two, three, four, or five meals. It stays firm, and plunges into battle.*";
P_HTM[3222]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo khamo hoti rasānaṃ. (4)**That’s how a royal bull elephant can endure tastes.*";
P_HTM[3223]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo khamo hoti phoṭṭhabbānaṃ?**And how is it that a royal bull elephant can endure touches?*";
P_HTM[3224]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo saṅgāmagato ekena vā saravegena viddho, dvīhi vā tīhi vā catūhi vā pañcahi vā saravegehi viddho na saṃsīdati na visīdati, santhambhati sakkoti saṅgāmaṃ otarituṃ.**It’s when a royal bull elephant gone to battle does not falter or founder when struck by a swift arrow, or by two, three, four, or five swift arrows. It stays firm, and plunges into battle.*";
P_HTM[3225]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo khamo hoti phoṭṭhabbānaṃ. (5)**That’s how a royal bull elephant can endure touches.*";
P_HTM[3226]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi aṅgehi samannāgato rañño nāgo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅgaṃtveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**A royal bull elephant with these five factors is worthy of a king, fit to serve a king, and is considered a factor of kingship.*";
P_HTM[3227]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa.**In the same way, a mendicant with five qualities is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.*";
P_HTM[3228]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3229]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu khamo hoti rūpānaṃ, khamo saddānaṃ, khamo gandhānaṃ, khamo rasānaṃ, khamo phoṭṭhabbānaṃ.**It’s when a mendicant can endure sights, sounds, smells, tastes, and touches.*";
P_HTM[3230]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu khamo hoti rūpānaṃ?**And how is it that a mendicant can endure sights?*";
P_HTM[3231]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā rajanīye rūpe na sārajjati, sakkoti cittaṃ samādahituṃ.**It’s when a mendicant, seeing a sight with their eyes, is not aroused by a desirable sight, so is able to still the mind.*";
P_HTM[3232]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu khamo hoti rūpānaṃ. (1)**That’s how a mendicant can endure sights.*";
P_HTM[3233]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu khamo hoti saddānaṃ?**And how is it that a mendicant can endure sounds?*";
P_HTM[3234]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sotena saddaṃ sutvā rajanīye sadde na sārajjati, sakkoti cittaṃ samādahituṃ.**It’s when a mendicant, hearing a sound with their ears, is not aroused by desirable sounds, so is able to still the mind.*";
P_HTM[3235]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu khamo hoti saddānaṃ. (2)**That’s how a mendicant can endure sounds.*";
P_HTM[3236]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu khamo hoti gandhānaṃ.**And how is it that a mendicant can endure smells?*";
P_HTM[3237]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā rajanīye gandhe na sārajjati, sakkoti cittaṃ samādahituṃ.**It’s when a mendicant, smelling an odor with their nose, is not aroused by a desirable smell, so is able to still the mind.*";
P_HTM[3238]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu khamo hoti gandhānaṃ. (3)**That’s how a mendicant can endure smells.*";
P_HTM[3239]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu khamo hoti rasānaṃ?**And how is it that a mendicant can endure tastes?*";
P_HTM[3240]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā rajanīye rase na sārajjati, sakkoti cittaṃ samādahituṃ.**It’s when a mendicant, tasting a flavor with their tongue, is not aroused by desirable tastes, so is able to still the mind.*";
P_HTM[3241]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu khamo hoti rasānaṃ. (4)**That’s how a mendicant can endure tastes.*";
P_HTM[3242]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu khamo hoti phoṭṭhabbānaṃ?**And how is it that a mendicant can endure touches?*";
P_HTM[3243]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā rajanīye phoṭṭhabbe na sārajjati, sakkoti cittaṃ samādahituṃ.**It’s when a mendicant, feeling a touch with their body, is not aroused by a desirable touch, so is able to still the mind.*";
P_HTM[3244]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu khamo hoti phoṭṭhabbānaṃ. (5)**That’s how a mendicant can endure touches.*";
P_HTM[3245]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti.**A mendicant with these five qualities is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.”*";
P_HTM[3246]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3247]="*10. Sotasuttaṃ**A Listener*";
P_HTM[3248]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato rañño nāgo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅgaṃtveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**“Mendicants, a royal bull elephant with five factors is worthy of a king, fit to serve a king, and is considered a factor of kingship.*";
P_HTM[3249]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3250]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo sotā ca hoti, hantā ca, rakkhitā ca, khantā ca, gantā ca.**A royal bull elephant listens, destroys, protects, endures, and goes fast.*";
P_HTM[3251]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo sotā hoti?**And how does a royal bull elephant listen?*";
P_HTM[3252]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo yamenaṃ hatthidammasārathi kāraṇaṃ kāreti—**It’s when a royal bull elephant pays heed, pays attention, engages wholeheartedly, and lends an ear to whatever task the elephant trainer has it do,*";
P_HTM[3253]="*yadi vā katapubbaṃ yadi vā akatapubbaṃ—**whether or not it has done it before.*";
P_HTM[3254]="*taṃ aṭṭhiṃ katvā manasi katvā sabbaṃ cetasā samannāharitvā ohitasoto suṇāti.* **";
P_HTM[3255]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo sotā hoti. (1)**That’s how a royal bull elephant listens.*";
P_HTM[3256]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo hantā hoti?**And how does a royal bull elephant destroy?*";
P_HTM[3257]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo saṅgāmagato hatthimpi hanati, hatthāruhampi hanati, assampi hanati, assāruhampi hanati, rathampi hanati, rathikampi hanati, pattikampi hanati.**It’s when a royal bull elephant in battle destroys elephants with their riders, horses with their riders, chariots and charioteers, and foot soldiers.*";
P_HTM[3258]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo hantā hoti. (2)**That’s how a royal bull elephant destroys.*";
P_HTM[3259]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo rakkhitā hoti?**And how does a royal bull elephant protect?*";
P_HTM[3260]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo saṅgāmagato rakkhati purimaṃ kāyaṃ, rakkhati pacchimaṃ kāyaṃ, rakkhati purime pāde, rakkhati pacchime pāde, rakkhati sīsaṃ, rakkhati kaṇṇe, rakkhati dante, rakkhati soṇḍaṃ, rakkhati vāladhiṃ, rakkhati hatthāruhaṃ.**It’s when a royal bull elephant in battle protects its fore-quarters and hind-quarters, its fore-feet and hind-feet, and its head, ears, tusks, trunk, tail, and rider.*";
P_HTM[3261]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo rakkhitā hoti. (3)**That’s how a royal bull elephant protects.*";
P_HTM[3262]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo khantā hoti?**And how does a royal bull elephant endure?*";
P_HTM[3263]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo saṅgāmagato khamo hoti sattippahārānaṃ asippahārānaṃ usuppahārānaṃ pharasuppahārānaṃ bheripaṇavasaṅkhatiṇavaninnādasaddānaṃ.**It’s when a royal bull elephant in battle endures being struck by spears, swords, arrows, and axes; it endures the thunder of the drums, kettledrums, horns, and cymbals.*";
P_HTM[3264]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo khantā hoti. (4)**That’s how a royal bull elephant endures.*";
P_HTM[3265]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo gantā hoti?**And how does a royal bull elephant go fast?*";
P_HTM[3266]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo yamenaṃ hatthidammasārathi disaṃ peseti—**It’s when a royal bull elephant swiftly goes in whatever direction the elephant trainer sends it,*";
P_HTM[3267]="*yadi vā gatapubbaṃ yadi vā agatapubbaṃ—**whether or not it has been there before.*";
P_HTM[3268]="*taṃ khippameva gantā hoti.* **";
P_HTM[3269]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo gantā hoti. (5)**That’s how a royal bull elephant goes fast.*";
P_HTM[3270]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi aṅgehi samannāgato rañño nāgo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅgantveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**A royal bull elephant with these five factors is worthy of a king, fit to serve a king, and is considered a factor of kingship.*";
P_HTM[3271]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa.**In the same way, a mendicant with five qualities is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.*";
P_HTM[3272]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3273]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sotā ca hoti, hantā ca, rakkhitā ca, khantā ca, gantā ca.**A mendicant listens, destroys, protects, endures, and goes fast.*";
P_HTM[3274]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sotā hoti?**And how does a mendicant listen?*";
P_HTM[3275]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye desiyamāne aṭṭhiṅkatvā manasi katvā sabbaṃ cetasā samannāharitvā ohitasoto dhammaṃ suṇāti.**It’s when a mendicant pays heed, pays attention, engages wholeheartedly, and lends an ear when the teaching and training proclaimed by a Realized One is being taught.*";
P_HTM[3276]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sotā hoti. (1)**That’s how a mendicant listens.*";
P_HTM[3277]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu hantā hoti?**And how does a mendicant destroy?*";
P_HTM[3278]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu uppannaṃ kāmavitakkaṃ nādhivāseti, pajahati vinodeti hanati byantīkaroti anabhāvaṃ gameti; uppannaṃ byāpādavitakkaṃ … pe … uppannaṃ vihiṃsāvitakkaṃ … pe … uppannuppanne pāpake akusale dhamme nādhivāseti, pajahati vinodeti hanati byantīkaroti anabhāvaṃ gameti.**It’s when a mendicant doesn’t tolerate a sensual, malicious, or cruel thought. They don’t tolerate any bad, unskillful qualities that have arisen, but give them up, get rid of them, calm them, eliminate them, and obliterate them.*";
P_HTM[3279]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu hantā hoti. (2)**That’s how a mendicant destroys.*";
P_HTM[3280]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu rakkhitā hoti?**And how does a mendicant protect?*";
P_HTM[3281]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī.**When a mendicant sees a sight with the eyes, they don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[3282]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati; rakkhati cakkhundriyaṃ; cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of sight were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of sight, and achieving restraint over it.*";
P_HTM[3283]="*Sotena saddaṃ sutvā …**Hearing a sound with the ears …*";
P_HTM[3284]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …**Smelling an odor with the nose …*";
P_HTM[3285]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …**Tasting a flavor with the tongue …*";
P_HTM[3286]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …**Feeling a touch with the body …*";
P_HTM[3287]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī.**Knowing a thought with the mind, they don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[3288]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati; rakkhati manindriyaṃ; manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of mind were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of mind, and achieving restraint over it.*";
P_HTM[3289]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu rakkhitā hoti. (3)**That’s how a mendicant protects.*";
P_HTM[3290]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu khantā hoti?**And how does a mendicant endure?*";
P_HTM[3291]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu khamo hoti sītassa uṇhassa jighacchāya pipāsāya ḍaṃsamakasavātātapasarīsapasamphassānaṃ; duruttānaṃ durāgatānaṃ vacanapathānaṃ uppannānaṃ sārīrikānaṃ vedanānaṃ dukkhānaṃ tibbānaṃ kharānaṃ kaṭukānaṃ asātānaṃ amanāpānaṃ pāṇaharānaṃ adhivāsakajātiko hoti.**It’s when a mendicant endures cold, heat, hunger, and thirst; the touch of flies, mosquitoes, wind, sun, and reptiles; rude and unwelcome criticism; and puts up with physical pain—sharp, severe, acute, unpleasant, disagreeable, and life-threatening.*";
P_HTM[3292]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu khantā hoti. (4)**That’s how a mendicant endures.*";
P_HTM[3293]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu gantā hoti?**And how does a mendicant go fast?*";
P_HTM[3294]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yā sā disā agatapubbā iminā dīghena addhunā, yadidaṃ sabbasaṅkhārasamatho sabbūpadhipaṭinissaggo taṇhākkhayo virāgo nirodho nibbānaṃ, taṃ khippaññeva gantā hoti.**It’s when a mendicant swiftly goes in the direction they’ve never gone before in all this long time; that is, the stilling of all activities, the letting go of all attachments, the ending of craving, fading away, cessation, extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[3295]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu gantā hoti. (5)**That’s how a mendicant goes fast.*";
P_HTM[3296]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti.**A mendicant with these five qualities … is the supreme field of merit for the world.”*";
P_HTM[3297]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3298]="*Rājavaggo catuttho.* **";
P_HTM[3299]="*Cakkānuvattanā rājā,* **";
P_HTM[3300]="*Yassaṃdisaṃ dve ceva patthanā;* **";
P_HTM[3301]="*Appaṃsupati bhattādo,* **";
P_HTM[3302]="*Akkhamo ca sotena cāti.* **";
P_HTM[3303]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**At Tikaṇḍakī*";
P_HTM[3304]="*1. Avajānātisuttaṃ**Scorn*";
P_HTM[3305]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these five people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[3306]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3307]="*Datvā avajānāti, saṃvāsena avajānāti, ādheyyamukho hoti, lolo hoti, mando momūho hoti.**One gives then scorns, one lives together then scorns, one is gullible for gossip, one is impulsive, and one is dull and stupid.*";
P_HTM[3308]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo datvā avajānāti?**And how does a person give then scorn?*";
P_HTM[3309]="*Idha, bhikkhave, puggalo puggalassa deti cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ.**It’s when a person gives someone robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick.*";
P_HTM[3310]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**They think:*";
P_HTM[3311]="*‘ahaṃ demi;**‘I give;*";
P_HTM[3312]="*ayaṃ paṭiggaṇhātī’ti.**this one receives.’*";
P_HTM[3313]="*Tamenaṃ datvā avajānāti.**They give to that person, then they scorn them.*";
P_HTM[3314]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo datvā avajānāti.**That’s how a person gives then scorns.*";
P_HTM[3315]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo saṃvāsena avajānāti?**And how does a person live together then scorn?*";
P_HTM[3316]="*Idha, bhikkhave, puggalo puggalena saddhiṃ saṃvasati dve vā tīṇi vā vassāni.**It’s when a person lives with someone else for two or three years.*";
P_HTM[3317]="*Tamenaṃ saṃvāsena avajānāti.**They live together with that person, then they scorn them.*";
P_HTM[3318]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo saṃvāsena avajānāti.**That’s how a person live together then scorns.*";
P_HTM[3319]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo ādheyyamukho hoti?**And how is a person gullible for gossip?*";
P_HTM[3320]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo parassa vaṇṇe vā avaṇṇe vā bhāsiyamāne taṃ khippaññeva adhimuccitā hoti.**It’s when they’re very quick to believe what a certain person says in praise or criticism of another.*";
P_HTM[3321]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo ādheyyamukho hoti.**That’s how a person is gullible for gossip.*";
P_HTM[3322]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo lolo hoti?**And how is a person impulsive?*";
P_HTM[3323]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo ittarasaddho hoti ittarabhattī ittarapemo ittarappasādo.**It’s when a certain person is fickle in faith, devotion, fondness, and confidence.*";
P_HTM[3324]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo lolo hoti.**That’s how a person is impulsive.*";
P_HTM[3325]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo mando momūho hoti?**And how is a person dull and stupid?*";
P_HTM[3326]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo kusalākusale dhamme na jānāti, sāvajjānavajje dhamme na jānāti, hīnappaṇīte dhamme na jānāti, kaṇhasukkasappaṭibhāge dhamme na jānāti.**It’s when they don’t know the difference between qualities that are skillful and unskillful, blameworthy and blameless, inferior and superior, and those on the side of dark and bright.*";
P_HTM[3327]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo mando momūho hoti.**That’s how a person is dull and stupid.*";
P_HTM[3328]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti.**These are the five people found in the world.”*";
P_HTM[3329]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3330]="*2. Ārabhatisuttaṃ**Violation*";
P_HTM[3331]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these five people are found in the world.*";
P_HTM[3332]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3333]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo ārabhati ca vippaṭisārī ca hoti;**One person violates and regrets it.*";
P_HTM[3334]="*tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti yatthassa te uppannā pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti. (1)**And they don’t truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[3335]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo ārabhati, na vippaṭisārī hoti;**One person violates and doesn’t regret it.*";
P_HTM[3336]="*tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti yatthassa te uppannā pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti. (2)**And they don’t understand …*";
P_HTM[3337]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo na ārabhati, vippaṭisārī hoti;**One person doesn’t violate yet still feels regret.*";
P_HTM[3338]="*tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti yatthassa te uppannā pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti. (3)**And they don’t understand …*";
P_HTM[3339]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo na ārabhati na vippaṭisārī hoti;**One person neither violates nor regrets.*";
P_HTM[3340]="*tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti yatthassa te uppannā pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti. (4)**But they don’t understand …*";
P_HTM[3341]="*Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo na ārabhati na vippaṭisārī hoti;**One person neither violates nor regrets.*";
P_HTM[3342]="*tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti yatthassa te uppannā pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti. (5)**And they do understand where those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[3343]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ puggalo ārabhati ca vippaṭisārī ca hoti,**Take the case of the person who violates and regrets it.*";
P_HTM[3344]="*tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti yatthassa te uppannā pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti,**And they don’t truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[3345]="*so evamassa vacanīyo:**They should be told:*";
P_HTM[3346]="*‘āyasmato kho ārambhajā āsavā saṃvijjanti, vippaṭisārajā āsavā pavaḍḍhanti, sādhu vatāyasmā ārambhaje āsave pahāya vippaṭisāraje āsave paṭivinodetvā cittaṃ paññañca bhāvetu;**‘Venerable, the defilements born of violation are found in you, and the defilements born of regret grow. You would do well to give up the defilements born of violation and get rid of the defilements born of regret, and then develop the mind and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3347]="*evamāyasmā amunā pañcamena puggalena samasamo bhavissatī’ti. (1)**In this way you’ll become just like the fifth person.’*";
P_HTM[3348]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ puggalo ārabhati na vippaṭisārī hoti,**Take the case of the person who violates and doesn’t regret it.*";
P_HTM[3349]="*tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti yatthassa te uppannā pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti,**And they don’t understand…*";
P_HTM[3350]="*so evamassa vacanīyo:**They should be told:*";
P_HTM[3351]="*‘āyasmato kho ārambhajā āsavā saṃvijjanti, vippaṭisārajā āsavā na pavaḍḍhanti, sādhu vatāyasmā ārambhaje āsave pahāya cittaṃ paññañca bhāvetu;**‘Venerable, the defilements born of violation are found in you, but the defilements born of regret don’t grow. You would do well to give up the defilements born of violation, and then develop the mind and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3352]="*evamāyasmā amunā pañcamena puggalena samasamo bhavissatī’ti. (2)**In this way you’ll become just like the fifth person.’*";
P_HTM[3353]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ puggalo na ārabhati vippaṭisārī hoti,**Take the case of the person who doesn’t violate yet feels regret.*";
P_HTM[3354]="*tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti yatthassa te uppannā pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti,**And they don’t understand…*";
P_HTM[3355]="*so evamassa vacanīyo:**They should be told:*";
P_HTM[3356]="*‘āyasmato kho ārambhajā āsavā na saṃvijjanti, vippaṭisārajā āsavā pavaḍḍhanti, sādhu vatāyasmā vippaṭisāraje āsave paṭivinodetvā cittaṃ paññañca bhāvetu;**‘Venerable, the defilements born of violation are not found in you, yet the defilements born of regret grow. You would do well to get rid of the defilements born of regret, and then develop the mind and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3357]="*evamāyasmā amunā pañcamena puggalena samasamo bhavissatī’ti. (3)**In this way you’ll become just like the fifth person.’*";
P_HTM[3358]="*Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ puggalo na ārabhati na vippaṭisārī hoti,**Take the case of the person who neither violates nor regrets.*";
P_HTM[3359]="*tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti yatthassa te uppannā pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti,**But they don’t understand…*";
P_HTM[3360]="*so evamassa vacanīyo:**They should be told:*";
P_HTM[3361]="*‘āyasmato kho ārambhajā āsavā na saṃvijjanti, vippaṭisārajā āsavā na pavaḍḍhanti, sādhu vatāyasmā cittaṃ paññañca bhāvetu;**‘Venerable, the defilements born of violation are not found in you, and the defilements born of regret don’t grow. You would do well to develop the mind and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3362]="*evamāyasmā amunā pañcamena puggalena samasamo bhavissatī’ti. (4)**In this way you’ll become just like the fifth person.’*";
P_HTM[3363]="*Iti kho, bhikkhave, ime cattāro puggalā amunā pañcamena puggalena evaṃ ovadiyamānā evaṃ anusāsiyamānā anupubbena āsavānaṃ khayaṃ pāpuṇantī”ti.**And so, mendicants, when these four people are advised and instructed by comparison with the fifth person, they gradually attain the ending of defilements.”*";
P_HTM[3364]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3365]="*3. Sārandadasuttaṃ**At Sārandada*";
P_HTM[3366]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof.*";
P_HTM[3367]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya vesāliṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Vesālī for alms.*";
P_HTM[3368]="*Tena kho pana samayena pañcamattānaṃ licchavisatānaṃ sārandade cetiye sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ ayamantarākathā udapādi:**Now at that time around five hundred Licchavis were sitting together at the Sārandada shrine, and this discussion came up among them,*";
P_HTM[3369]="*“pañcannaṃ ratanānaṃ pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ.**“The appearance of five treasures is rare in the world.*";
P_HTM[3370]="*Katamesaṃ pañcannaṃ?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3371]="*Hatthiratanassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ, assaratanassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ, maṇiratanassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ, itthiratanassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ, gahapatiratanassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ.**The elephant-treasure, the horse-treasure, the jewel-treasure, the woman-treasure, and the householder-treasure.*";
P_HTM[3372]="*Imesaṃ pañcannaṃ ratanānaṃ pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmin”ti.**The appearance of these five treasures is rare in the world.”*";
P_HTM[3373]="*Atha kho te licchavī magge purisaṃ ṭhapesuṃ:**Then those Licchavis sent a man out on to the road, saying,*";
P_HTM[3374]="*“yadā tvaṃ, ambho purisa, passeyyāsi bhagavantaṃ, atha amhākaṃ āroceyyāsī”ti.**“Mister, please tell us when you see the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[3375]="*Addasā kho so puriso bhagavantaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ;**That man saw the Buddha coming off in the distance.*";
P_HTM[3376]="*disvāna yena te licchavī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā te licchavī etadavoca:**He went to the Licchavis and said,*";
P_HTM[3377]="*“ayaṃ so, bhante, bhagavā gacchati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho;**“Sirs, the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha is coming.*";
P_HTM[3378]="*yassadāni kālaṃ maññathā”ti.**Please go at your convenience.”*";
P_HTM[3379]="*Atha kho te licchavī yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho te licchavī bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then those Licchavis went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[3380]="*“Sādhu, bhante, yena sārandadaṃ cetiyaṃ tenupasaṅkamatu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti.**“Please go to the Sārandada shrine, out of compassion.”*";
P_HTM[3381]="*Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena.**The Buddha consented in silence.*";
P_HTM[3382]="*Atha kho bhagavā yena sārandadaṃ cetiyaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. Nisajja kho bhagavā te licchavī etadavoca:**Then the Buddha went up to the Sārandada shrine, where he sat on the seat spread out, and said to the Licchavis,*";
P_HTM[3383]="*“kāya nuttha, licchavī, etarahi kathāya sannisinnā, kā ca pana vo antarākathā vippakatā”ti?**“Licchavis, what were you sitting talking about just now? What conversation was unfinished?”*";
P_HTM[3384]="*“Idha, bhante, amhākaṃ sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ ayamantarākathā udapādi:**“Well, Master Gotama, this discussion came up among us while we were sitting together:*";
P_HTM[3385]="*‘pañcannaṃ ratanānaṃ pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ.**‘The appearance of five treasures is rare in the world. …’”*";
P_HTM[3386]="*Katamesaṃ pañcannaṃ?* **";
P_HTM[3387]="*Hatthiratanassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ, assaratanassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ, maṇiratanassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ, itthiratanassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ, gahapatiratanassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3388]="*Imesaṃ pañcannaṃ ratanānaṃ pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmin’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3389]="*“Kāmādhimuttānaṃ vata bho licchavīnaṃ kāmaṃyeva ārabbha antarākathā udapādi.**“You Licchavis are so fixated on sensual pleasures, that’s the only discussion that came up!*";
P_HTM[3390]="*Pañcannaṃ, licchavī, ratanānaṃ pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ.**Licchavis, the appearance of five treasures is rare in the world.*";
P_HTM[3391]="*Katamesaṃ pañcannaṃ?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3392]="*Tathāgatassa arahato sammāsambuddhassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ,**The appearance of a Realized One, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[3393]="*tathāgatappaveditassa dhammavinayassa desetā puggalo dullabho lokasmiṃ,**A person who explains the teaching and training proclaimed by a Realized One.*";
P_HTM[3394]="*tathāgatappaveditassa dhammavinayassa desitassa viññātā puggalo dullabho lokasmiṃ,**A person who understands the teaching and training proclaimed by a Realized One.*";
P_HTM[3395]="*tathāgatappaveditassa dhammavinayassa desitassa viññātā dhammānudhammappaṭipanno puggalo dullabho lokasmiṃ,**A person who practices in line with the teaching.*";
P_HTM[3396]="*kataññū katavedī puggalo dullabho lokasmiṃ.**A person who is grateful and thankful.*";
P_HTM[3397]="*Imesaṃ kho, licchavī, pañcannaṃ ratanānaṃ pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmin”ti.**The appearance of these five treasures is rare in the world.”*";
P_HTM[3398]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3399]="*4. Tikaṇḍakīsuttaṃ**At Tikaṇḍakī*";
P_HTM[3400]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sākete viharati tikaṇḍakīvane.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāketa, in Tikaṇḍakī Wood.*";
P_HTM[3401]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[3402]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[3403]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[3404]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[3405]="*“Sādhu, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kālena kālaṃ appaṭikūle paṭikūlasaññī vihareyya.**“Mendicants, a mendicant would do well to meditate from time to time perceiving the following:*";
P_HTM[3406]="*appaṭikūle paṭikūlasaññī vihareyya.**the repulsive in the unrepulsive,*";
P_HTM[3407]="*Sādhu, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kālena kālaṃ paṭikūle appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyya.**the unrepulsive in the repulsive,*";
P_HTM[3408]="*Sādhu, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kālena kālaṃ appaṭikūle ca paṭikūle ca paṭikūlasaññī vihareyya.**the repulsive in both the unrepulsive and the repulsive, and*";
P_HTM[3409]="*Sādhu, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kālena kālaṃ paṭikūle ca appaṭikūle ca appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyya.**the unrepulsive in both the repulsive and the unrepulsive.*";
P_HTM[3410]="*Sādhu, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kālena kālaṃ paṭikūlañca appaṭikūlañca tadubhayaṃ abhinivajjetvā upekkhako vihareyya sato sampajāno.**A mendicant would do well to meditate from time to time staying equanimous, mindful and aware, rejecting both the repulsive and the unrepulsive.*";
P_HTM[3411]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu atthavasaṃ paṭicca appaṭikūle paṭikūlasaññī vihareyya?**For what reason should a mendicant meditate perceiving the repulsive in the unrepulsive?*";
P_HTM[3412]="*‘Mā me rajanīyesu dhammesu rāgo udapādī’ti—**‘May greed not arise in me for things that arouse greed.’*";
P_HTM[3413]="*idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu atthavasaṃ paṭicca appaṭikūle paṭikūlasaññī vihareyya.**A mendicant should meditate perceiving the repulsive in the unrepulsive for this reason.*";
P_HTM[3414]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu atthavasaṃ paṭicca paṭikūle appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyya?**For what reason should a mendicant meditate perceiving the unrepulsive in the repulsive?*";
P_HTM[3415]="*‘Mā me dosanīyesu dhammesu doso udapādī’ti—**‘May hate not arise in me for things that provoke hate.’ …*";
P_HTM[3416]="*idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu atthavasaṃ paṭicca paṭikūle appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyya.* **";
P_HTM[3417]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu atthavasaṃ paṭicca appaṭikūle ca paṭikūle ca paṭikūlasaññī vihareyya?**For what reason should a mendicant meditate perceiving the repulsive in both the unrepulsive and the repulsive?*";
P_HTM[3418]="*‘Mā me rajanīyesu dhammesu rāgo udapādi, mā me dosanīyesu dhammesu doso udapādī’ti—**‘May greed not arise in me for things that arouse greed. May hate not arise in me for things that provoke hate.’ …*";
P_HTM[3419]="*idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu atthavasaṃ paṭicca appaṭikūle ca paṭikūle ca paṭikūlasaññī vihareyya.* **";
P_HTM[3420]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu atthavasaṃ paṭicca paṭikūle ca appaṭikūle ca appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyya?**For what reason should a mendicant meditate perceiving the unrepulsive in both the repulsive and the unrepulsive?*";
P_HTM[3421]="*‘Mā me dosanīyesu dhammesu doso udapādi, mā me rajanīyesu dhammesu rāgo udapādī’ti—**‘May hate not arise in me for things that provoke hate. May greed not arise in me for things that arouse greed.’ …*";
P_HTM[3422]="*idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu atthavasaṃ paṭicca paṭikūle ca appaṭikūle ca appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyya.* **";
P_HTM[3423]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu atthavasaṃ paṭicca paṭikūlañca appaṭikūlañca tadubhayaṃ abhinivajjetvā upekkhako vihareyya?**For what reason should a mendicant meditate staying equanimous, mindful and aware, rejecting both the repulsive and the unrepulsive?*";
P_HTM[3424]="*‘Sato sampajāno mā me kvacani katthaci kiñcanaṃ rajanīyesu dhammesu rāgo udapādi, mā me kvacani katthaci kiñcanaṃ dosanīyesu dhammesu doso udapādi, mā me kvacani katthaci kiñcanaṃ mohanīyesu dhammesu moho udapādī’ti—**‘May no greed for things that arouse greed, hate for things that provoke hate, or delusion for things that promote delusion arise in me in any way at all.’*";
P_HTM[3425]="*idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu atthavasaṃ paṭicca paṭikūlañca appaṭikūlañca tadubhayaṃ abhinivajjetvā upekkhako vihareyya sato sampajāno”ti.**For this reason a mendicant should meditate staying equanimous, mindful and aware, rejecting both the repulsive and the unrepulsive.”*";
P_HTM[3426]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3427]="*5. Nirayasuttaṃ**Hell*";
P_HTM[3428]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, someone with five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[3429]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3430]="*Pāṇātipātī hoti, adinnādāyī hoti, kāmesumicchācārī hoti, musāvādī hoti, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhāyī hoti.**They kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, lie, and use alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[3431]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**Someone with these five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[3432]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.**Someone with five qualities is raised up to heaven*";
P_HTM[3433]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3434]="*Pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti.**They don’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, lie, or use alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[3435]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.**Someone with these five qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[3436]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3437]="*6. Mittasuttaṃ**A Friend*";
P_HTM[3438]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu mitto na sevitabbo.**“Mendicants, you shouldn’t associate with a mendicant friend who has five qualities.*";
P_HTM[3439]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3440]="*Kammantaṃ kāreti, adhikaraṇaṃ ādiyati, pāmokkhesu bhikkhūsu paṭiviruddho hoti, dīghacārikaṃ anavatthacārikaṃ anuyutto viharati, nappaṭibalo hoti kālena kālaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassetuṃ samādapetuṃ samuttejetuṃ sampahaṃsetuṃ.**They start up work projects. They take up disciplinary issues. They conflict with leading mendicants. They like long and aimless wandering. They’re unable to educate, encourage, fire up, and inspire you from time to time with a Dhamma talk.*";
P_HTM[3441]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu mitto na sevitabbo.**Mendicants, you shouldn’t associate with a mendicant friend who has these five qualities.*";
P_HTM[3442]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu mitto sevitabbo.**You should associate with a mendicant friend who has five qualities.*";
P_HTM[3443]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3444]="*Na kammantaṃ kāreti, na adhikaraṇaṃ ādiyati, na pāmokkhesu bhikkhūsu paṭiviruddho hoti, na dīghacārikaṃ anavatthacārikaṃ anuyutto viharati, paṭibalo hoti kālena kālaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassetuṃ samādapetuṃ samuttejetuṃ sampahaṃsetuṃ.**They don’t start up work projects. They don’t take up disciplinary issues. They don’t conflict with leading mendicants. They don’t like long and aimless wandering. They’re able to educate, encourage, fire up, and inspire you from time to time with a Dhamma talk.*";
P_HTM[3445]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu mitto sevitabbo”ti.**You should associate with a mendicant friend who has these five qualities.”*";
P_HTM[3446]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3447]="*7. Asappurisadānasuttaṃ**Gifts of a Bad Person*";
P_HTM[3448]="*“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, asappurisadānāni.**“Mendicants, there are these five gifts of a bad person.*";
P_HTM[3449]="*Katamāni pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3450]="*Asakkaccaṃ deti, acittīkatvā deti, asahatthā deti, apaviddhaṃ deti, anāgamanadiṭṭhiko deti.**They give carelessly. They give thoughtlessly. They don’t give with their own hand. They give the dregs. They give without consideration for consequences.*";
P_HTM[3451]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca asappurisadānāni.**These are the five gifts of a bad person.*";
P_HTM[3452]="*Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, sappurisadānāni.**There are these five gifts of a good person.*";
P_HTM[3453]="*Katamāni pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3454]="*Sakkaccaṃ deti, cittīkatvā deti, sahatthā deti, anapaviddhaṃ deti, āgamanadiṭṭhiko deti.**They give carefully. They give thoughtfully. They give with their own hand. They don’t give the dregs. They give with consideration for consequences.*";
P_HTM[3455]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca sappurisadānānī”ti.**These are the five gifts of a good person.”*";
P_HTM[3456]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3457]="*8. Sappurisadānasuttaṃ**Gifts of a Good Person*";
P_HTM[3458]="*“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, sappurisadānāni.**“There are these five gifts of a good person.*";
P_HTM[3459]="*Katamāni pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3460]="*Saddhāya dānaṃ deti, sakkaccaṃ dānaṃ deti, kālena dānaṃ deti, anuggahitacitto dānaṃ deti, attānañca parañca anupahacca dānaṃ deti.**They give a gift out of faith. They give a gift carefully. They give a gift at the right time. They give a gift with no strings attached. They give a gift without hurting themselves or others.*";
P_HTM[3461]="*Saddhāya kho pana, bhikkhave, dānaṃ datvā yattha yattha tassa dānassa vipāko nibbattati, aḍḍho ca hoti mahaddhano mahābhogo, abhirūpo ca hoti dassanīyo pāsādiko paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgato.**Having given a gift out of faith, in whatever place the result of that gift manifests they become rich, affluent, and wealthy. And they’re attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty.*";
P_HTM[3462]="*Sakkaccaṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, dānaṃ datvā yattha yattha tassa dānassa vipāko nibbattati, aḍḍho ca hoti mahaddhano mahābhogo.**Having given a gift carefully, in whatever place the result of that gift manifests they become rich, affluent, and wealthy.*";
P_HTM[3463]="*Yepissa te honti puttāti vā dārāti vā dāsāti vā pessāti vā kammakarāti vā, tepi sussūsanti sotaṃ odahanti aññā cittaṃ upaṭṭhapenti.**And their children, wives, bondservants, workers, and staff want to listen. They pay attention and try to understand.*";
P_HTM[3464]="*Kālena kho pana, bhikkhave, dānaṃ datvā yattha yattha tassa dānassa vipāko nibbattati, aḍḍho ca hoti mahaddhano mahābhogo;**Having given a gift at the right time, in whatever place the result of that gift manifests they become rich, affluent, and wealthy.*";
P_HTM[3465]="*kālāgatā cassa atthā pacurā honti.**And when the time is right, they get all that they need.*";
P_HTM[3466]="*Anuggahitacitto kho pana, bhikkhave, dānaṃ datvā yattha yattha tassa dānassa vipāko nibbattati, aḍḍho ca hoti mahaddhano mahābhogo;**Having given a gift with no strings attached, in whatever place the result of that gift manifests they become rich, affluent, and wealthy.*";
P_HTM[3467]="*uḷāresu ca pañcasu kāmaguṇesu bhogāya cittaṃ namati.**And their mind tends to enjoy the five refined kinds of sensual stimulation.*";
P_HTM[3468]="*Attānañca parañca anupahacca kho pana, bhikkhave, dānaṃ datvā yattha yattha tassa dānassa vipāko nibbattati, aḍḍho ca hoti mahaddhano mahābhogo;**Having given a gift without hurting themselves or others, in whatever place the result of that gift manifests they become rich, affluent, and wealthy.*";
P_HTM[3469]="*na cassa kutoci bhogānaṃ upaghāto āgacchati aggito vā udakato vā rājato vā corato vā appiyato vā dāyādato.**And no damage comes to their property from anywhere, whether fire, flood, rulers, bandits, or unloved heirs.*";
P_HTM[3470]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca sappurisadānānī”ti.**These are the five gifts of a good person.”*";
P_HTM[3471]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3472]="*9. Paṭhamasamayavimuttasuttaṃ**Temporarily Free (1st)*";
P_HTM[3473]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhammā samayavimuttassa bhikkhuno parihānāya saṃvattanti.**“Mendicants, these five things lead to the decline of a mendicant who is temporarily free.*";
P_HTM[3474]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3475]="*Kammārāmatā, bhassārāmatā, niddārāmatā, saṅgaṇikārāmatā, yathāvimuttaṃ cittaṃ na paccavekkhati.**They relish work, talk, sleep, and company. And they don’t review the extent of their mind’s freedom.*";
P_HTM[3476]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhammā samayavimuttassa bhikkhuno parihānāya saṃvattanti.**These five things lead to the decline of a mendicant who is temporarily free.*";
P_HTM[3477]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhammā samayavimuttassa bhikkhuno aparihānāya saṃvattanti.**These five things don’t lead to the decline of a mendicant who is temporarily free.*";
P_HTM[3478]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3479]="*Na kammārāmatā, na bhassārāmatā, na niddārāmatā, na saṅgaṇikārāmatā, yathāvimuttaṃ cittaṃ paccavekkhati.**They don’t relish work, talk, sleep, and company. And they review the extent of their mind’s freedom.*";
P_HTM[3480]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhammā samayavimuttassa bhikkhuno aparihānāya saṃvattantī”ti.**These five things don’t lead to the decline of a mendicant who is temporarily free.”*";
P_HTM[3481]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3482]="*10. Dutiyasamayavimuttasuttaṃ**Temporarily Free (2nd)*";
P_HTM[3483]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhammā samayavimuttassa bhikkhuno parihānāya saṃvattanti.**“Mendicants, these five things lead to the decline of a mendicant who is temporarily free.*";
P_HTM[3484]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3485]="*Kammārāmatā, bhassārāmatā, niddārāmatā, indriyesu aguttadvāratā, bhojane amattaññutā.**They relish work, talk, and sleep. They don’t guard the sense doors and they eat too much.*";
P_HTM[3486]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhammā samayavimuttassa bhikkhuno parihānāya saṃvattanti.**These five things lead to the decline of a mendicant who is temporarily free.*";
P_HTM[3487]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhammā samayavimuttassa bhikkhuno aparihānāya saṃvattanti.**These five things don’t lead to the decline of a mendicant who is temporarily free.*";
P_HTM[3488]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3489]="*Na kammārāmatā, na bhassārāmatā, na niddārāmatā, indriyesu guttadvāratā, bhojane mattaññutā.**They don’t relish work, talk, sleep, and company. They guard the sense doors and they have moderation in eating.*";
P_HTM[3490]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhammā samayavimuttassa bhikkhuno aparihānāya saṃvattantī”ti.**These five things don’t lead to the decline of a mendicant who is temporarily free.”*";
P_HTM[3491]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3492]="*Tikaṇḍakīvaggo pañcamo.* **";
P_HTM[3493]="*Datvā avajānāti ārabhati ca,* **";
P_HTM[3494]="*Sārandada tikaṇḍa nirayena ca;* **";
P_HTM[3495]="*Mitto asappurisasappurisena,* **";
P_HTM[3496]="*Samayavimuttaṃ apare dveti.* **";
P_HTM[3497]="*Tatiyo paṇṇāsako samatto.* **";
P_HTM[3498]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**The True Teaching*";
P_HTM[3499]="*1. Paṭhamasammattaniyāmasuttaṃ**Inevitability Regarding the Right Path (1st)*";
P_HTM[3500]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato suṇantopi saddhammaṃ abhabbo niyāmaṃ okkamituṃ kusalesu dhammesu sammattaṃ.**“Mendicants, someone with five qualities is unable to enter the sure path with regards to skillful qualities even when listening to the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3501]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3502]="*Kathaṃ paribhoti, kathikaṃ paribhoti, attānaṃ paribhoti, vikkhittacitto dhammaṃ suṇāti, anekaggacitto ayoniso ca manasi karoti.**They disparage the talk, the speaker, or themselves. They listen with distracted and scattered mind. They attend improperly.*";
P_HTM[3503]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato suṇantopi saddhammaṃ abhabbo niyāmaṃ okkamituṃ kusalesu dhammesu sammattaṃ.**Someone with these five qualities is unable to enter the sure path with regards to skillful qualities, even when listening to the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3504]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato suṇanto saddhammaṃ bhabbo niyāmaṃ okkamituṃ kusalesu dhammesu sammattaṃ.**Someone with five qualities is able to enter the sure path with regards to skillful qualities when listening to the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3505]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3506]="*Na kathaṃ paribhoti, na kathikaṃ paribhoti, na attānaṃ paribhoti, avikkhittacitto dhammaṃ suṇāti, ekaggacitto yoniso ca manasi karoti.**They don’t disparage the talk, the speaker, or themselves. They listen with undistracted and unified mind. They attend properly.*";
P_HTM[3507]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato suṇanto saddhammaṃ bhabbo niyāmaṃ okkamituṃ kusalesu dhammesu sammattan”ti.**Someone with these five qualities is able to enter the sure path with regards to skillful qualities when listening to the true teaching.”*";
P_HTM[3508]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3509]="*2. Dutiyasammattaniyāmasuttaṃ**Inevitability Regarding the Right Path (2nd)*";
P_HTM[3510]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato suṇantopi saddhammaṃ abhabbo niyāmaṃ okkamituṃ kusalesu dhammesu sammattaṃ.**“Mendicants, someone with five qualities is unable to enter the sure path with regards to skillful qualities even when listening to the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3511]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3512]="*Kathaṃ paribhoti, kathikaṃ paribhoti, attānaṃ paribhoti, duppañño hoti jaḷo eḷamūgo, anaññāte aññātamānī hoti.**They disparage the talk, the speaker, or themselves. They’re witless, dull, and stupid. They think they know what they don’t know.*";
P_HTM[3513]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato suṇantopi saddhammaṃ abhabbo niyāmaṃ okkamituṃ kusalesu dhammesu sammattaṃ.**Someone with these five qualities is unable to enter the sure path with regards to skillful qualities, even when listening to the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3514]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato suṇanto saddhammaṃ bhabbo niyāmaṃ okkamituṃ kusalesu dhammesu sammattaṃ.**Someone with five qualities is able to enter the sure path with regards to skillful qualities when listening to the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3515]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3516]="*Na kathaṃ paribhoti, na kathikaṃ paribhoti, na attānaṃ paribhoti, paññavā hoti ajaḷo aneḷamūgo, na anaññāte aññātamānī hoti.**They don’t disparage the talk, the speaker, or themselves. They’re wise, bright, and clever. They don’t think they know what they don’t know.*";
P_HTM[3517]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato suṇanto saddhammaṃ bhabbo niyāmaṃ okkamituṃ kusalesu dhammesu sammattan”ti.**Someone with these five qualities is able to enter the sure path with regards to skillful qualities when listening to the true teaching.”*";
P_HTM[3518]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3519]="*3. Tatiyasammattaniyāmasuttaṃ**Inevitability Regarding the Right Path (3rd)*";
P_HTM[3520]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato suṇantopi saddhammaṃ abhabbo niyāmaṃ okkamituṃ kusalesu dhammesu sammattaṃ.**“Mendicants, someone with five qualities is unable to enter the sure path with regards to skillful qualities even when listening to the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3521]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3522]="*Makkhī dhammaṃ suṇāti makkhapariyuṭṭhito, upārambhacitto dhammaṃ suṇāti randhagavesī, dhammadesake āhatacitto hoti khīlajāto, duppañño hoti jaḷo eḷamūgo, anaññāte aññātamānī hoti.**They listen to the teaching bent only on putting it down. They listen to the teaching with a hostile, fault-finding mind. They’re antagonistic to the teacher, planning to attack them. They’re witless, dull, and stupid. And they think they know what they don’t know.*";
P_HTM[3523]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato suṇantopi saddhammaṃ abhabbo niyāmaṃ okkamituṃ kusalesu dhammesu sammattaṃ.**Someone with these five qualities is unable to enter the sure path with regards to skillful qualities even when listening to the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3524]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato suṇanto saddhammaṃ bhabbo niyāmaṃ okkamituṃ kusalesu dhammesu sammattaṃ.**Someone with five qualities is able to enter the sure path with regards to skillful qualities when listening to the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3525]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3526]="*Amakkhī dhammaṃ suṇāti na makkhapariyuṭṭhito, anupārambhacitto dhammaṃ suṇāti na randhagavesī, dhammadesake anāhatacitto hoti akhīlajāto, paññavā hoti ajaḷo aneḷamūgo, na anaññāte aññātamānī hoti.**They don’t listen to the teaching bent only on putting it down. They don’t listen to the teaching with a hostile, fault-finding mind. They’re not antagonistic to the teacher, and not planning to attack them. They’re wise, bright, and clever. And they don’t think they know what they don’t know.*";
P_HTM[3527]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato suṇanto saddhammaṃ bhabbo niyāmaṃ okkamituṃ kusalesu dhammesu sammattan”ti.**Someone with these five qualities is able to enter the sure path with regards to skillful qualities when listening to the true teaching.”*";
P_HTM[3528]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3529]="*4. Paṭhamasaddhammasammosasuttaṃ**The Decline of the True Teaching (1st)*";
P_HTM[3530]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhammā saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattanti.**“Mendicants, these five things lead to the decline and disappearance of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3531]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3532]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhū na sakkaccaṃ dhammaṃ suṇanti, na sakkaccaṃ dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇanti, na sakkaccaṃ dhammaṃ dhārenti, na sakkaccaṃ dhātānaṃ dhammānaṃ atthaṃ upaparikkhanti, na sakkaccaṃ atthamaññāya dhammamaññāya dhammānudhammaṃ paṭipajjanti.**It’s when mendicants don’t carefully listen to the teachings, memorize them, and remember them. They don’t carefully examine the meaning of teachings that they remember. And they don’t carefully practice in line with the meaning and the teaching they’ve understood.*";
P_HTM[3533]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhammā saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattanti.**These five things lead to the decline and disappearance of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3534]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhammā saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattanti.**These five things lead to the continuation, persistence, and enduring of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3535]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3536]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhū sakkaccaṃ dhammaṃ suṇanti, sakkaccaṃ dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇanti, sakkaccaṃ dhammaṃ dhārenti, sakkaccaṃ dhātānaṃ dhammānaṃ atthaṃ upaparikkhanti, sakkaccaṃ atthamaññāya dhammamaññāya dhammānudhammaṃ paṭipajjanti.**It’s when mendicants carefully listen to the teachings, memorize them, and remember them. They carefully examine the meaning of teachings that they remember. And they carefully practice in line with the meaning and the teaching they’ve understood.*";
P_HTM[3537]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhammā saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattantī”ti.**These five things lead to the continuation, persistence, and enduring of the true teaching.”*";
P_HTM[3538]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3539]="*5. Dutiyasaddhammasammosasuttaṃ**The Decline of the True Teaching (2nd)*";
P_HTM[3540]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhammā saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattanti.**“Mendicants, these five things lead to the decline and disappearance of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3541]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3542]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhū dhammaṃ na pariyāpuṇanti—**It’s when the mendicants don’t memorize the teaching—*";
P_HTM[3543]="*suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ.**statements, songs, discussions, verses, inspired exclamations, legends, stories of past lives, amazing stories, and classifications.*";
P_HTM[3544]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo dhammo saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the first thing that leads to the decline and disappearance of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3545]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhū yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ na vitthārena paresaṃ desenti.**Furthermore, the mendicants don’t explain the teaching in detail to others as they learned and memorized it.*";
P_HTM[3546]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo dhammo saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the second thing …*";
P_HTM[3547]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhū yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ na vitthārena paraṃ vācenti.**Furthermore, the mendicants don’t make others recite the teaching in detail as they learned and memorized it.*";
P_HTM[3548]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo dhammo saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the third thing …*";
P_HTM[3549]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhū yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ na vitthārena sajjhāyaṃ karonti.**Furthermore, the mendicants don’t recite the teaching in detail as they learned and memorized it.*";
P_HTM[3550]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho dhammo saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the fourth thing …*";
P_HTM[3551]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhū yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ na cetasā anuvitakkenti anuvicārenti manasānupekkhanti.**Furthermore, the mendicants don’t think about and consider the teaching in their hearts, examining it with their minds as they learned and memorized it.*";
P_HTM[3552]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo dhammo saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the fifth thing that leads to the decline and disappearance of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3553]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhammā saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattanti.**These five things lead to the decline and disappearance of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3554]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhammā saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattanti.**These five things lead to the continuation, persistence, and enduring of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3555]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3556]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhū dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇanti—**It’s when the mendicants memorize the teaching—*";
P_HTM[3557]="*suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ.**statements, songs, discussions, verses, inspired exclamations, legends, stories of past lives, amazing stories, and classifications.*";
P_HTM[3558]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo dhammo saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the first thing that leads to the continuation, persistence, and enduring of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3559]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhū yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ vitthārena paresaṃ desenti.**Furthermore, the mendicants explain the teaching in detail to others as they learned and memorized it.*";
P_HTM[3560]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo dhammo saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the second thing …*";
P_HTM[3561]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhū yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ vitthārena paraṃ vācenti.**Furthermore, the mendicants make others recite the teaching in detail as they learned and memorized it.*";
P_HTM[3562]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo dhammo saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the third thing …*";
P_HTM[3563]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhū yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ vitthārena sajjhāyaṃ karonti.**Furthermore, the mendicants recite the teaching in detail as they learned and memorized it.*";
P_HTM[3564]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho dhammo saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the fourth thing …*";
P_HTM[3565]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhū yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ cetasā anuvitakkenti anuvicārenti manasānupekkhanti.**Furthermore, the mendicants think about and consider the teaching in their hearts, examining it with their minds as they learned and memorized it.*";
P_HTM[3566]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo dhammo saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the fifth thing that leads to the continuation, persistence, and enduring of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3567]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhammā saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattantī”ti.**These five things lead to the continuation, persistence, and enduring of the true teaching.”*";
P_HTM[3568]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3569]="*6. Tatiyasaddhammasammosasuttaṃ**The Decline of the True Teaching (3rd)*";
P_HTM[3570]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhammā saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattanti.**“Mendicants, these five things lead to the decline and disappearance of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3571]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3572]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhū duggahitaṃ suttantaṃ pariyāpuṇanti dunnikkhittehi padabyañjanehi.**It’s when the mendicants memorize discourses that they learned incorrectly, with misplaced words and phrases.*";
P_HTM[3573]="*Dunnikkhittassa, bhikkhave, padabyañjanassa atthopi dunnayo hoti.**When the words and phrases are misplaced, the meaning is misinterpreted.*";
P_HTM[3574]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo dhammo saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the first thing that leads to the decline and disappearance of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3575]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhū dubbacā honti, dovacassakaraṇehi dhammehi samannāgatā, akkhamā appadakkhiṇaggāhino anusāsaniṃ.**Furthermore, the mendicants are hard to admonish, having qualities that make them hard to admonish. They’re impatient, and don’t take instruction respectfully.*";
P_HTM[3576]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo dhammo saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the second thing …*";
P_HTM[3577]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ye te bhikkhū bahussutā āgatāgamā dhammadharā vinayadharā mātikādharā, te na sakkaccaṃ suttantaṃ paraṃ vācenti;**Furthermore, the mendicants who are very learned—knowledgeable in the scriptures, who have memorized the teachings, the texts on monastic training, and the outlines—don’t carefully make others recite the discourses.*";
P_HTM[3578]="*tesaṃ accayena chinnamūlako suttanto hoti appaṭisaraṇo.**When they pass away, the discourses are cut off at the root, with no-one to preserve them.*";
P_HTM[3579]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo dhammo saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the third thing …*";
P_HTM[3580]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, therā bhikkhū bāhulikā honti sāthalikā okkamane pubbaṅgamā paviveke nikkhittadhurā, na vīriyaṃ ārabhanti appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya.**Furthermore, the senior mendicants are indulgent and slack, leaders in backsliding, neglecting seclusion, not rousing energy for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized.*";
P_HTM[3581]="*Tesaṃ pacchimā janatā diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjati.**Those who come after them follow their example.*";
P_HTM[3582]="*Sāpi hoti bāhulikā sāthalikā okkamane pubbaṅgamā paviveke nikkhittadhurā, na vīriyaṃ ārabhati appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya.**They too are indulgent and slack …*";
P_HTM[3583]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho dhammo saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the fourth thing …*";
P_HTM[3584]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃgho bhinno hoti.**Furthermore, there’s a schism in the Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[3585]="*Saṃghe kho pana, bhikkhave, bhinne aññamaññaṃ akkosā ca honti, aññamaññaṃ paribhāsā ca honti, aññamaññaṃ parikkhepā ca honti, aññamaññaṃ pariccajanā ca honti.**When the Saṅgha is split, they abuse, insult, block, and reject each other.*";
P_HTM[3586]="*Tattha appasannā ceva nappasīdanti, pasannānañca ekaccānaṃ aññathattaṃ hoti.**This doesn’t inspire confidence in those without it, and it causes some with confidence to change their minds.*";
P_HTM[3587]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo dhammo saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the fifth thing that leads to the decline and disappearance of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3588]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhammā saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattanti.**These five things lead to the decline and disappearance of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3589]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhammā saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattanti.**These five things lead to the continuation, persistence, and enduring of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3590]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3591]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhū suggahitaṃ suttantaṃ pariyāpuṇanti sunikkhittehi padabyañjanehi.**It’s when the mendicants memorize discourses that have been learned correctly, with well placed words and phrases.*";
P_HTM[3592]="*Sunikkhittassa, bhikkhave, padabyañjanassa atthopi sunayo hoti.**When the words and phrases are well organized, the meaning is correctly interpreted.*";
P_HTM[3593]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo dhammo saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the first thing that leads to the continuation, persistence, and enduring of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3594]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhū suvacā honti sovacassakaraṇehi dhammehi samannāgatā, khamā padakkhiṇaggāhino anusāsaniṃ.**Furthermore, the mendicants are easy to admonish, having qualities that make them easy to admonish. They’re patient, and take instruction respectfully.*";
P_HTM[3595]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo dhammo saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the second thing …*";
P_HTM[3596]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ye te bhikkhū bahussutā āgatāgamā dhammadharā vinayadharā mātikādharā, te sakkaccaṃ suttantaṃ paraṃ vācenti;**Furthermore, the mendicants who are very learned—knowledgeable in the scriptures, who have memorized the teachings, the texts on monastic training, and the outlines—carefully make others recite the discourses.*";
P_HTM[3597]="*tesaṃ accayena na chinnamūlako suttanto hoti sappaṭisaraṇo.**When they pass away, the discourses aren’t cut off at the root, and they have someone to preserve them.*";
P_HTM[3598]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo dhammo saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the third thing …*";
P_HTM[3599]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, therā bhikkhū na bāhulikā honti na sāthalikā, okkamane nikkhittadhurā paviveke pubbaṅgamā; vīriyaṃ ārabhanti appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya.**Furthermore, the senior mendicants are not indulgent and slack, leaders in backsliding, neglecting seclusion. They rouse energy for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized.*";
P_HTM[3600]="*Tesaṃ pacchimā janatā diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjati.**Those who come after them follow their example.*";
P_HTM[3601]="*Sāpi hoti na bāhulikā na sāthalikā, okkamane nikkhittadhurā paviveke pubbaṅgamā, vīriyaṃ ārabhati appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya.**They too are not indulgent or slack …*";
P_HTM[3602]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho dhammo saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the fourth thing …*";
P_HTM[3603]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, saṅgho samaggo sammodamāno avivadamāno ekuddeso phāsuṃ viharati.**Furthermore, the Saṅgha lives comfortably, in harmony, appreciating each other, without quarreling, with one recitation.*";
P_HTM[3604]="*Saṅghe kho pana, bhikkhave, samagge na ceva aññamaññaṃ akkosā honti, na ca aññamaññaṃ paribhāsā honti, na ca aññamaññaṃ parikkhepā honti, na ca aññamaññaṃ pariccajanā honti.**When the Saṅgha is in harmony, they don’t abuse, insult, block, or reject each other.*";
P_HTM[3605]="*Tattha appasannā ceva pasīdanti, pasannānañca bhiyyobhāvo hoti.**This inspires confidence in those without it, and increases confidence in those who have it.*";
P_HTM[3606]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo dhammo saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattati.**This is the fifth thing that leads to the continuation, persistence, and enduring of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[3607]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhammā saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattantī”ti.**These five things lead to the continuation, persistence, and enduring of the true teaching.”*";
P_HTM[3608]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3609]="*7. Dukkathāsuttaṃ**Inappropriate Talk*";
P_HTM[3610]="*“Pañcannaṃ, bhikkhave, puggalānaṃ kathā dukkathā puggale puggalaṃ upanidhāya.**“Mendicants, there are certain topics that are inappropriate to talk about, taking into consideration which specific one of five people you are talking to.*";
P_HTM[3611]="*Katamesaṃ pañcannaṃ?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3612]="*Assaddhassa, bhikkhave, saddhākathā dukkathā;**It’s inappropriate to talk to an unfaithful person about faith.*";
P_HTM[3613]="*dussīlassa sīlakathā dukkathā;**It’s inappropriate to talk to an unethical person about ethics.*";
P_HTM[3614]="*appassutassa bāhusaccakathā dukkathā;**It’s inappropriate to talk to an unlearned person about learning.*";
P_HTM[3615]="*maccharissa cāgakathā dukkathā;**It’s inappropriate to talk to a stingy person about generosity.*";
P_HTM[3616]="*duppaññassa paññākathā dukkathā.**It’s inappropriate to talk to a witless person about wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3617]="*Kasmā ca, bhikkhave, assaddhassa saddhākathā dukkathā?**And why is it inappropriate to talk to an unfaithful person about faith?*";
P_HTM[3618]="*Assaddho, bhikkhave, saddhākathāya kacchamānāya abhisajjati kuppati byāpajjati patitthīyati kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti.**When an unfaithful person is spoken to about faith they lose their temper, becoming annoyed, hostile, and hard-hearted, and displaying annoyance, hate, and bitterness.*";
P_HTM[3619]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3620]="*Tañhi so, bhikkhave, saddhāsampadaṃ attani na samanupassati, na ca labhati tatonidānaṃ pītipāmojjaṃ.**Not seeing that faith in themselves, they don’t get the rapture and joy that faith brings.*";
P_HTM[3621]="*Tasmā assaddhassa saddhākathā dukkathā.**That’s why it’s inappropriate to talk to an unfaithful person about faith.*";
P_HTM[3622]="*Kasmā ca, bhikkhave, dussīlassa sīlakathā dukkathā?**And why is it inappropriate to talk to an unethical person about ethics?*";
P_HTM[3623]="*Dussīlo, bhikkhave, sīlakathāya kacchamānāya abhisajjati kuppati byāpajjati patitthīyati kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti.**When an unethical person is spoken to about ethics they lose their temper …*";
P_HTM[3624]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3625]="*Tañhi so, bhikkhave, sīlasampadaṃ attani na samanupassati na ca labhati tatonidānaṃ pītipāmojjaṃ.**Not seeing that ethical conduct in themselves, they don’t get the rapture and joy that ethical conduct brings.*";
P_HTM[3626]="*Tasmā dussīlassa sīlakathā dukkathā.**That’s why it’s inappropriate to talk to an unethical person about ethics.*";
P_HTM[3627]="*Kasmā ca, bhikkhave, appassutassa bāhusaccakathā dukkathā?**And why is it inappropriate to talk to an unlearned person about learning?*";
P_HTM[3628]="*Appassuto, bhikkhave, bāhusaccakathāya kacchamānāya abhisajjati kuppati byāpajjati patitthīyati kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti.**When an unlearned person is spoken to about learning they lose their temper …*";
P_HTM[3629]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3630]="*Tañhi so, bhikkhave, sutasampadaṃ attani na samanupassati, na ca labhati tatonidānaṃ pītipāmojjaṃ.**Not seeing that learning in themselves, they don’t get the rapture and joy that learning brings.*";
P_HTM[3631]="*Tasmā appassutassa bāhusaccakathā dukkathā.**That’s why it’s inappropriate to talk to an unlearned person about learning.*";
P_HTM[3632]="*Kasmā ca, bhikkhave, maccharissa cāgakathā dukkathā?**And why is it inappropriate to talk to a stingy person about generosity?*";
P_HTM[3633]="*Maccharī, bhikkhave, cāgakathāya kacchamānāya abhisajjati kuppati byāpajjati patitthīyati kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti.**When an stingy person is spoken to about generosity they lose their temper …*";
P_HTM[3634]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3635]="*Tañhi so, bhikkhave, cāgasampadaṃ attani na samanupassati na ca labhati tatonidānaṃ pītipāmojjaṃ.**Not seeing that generosity in themselves, they don’t get the rapture and joy that generosity brings.*";
P_HTM[3636]="*Tasmā maccharissa cāgakathā dukkathā.**That’s why it’s inappropriate to talk to a stingy person about generosity.*";
P_HTM[3637]="*Kasmā ca, bhikkhave, duppaññassa paññākathā dukkathā?**And why is it inappropriate to talk to a witless person about wisdom?*";
P_HTM[3638]="*Duppañño, bhikkhave, paññākathāya kacchamānāya abhisajjati kuppati byāpajjati patitthīyati kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti.**When a witless person is spoken to about wisdom they lose their temper, becoming annoyed, hostile, and hard-hearted, and displaying annoyance, hate, and bitterness.*";
P_HTM[3639]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3640]="*Tañhi so, bhikkhave, paññāsampadaṃ attani na samanupassati, na ca labhati tatonidānaṃ pītipāmojjaṃ.**Not seeing that wisdom in themselves, they don’t get the rapture and joy that wisdom brings.*";
P_HTM[3641]="*Tasmā duppaññassa paññākathā dukkathā.**That’s why it’s inappropriate to talk to a witless person about wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3642]="*Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ puggalānaṃ kathā dukkathā puggale puggalaṃ upanidhāya.**These are topics that are inappropriate to talk about, taking into consideration which specific one of five people you are talking to.*";
P_HTM[3643]="*Pañcannaṃ, bhikkhave, puggalānaṃ kathā sukathā puggale puggalaṃ upanidhāya.**There are certain topics that are appropriate to talk about, taking into consideration which specific one of five people you are talking to.*";
P_HTM[3644]="*Katamesaṃ pañcannaṃ?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3645]="*Saddhassa, bhikkhave, saddhākathā sukathā;**It’s appropriate to talk to a faithful person about faith.*";
P_HTM[3646]="*sīlavato sīlakathā sukathā;**It’s appropriate to talk to an ethical person about ethical conduct.*";
P_HTM[3647]="*bahussutassa bāhusaccakathā sukathā;**It’s appropriate to talk to a learned person about learning.*";
P_HTM[3648]="*cāgavato cāgakathā sukathā;**It’s appropriate to talk to a generous person about generosity.*";
P_HTM[3649]="*paññavato paññākathā sukathā.**It’s appropriate to talk to a wise person about wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3650]="*Kasmā ca, bhikkhave, saddhassa saddhākathā sukathā?**And why is it appropriate to talk to a faithful person about faith?*";
P_HTM[3651]="*Saddho, bhikkhave, saddhākathāya kacchamānāya nābhisajjati na kuppati na byāpajjati na patitthīyati na kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti.**When a faithful person is spoken to about faith they don’t lose their temper, they don’t get annoyed, hostile, and hard-hearted, or display annoyance, hate, and bitterness.*";
P_HTM[3652]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3653]="*Tañhi so, bhikkhave, saddhāsampadaṃ attani samanupassati labhati ca tatonidānaṃ pītipāmojjaṃ.**Seeing that faith in themselves, they get the rapture and joy that faith brings.*";
P_HTM[3654]="*Tasmā saddhassa saddhākathā sukathā.**That’s why it’s appropriate to talk to a faithful person about faith.*";
P_HTM[3655]="*Kasmā ca, bhikkhave, sīlavato sīlakathā sukathā?**And why is it appropriate to talk to an ethical person about ethical conduct?*";
P_HTM[3656]="*Sīlavā, bhikkhave, sīlakathāya kacchamānāya nābhisajjati na kuppati na byāpajjati na patitthīyati na kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti.**When an ethical person is spoken to about ethical conduct they don’t lose their temper …*";
P_HTM[3657]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3658]="*Tañhi so, bhikkhave, sīlasampadaṃ attani samanupassati, labhati ca tatonidānaṃ pītipāmojjaṃ.**Seeing that ethical conduct in themselves, they get the rapture and joy that ethical conduct brings.*";
P_HTM[3659]="*Tasmā sīlavato sīlakathā sukathā.**That’s why it’s appropriate to talk to an ethical person about ethical conduct.*";
P_HTM[3660]="*Kasmā ca, bhikkhave, bahussutassa bāhusaccakathā sukathā?**And why is it appropriate to talk to a learned person about learning?*";
P_HTM[3661]="*Bahussuto, bhikkhave, bāhusaccakathāya kacchamānāya nābhisajjati na kuppati na byāpajjati na patitthīyati na kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti.**When a learned person is spoken to about learning they don’t lose their temper …*";
P_HTM[3662]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3663]="*Tañhi so, bhikkhave, sutasampadaṃ attani samanupassati, labhati ca tatonidānaṃ pītipāmojjaṃ.**Seeing that learning in themselves, they get the rapture and joy that learning brings.*";
P_HTM[3664]="*Tasmā bahussutassa bāhusaccakathā sukathā.**That’s why it’s appropriate to talk to a learned person about learning.*";
P_HTM[3665]="*Kasmā ca, bhikkhave, cāgavato cāgakathā sukathā?**And why is it appropriate to talk to a generous person about generosity?*";
P_HTM[3666]="*Cāgavā, bhikkhave, cāgakathāya kacchamānāya nābhisajjati na kuppati na byāpajjati na patitthīyati na kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti.**When a generous person is spoken to about generosity they don’t lose their temper …*";
P_HTM[3667]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3668]="*Tañhi so, bhikkhave, cāgasampadaṃ attani samanupassati, labhati ca tatonidānaṃ pītipāmojjaṃ.**Seeing that generosity in themselves, they get the rapture and joy that generosity brings.*";
P_HTM[3669]="*Tasmā cāgavato cāgakathā sukathā.**That’s why it’s appropriate to talk to a generous person about generosity.*";
P_HTM[3670]="*Kasmā ca, bhikkhave, paññavato paññākathā sukathā?**And why is it appropriate to talk to a wise person about wisdom?*";
P_HTM[3671]="*Paññavā, bhikkhave, paññākathāya kacchamānāya nābhisajjati na kuppati na byāpajjati na patitthīyati na kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti.**When a wise person is spoken to about wisdom they don’t lose their temper, they don’t get annoyed, hostile, and hard-hearted, or display annoyance, hate, and bitterness.*";
P_HTM[3672]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3673]="*Tañhi so, bhikkhave, paññāsampadaṃ attani samanupassati labhati ca tatonidānaṃ pītipāmojjaṃ.**Seeing that wisdom in themselves, they get the rapture and joy that wisdom brings.*";
P_HTM[3674]="*Tasmā paññavato paññākathā sukathā.**That’s why it’s appropriate to talk to a wise person about wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3675]="*Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ puggalānaṃ kathā sukathā puggale puggalaṃ upanidhāyā”ti.**These are topics that are appropriate to talk about, taking into consideration which specific one of five people you are talking to.”*";
P_HTM[3676]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3677]="*8. Sārajjasuttaṃ**Timidity*";
P_HTM[3678]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu sārajjaṃ okkanto hoti.**“Mendicants, a mendicant with five qualities is overcome by timidity.*";
P_HTM[3679]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3680]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu assaddho hoti, dussīlo hoti, appassuto hoti, kusīto hoti, duppañño hoti.**It’s when a mendicant is faithless, unethical, with little learning, lazy, and witless.*";
P_HTM[3681]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu sārajjaṃ okkanto hoti.**A mendicant with these five qualities is overcome by timidity.*";
P_HTM[3682]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu visārado hoti.**A mendicant with five qualities is self-assured.*";
P_HTM[3683]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3684]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saddho hoti, sīlavā hoti, bahussuto hoti, āraddhavīriyo hoti, paññavā hoti.**It’s when a mendicant is faithful, ethical, learned, energetic, and wise.*";
P_HTM[3685]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu visārado hotī”ti.**A mendicant with these five qualities is self-assured.”*";
P_HTM[3686]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3687]="*9. Udāyīsuttaṃ**With Udāyī*";
P_HTM[3688]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[3689]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[3690]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā udāyī mahatiyā gihiparisāya parivuto dhammaṃ desento nisinno hoti.**Now, at that time Venerable Udāyī was sitting teaching Dhamma, surrounded by a large assembly of laypeople.*";
P_HTM[3691]="*Addasā kho āyasmā ānando āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ mahatiyā gihiparisāya parivutaṃ dhammaṃ desentaṃ nisinnaṃ.**Seeing this, Venerable Ānanda*";
P_HTM[3692]="*Disvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[3693]="*“āyasmā, bhante, udāyī mahatiyā gihiparisāya parivuto dhammaṃ desetī”ti.**“Sir, Venerable Udāyī is teaching Dhamma, surrounded by a large assembly of laypeople.”*";
P_HTM[3694]="*“Na kho, ānanda, sukaraṃ paresaṃ dhammaṃ desetuṃ.**“Ānanda, it’s not easy to teach Dhamma to others.*";
P_HTM[3695]="*Paresaṃ, ānanda, dhammaṃ desentena pañca dhamme ajjhattaṃ upaṭṭhāpetvā paresaṃ dhammo desetabbo.**You should establish five things in yourself before teaching Dhamma to others.*";
P_HTM[3696]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3697]="*‘Anupubbiṃ kathaṃ kathessāmī’ti paresaṃ dhammo desetabbo;**You should teach Dhamma to others thinking: ‘I will teach step by step.’ …*";
P_HTM[3698]="*‘pariyāyadassāvī kathaṃ kathessāmī’ti paresaṃ dhammo desetabbo;**‘I will teach explaining my methods.’ …*";
P_HTM[3699]="*‘anuddayataṃ paṭicca kathaṃ kathessāmī’ti paresaṃ dhammo desetabbo;**‘I will teach out of kindness.’ …*";
P_HTM[3700]="*‘na āmisantaro kathaṃ kathessāmī’ti paresaṃ dhammo desetabbo;**‘I will not teach while secretly hoping to profit.’ …*";
P_HTM[3701]="*‘attānañca parañca anupahacca kathaṃ kathessāmī’ti paresaṃ dhammo desetabbo.**‘I will teach without hurting myself or others.’*";
P_HTM[3702]="*Na kho, ānanda, sukaraṃ paresaṃ dhammaṃ desetuṃ.**It’s not easy to teach Dhamma to others.*";
P_HTM[3703]="*Paresaṃ, ānanda, dhammaṃ desentena ime pañca dhamme ajjhattaṃ upaṭṭhāpetvā paresaṃ dhammo desetabbo”ti.**You should establish these five things in yourself before teaching Dhamma to others.”*";
P_HTM[3704]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3705]="*10. Duppaṭivinodayasuttaṃ**Hard to Get Rid Of*";
P_HTM[3706]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, uppannā duppaṭivinodayā.**“Mendicants, these five things are hard to get rid of once they’ve arisen.*";
P_HTM[3707]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3708]="*Uppanno rāgo duppaṭivinodayo, uppanno doso duppaṭivinodayo, uppanno moho duppaṭivinodayo, uppannaṃ paṭibhānaṃ duppaṭivinodayaṃ, uppannaṃ gamikacittaṃ duppaṭivinodayaṃ.**Greed, hate, delusion, the feeling of being inspired to speak out, and thoughts of traveling.*";
P_HTM[3709]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca uppannā duppaṭivinodayā”ti.**These five things are hard to get rid of once they’ve arisen.”*";
P_HTM[3710]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3711]="*Saddhammavaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[3712]="*Tayo sammattaniyāmā,* **";
P_HTM[3713]="*tayo saddhammasammosā;* **";
P_HTM[3714]="*Dukkathā ceva sārajjaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[3715]="*udāyidubbinodayāti.* **";
P_HTM[3716]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**Resentment*";
P_HTM[3717]="*1. Paṭhamaāghātapaṭivinayasuttaṃ**Getting Rid of Resentment (1st)*";
P_HTM[3718]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, āghātapaṭivinayā yattha bhikkhuno uppanno āghāto sabbaso paṭivinetabbo.**“Mendicants, a mendicant should use these five methods to completely get rid of resentment when it has arisen toward anyone.*";
P_HTM[3719]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3720]="*Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, puggale āghāto jāyetha, mettā tasmiṃ puggale bhāvetabbā;**You should develop love for a person you resent.*";
P_HTM[3721]="*evaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo.**That’s how to get rid of resentment for that person.*";
P_HTM[3722]="*Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, puggale āghāto jāyetha, karuṇā tasmiṃ puggale bhāvetabbā;**You should develop compassion for a person you resent. …*";
P_HTM[3723]="*evaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo.* **";
P_HTM[3724]="*Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, puggale āghāto jāyetha, upekkhā tasmiṃ puggale bhāvetabbā;**You should develop equanimity for a person you resent. …*";
P_HTM[3725]="*evaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo.* **";
P_HTM[3726]="*Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, puggale āghāto jāyetha, asatiamanasikāro tasmiṃ puggale āpajjitabbo;**You should disregard a person you resent, paying no attention to them. …*";
P_HTM[3727]="*evaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo.* **";
P_HTM[3728]="*Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, puggale āghāto jāyetha, kammassakatā tasmiṃ puggale adhiṭṭhātabbā:**You should apply the concept that we are the owners of our deeds to that person:*";
P_HTM[3729]="*‘kammassako ayamāyasmā kammadāyādo kammayoni kammabandhu kammapaṭisaraṇo,**‘This venerable is the owner of their deeds and heir to their deeds. Deeds are their womb, their relative, and their refuge.*";
P_HTM[3730]="*yaṃ kammaṃ karissati kalyāṇaṃ vā pāpakaṃ vā tassa dāyādo bhavissatī’ti;**They shall be the heir of whatever deeds they do, whether good or bad.’*";
P_HTM[3731]="*evaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo.**That’s how to get rid of resentment for that person.*";
P_HTM[3732]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca āghātapaṭivinayā, yattha bhikkhuno uppanno āghāto sabbaso paṭivinetabbo”ti.**A mendicant should use these five methods to completely get rid of resentment when it has arisen toward anyone.”*";
P_HTM[3733]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3734]="*2. Dutiyaāghātapaṭivinayasuttaṃ**Getting Rid of Resentment (2nd)*";
P_HTM[3735]="*Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi:**There Venerable Sāriputta addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[3736]="*“āvuso bhikkhave”ti.**“Reverends, mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[3737]="*“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosuṃ.**“Reverend,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[3738]="*Āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca:**Sāriputta said this:*";
P_HTM[3739]="*“Pañcime, āvuso, āghātapaṭivinayā yattha bhikkhuno uppanno āghāto sabbaso paṭivinetabbo.**“Reverends, a mendicant should use these five methods to completely get rid of resentment when it has arisen toward anyone.*";
P_HTM[3740]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3741]="*Idhāvuso, ekacco puggalo aparisuddhakāyasamācāro hoti parisuddhavacīsamācāro;**In the case of a person whose behavior by way of body is impure, but whose behavior by way of speech is pure,*";
P_HTM[3742]="*evarūpepi, āvuso, puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo.**you should get rid of resentment for that kind of person.*";
P_HTM[3743]="*Idha panāvuso, ekacco puggalo aparisuddhavacīsamācāro hoti parisuddhakāyasamācāro;**In the case of a person whose behavior by way of speech is impure, but whose behavior by way of body is pure, …*";
P_HTM[3744]="*evarūpepi, āvuso, puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo.* **";
P_HTM[3745]="*Idha panāvuso, ekacco puggalo aparisuddhakāyasamācāro hoti aparisuddhavacīsamācāro, labhati ca kālena kālaṃ cetaso vivaraṃ cetaso pasādaṃ;**In the case of a person whose behavior by way of body and speech is impure, but who gets an openness and clarity of heart from time to time, …*";
P_HTM[3746]="*evarūpepi, āvuso, puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo.* **";
P_HTM[3747]="*Idha panāvuso, ekacco puggalo aparisuddhakāyasamācāro hoti aparisuddhavacīsamācāro, na ca labhati kālena kālaṃ cetaso vivaraṃ cetaso pasādaṃ;**In the case of a person whose behavior by way of body and speech is impure, and who doesn’t get an openness and clarity of heart from time to time, …*";
P_HTM[3748]="*evarūpepi, āvuso, puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo.* **";
P_HTM[3749]="*Idha panāvuso, ekacco puggalo parisuddhakāyasamācāro parisuddhavacīsamācāro, labhati ca kālena vā kālaṃ cetaso vivaraṃ cetaso pasādaṃ;**In the case of a person whose behavior by way of body and speech is pure, and who gets an openness and clarity of heart from time to time,*";
P_HTM[3750]="*evarūpepi, āvuso, puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo.**you should get rid of resentment for that kind of person.*";
P_HTM[3751]="*Tatrāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo aparisuddhakāyasamācāro parisuddhavacīsamācāro, kathaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo?**How should you get rid of resentment for a person whose behavior by way of body is impure, but whose behavior by way of speech is pure?*";
P_HTM[3752]="*Seyyathāpi, āvuso, bhikkhu paṃsukūliko rathiyāya nantakaṃ disvā vāmena pādena niggaṇhitvā dakkhiṇena pādena pattharitvā, yo tattha sāro taṃ paripātetvā ādāya pakkameyya;**Suppose a mendicant wearing rag robes sees a rag by the side of the road. They’d hold it down with the left foot, spread it out with the right foot, tear out what was intact, and take it away with them.*";
P_HTM[3753]="*evamevaṃ khvāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo aparisuddhakāyasamācāro parisuddhavacīsamācāro, yāssa aparisuddhakāyasamācāratā na sāssa tasmiṃ samaye manasi kātabbā, yā ca khvassa parisuddhavacīsamācāratā sāssa tasmiṃ samaye manasi kātabbā.**In the same way, at that time you should ignore that person’s impure behavior by way of body and focus on their pure behavior by way of speech.*";
P_HTM[3754]="*Evaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo. (1)**That’s how to get rid of resentment for that person.*";
P_HTM[3755]="*Tatrāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo aparisuddhavacīsamācāro parisuddhakāyasamācāro, kathaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo?**How should you get rid of resentment for a person whose behavior by way of speech is impure, but whose behavior by way of body is pure?*";
P_HTM[3756]="*Seyyathāpi, āvuso, pokkharaṇī sevālapaṇakapariyonaddhā.**Suppose there was a lotus pond covered with moss and aquatic plants.*";
P_HTM[3757]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya ghammābhitatto ghammapareto kilanto tasito pipāsito.**Then along comes a person struggling in the oppressive heat, weary, thirsty, and parched.*";
P_HTM[3758]="*So taṃ pokkharaṇiṃ ogāhetvā ubhohi hatthehi iticiti ca sevālapaṇakaṃ apaviyūhitvā añjalinā pivitvā pakkameyya.**They’d plunge into the lotus pond, sweep apart the moss and aquatic plants, drink from their cupped hands, and be on their way.*";
P_HTM[3759]="*Evamevaṃ kho, āvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo aparisuddhavacīsamācāro parisuddhakāyasamācāro, yāssa aparisuddhavacīsamācāratā na sāssa tasmiṃ samaye manasi kātabbā, yā ca khvassa parisuddhakāyasamācāratā sāssa tasmiṃ samaye manasi kātabbā.**In the same way, at that time you should ignore that person’s impure behavior by way of speech and focus on their pure behavior by way of body.*";
P_HTM[3760]="*Evaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo. (2)**That’s how to get rid of resentment for that person.*";
P_HTM[3761]="*Tatrāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo aparisuddhakāyasamācāro aparisuddhavacīsamācāro labhati ca kālena kālaṃ cetaso vivaraṃ cetaso pasādaṃ, kathaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo?**How should you get rid of resentment for a person whose behavior by way of body and speech is impure, but who gets an openness and clarity of heart from time to time?*";
P_HTM[3762]="*Seyyathāpi, āvuso, parittaṃ gopade udakaṃ.**Suppose there was a little water in a cow’s hoofprint.*";
P_HTM[3763]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya ghammābhitatto ghammapareto kilanto tasito pipāsito.**Then along comes a person struggling in the oppressive heat, weary, thirsty, and parched.*";
P_HTM[3764]="*Tassa evamassa:**They might think:*";
P_HTM[3765]="*‘idaṃ kho parittaṃ gopade udakaṃ.**‘This little bit of water is in a cow’s hoofprint.*";
P_HTM[3766]="*Sacāhaṃ añjalinā vā pivissāmi bhājanena vā khobhessāmipi taṃ loḷessāmipi taṃ apeyyampi taṃ karissāmi.**If I drink it with my cupped hands or a bowl, I’ll stir it and disturb it, making it undrinkable.*";
P_HTM[3767]="*Yannūnāhaṃ catukkuṇḍiko nipatitvā gopītakaṃ pivitvā pakkameyyan’ti.**Why don’t I get down on all fours and drink it up like a cow, then be on my way?’*";
P_HTM[3768]="*So catukkuṇḍiko nipatitvā gopītakaṃ pivitvā pakkameyya.**So that’s what they do.*";
P_HTM[3769]="*Evamevaṃ kho, āvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo aparisuddhakāyasamācāro aparisuddhavacīsamācāro labhati ca kālena kālaṃ cetaso vivaraṃ cetaso pasādaṃ, yāssa aparisuddhakāyasamācāratā na sāssa tasmiṃ samaye manasi kātabbā;**In the same way, at that time you should ignore that person’s impure behavior by way of speech and body,*";
P_HTM[3770]="*yāpissa aparisuddhavacīsamācāratā na sāpissa tasmiṃ samaye manasi kātabbā.* **";
P_HTM[3771]="*Yañca kho so labhati kālena kālaṃ cetaso vivaraṃ cetaso pasādaṃ, tamevassa tasmiṃ samaye manasi kātabbaṃ.**and focus on the fact that they get an openness and clarity of heart from time to time.*";
P_HTM[3772]="*Evaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo. (3)**That’s how to get rid of resentment for that person.*";
P_HTM[3773]="*Tatrāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo aparisuddhakāyasamācāro aparisuddhavacīsamācāro na ca labhati kālena kālaṃ cetaso vivaraṃ cetaso pasādaṃ, kathaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo?**How should you get rid of resentment for a person whose behavior by way of body and speech is impure, and who doesn’t get an openness and clarity of heart from time to time?*";
P_HTM[3774]="*Seyyathāpi, āvuso, puriso ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno addhānamaggappaṭipanno.**Suppose a person was traveling along a road, and they were sick, suffering, gravely ill.*";
P_HTM[3775]="*Tassa puratopissa dūre gāmo pacchatopissa dūre gāmo.**And it was a long way to a village, whether ahead or behind.*";
P_HTM[3776]="*So na labheyya sappāyāni bhojanāni, na labheyya sappāyāni bhesajjāni, na labheyya patirūpaṃ upaṭṭhākaṃ, na labheyya gāmantanāyakaṃ.**And they didn’t have any suitable food or medicine, or a competent carer, or someone to bring them to the neighborhood of a village.*";
P_HTM[3777]="*Tamenaṃ aññataro puriso passeyya addhānamaggappaṭipanno.**Then another person traveling along the road sees them,*";
P_HTM[3778]="*So tasmiṃ purise kāruññaṃyeva upaṭṭhāpeyya, anuddayaṃyeva upaṭṭhāpeyya, anukampaṃyeva upaṭṭhāpeyya:**and thinks of them with nothing but compassion, kindness, and sympathy:*";
P_HTM[3779]="*‘aho vatāyaṃ puriso labheyya sappāyāni bhojanāni, labheyya sappāyāni bhesajjāni, labheyya patirūpaṃ upaṭṭhākaṃ, labheyya gāmantanāyakaṃ.**‘Oh, may this person get suitable food or medicine, or a competent carer, or someone to bring them to the neighborhood of a village.*";
P_HTM[3780]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3781]="*Māyaṃ puriso idheva anayabyasanaṃ āpajjī’ti.**So that they don’t come to ruin right here.’*";
P_HTM[3782]="*Evamevaṃ kho, āvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo aparisuddhakāyasamācāro aparisuddhavacīsamācāro na ca labhati kālena kālaṃ cetaso vivaraṃ cetaso pasādaṃ, evarūpepi, āvuso, puggale kāruññaṃyeva upaṭṭhāpetabbaṃ anuddayāyeva upaṭṭhāpetabbā anukampāyeva upaṭṭhāpetabbā:**In the same way, at that time you should ignore that person’s impure behavior by way of speech and body, and the fact that they don’t get an openness and clarity of heart from time to time, and think of them with nothing but compassion, kindness, and sympathy:*";
P_HTM[3783]="*‘aho vata ayamāyasmā kāyaduccaritaṃ pahāya kāyasucaritaṃ bhāveyya, vacīduccaritaṃ pahāya vacīsucaritaṃ bhāveyya, manoduccaritaṃ pahāya manosucaritaṃ bhāveyya.**‘Oh, may this person give up bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and develop good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[3784]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3785]="*Māyaṃ āyasmā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjī’ti.**So that, when their body breaks up, after death, they’re not reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.’*";
P_HTM[3786]="*Evaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo. (4)**That’s how to get rid of resentment for that person.*";
P_HTM[3787]="*Tatrāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo parisuddhakāyasamācāro parisuddhavacīsamācāro labhati ca kālena kālaṃ cetaso vivaraṃ cetaso pasādaṃ, kathaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo?**How should you get rid of resentment for a person whose behavior by way of body and speech is pure, and who gets an openness and clarity of heart from time to time?*";
P_HTM[3788]="*Seyyathāpi, āvuso, pokkharaṇī acchodakā sātodakā sītodakā setakā supatitthā ramaṇīyā nānārukkhehi sañchannā.**Suppose there was a lotus pond with clear, sweet, cool water, clean, with smooth banks, delightful, and shaded by many trees.*";
P_HTM[3789]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya ghammābhitatto ghammapareto kilanto tasito pipāsito.**Then along comes a person struggling in the oppressive heat, weary, thirsty, and parched.*";
P_HTM[3790]="*So taṃ pokkharaṇiṃ ogāhetvā nhātvā ca pivitvā ca paccuttaritvā tattheva rukkhacchāyāya nisīdeyya vā nipajjeyya vā.**They’d plunge into the lotus pond to bathe and drink. And after emerging they’d sit or lie down right there in the shade of the trees.*";
P_HTM[3791]="*Evamevaṃ kho, āvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo parisuddhakāyasamācāro parisuddhavacīsamācāro labhati ca kālena kālaṃ cetaso vivaraṃ cetaso pasādaṃ, yāpissa parisuddhakāyasamācāratā sāpissa tasmiṃ samaye manasi kātabbā;**In the same way, at that time you should focus on that person’s pure behavior by way of body and speech, and on the fact that they get an openness and clarity of heart from time to time.*";
P_HTM[3792]="*yāpissa parisuddhavacīsamācāratā sāpissa tasmiṃ samaye manasi kātabbā;* **";
P_HTM[3793]="*yampi labhati kālena kālaṃ cetaso vivaraṃ cetaso pasādaṃ, tampissa tasmiṃ samaye manasi kātabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3794]="*Evaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo.**That’s how to get rid of resentment for that person.*";
P_HTM[3795]="*Samantapāsādikaṃ, āvuso, puggalaṃ āgamma cittaṃ pasīdati. (5)**Relying on a person who is impressive all around, the mind becomes confident.*";
P_HTM[3796]="*Ime kho, āvuso, pañca āghātapaṭivinayā, yattha bhikkhuno uppanno āghāto sabbaso paṭivinetabbo”ti.**A mendicant should use these five methods to completely get rid of resentment when it has arisen toward anyone.”*";
P_HTM[3797]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3798]="*3. Sākacchasuttaṃ**Discussions*";
P_HTM[3799]="*Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi:**There Venerable Sāriputta addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[3800]="*“āvuso bhikkhave”ti.**“Reverends, mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[3801]="*“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosuṃ.**“Reverend,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[3802]="*Āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca:**Sāriputta said this:*";
P_HTM[3803]="*“Pañcahāvuso, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ sākaccho sabrahmacārīnaṃ.**“A mendicant with five qualities is fit to hold a discussion with their spiritual companions.*";
P_HTM[3804]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3805]="*Idhāvuso, bhikkhu attanā ca sīlasampanno hoti, sīlasampadākathāya ca āgataṃ pañhaṃ byākattā hoti;**A mendicant is personally accomplished in ethics, and answers questions that come up when discussing accomplishment in ethics.*";
P_HTM[3806]="*attanā ca samādhisampanno hoti, samādhisampadākathāya ca āgataṃ pañhaṃ byākattā hoti;**They’re personally accomplished in immersion, …*";
P_HTM[3807]="*attanā ca paññāsampanno hoti, paññāsampadākathāya ca āgataṃ pañhaṃ byākattā hoti;**They’re personally accomplished in wisdom, …*";
P_HTM[3808]="*attanā ca vimuttisampanno hoti, vimuttisampadākathāya ca āgataṃ pañhaṃ byākattā hoti;**They’re personally accomplished in freedom, …*";
P_HTM[3809]="*attanā ca vimuttiñāṇadassanasampanno hoti, vimuttiñāṇadassanasampadākathāya ca āgataṃ pañhaṃ byākattā hoti.**They’re personally accomplished in the knowledge and vision of freedom, and they answer questions that come up when discussing accomplishment in the knowledge and vision of freedom.*";
P_HTM[3810]="*Imehi kho, āvuso, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ sākaccho sabrahmacārīnan”ti.**A mendicant with these five qualities is fit to hold a discussion with their spiritual companions.”*";
P_HTM[3811]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3812]="*4. Sājīvasuttaṃ**Sharing a Way of Life*";
P_HTM[3813]="*Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi … pe …**There Venerable Sāriputta addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[3814]="*pañcahi, āvuso, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃsājīvo sabrahmacārīnaṃ.**“A mendicant with five qualities is fit to share their life with their spiritual companions.*";
P_HTM[3815]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3816]="*Idhāvuso, bhikkhu attanā ca sīlasampanno hoti, sīlasampadākathāya ca āgataṃ pañhaṃ byākattā hoti;**A mendicant is personally accomplished in ethics, and answers questions that come up when discussing accomplishment in ethics.*";
P_HTM[3817]="*attanā ca samādhisampanno hoti, samādhisampadākathāya ca āgataṃ pañhaṃ byākattā hoti;**They’re personally accomplished in immersion, …*";
P_HTM[3818]="*attanā ca paññāsampanno hoti, paññāsampadākathāya ca āgataṃ pañhaṃ byākattā hoti;**They’re personally accomplished in wisdom, …*";
P_HTM[3819]="*attanā ca vimuttisampanno hoti, vimuttisampadākathāya ca āgataṃ pañhaṃ byākattā hoti;**They’re personally accomplished in freedom, …*";
P_HTM[3820]="*attanā ca vimuttiñāṇadassanasampanno hoti, vimuttiñāṇadassanasampadākathāya ca āgataṃ pañhaṃ byākattā hoti.**They’re personally accomplished in the knowledge and vision of freedom, and they answer questions that come up when discussing accomplishment in the knowledge and vision of freedom.*";
P_HTM[3821]="*Imehi kho, āvuso, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃsājīvo sabrahmacārīnan”ti.**A mendicant with these five qualities is fit to share their life with their spiritual companions.”*";
P_HTM[3822]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3823]="*5. Pañhapucchāsuttaṃ**Asking Questions*";
P_HTM[3824]="*Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi … pe … “yo hi koci, āvuso, paraṃ pañhaṃ pucchati, sabbo so pañcahi ṭhānehi, etesaṃ vā aññatarena.**There Venerable Sāriputta addressed the mendicants: … “Whoever asks a question of another, does so for one or other of these five reasons.*";
P_HTM[3825]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3826]="*Mandattā momūhattā paraṃ pañhaṃ pucchati, pāpiccho icchāpakato paraṃ pañhaṃ pucchati, paribhavaṃ paraṃ pañhaṃ pucchati, aññātukāmo paraṃ pañhaṃ pucchati, atha vā panevaṃcitto paraṃ pañhaṃ pucchati:**Someone asks a question of another from stupidity and folly. Or they ask from wicked desires, being naturally full of desires. Or they ask in order to disparage. Or they ask wanting to understand. Or they ask with the thought,*";
P_HTM[3827]="*‘sace me pañhaṃ puṭṭho sammadeva byākarissati iccetaṃ kusalaṃ, no ce me pañhaṃ puṭṭho sammadeva byākarissati ahamassa sammadeva byākarissāmī’ti.**‘If they correctly answer the question I ask it’s good. If not, I’ll correctly answer it for them.’*";
P_HTM[3828]="*Yo hi koci, āvuso, paraṃ pañhaṃ pucchati, sabbo so imehi pañcahi ṭhānehi, etesaṃ vā aññatarena.**Whoever asks a question of another, does so for one or other of these five reasons.*";
P_HTM[3829]="*Ahaṃ kho panāvuso, evaṃcitto paraṃ pañhaṃ pucchāmi:**As for myself, I ask with the thought,*";
P_HTM[3830]="*‘sace me pañhaṃ puṭṭho sammadeva byākarissati iccetaṃ kusalaṃ, no ce me pañhaṃ puṭṭho sammadeva byākarissati, ahamassa sammadeva byākarissāmī’”ti.**‘If they correctly answer the question I ask it’s good. If not, I’ll correctly answer it for them.’”*";
P_HTM[3831]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3832]="*6. Nirodhasuttaṃ**Cessation*";
P_HTM[3833]="*Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi … pe …**There Venerable Sāriputta addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[3834]="*“idhāvuso, bhikkhu sīlasampanno samādhisampanno paññāsampanno saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—**“Reverends, take a mendicant who is accomplished in ethics, immersion, and wisdom. They might enter into and emerge from the cessation of perception and feeling.*";
P_HTM[3835]="*atthetaṃ ṭhānaṃ.**That is possible.*";
P_HTM[3836]="*No ce diṭṭheva dhamme aññaṃ ārādheyya, atikkammeva kabaḷīkārāhārabhakkhānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ aññataraṃ manomayaṃ kāyaṃ upapanno saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—**If they don’t reach enlightenment in this very life, then, surpassing the company of gods that consume solid food, they’re reborn in a certain host of mind-made gods. There they might enter into and emerge from the cessation of perception and feeling.*";
P_HTM[3837]="*atthetaṃ ṭhānan”ti.**That is possible.”*";
P_HTM[3838]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā udāyī āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Venerable Udāyī said to him,*";
P_HTM[3839]="*“aṭṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, āvuso sāriputta, anavakāso yaṃ so bhikkhu atikkammeva kabaḷīkārāhārabhakkhānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ aññataraṃ manomayaṃ kāyaṃ upapanno saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—**“This is not possible, Reverend Sāriputta, it cannot happen!”*";
P_HTM[3840]="*natthetaṃ ṭhānan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3841]="*Dutiyampi kho … pe … tatiyampi kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi:**But for a second … and a third time Sāriputta repeated his statement.*";
P_HTM[3842]="*“idhāvuso, bhikkhu sīlasampanno samādhisampanno paññāsampanno saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—* **";
P_HTM[3843]="*atthetaṃ ṭhānaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3844]="*No ce diṭṭheva dhamme aññaṃ ārādheyya, atikkammeva kabaḷīkārāhārabhakkhānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ aññataraṃ manomayaṃ kāyaṃ upapanno saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—* **";
P_HTM[3845]="*atthetaṃ ṭhānan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3846]="*Tatiyampi kho āyasmā udāyī āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:**And for a third time, Udāyī said to him,*";
P_HTM[3847]="*“aṭṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, āvuso sāriputta, anavakāso yaṃ so bhikkhu atikkammeva kabaḷīkārāhārabhakkhānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ aññataraṃ manomayaṃ kāyaṃ upapanno saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—**“This is not possible, Reverend Sāriputta, it cannot happen!”*";
P_HTM[3848]="*natthetaṃ ṭhānan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3849]="*Atha kho āyasmato sāriputtassa etadahosi:**Then Venerable Sāriputta thought,*";
P_HTM[3850]="*“yāvatatiyakampi kho me āyasmā udāyī paṭikkosati, na ca me koci bhikkhu anumodati.**“Venerable Udāyī disagrees with me three times, and not one mendicant agrees with me.*";
P_HTM[3851]="*Yannūnāhaṃ yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkameyyan”ti.**Why don’t I go to see the Buddha?”*";
P_HTM[3852]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Then Sāriputta went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side,*";
P_HTM[3853]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi:**and said to the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[3854]="*“idhāvuso, bhikkhu sīlasampanno samādhisampanno paññāsampanno saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—**“Reverends, take a mendicant who is accomplished in ethics, immersion, and wisdom. They might enter into and emerge from the cessation of perception and feeling.*";
P_HTM[3855]="*atthetaṃ ṭhānaṃ.**There is such a possibility.*";
P_HTM[3856]="*No ce diṭṭheva dhamme aññaṃ ārādheyya, atikkammeva kabaḷīkārāhārabhakkhānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ aññataraṃ manomayaṃ kāyaṃ upapanno saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—**If they don’t reach enlightenment in this very life, they’re reborn in the company of a certain host of mind-made gods, who surpass the gods that consume solid food. There they might enter into and emerge from the cessation of perception and feeling.*";
P_HTM[3857]="*atthetaṃ ṭhānan”ti.**That is possible.”*";
P_HTM[3858]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā udāyī āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Udāyī said to him,*";
P_HTM[3859]="*“aṭṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, āvuso sāriputta, anavakāso yaṃ so bhikkhu atikkammeva kabaḷīkārāhārabhakkhānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ aññataraṃ manomayaṃ kāyaṃ upapanno saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—**“This is not possible, Reverend Sāriputta, it cannot happen!”*";
P_HTM[3860]="*natthetaṃ ṭhānan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3861]="*Dutiyampi kho … pe … tatiyampi kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi:**But for a second … and a third time Sāriputta repeated his statement.*";
P_HTM[3862]="*“idhāvuso, bhikkhu sīlasampanno samādhisampanno paññāsampanno saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—* **";
P_HTM[3863]="*atthetaṃ ṭhānaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3864]="*No ce diṭṭheva dhamme aññaṃ ārādheyya, atikkammeva kabaḷīkārāhārabhakkhānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ aññataraṃ manomayaṃ kāyaṃ upapanno saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—* **";
P_HTM[3865]="*atthetaṃ ṭhānan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3866]="*Tatiyampi kho āyasmā udāyī āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:**And for a third time, Udāyī said to him,*";
P_HTM[3867]="*“aṭṭhānaṃ kho etaṃ, āvuso sāriputta, anavakāso yaṃ so bhikkhu atikkammeva kabaḷīkārāhārabhakkhānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ aññataraṃ manomayaṃ kāyaṃ upapanno saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—**“This is not possible, Reverend Sāriputta, it cannot happen!”*";
P_HTM[3868]="*natthetaṃ ṭhānan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3869]="*Atha kho āyasmato sāriputtassa etadahosi:**Then Venerable Sāriputta thought,*";
P_HTM[3870]="*“bhagavatopi kho me sammukhā āyasmā udāyī yāvatatiyakaṃ paṭikkosati, na ca me koci bhikkhu anumodati.**“Even in front of the Buddha Venerable Udāyī disagrees with me three times, and not one mendicant agrees with me.*";
P_HTM[3871]="*Yannūnāhaṃ tuṇhī assan”ti.**I’d better stay silent.”*";
P_HTM[3872]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto tuṇhī ahosi.**Then Sāriputta fell silent.*";
P_HTM[3873]="*Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ āmantesi:**Then the Buddha said to Venerable Udāyī,*";
P_HTM[3874]="*“kaṃ pana tvaṃ, udāyi, manomayaṃ kāyaṃ paccesī”ti?**“But Udāyī, do you believe in a mind-made body?”*";
P_HTM[3875]="*“Ye te, bhante, devā arūpino saññāmayā”ti.**“For those gods, sir, who are formless, made of perception.”*";
P_HTM[3876]="*“Kiṃ nu kho tuyhaṃ, udāyi, bālassa abyattassa bhaṇitena.**“Udāyī, what has an incompetent fool like you got to say?*";
P_HTM[3877]="*Tvampi nāma bhaṇitabbaṃ maññasī”ti.**How on earth could you imagine you’ve got something worth saying!”*";
P_HTM[3878]="*Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:**Then the Buddha said to Venerable Ānanda,*";
P_HTM[3879]="*“atthi nāma, ānanda, theraṃ bhikkhuṃ vihesiyamānaṃ ajjhupekkhissatha.**“Ānanda! There’s a senior mendicant being harassed, and you just watch it happening.*";
P_HTM[3880]="*Na hi nāma, ānanda, kāruññampi bhavissati theramhi bhikkhumhi vihesiyamānamhī”ti.**Don’t you have any compassion for a senior mendicant who is being harassed?”*";
P_HTM[3881]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then the Buddha addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[3882]="*“idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlasampanno samādhisampanno paññāsampanno saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—**“Mendicants, take a mendicant who is accomplished in ethics, immersion, and wisdom. They might enter into and emerge from the cessation of perception and feeling.*";
P_HTM[3883]="*atthetaṃ ṭhānaṃ.**That is possible.*";
P_HTM[3884]="*No ce diṭṭheva dhamme aññaṃ ārādheyya, atikkammeva kabaḷīkārāhārabhakkhānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ aññataraṃ manomayaṃ kāyaṃ upapanno saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjeyyāpi vuṭṭhaheyyāpi—**If they don’t reach enlightenment in this very life, they’re reborn in the company of a certain host of mind-made gods, who surpass the gods that consume solid food. There they might enter into and emerge from the cessation of perception and feeling.*";
P_HTM[3885]="*atthetaṃ ṭhānan”ti.**That is possible.”*";
P_HTM[3886]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[3887]="*Idaṃ vatvāna sugato uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ pāvisi.**When he had spoken, the Holy One got up from his seat and entered his dwelling.*";
P_HTM[3888]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando acirapakkantassa bhagavato yenāyasmā upavāṇo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ upavāṇaṃ etadavoca:**Then, not long after the Buddha had left, Venerable Ānanda went to Venerable Upavāṇa and said to him,*";
P_HTM[3889]="*“idhāvuso upavāṇa, aññe there bhikkhū vihesenti.**“Reverend Upavāṇa, they’ve been harassing other senior mendicants,*";
P_HTM[3890]="*Mayaṃ tena na muccāma.**but I didn’t question them.*";
P_HTM[3891]="*Anacchariyaṃ kho, panetaṃ āvuso upavāṇa, yaṃ bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito etadeva ārabbha udāhareyya yathā āyasmantaṃyevettha upavāṇaṃ paṭibhāseyya.**I wouldn’t be surprised if the Buddha makes a statement about this when he comes out of retreat later this afternoon. He might even call upon Venerable Upavāṇa himself.*";
P_HTM[3892]="*Idāneva amhākaṃ sārajjaṃ okkantan”ti.**And right now I feel timid.”*";
P_HTM[3893]="*Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena upaṭṭhānasālā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. Nisajja kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ upavāṇaṃ etadavoca:**Then in the late afternoon, the Buddha came out of retreat and went to the assembly hall, where he sat on the seat spread out, and said to Upavāṇa,*";
P_HTM[3894]="*“Katihi nu kho, upavāṇa, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo cā”ti?**“Upavāṇa, how many qualities should a senior mendicant have to be dear and beloved to their spiritual companions, respected and admired?”*";
P_HTM[3895]="*“Pañcahi, bhante, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo ca.**“Sir, a senior mendicant with five qualities is dear and beloved to their spiritual companions, respected and admired.*";
P_HTM[3896]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3897]="*Idha, bhante, thero bhikkhu sīlavā hoti … pe … samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu;**It’s when a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the code of conduct, with good behavior and supporters. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken.*";
P_HTM[3898]="*bahussuto hoti … pe … diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā;**They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s totally full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering them, reciting them, mentally scrutinizing them, and understanding them with right view.*";
P_HTM[3899]="*kalyāṇavāco hoti kalyāṇavākkaraṇo poriyā vācāya samannāgato vissaṭṭhāya anelagalāya atthassa viññāpaniyā;**They’re a good speaker, with a polished, clear, and articulate voice that expresses the meaning.*";
P_HTM[3900]="*catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī;**They get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that belong to the higher mind—when they want, without trouble or difficulty.*";
P_HTM[3901]="*āsavānaṃ khayā … pe … sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati.**They realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[3902]="*Imehi kho, bhante, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo cā”ti.**A senior mendicant with these five qualities is dear and beloved to their spiritual companions, respected and admired.”*";
P_HTM[3903]="*“Sādhu sādhu, upavāṇa.**“Good, good, Upavāṇa!*";
P_HTM[3904]="*Imehi kho, upavāṇa, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo ca.**A senior mendicant with these five qualities is dear and beloved to their spiritual companions, respected and admired.*";
P_HTM[3905]="*Ime ce, upavāṇa, pañca dhammā therassa bhikkhuno na saṃvijjeyyuṃ, taṃ sabrahmacārī na sakkareyyuṃ na garuṃ kareyyuṃ na māneyyuṃ na pūjeyyuṃ khaṇḍiccena pāliccena valittacatāya.**If these five qualities are not found in a senior mendicant, why would their spiritual companions honor, respect, revere, or venerate them? Because of their broken teeth, gray hair, and wrinkled skin?*";
P_HTM[3906]="*Yasmā ca kho, upavāṇa, ime pañca dhammā therassa bhikkhuno saṃvijjanti, tasmā taṃ sabrahmacārī sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjentī”ti.**But since these five qualities are found in a senior mendicant, their spiritual companions honor, respect, revere, or venerate them.”*";
P_HTM[3907]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3908]="*7. Codanāsuttaṃ**Accusation*";
P_HTM[3909]="*Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi:**There Sāriputta addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[3910]="*“codakena, āvuso, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena pañca dhamme ajjhattaṃ upaṭṭhāpetvā paro codetabbo.**“Reverends, a mendicant who wants to accuse another should first establish five things in themselves.*";
P_HTM[3911]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[3912]="*Kālena vakkhāmi, no akālena;**I will speak at the right time, not at the wrong time.*";
P_HTM[3913]="*bhūtena vakkhāmi, no abhūtena;**I will speak truthfully, not falsely.*";
P_HTM[3914]="*saṇhena vakkhāmi, no pharusena;**I will speak gently, not harshly.*";
P_HTM[3915]="*atthasaṃhitena vakkhāmi, no anatthasaṃhitena;**I will speak beneficially, not harmfully.*";
P_HTM[3916]="*mettacitto vakkhāmi, no dosantaro.**I will speak lovingly, not from secret hate.*";
P_HTM[3917]="*Codakena, āvuso, bhikkhunā paraṃ codetukāmena ime pañca dhamme ajjhattaṃ upaṭṭhāpetvā paro codetabbo.**A mendicant who wants to accuse another should first establish these five things in themselves.*";
P_HTM[3918]="*Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ passāmi akālena codiyamānaṃ no kālena kupitaṃ, abhūtena codiyamānaṃ no bhūtena kupitaṃ, pharusena codiyamānaṃ no saṇhena kupitaṃ, anatthasaṃhitena codiyamānaṃ no atthasaṃhitena kupitaṃ, dosantarena codiyamānaṃ no mettacittena kupitaṃ.**Take a case where I see a certain person being accused at the wrong time, not being disturbed at the right time. They’re accused falsely, not disturbed truthfully. They’re accused harshly, not disturbed gently. They’re accused harmfully, not disturbed beneficially. They’re accused with secret hate, not disturbed lovingly.*";
P_HTM[3919]="*Adhammacuditassa, āvuso, bhikkhuno pañcahākārehi avippaṭisāro upadahātabbo:**The mendicant who is accused improperly should be reassured in five ways.*";
P_HTM[3920]="*‘akālenāyasmā cudito no kālena, alaṃ te avippaṭisārāya;**‘Venerable, you were accused at the wrong time, not at the right time. There’s no need for you to feel remorse.*";
P_HTM[3921]="*abhūtenāyasmā cudito no bhūtena, alaṃ te avippaṭisārāya;**You were accused falsely, not truthfully. …*";
P_HTM[3922]="*pharusenāyasmā cudito no saṇhena, alaṃ te avippaṭisārāya;**You were accused harshly, not gently. …*";
P_HTM[3923]="*anatthasaṃhitenāyasmā cudito no atthasaṃhitena, alaṃ te avippaṭisārāya;**You were accused harmfully, not beneficially. …*";
P_HTM[3924]="*dosantarenāyasmā cudito no mettacittena, alaṃ te avippaṭisārāyā’ti.**You were accused with secret hate, not lovingly. There’s no need for you to feel remorse.’*";
P_HTM[3925]="*Adhammacuditassa, āvuso, bhikkhuno imehi pañcahākārehi avippaṭisāro upadahātabbo.**A mendicant who is accused improperly should be reassured in these five ways.*";
P_HTM[3926]="*Adhammacodakassa, āvuso, bhikkhuno pañcahākārehi vippaṭisāro upadahātabbo:**The mendicant who makes improper accusations should be chastened in five ways.*";
P_HTM[3927]="*‘akālena te, āvuso, codito no kālena, alaṃ te vippaṭisārāya;**‘Reverend, you made an accusation at the wrong time, not at the right time. There’s a reason for you to feel remorse.*";
P_HTM[3928]="*abhūtena te, āvuso, codito no bhūtena, alaṃ te vippaṭisārāya;**You made an accusation falsely, not truthfully. …*";
P_HTM[3929]="*pharusena te, āvuso, codito no saṇhena, alaṃ te vippaṭisārāya;**You made an accusation harshly, not gently. …*";
P_HTM[3930]="*anatthasaṃhitena te, āvuso, codito no atthasaṃhitena, alaṃ te vippaṭisārāya;**You made an accusation harmfully, not beneficially. …*";
P_HTM[3931]="*dosantarena te, āvuso, codito no mettacittena, alaṃ te vippaṭisārāyā’ti.**You made an accusation with secret hate, not lovingly. There’s a reason for you to feel remorse.’*";
P_HTM[3932]="*Adhammacodakassa, āvuso, bhikkhuno imehi pañcahākārehi vippaṭisāro upadahātabbo.**The mendicant who makes improper accusations should be chastened in these five ways.*";
P_HTM[3933]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3934]="*Yathā na aññopi bhikkhu abhūtena codetabbaṃ maññeyyāti.**So that another mendicant wouldn’t think to make a false accusation.*";
P_HTM[3935]="*Idha panāhaṃ, āvuso, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ passāmi kālena codiyamānaṃ no akālena kupitaṃ, bhūtena codiyamānaṃ no abhūtena kupitaṃ, saṇhena codiyamānaṃ no pharusena kupitaṃ, atthasaṃhitena codiyamānaṃ no anatthasaṃhitena kupitaṃ, mettacittena codiyamānaṃ no dosantarena kupitaṃ.**Take a case where I see a certain person being accused at the right time, not being disturbed at the wrong time. They’re accused truthfully, not disturbed falsely. They’re accused gently, not disturbed harshly. They’re accused beneficially, not disturbed harmfully. They’re accused lovingly, not disturbed with secret hate.*";
P_HTM[3936]="*Dhammacuditassa, āvuso, bhikkhuno pañcahākārehi vippaṭisāro upadahātabbo:**The mendicant who is accused properly should be chastened in five ways.*";
P_HTM[3937]="*‘kālenāyasmā cudito no akālena, alaṃ te vippaṭisārāya;**‘Venerable, you were accused at the right time, not at the wrong time. There’s a reason for you to feel remorse.*";
P_HTM[3938]="*bhūtenāyasmā cudito no abhūtena, alaṃ te vippaṭisārāya;**You were accused truthfully, not falsely. …*";
P_HTM[3939]="*saṇhenāyasmā cudito no pharusena, alaṃ te vippaṭisārāya;**You were accused gently, not harshly. …*";
P_HTM[3940]="*atthasaṃhitenāyasmā cudito no anatthasaṃhitena, alaṃ te vippaṭisārāya;**You were accused beneficially, not harmfully. …*";
P_HTM[3941]="*mettacittenāyasmā cudito no dosantarena, alaṃ te vippaṭisārāyā’ti.**You were accused lovingly, not with secret hate. There’s a reason for you to feel remorse.’*";
P_HTM[3942]="*Dhammacuditassa, āvuso, bhikkhuno imehi pañcahākārehi vippaṭisāro upadahātabbo.**The mendicant who is accused properly should be chastened in these five ways.*";
P_HTM[3943]="*Dhammacodakassa, āvuso, bhikkhuno pañcahākārehi avippaṭisāro upadahātabbo:**The mendicant who makes proper accusations should be reassured in five ways.*";
P_HTM[3944]="*‘kālena te, āvuso, codito no akālena, alaṃ te avippaṭisārāya;**‘Reverend, you made an accusation at the right time, not at the wrong time. There’s no need for you to feel remorse.*";
P_HTM[3945]="*bhūtena te, āvuso, codito no abhūtena, alaṃ te avippaṭisārāya;**You made an accusation truthfully, not falsely. …*";
P_HTM[3946]="*saṇhena te, āvuso, codito no pharusena, alaṃ te avippaṭisārāya;**You made an accusation gently, not harshly. …*";
P_HTM[3947]="*atthasaṃhitena te, āvuso, codito no anatthasaṃhitena, alaṃ te avippaṭisārāya;**You made an accusation beneficially, not harmfully. …*";
P_HTM[3948]="*mettacittena te, āvuso, codito no dosantarena, alaṃ te avippaṭisārāyā’ti.**You made an accusation lovingly, not with secret hate. There’s no need for you to feel remorse.’*";
P_HTM[3949]="*Dhammacodakassa, āvuso, bhikkhuno imehi pañcahākārehi avippaṭisāro upadahātabbo.**The mendicant who makes proper accusations should be reassured in these five ways.*";
P_HTM[3950]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3951]="*Yathā aññopi bhikkhu bhūtena coditabbaṃ maññeyyāti.**So that another mendicant would think to make a true accusation.*";
P_HTM[3952]="*Cuditena, āvuso, puggalena dvīsu dhammesu patiṭṭhātabbaṃ—**A person who is accused should ground themselves in two things:*";
P_HTM[3953]="*sacce ca, akuppe ca.**truth and an even temper.*";
P_HTM[3954]="*Mañcepi, āvuso, pare codeyyuṃ kālena vā akālena vā bhūtena vā abhūtena vā saṇhena vā pharusena vā atthasaṃhitena vā anatthasaṃhitena vā mettacittā vā dosantarā vā, ahampi dvīsuyeva dhammesu patiṭṭhaheyyaṃ—**Even if others accuse me—at the right time or the wrong time, truthfully or falsely, gently or harshly, lovingly or with secret hate—I will still ground myself in two things:*";
P_HTM[3955]="*sacce ca, akuppe ca.**truth and an even temper.*";
P_HTM[3956]="*Sace jāneyyaṃ:**If I know that*";
P_HTM[3957]="*‘attheso mayi dhammo’ti, ‘atthī’ti naṃ vadeyyaṃ:**that quality is found in me, I will tell them that it is.*";
P_HTM[3958]="*‘saṃvijjateso mayi dhammo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3959]="*Sace jāneyyaṃ:**If I know that*";
P_HTM[3960]="*‘nattheso mayi dhammo’ti, ‘natthī’ti naṃ vadeyyaṃ:**that quality is not found in me, I will tell them that it is not.”*";
P_HTM[3961]="*‘neso dhammo mayi saṃvijjatī’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3962]="*“Evampi kho te, sāriputta, vuccamānā atha ca panidhekacce moghapurisā na padakkhiṇaṃ gaṇhantī”ti.**“Even when you speak like this, Sāriputta, there are still some foolish people here who do not respectfully take it up.”*";
P_HTM[3963]="*“Ye te, bhante, puggalā assaddhā jīvikatthā na saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā saṭhā māyāvino ketabino uddhatā unnaḷā capalā mukharā vikiṇṇavācā indriyesu aguttadvārā bhojane amattaññuno jāgariyaṃ ananuyuttā sāmaññe anapekkhavanto sikkhāya na tibbagāravā bāhulikā sāthalikā okkamane pubbaṅgamā paviveke nikkhittadhurā kusītā hīnavīriyā muṭṭhassatino asampajānā asamāhitā vibbhantacittā duppaññā eḷamūgā, te mayā evaṃ vuccamānā na padakkhiṇaṃ gaṇhanti.**“Sir, there are those faithless people who went forth from the lay life to homelessness not out of faith but to earn a livelihood. They’re devious, deceitful, and sneaky. They’re restless, insolent, fickle, gossipy, and loose-tongued. They do not guard their sense doors or eat in moderation, and they are not dedicated to wakefulness. They don’t care about the ascetic life, and don’t keenly respect the training. They’re indulgent and slack, leaders in backsliding, neglecting seclusion, lazy, and lacking energy. They’re unmindful, lacking situational awareness and immersion, with straying minds, witless and stupid. When I speak to them like this, they don’t respectfully take it up.*";
P_HTM[3964]="*Ye pana te, bhante, kulaputtā saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā asaṭhā amāyāvino aketabino anuddhatā anunnaḷā acapalā amukharā avikiṇṇavācā indriyesu guttadvārā bhojane mattaññuno jāgariyaṃ anuyuttā sāmaññe apekkhavanto sikkhāya tibbagāravā na bāhulikā na sāthalikā okkamane nikkhittadhurā paviveke pubbaṅgamā āraddhavīriyā pahitattā upaṭṭhitassatino sampajānā samāhitā ekaggacittā paññavanto aneḷamūgā, te mayā evaṃ vuccamānā padakkhiṇaṃ gaṇhantī”ti.**Sir, there are those gentlemen who went forth from the lay life to homelessness out of faith. They’re not devious, deceitful, and sneaky. They’re not restless, insolent, fickle, gossipy, and loose-tongued. They guard their sense doors and eat in moderation, and they are dedicated to wakefulness. They care about the ascetic life, and keenly respect the training. They’re not indulgent or slack, nor are they leaders in backsliding, neglecting seclusion. They’re energetic and determined. They’re mindful, with situational awareness, immersion, and unified minds; wise, not stupid. When I speak to them like this, they do respectfully take it up.”*";
P_HTM[3965]="*“Ye te, sāriputta, puggalā assaddhā jīvikatthā na saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā saṭhā māyāvino ketabino uddhatā unnaḷā capalā mukharā vikiṇṇavācā indriyesu aguttadvārā bhojane amattaññuno jāgariyaṃ ananuyuttā sāmaññe anapekkhavanto sikkhāya na tibbagāravā bāhulikā sāthalikā okkamane pubbaṅgamā paviveke nikkhittadhurā kusītā hīnavīriyā muṭṭhassatino asampajānā asamāhitā vibbhantacittā duppaññā eḷamūgā, tiṭṭhantu te.**“Sāriputta, those faithless people who went forth from the lay life to homelessness not out of faith but to earn a livelihood … Leave them be.*";
P_HTM[3966]="*Ye pana te, sāriputta, kulaputtā saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā asaṭhā amāyāvino aketabino anuddhatā anunnaḷā acapalā amukharā avikiṇṇavācā indriyesu guttadvārā bhojane mattaññuno jāgariyaṃ anuyuttā sāmaññe apekkhavanto sikkhāya tibbagāravā na bāhulikā na sāthalikā okkamane nikkhittadhurā paviveke pubbaṅgamā āraddhavīriyā pahitattā upaṭṭhitassatino sampajānā samāhitā ekaggacittā paññavanto aneḷamūgā, te tvaṃ, sāriputta, vadeyyāsi.**But those gentlemen who went forth from the lay life to homelessness out of faith … You should speak to them.*";
P_HTM[3967]="*Ovada, sāriputta, sabrahmacārī;**Sāriputta, you should advise your spiritual companions!*";
P_HTM[3968]="*anusāsa, sāriputta, sabrahmacārī:**You should instruct your spiritual companions!*";
P_HTM[3969]="*‘asaddhammā vuṭṭhāpetvā saddhamme patiṭṭhāpessāmi sabrahmacārī’ti.**Thinking: ‘I will draw my spiritual companions away from false teachings and ground them in true teachings.’*";
P_HTM[3970]="*Evañhi te, sāriputta, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[3971]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3972]="*8. Sīlasuttaṃ**Ethics*";
P_HTM[3973]="*Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi:**There Venerable Sāriputta addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[3974]="*“dussīlassa, āvuso, sīlavipannassa hatūpaniso hoti sammāsamādhi;**“Reverends, an unethical person, who lacks ethics, has destroyed a vital condition for right immersion.*";
P_HTM[3975]="*sammāsamādhimhi asati sammāsamādhivipannassa hatūpanisaṃ hoti yathābhūtañāṇadassanaṃ;**When there is no right immersion, one who lacks right immersion has destroyed a vital condition for true knowledge and vision.*";
P_HTM[3976]="*yathābhūtañāṇadassane asati yathābhūtañāṇadassanavipannassa hatūpaniso hoti nibbidāvirāgo;**When there is no true knowledge and vision, one who lacks true knowledge and vision has destroyed a vital condition for disillusionment and dispassion.*";
P_HTM[3977]="*nibbidāvirāge asati nibbidāvirāgavipannassa hatūpanisaṃ hoti vimuttiñāṇadassanaṃ.**When there is no disillusionment and dispassion, one who lacks disillusionment and dispassion has destroyed a vital condition for knowledge and vision of freedom.*";
P_HTM[3978]="*Seyyathāpi, āvuso, rukkho sākhāpalāsavipanno.**Suppose there was a tree that lacked branches and foliage.*";
P_HTM[3979]="*Tassa papaṭikāpi na pāripūriṃ gacchati, tacopi pheggupi sāropi na pāripūriṃ gacchati.**Its shoots, bark, softwood, and heartwood would not grow to fullness.*";
P_HTM[3980]="*Evamevaṃ kho, āvuso, dussīlassa sīlavipannassa hatūpaniso hoti sammāsamādhi;**In the same way, an unethical person, who lacks ethics, has destroyed a vital condition for right immersion.*";
P_HTM[3981]="*sammāsamādhimhi asati sammāsamādhivipannassa hatūpanisaṃ hoti yathābhūtañāṇadassanaṃ;**When there is no right immersion, one who lacks right immersion has destroyed a vital condition for true knowledge and vision.*";
P_HTM[3982]="*yathābhūtañāṇadassane asati yathābhūtañāṇadassanavipannassa hatūpaniso hoti nibbidāvirāgo;**When there is no true knowledge and vision, one who lacks true knowledge and vision has destroyed a vital condition for disillusionment and dispassion.*";
P_HTM[3983]="*nibbidāvirāge asati nibbidāvirāgavipannassa hatūpanisaṃ hoti vimuttiñāṇadassanaṃ.**When there is no disillusionment and dispassion, one who lacks disillusionment and dispassion has destroyed a vital condition for knowledge and vision of freedom.*";
P_HTM[3984]="*Sīlavato, āvuso, sīlasampannassa upanisasampanno hoti sammāsamādhi;**An ethical person, who has fulfilled ethics, has fulfilled a vital condition for right immersion.*";
P_HTM[3985]="*sammāsamādhimhi sati sammāsamādhisampannassa upanisasampannaṃ hoti yathābhūtañāṇadassanaṃ;**When there is right immersion, one who has fulfilled right immersion has fulfilled a vital condition for true knowledge and vision.*";
P_HTM[3986]="*yathābhūtañāṇadassane sati yathābhūtañāṇadassanasampannassa upanisasampanno hoti nibbidāvirāgo;**When there is true knowledge and vision, one who has fulfilled true knowledge and vision has fulfilled a vital condition for disillusionment and dispassion.*";
P_HTM[3987]="*nibbidāvirāge sati nibbidāvirāgasampannassa upanisasampannaṃ hoti vimuttiñāṇadassanaṃ.**When there is disillusionment and dispassion, one who has fulfilled disillusionment and dispassion has fulfilled a vital condition for knowledge and vision of freedom.*";
P_HTM[3988]="*Seyyathāpi, āvuso, rukkho, sākhāpalāsasampanno. Tassa papaṭikāpi pāripūriṃ gacchati, tacopi pheggupi sāropi pāripūriṃ gacchati.**Suppose there was a tree that was complete with branches and foliage. Its shoots, bark, softwood, and heartwood would grow to fullness.*";
P_HTM[3989]="*Evamevaṃ kho, āvuso, sīlavato sīlasampannassa upanisasampanno hoti sammāsamādhi;**In the same way, an ethical person, who has fulfilled ethics, has fulfilled a vital condition for right immersion.*";
P_HTM[3990]="*sammāsamādhimhi sati sammāsamādhisampannassa upanisasampannaṃ hoti yathābhūtañāṇadassanaṃ;**When there is right immersion, one who has fulfilled right immersion has fulfilled a vital condition for true knowledge and vision.*";
P_HTM[3991]="*yathābhūtañāṇadassane sati yathābhūtañāṇadassanasampannassa upanisasampanno hoti nibbidāvirāgo;**When there is true knowledge and vision, one who has fulfilled true knowledge and vision has fulfilled a vital condition for disillusionment and dispassion.*";
P_HTM[3992]="*nibbidāvirāge sati nibbidāvirāgasampannassa upanisasampannaṃ hoti vimuttiñāṇadassanan”ti.**When there is disillusionment and dispassion, one who has fulfilled disillusionment and dispassion has fulfilled a vital condition for knowledge and vision of freedom.”*";
P_HTM[3993]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3994]="*9. Khippanisantisuttaṃ**Quick*";
P_HTM[3995]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā sāriputtena saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then Venerable Ānanda went up to Venerable Sāriputta, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[3996]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to him:*";
P_HTM[3997]="*“Kittāvatā nu kho, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhu khippanisanti ca hoti, kusalesu dhammesu suggahitaggāhī ca, bahuñca gaṇhāti, gahitañcassa nappamussatī”ti?**“Reverend Sāriputta, how are we to define a mendicant who is quick-witted when it comes to skillful principles, who learns well, learns much, and does not forget what they’ve learned?”*";
P_HTM[3998]="*“Āyasmā kho ānando bahussuto.**“Well, Venerable Ānanda, you’re very learned.*";
P_HTM[3999]="*Paṭibhātu āyasmantaṃyeva ānandan”ti.**Why don’t you clarify this yourself?”*";
P_HTM[4000]="*“Tenahāvuso sāriputta, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, Reverend Sāriputta, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[4001]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmato ānandassa paccassosi.**“Yes, reverend,” Sāriputta replied.*";
P_HTM[4002]="*Āyasmā ānando etadavoca:**Venerable Ānanda said this:*";
P_HTM[4003]="*“Idhāvuso sāriputta, bhikkhu atthakusalo ca hoti, dhammakusalo ca, byañjanakusalo ca, niruttikusalo ca, pubbāparakusalo ca.**“It’s when a mendicant is skilled in the meaning, skilled in the teaching, skilled in terminology, skilled in phrasing, and skilled in sequence.*";
P_HTM[4004]="*Ettāvatā kho, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhu khippanisanti ca hoti kusalesu dhammesu, suggahitaggāhī ca, bahuñca gaṇhāti, gahitañcassa nappamussatī”ti.**That is how to define a mendicant who is quick-witted when it comes to skillful principles, who learns well, learns much, and does not forget what they’ve learned.”*";
P_HTM[4005]="*“Acchariyaṃ, āvuso, abbhutaṃ, āvuso.**“It’s incredible, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[4006]="*Yāva subhāsitañcidaṃ āyasmatā ānandena.**How well this was said by Venerable Ānanda!*";
P_HTM[4007]="*Imehi ca mayaṃ pañcahi dhammehi samannāgataṃ āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ dhārema:**And we will remember Venerable Ānanda as someone who has these five qualities:*";
P_HTM[4008]="*‘āyasmā ānando atthakusalo dhammakusalo byañjanakusalo niruttikusalo pubbāparakusalo’”ti.**‘Reverend Ānanda is skilled in the meaning, skilled in the teaching, skilled in terminology, skilled in phrasing, and skilled in sequence.’”*";
P_HTM[4009]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4010]="*10. Bhaddajisuttaṃ**With Bhaddaji*";
P_HTM[4011]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ānando kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme.**At one time Venerable Ānanda was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[4012]="*Atha kho āyasmā bhaddaji yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then Venerable Bhaddaji went up to Venerable Ānanda, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[4013]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ bhaddajiṃ āyasmā ānando etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side, and Venerable Ānanda said to him:*";
P_HTM[4014]="*“kiṃ nu kho, āvuso bhaddaji, dassanānaṃ aggaṃ, kiṃ savanānaṃ aggaṃ, kiṃ sukhānaṃ aggaṃ, kiṃ saññānaṃ aggaṃ, kiṃ bhavānaṃ aggan”ti?**“Reverend Bhaddaji, what is the best sight, the best sound, the best happiness, the best perception, and the best state of existence?”*";
P_HTM[4015]="*“Atthāvuso, brahmā abhibhū anabhibhūto aññadatthudaso vasavattī, yo taṃ brahmānaṃ passati, idaṃ dassanānaṃ aggaṃ.**“Reverend, there is this Brahmā, the undefeated, the champion, the universal seer, the wielder of power. When you see Brahmā, that’s the best sight.*";
P_HTM[4016]="*Atthāvuso, ābhassarā nāma devā sukhena abhisannā parisannā.**There are the gods called ‘of streaming radiance’, who are drenched and steeped in pleasure.*";
P_HTM[4017]="*Te kadāci karahaci udānaṃ udānenti:**Every so often they feel inspired to exclaim:*";
P_HTM[4018]="*‘aho sukhaṃ, aho sukhan’ti.**‘Oh, what bliss! Oh, what bliss!’*";
P_HTM[4019]="*Yo taṃ saddaṃ suṇāti, idaṃ savanānaṃ aggaṃ.**When you hear that, it’s the best sound.*";
P_HTM[4020]="*Atthāvuso, subhakiṇhā nāma devā.**There are the gods called ‘replete with glory’.*";
P_HTM[4021]="*Te santaṃyeva tusitā sukhaṃ paṭivedenti, idaṃ sukhānaṃ aggaṃ.**Since they’re truly content, they experience pleasure. This is the best happiness.*";
P_HTM[4022]="*Atthāvuso, ākiñcaññāyatanūpagā devā, idaṃ saññānaṃ aggaṃ.**There are the gods reborn in the dimension of nothingness. This is the best perception.*";
P_HTM[4023]="*Atthāvuso, nevasaññānāsaññāyatanūpagā devā, idaṃ bhavānaṃ aggan”ti.**There are the gods reborn in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception. This is the best state of existence.”*";
P_HTM[4024]="*“Sameti kho idaṃ āyasmato bhaddajissa, yadidaṃ bahunā janenā”ti?**“So, Venerable Bhaddaji, do you agree with what most people say about this?”*";
P_HTM[4025]="*“Āyasmā kho ānando bahussuto.**“Well, Venerable Ānanda, you’re very learned.*";
P_HTM[4026]="*Paṭibhātu āyasmantaṃyeva ānandan”ti.**Why don’t you clarify this yourself?”*";
P_HTM[4027]="*“Tenahāvuso bhaddaji, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, Reverend Bhaddaji, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[4028]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā bhaddaji āyasmato ānandassa paccassosi.**“Yes, reverend,” Bhaddaji replied.*";
P_HTM[4029]="*Āyasmā ānando etadavoca:**Ānanda said this:*";
P_HTM[4030]="*“Yathā passato kho, āvuso, anantarā āsavānaṃ khayo hoti, idaṃ dassanānaṃ aggaṃ.**“What you see when the defilements end in the present life is the best sight.*";
P_HTM[4031]="*Yathā suṇato anantarā āsavānaṃ khayo hoti, idaṃ savanānaṃ aggaṃ.**What you hear when the defilements end in the present life is the best sound.*";
P_HTM[4032]="*Yathā sukhitassa anantarā āsavānaṃ khayo hoti, idaṃ sukhānaṃ aggaṃ.**The happiness you feel when the defilements end in the present life is the best happiness.*";
P_HTM[4033]="*Yathā saññissa anantarā āsavānaṃ khayo hoti, idaṃ saññānaṃ aggaṃ.**What you perceive when the defilements end in the present life is the best perception.*";
P_HTM[4034]="*Yathā bhūtassa anantarā āsavānaṃ khayo hoti, idaṃ bhavānaṃ aggan”ti.**The state of existence in which the defilements end in the present life is the best state of existence.”*";
P_HTM[4035]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4036]="*Āghātavaggo dutiyo.* **";
P_HTM[4037]="*Dve āghātavinayā,* **";
P_HTM[4038]="*sākacchā sājīvato pañhaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4039]="*Pucchā nirodho codanā,* **";
P_HTM[4040]="*sīlaṃ nisanti bhaddajīti.* **";
P_HTM[4041]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**A Lay Follower*";
P_HTM[4042]="*1. Sārajjasuttaṃ**Timidity*";
P_HTM[4043]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[4044]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[4045]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[4046]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[4047]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[4048]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[4049]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato upāsako sārajjaṃ okkanto hoti.**“A lay follower with five qualities is overcome by timidity.*";
P_HTM[4050]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4051]="*Pāṇātipātī hoti, adinnādāyī hoti, kāmesumicchācārī hoti, musāvādī hoti, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhāyī hoti.**They kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, lie, and use alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[4052]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato upāsako sārajjaṃ okkanto hoti.**A lay follower with these five qualities is overcome by timidity.*";
P_HTM[4053]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato upāsako visārado hoti.**A lay follower with five qualities is self-assured.*";
P_HTM[4054]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4055]="*Pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti.**They don’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, lie, or use alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[4056]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato upāsako visārado hotī”ti.**A lay follower with these five qualities is self-assured.”*";
P_HTM[4057]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4058]="*2. Visāradasuttaṃ**Assured*";
P_HTM[4059]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato upāsako avisārado agāraṃ ajjhāvasati.**“A lay follower living at home with five qualities is not self-assured.*";
P_HTM[4060]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4061]="*Pāṇātipātī hoti … pe … surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhāyī hoti.**They kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, lie, and use alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[4062]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato upāsako avisārado agāraṃ ajjhāvasati.**A lay follower living at home with these five qualities is not self-assured.*";
P_HTM[4063]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato upāsako visārado agāraṃ ajjhāvasati.**A lay follower living at home with these five qualities is self-assured.*";
P_HTM[4064]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4065]="*Pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti … pe … surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti.**They don’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, lie, or use alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[4066]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato upāsako visārado agāraṃ ajjhāvasatī”ti.**A lay follower living at home with these five qualities is self-assured.”*";
P_HTM[4067]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4068]="*3. Nirayasuttaṃ**Hell*";
P_HTM[4069]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato upāsako yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, a lay follower with five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[4070]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4071]="*Pāṇātipātī hoti … pe … surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhāyī hoti.**They kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, lie, and use alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[4072]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato upāsako yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**A lay follower with these five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[4073]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato upāsako yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.**A lay follower with five qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[4074]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4075]="*Pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti … pe … surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti.**They don’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, lie, or use alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[4076]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato upāsako yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.**A lay follower with these five qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[4077]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4078]="*4. Verasuttaṃ**Threats*";
P_HTM[4079]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**Then the householder Anāthapiṇḍika went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[4080]="*“Pañca, gahapati, bhayāni verāni appahāya ‘dussīlo’ iti vuccati, nirayañca upapajjati.**“Householder, unless these five dangers and threats are given up, one is said to be unethical, and is reborn in hell.*";
P_HTM[4081]="*Katamāni pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4082]="*Pāṇātipātaṃ, adinnādānaṃ, kāmesumicchācāraṃ, musāvādaṃ, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānaṃ—**Killing living creatures, stealing, committing sexual misconduct, lying, and using alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[4083]="*imāni kho, gahapati, pañca bhayāni verāni appahāya ‘dussīlo’ iti vuccati, nirayañca upapajjati.**Unless these five dangers and threats are given up, one is said to be unethical, and is reborn in hell.*";
P_HTM[4084]="*Pañca, gahapati, bhayāni verāni pahāya ‘sīlavā’ iti vuccati, sugatiñca upapajjati.**Once these five dangers and threats are given up, one is said to be ethical, and is reborn in heaven.*";
P_HTM[4085]="*Katamāni pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4086]="*Pāṇātipātaṃ, adinnādānaṃ, kāmesumicchācāraṃ, musāvādaṃ, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānaṃ—**Killing living creatures, stealing, committing sexual misconduct, lying, and using alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[4087]="*imāni kho, gahapati, pañca bhayāni verāni pahāya ‘sīlavā’ iti vuccati, sugatiñca upapajjati.**Once these five dangers and threats are given up, one is said to be ethical, and is reborn in heaven.*";
P_HTM[4088]="*Yaṃ, gahapati, pāṇātipātī pāṇātipātapaccayā diṭṭhadhammikampi bhayaṃ veraṃ pasavati, samparāyikampi bhayaṃ veraṃ pasavati, cetasikampi dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti, pāṇātipātā paṭivirato neva diṭṭhadhammikaṃ bhayaṃ veraṃ pasavati, na samparāyikaṃ bhayaṃ veraṃ pasavati, na cetasikaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.**Anyone who kills living creatures creates dangers and threats both in the present life and in lives to come, and experiences mental pain and sadness. Anyone who refrains from killing living creatures creates no dangers and threats either in the present life or in lives to come, and doesn’t experience mental pain and sadness.*";
P_HTM[4089]="*Pāṇātipātā paṭiviratassa evaṃ taṃ bhayaṃ veraṃ vūpasantaṃ hoti.**So that danger and threat is quelled for anyone who refrains from killing living creatures.*";
P_HTM[4090]="*Yaṃ, gahapati, adinnādāyī … pe ….**Anyone who steals …*";
P_HTM[4091]="*Yaṃ, gahapati, kāmesumicchācārī … pe ….**Anyone who commits sexual misconduct …*";
P_HTM[4092]="*Yaṃ, gahapati, musāvādī … pe ….**Anyone who lies …*";
P_HTM[4093]="*Yaṃ, gahapati, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhāyī surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānapaccayā diṭṭhadhammikampi bhayaṃ veraṃ pasavati, samparāyikampi bhayaṃ veraṃ pasavati, cetasikampi dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato neva diṭṭhadhammikaṃ bhayaṃ veraṃ pasavati, na samparāyikaṃ bhayaṃ veraṃ pasavati, na cetasikaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti.**Anyone who uses alcoholic drinks that cause negligence creates dangers and threats both in the present life and in lives to come, and experiences mental pain and sadness. Anyone who refrains from using alcoholic drinks that cause negligence creates no dangers and threats either in the present life or in lives to come, and doesn’t experience mental pain and sadness.*";
P_HTM[4094]="*Surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭiviratassa evaṃ taṃ bhayaṃ veraṃ vūpasantaṃ hotīti.**So that danger and threat is quelled for anyone who refrains from using alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[4095]="*Yo pāṇamatipāteti,**A person in the world kills living creatures,*";
P_HTM[4096]="*musāvādañca bhāsati;**speaks falsely,*";
P_HTM[4097]="*Loke adinnaṃ ādiyati,**steals,*";
P_HTM[4098]="*paradārañca gacchati;**commits adultery,*";
P_HTM[4099]="*Surāmerayapānañca,**and indulges in drinking*";
P_HTM[4100]="*yo naro anuyuñjati.**alcohol and liquor.*";
P_HTM[4101]="*Appahāya pañca verāni,**Unless they give up these five threats,*";
P_HTM[4102]="*dussīlo iti vuccati;**they’re said to be unethical.*";
P_HTM[4103]="*Kāyassa bhedā duppañño,**When their body breaks up, that witless person*";
P_HTM[4104]="*nirayaṃ sopapajjati.**is reborn in hell.*";
P_HTM[4105]="*Yo pāṇaṃ nātipāteti,**A person in the world doesn’t kill living creatures,*";
P_HTM[4106]="*musāvādaṃ na bhāsati;**speak falsely,*";
P_HTM[4107]="*Loke adinnaṃ nādiyati,**steal,*";
P_HTM[4108]="*paradāraṃ na gacchati;**commit adultery,*";
P_HTM[4109]="*Surāmerayapānañca,**or indulge in drinking*";
P_HTM[4110]="*yo naro nānuyuñjati.**alcohol and liquor.*";
P_HTM[4111]="*Pahāya pañca verāni,**Giving up these five threats,*";
P_HTM[4112]="*sīlavā iti vuccati;**they’re said to be ethical.*";
P_HTM[4113]="*Kāyassa bhedā sappañño,**When their body breaks up, that wise person*";
P_HTM[4114]="*sugatiṃ sopapajjatī”ti.**is reborn in a good place.”*";
P_HTM[4115]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4116]="*5. Caṇḍālasuttaṃ**Outcaste*";
P_HTM[4117]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato upāsako upāsakacaṇḍālo ca hoti upāsakamalañca upāsakapatikuṭṭho ca.**“Mendicants, a lay follower with five qualities is an outcaste, a stain, and a reject among lay followers.*";
P_HTM[4118]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4119]="*Assaddho hoti;**They’re faithless.*";
P_HTM[4120]="*dussīlo hoti;**They’re unethical.*";
P_HTM[4121]="*kotūhalamaṅgaliko hoti, maṅgalaṃ pacceti no kammaṃ;**They practice noisy, superstitious rites, believing in omens rather than deeds.*";
P_HTM[4122]="*ito ca bahiddhā dakkhiṇeyyaṃ gavesati;**They seek outside of the Buddhist community for those worthy of religious donations.*";
P_HTM[4123]="*tattha ca pubbakāraṃ karoti.**And they make offerings there first.*";
P_HTM[4124]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato upāsako upāsakacaṇḍālo ca hoti upāsakamalañca upāsakapatikuṭṭho ca.**A lay follower with these five qualities is an outcaste, a stain, and a reject among lay followers.*";
P_HTM[4125]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato upāsako upāsakaratanañca hoti upāsakapadumañca upāsakapuṇḍarīkañca.**A lay follower with five qualities is a gem, a pink lotus, and a white lotus among lay followers.*";
P_HTM[4126]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4127]="*Saddho hoti;**They’re faithful.*";
P_HTM[4128]="*sīlavā hoti;**They’re ethical.*";
P_HTM[4129]="*akotūhalamaṅgaliko hoti, kammaṃ pacceti no maṅgalaṃ;**They don’t practice noisy, superstitious rites, and believe in deeds rather than omens.*";
P_HTM[4130]="*na ito bahiddhā dakkhiṇeyyaṃ gavesati;**They don’t seek outside of the Buddhist community for those worthy of religious donations.*";
P_HTM[4131]="*idha ca pubbakāraṃ karoti.**And they don’t make offerings there first.*";
P_HTM[4132]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato upāsako upāsakaratanañca hoti upāsakapadumañca upāsakapuṇḍarīkañcā”ti.**A lay follower with these five qualities is a gem, a pink lotus, and a white lotus among lay followers.”*";
P_HTM[4133]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4134]="*6. Pītisuttaṃ**Rapture*";
P_HTM[4135]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati pañcamattehi upāsakasatehi parivuto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho anāthapiṇḍikaṃ gahapatiṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**Then the householder Anāthapiṇḍika, escorted by around five hundred lay followers, went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[4136]="*“Tumhe kho, gahapati, bhikkhusaṅghaṃ paccupaṭṭhitā cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena.**“Householders, you have supplied the mendicant Saṅgha with robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick.*";
P_HTM[4137]="*Na kho, gahapati, tāvatakeneva tuṭṭhi karaṇīyā:**But you should not be content with just this much.*";
P_HTM[4138]="*‘mayaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ paccupaṭṭhitā cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārenā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4139]="*Tasmātiha, gahapati, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**So you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[4140]="*‘kinti mayaṃ kālena kālaṃ pavivekaṃ pītiṃ upasampajja vihareyyāmā’ti.**‘How can we, from time to time, enter and dwell in the rapture of seclusion?’*";
P_HTM[4141]="*Evañhi vo, gahapati, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[4142]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā sāriputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Venerable Sāriputta said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[4143]="*“acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante.**“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[4144]="*Yāva subhāsitañcidaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā:**How well said this was by the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[4145]="*‘tumhe kho, gahapati, bhikkhusaṃghaṃ paccupaṭṭhitā cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena.**‘Householders, you have supplied the mendicant Saṅgha with robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick.*";
P_HTM[4146]="*Na kho, gahapati, tāvatakeneva tuṭṭhi karaṇīyā—**But you should not be content with just this much.*";
P_HTM[4147]="*mayaṃ bhikkhusaṃghaṃ paccupaṭṭhitā cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārenāti.* **";
P_HTM[4148]="*Tasmātiha, gahapati, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ—**So you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[4149]="*kinti mayaṃ kālena kālaṃ pavivekaṃ pītiṃ upasampajja vihareyyāmāti.**“How can we, from time to time, enter and dwell in the rapture of seclusion?”*";
P_HTM[4150]="*Evañhi vo, gahapati, sikkhitabban’ti.**That’s how you should train.’*";
P_HTM[4151]="*Yasmiṃ, bhante, samaye ariyasāvako pavivekaṃ pītiṃ upasampajja viharati, pañcassa ṭhānāni tasmiṃ samaye na honti.**At a time when a noble disciple enters and dwells in the rapture of seclusion, five things aren’t present in him.*";
P_HTM[4152]="*Yampissa kāmūpasaṃhitaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ, tampissa tasmiṃ samaye na hoti.**The pain and sadness connected with sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[4153]="*Yampissa kāmūpasaṃhitaṃ sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, tampissa tasmiṃ samaye na hoti.**The pleasure and happiness connected with sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[4154]="*Yampissa akusalūpasaṃhitaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ, tampissa tasmiṃ samaye na hoti.**The pain and sadness connected with the unskillful.*";
P_HTM[4155]="*Yampissa akusalūpasaṃhitaṃ sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, tampissa tasmiṃ samaye na hoti.**The pleasure and happiness connected with the unskillful.*";
P_HTM[4156]="*Yampissa kusalūpasaṃhitaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ, tampissa tasmiṃ samaye na hoti.**The pain and sadness connected with the skillful.*";
P_HTM[4157]="*Yasmiṃ, bhante, samaye ariyasāvako pavivekaṃ pītiṃ upasampajja viharati, imānissa pañca ṭhānāni tasmiṃ samaye na hontī”ti.**At a time when a noble disciple enters and dwells in the rapture of seclusion, these five things aren’t present in him.”*";
P_HTM[4158]="*“Sādhu sādhu, sāriputta.**“Good, good, Sāriputta!*";
P_HTM[4159]="*Yasmiṃ, sāriputta, samaye ariyasāvako pavivekaṃ pītiṃ upasampajja viharati, pañcassa ṭhānāni tasmiṃ samaye na honti.**At a time when a noble disciple enters and dwells in the rapture of seclusion, five things aren’t present in him.*";
P_HTM[4160]="*Yampissa kāmūpasaṃhitaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ, tampissa tasmiṃ samaye na hoti.**The pain and sadness connected with sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[4161]="*Yampissa kāmūpasaṃhitaṃ sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, tampissa tasmiṃ samaye na hoti.**The pleasure and happiness connected with sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[4162]="*Yampissa akusalūpasaṃhitaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ, tampissa tasmiṃ samaye na hoti.**The pain and sadness connected with the unskillful.*";
P_HTM[4163]="*Yampissa akusalūpasaṃhitaṃ sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, tampissa tasmiṃ samaye na hoti.**The pleasure and happiness connected with the unskillful.*";
P_HTM[4164]="*Yampissa kusalūpasaṃhitaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ, tampissa tasmiṃ samaye na hoti.**The pain and sadness connected with the skillful.*";
P_HTM[4165]="*Yasmiṃ, sāriputta, samaye ariyasāvako pavivekaṃ pītiṃ upasampajja viharati, imānissa pañca ṭhānāni tasmiṃ samaye na hontī”ti.**At a time when a noble disciple enters and dwells in the rapture of seclusion, these five things aren’t present in him.”*";
P_HTM[4166]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4167]="*7. Vaṇijjāsuttaṃ**Trades*";
P_HTM[4168]="*“Pañcimā, bhikkhave, vaṇijjā upāsakena akaraṇīyā.**“Mendicants, a lay follower should not engage in these five trades.*";
P_HTM[4169]="*Katamā pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4170]="*Satthavaṇijjā, sattavaṇijjā, maṃsavaṇijjā, majjavaṇijjā, visavaṇijjā—**Trade in weapons, living creatures, meat, intoxicants, and poisons.*";
P_HTM[4171]="*imā kho, bhikkhave, pañca vaṇijjā upāsakena akaraṇīyā”ti.**A lay follower should not engage in these five trades.”*";
P_HTM[4172]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4173]="*8. Rājāsuttaṃ**Kings*";
P_HTM[4174]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**“What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[4175]="*api nu tumhehi diṭṭhaṃ vā sutaṃ vā:**Have you ever seen or heard*";
P_HTM[4176]="*‘ayaṃ puriso pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭiviratoti.**of a person who has given up killing living creatures,*";
P_HTM[4177]="*Tamenaṃ rājāno gahetvā pāṇātipātā veramaṇihetu hananti vā bandhanti vā pabbājenti vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā karontī’”ti?**and then the kings have them arrested for that, and execute, imprison, or banish them, or do what the case requires?”*";
P_HTM[4178]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4179]="*“Sādhu, bhikkhave.**“Good, mendicants!*";
P_HTM[4180]="*Mayāpi kho etaṃ, bhikkhave, neva diṭṭhaṃ na sutaṃ:**I too have never seen or heard of such a thing.*";
P_HTM[4181]="*‘ayaṃ puriso pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭiviratoti.* **";
P_HTM[4182]="*Tamenaṃ rājāno gahetvā pāṇātipātā veramaṇihetu hananti vā bandhanti vā pabbājenti vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā karontī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4183]="*Api ca khvassa tatheva pāpakammaṃ pavedenti:**Rather, the kings are informed of someone’s bad deed:*";
P_HTM[4184]="*‘ayaṃ puriso itthiṃ vā purisaṃ vā jīvitā voropesīti.**‘This person has murdered a man or a woman.’*";
P_HTM[4185]="*Tamenaṃ rājāno gahetvā pāṇātipātahetu hananti vā bandhanti vā pabbājenti vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā karonti.**Then the kings have them arrested for killing, and execute, imprison, or banish them, or do what the case requires.*";
P_HTM[4186]="*Api nu tumhehi evarūpaṃ diṭṭhaṃ vā sutaṃ vā’”ti?**Have you ever seen or heard of such a case?”*";
P_HTM[4187]="*“Diṭṭhañca no, bhante, sutañca suyyissati cā”ti.**“Sir, we have seen it and heard of it, and we will hear of it again.”*";
P_HTM[4188]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**“What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[4189]="*api nu tumhehi diṭṭhaṃ vā sutaṃ vā:**Have you ever seen or heard*";
P_HTM[4190]="*‘ayaṃ puriso adinnādānaṃ pahāya adinnādānā paṭiviratoti.**of a person who has given up stealing,*";
P_HTM[4191]="*Tamenaṃ rājāno gahetvā adinnādānā veramaṇihetu hananti vā bandhanti vā pabbājenti vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā karontī’”ti?**and then the kings have them arrested for that …?”*";
P_HTM[4192]="*“No hetaṃ bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4193]="*“Sādhu, bhikkhave.**“Good, mendicants!*";
P_HTM[4194]="*Mayāpi kho etaṃ, bhikkhave, neva diṭṭhaṃ na sutaṃ:**I too have never seen or heard of such a thing.*";
P_HTM[4195]="*‘ayaṃ puriso adinnādānaṃ pahāya adinnādānā paṭiviratoti.* **";
P_HTM[4196]="*Tamenaṃ rājāno gahetvā adinnādānā veramaṇihetu hananti vā bandhanti vā pabbājenti vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā karontī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4197]="*Api ca khvassa tatheva pāpakammaṃ pavedenti:**Rather, the kings are informed of someone’s bad deed:*";
P_HTM[4198]="*‘ayaṃ puriso gāmā vā araññā vā adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyīti.**‘This person took something from a village or wilderness, with the intention to commit theft.’*";
P_HTM[4199]="*Tamenaṃ rājāno gahetvā adinnādānahetu hananti vā bandhanti vā pabbājenti vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā karonti.**Then the kings have them arrested for stealing …*";
P_HTM[4200]="*Api nu tumhehi evarūpaṃ diṭṭhaṃ vā sutaṃ vā’”ti?**Have you ever seen or heard of such a case?”*";
P_HTM[4201]="*“Diṭṭhañca no, bhante, sutañca suyyissati cā”ti.**“Sir, we have seen it and heard of it, and we will hear of it again.”*";
P_HTM[4202]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**“What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[4203]="*api nu tumhehi diṭṭhaṃ vā sutaṃ vā:**Have you ever seen or heard*";
P_HTM[4204]="*‘ayaṃ puriso kāmesumicchācāraṃ pahāya kāmesumicchācārā paṭiviratoti.**of a person who has given up sexual misconduct,*";
P_HTM[4205]="*Tamenaṃ rājāno gahetvā kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇihetu hananti vā bandhanti vā pabbājenti vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā karontī’”ti?**and then the kings have them arrested for that …?”*";
P_HTM[4206]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4207]="*“Sādhu, bhikkhave.**“Good, mendicants!*";
P_HTM[4208]="*Mayāpi kho etaṃ, bhikkhave, neva diṭṭhaṃ na sutaṃ:**I too have never seen or heard of such a thing.*";
P_HTM[4209]="*‘ayaṃ puriso kāmesumicchācāraṃ pahāya kāmesumicchācārā paṭiviratoti.* **";
P_HTM[4210]="*Tamenaṃ rājāno gahetvā kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇihetu hananti vā bandhanti vā pabbājenti vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā karontī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4211]="*Api ca khvassa tatheva pāpakammaṃ pavedenti:**Rather, the kings are informed of someone’s bad deed:*";
P_HTM[4212]="*‘ayaṃ puriso paritthīsu parakumārīsu cārittaṃ āpajjīti.**‘This person had sexual relations with women or maidens under someone else’s protection.’*";
P_HTM[4213]="*Tamenaṃ rājāno gahetvā kāmesumicchācārahetu hananti vā bandhanti vā pabbājenti vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā karonti.**Then the kings have them arrested for that …*";
P_HTM[4214]="*Api nu tumhehi evarūpaṃ diṭṭhaṃ vā sutaṃ vā’”ti?**Have you ever seen or heard of such a case?”*";
P_HTM[4215]="*“Diṭṭhañca no, bhante, sutañca suyyissati cā”ti.**“Sir, we have seen it and heard of it, and we will hear of it again.”*";
P_HTM[4216]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**“What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[4217]="*api nu tumhehi diṭṭhaṃ vā sutaṃ vā:**Have you ever seen or heard*";
P_HTM[4218]="*‘ayaṃ puriso musāvādaṃ pahāya musāvādā paṭiviratoti.**of a person who has given up lying,*";
P_HTM[4219]="*Tamenaṃ rājāno gahetvā musāvādā veramaṇihetu hananti vā bandhanti vā pabbājenti vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā karontī’”ti?**and then the kings have them arrested for that …?”*";
P_HTM[4220]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4221]="*“Sādhu, bhikkhave.**“Good, mendicants!*";
P_HTM[4222]="*Mayāpi kho etaṃ, bhikkhave, neva diṭṭhaṃ na sutaṃ:**I too have never seen or heard of such a thing.*";
P_HTM[4223]="*‘ayaṃ puriso musāvādaṃ pahāya musāvādā paṭiviratoti.* **";
P_HTM[4224]="*Tamenaṃ rājāno gahetvā musāvādā veramaṇihetu hananti vā bandhanti vā pabbājenti vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā karontī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4225]="*Api ca khvassa tatheva pāpakammaṃ pavedenti:**Rather, the kings are informed of someone’s bad deed:*";
P_HTM[4226]="*‘ayaṃ puriso gahapatissa vā gahapatiputtassa vā musāvādena atthaṃ pabhañjīti.**‘This person has ruined a householder or householder’s child by lying.’*";
P_HTM[4227]="*Tamenaṃ rājāno gahetvā musāvādahetu hananti vā bandhanti vā pabbājenti vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā karonti.**Then the kings have them arrested for that …*";
P_HTM[4228]="*Api nu tumhehi evarūpaṃ diṭṭhaṃ vā sutaṃ vā’”ti?**Have you ever seen or heard of such a case?”*";
P_HTM[4229]="*“Diṭṭhañca no, bhante, sutañca suyyissati cā”ti.**“Sir, we have seen it and heard of it, and we will hear of it again.”*";
P_HTM[4230]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**“What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[4231]="*api nu tumhehi diṭṭhaṃ vā sutaṃ vā:**Have you ever seen or heard*";
P_HTM[4232]="*‘ayaṃ puriso surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānaṃ pahāya surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭiviratoti.**of a person who has given up alcoholic drinks that cause negligence,*";
P_HTM[4233]="*Tamenaṃ rājāno gahetvā surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā veramaṇihetu hananti vā bandhanti vā pabbājenti vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā karontī’”ti?**and then the kings have them arrested for that, and execute, imprison, or banish them, or do what the case requires?”*";
P_HTM[4234]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4235]="*“Sādhu, bhikkhave.**“Good, mendicants!*";
P_HTM[4236]="*Mayāpi kho etaṃ, bhikkhave, neva diṭṭhaṃ na sutaṃ:**I too have never seen or heard of such a thing.*";
P_HTM[4237]="*‘ayaṃ puriso surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānaṃ pahāya surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭiviratoti.* **";
P_HTM[4238]="*Tamenaṃ rājāno gahetvā surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā veramaṇihetu hananti vā bandhanti vā pabbājenti vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā karontī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4239]="*Api ca khvassa tatheva pāpakammaṃ pavedenti:**Rather, the kings are informed of someone’s bad deed:*";
P_HTM[4240]="*‘ayaṃ puriso surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānaṃ anuyutto itthiṃ vā purisaṃ vā jīvitā voropesi;**‘While under the influence of alcoholic drinks that cause negligence, this person murdered a woman or a man.*";
P_HTM[4241]="*ayaṃ puriso surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānaṃ anuyutto gāmā vā araññā vā adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyi;**Or they stole something from a village or wilderness.*";
P_HTM[4242]="*ayaṃ puriso surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānaṃ anuyutto paritthīsu parakumārīsu cārittaṃ āpajji;**Or they had sexual relations with women or maidens under someone else’s protection.*";
P_HTM[4243]="*ayaṃ puriso surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānaṃ anuyutto gahapatissa vā gahapatiputtassa vā musāvādena atthaṃ pabhañjīti.**Or they ruined a householder or householder’s child by lying.’*";
P_HTM[4244]="*Tamenaṃ rājāno gahetvā surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānahetu hananti vā bandhanti vā pabbājenti vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā karonti.**Then the kings have them arrested for being under the influence of alcoholic drinks that cause negligence, and execute, imprison, or banish them, or do what the case requires.*";
P_HTM[4245]="*Api nu tumhehi evarūpaṃ diṭṭhaṃ vā sutaṃ vā’”ti?**Have you ever seen or heard of such a case?”*";
P_HTM[4246]="*“Diṭṭhañca no, bhante, sutañca suyyissati cā”ti.**“Sir, we have seen it and heard of it, and we will hear of it again.”*";
P_HTM[4247]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4248]="*9. Gihisuttaṃ**A Layperson*";
P_HTM[4249]="*Atha kho anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati pañcamattehi upāsakasatehi parivuto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Then the householder Anāthapiṇḍika, escorted by around five hundred lay followers, went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side.*";
P_HTM[4250]="*Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ āmantesi:**Then the Buddha said to Venerable Sāriputta:*";
P_HTM[4251]="*“yaṃ kañci, sāriputta, jāneyyātha gihiṃ odātavasanaṃ pañcasu sikkhāpadesu saṃvutakammantaṃ catunnaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhiṃ akicchalābhiṃ akasiralābhiṃ, so ākaṅkhamāno attanāva attānaṃ byākareyya:**“You should know this, Sāriputta, about those white-clothed laypeople whose actions are restrained in the five precepts, and who get four blissful meditations in the present life belonging to the higher mind when they want, without trouble or difficulty. They may, if they wish, declare of themselves:*";
P_HTM[4252]="*‘khīṇanirayomhi khīṇatiracchānayoni khīṇapettivisayo khīṇāpāyaduggativinipāto, sotāpannohamasmi avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo’ti.**‘I’ve finished with rebirth in hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. I’ve finished with all places of loss, bad places, the underworld. I am a stream-enterer! I’m not liable to be reborn in the underworld, and am bound for awakening.’*";
P_HTM[4253]="*Katamesu pañcasu sikkhāpadesu saṃvutakammanto hoti?**And what are the five precepts in which their actions are restrained?*";
P_HTM[4254]="*Idha, sāriputta, ariyasāvako pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti.**It’s when a noble disciple doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, lie, or use alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[4255]="*Imesu pañcasu sikkhāpadesu saṃvutakammanto hoti.**These are the five precepts in which their actions are restrained.*";
P_HTM[4256]="*Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī?**And what are the four blissful meditations in the present life belonging to the higher mind that they get when they want, without trouble or difficulty?*";
P_HTM[4257]="*Idha, sāriputta, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti:**It’s when a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[4258]="*‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi, satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti.**‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’*";
P_HTM[4259]="*Ayamassa paṭhamo ābhicetasiko diṭṭhadhammasukhavihāro adhigato hoti avisuddhassa cittassa visuddhiyā apariyodātassa cittassa pariyodapanāya.**This is the first blissful meditation in the present life belonging to the higher mind, which they achieve in order to purify the unpurified mind and cleanse the unclean mind.*";
P_HTM[4260]="*Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, ariyasāvako dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti:**Furthermore, a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the teaching:*";
P_HTM[4261]="*‘svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo sandiṭṭhiko akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhī’ti.**‘The teaching is well explained by the Buddha—visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves.’*";
P_HTM[4262]="*Ayamassa dutiyo ābhicetasiko diṭṭhadhammasukhavihāro adhigato hoti avisuddhassa cittassa visuddhiyā apariyodātassa cittassa pariyodapanāya.**This is the second blissful meditation …*";
P_HTM[4263]="*Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, ariyasāvako saṅghe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti:**Furthermore, a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Saṅgha:*";
P_HTM[4264]="*‘suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho ujuppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho ñāyappaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho sāmīcippaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho, yadidaṃ cattāri purisayugāni aṭṭha purisapuggalā esa bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho āhuneyyo pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā’ti.**‘The Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples is practicing the way that’s good, straightforward, methodical, and proper. It consists of the four pairs, the eight individuals. This is the Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples that is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of greeting with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.’*";
P_HTM[4265]="*Ayamassa tatiyo ābhicetasiko diṭṭhadhammasukhavihāro adhigato hoti avisuddhassa cittassa visuddhiyā apariyodātassa cittassa pariyodapanāya.**This is the third blissful meditation …*";
P_HTM[4266]="*Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, ariyasāvako ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti akhaṇḍehi acchiddehi asabalehi akammāsehi bhujissehi viññuppasatthehi aparāmaṭṭhehi samādhisaṃvattanikehi.**Furthermore, a noble disciple’s ethical conduct is loved by the noble ones, unbroken, impeccable, spotless, and unmarred, liberating, praised by sensible people, not mistaken, and leading to immersion.*";
P_HTM[4267]="*Ayamassa catuttho ābhicetasiko diṭṭhadhammasukhavihāro adhigato hoti avisuddhassa cittassa visuddhiyā apariyodātassa cittassa pariyodapanāya.**This is the fourth blissful meditation in the present life belonging to the higher mind, which they achieve in order to purify the unpurified mind and cleanse the unclean mind.*";
P_HTM[4268]="*Imesaṃ catunnaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī.**These are the four blissful meditations in the present life belonging to the higher mind that they get when they want, without trouble or difficulty.*";
P_HTM[4269]="*Yaṃ kañci, sāriputta, jāneyyātha gihiṃ odātavasanaṃ—imesu pañcasu sikkhāpadesu saṃvutakammantaṃ, imesañca catunnaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhiṃ akicchalābhiṃ akasiralābhiṃ, so ākaṅkhamāno attanāva attānaṃ byākareyya:**You should know this, Sāriputta, about those white-clothed laypeople whose actions are restrained in the five precepts, and who get four blissful meditations in the present life belonging to the higher mind when they want, without trouble or difficulty. They may, if they wish, declare of themselves:*";
P_HTM[4270]="*‘khīṇanirayomhi khīṇatiracchānayoni khīṇapettivisayo khīṇāpāyaduggativinipāto, sotāpannohamasmi avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo’ti.**‘I’ve finished with rebirth in hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. I’ve finished with all places of loss, bad places, the underworld. I am a stream-enterer! I’m not liable to be reborn in the underworld, and am bound for awakening.’*";
P_HTM[4271]="*Nirayesu bhayaṃ disvā,**Seeing the peril in the hells,*";
P_HTM[4272]="*pāpāni parivajjaye;**you should shun bad deeds.*";
P_HTM[4273]="*Ariyadhammaṃ samādāya,**Taking up the teaching of the noble ones,*";
P_HTM[4274]="*paṇḍito parivajjaye.**an astute person should shun them.*";
P_HTM[4275]="*Na hiṃse pāṇabhūtāni,**You shouldn’t harm living beings,*";
P_HTM[4276]="*vijjamāne parakkame;**as far as that’s possible to do.*";
P_HTM[4277]="*Musā ca na bhaṇe jānaṃ,**Nor should you knowingly speak falsehood,*";
P_HTM[4278]="*adinnaṃ na parāmase.**or take what is not given.*";
P_HTM[4279]="*Sehi dārehi santuṭṭho,**Content with your own partners,*";
P_HTM[4280]="*paradārañca ārame;**you should stay away from the partners of others.*";
P_HTM[4281]="*Merayaṃ vāruṇiṃ jantu,**A man shouldn’t drink liquor or wine,*";
P_HTM[4282]="*na pive cittamohaniṃ.**as they confuse the mind.*";
P_HTM[4283]="*Anussareyya sambuddhaṃ,**You should recollect the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[4284]="*dhammañcānuvitakkaye;**and reflect on the teaching.*";
P_HTM[4285]="*Abyāpajjaṃ hitaṃ cittaṃ,**You should develop a harmless mind of welfare,*";
P_HTM[4286]="*devalokāya bhāvaye.**which leads to the realms of gods.*";
P_HTM[4287]="*Upaṭṭhite deyyadhamme,**When suitable gifts to give are available*";
P_HTM[4288]="*puññatthassa jigīsato;**to someone who wants and needs merit,*";
P_HTM[4289]="*Santesu paṭhamaṃ dinnā,**a religious donation is abundant*";
P_HTM[4290]="*vipulā hoti dakkhiṇā.**if given first to the peaceful ones.*";
P_HTM[4291]="*Santo have pavakkhāmi,**I will tell of the peaceful ones,*";
P_HTM[4292]="*sāriputta suṇohi me;**Sāriputta, listen to me.*";
P_HTM[4293]="*Iti kaṇhāsu setāsu,**Cows may be black or white,*";
P_HTM[4294]="*rohiṇīsu harīsu vā.**red or tawny,*";
P_HTM[4295]="*Kammāsāsu sarūpāsu,**mottled or uniform,*";
P_HTM[4296]="*gosu pārevatāsu vā;**or pigeon-colored.*";
P_HTM[4297]="*Yāsu kāsuci etāsu,**But when one is born among them,*";
P_HTM[4298]="*danto jāyati puṅgavo.**the bull that’s tamed,*";
P_HTM[4299]="*Dhorayho balasampanno,**—a behemoth, powerful,*";
P_HTM[4300]="*kalyāṇajavanikkamo;**well-paced in pulling forward—*";
P_HTM[4301]="*Tameva bhāre yuñjanti,**they yoke the load just to him,*";
P_HTM[4302]="*nāssa vaṇṇaṃ parikkhare.**regardless of his color.*";
P_HTM[4303]="*Evamevaṃ manussesu,**So it is for humans,*";
P_HTM[4304]="*yasmiṃ kismiñci jātiye;**wherever they may be born,*";
P_HTM[4305]="*Khattiye brāhmaṇe vesse,**—among aristocrats, brahmins, merchants,*";
P_HTM[4306]="*sudde caṇḍālapukkuse.**workers, or outcastes and scavengers—*";
P_HTM[4307]="*Yāsu kāsuci etāsu,**but when one is born among them,*";
P_HTM[4308]="*danto jāyati subbato;**tamed, true to their vows.*";
P_HTM[4309]="*Dhammaṭṭho sīlasampanno,**Firm in principle, accomplished in ethical conduct,*";
P_HTM[4310]="*saccavādī hirīmano.**truthful, conscientious,*";
P_HTM[4311]="*Pahīnajātimaraṇo,**they’ve given up birth and death,*";
P_HTM[4312]="*brahmacariyassa kevalī;**and have completed the spiritual journey.*";
P_HTM[4313]="*Pannabhāro visaṃyutto,**With burden put down, detached,*";
P_HTM[4314]="*katakicco anāsavo.**they’ve completed the task and are free of defilements.*";
P_HTM[4315]="*Pāragū sabbadhammānaṃ,**Gone beyond all things,*";
P_HTM[4316]="*anupādāya nibbuto;**they’re extinguished by not grasping.*";
P_HTM[4317]="*Tasmiñca viraje khette,**In that flawless field,*";
P_HTM[4318]="*vipulā hoti dakkhiṇā.**a religious donation is abundant.*";
P_HTM[4319]="*Bālā ca avijānantā,**Fools who don’t understand*";
P_HTM[4320]="*dummedhā assutāvino;**—stupid, uneducated—*";
P_HTM[4321]="*Bahiddhā dadanti dānāni,**give their gifts to those outside,*";
P_HTM[4322]="*na hi sante upāsare.**and don’t attend the peaceful ones.*";
P_HTM[4323]="*Ye ca sante upāsanti,**But those who do attend the peaceful ones*";
P_HTM[4324]="*sappaññe dhīrasammate;**—wise, esteemed as sages—*";
P_HTM[4325]="*Saddhā ca nesaṃ sugate,**and whose faith in the Holy One*";
P_HTM[4326]="*mūlajātā patiṭṭhitā.**has roots planted deep,*";
P_HTM[4327]="*Devalokañca te yanti,**they go to the realm of the gods,*";
P_HTM[4328]="*kule vā idha jāyare;**or are born here in a good family.*";
P_HTM[4329]="*Anupubbena nibbānaṃ,**Gradually those astute ones*";
P_HTM[4330]="*adhigacchanti paṇḍitā”ti.**reach extinguishment.”*";
P_HTM[4331]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4332]="*10. Gavesīsuttaṃ**About Gavesī*";
P_HTM[4333]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosalesu cārikaṃ carati mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ.**At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Kosalans together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants.*";
P_HTM[4334]="*Addasā kho bhagavā addhānamaggappaṭipanno aññatarasmiṃ padese mahantaṃ sālavanaṃ;**While traveling along a road the Buddha saw a large sal grove in a certain spot.*";
P_HTM[4335]="*disvāna maggā okkamma yena taṃ sālavanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ sālavanaṃ ajjhogāhetvā aññatarasmiṃ padese sitaṃ pātvākāsi.**He left the road, went to the sal grove, and plunged deep into it. And at a certain spot he smiled.*";
P_HTM[4336]="*Atha kho āyasmato ānandassa etadahosi:**Then Venerable Ānanda thought,*";
P_HTM[4337]="*“ko nu kho hetu ko paccayo bhagavato sitassa pātukammāya?**“What is the cause, what is the reason why the Buddha smiled?*";
P_HTM[4338]="*Na akāraṇena tathāgatā sitaṃ pātukarontī”ti.**Realized Ones do not smile for no reason.”*";
P_HTM[4339]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**So Venerable Ānanda said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[4340]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu ko paccayo bhagavato sitassa pātukammāya?**“What is the cause, what is the reason why the Buddha smiled?*";
P_HTM[4341]="*Na akāraṇena tathāgatā sitaṃ pātukarontī”ti.**Realized Ones do not smile for no reason.”*";
P_HTM[4342]="*“Bhūtapubbaṃ, ānanda, imasmiṃ padese nagaraṃ ahosi iddhañceva phītañca bahujanaṃ ākiṇṇamanussaṃ.**“Once upon a time, Ānanda, there was a city in this spot that was successful and prosperous and full of people.*";
P_HTM[4343]="*Taṃ kho panānanda, nagaraṃ kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho upanissāya vihāsi.**And Kassapa, a blessed one, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha, lived supported by that city.*";
P_HTM[4344]="*Kassapassa kho panānanda, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa gavesī nāma upāsako ahosi sīlesu aparipūrakārī.**He had a lay follower called Gavesī who had not fulfilled all the precepts.*";
P_HTM[4345]="*Gavesinā kho, ānanda, upāsakena pañcamattāni upāsakasatāni paṭidesitāni samādapitāni ahesuṃ sīlesu aparipūrakārino.**And the five hundred lay followers who were taught and advised by Gavesī also had not fulfilled all the precepts.*";
P_HTM[4346]="*Atha kho, ānanda, gavesissa upāsakassa etadahosi:**Then Gavesī thought:*";
P_HTM[4347]="*‘ahaṃ kho imesaṃ pañcannaṃ upāsakasatānaṃ bahūpakāro pubbaṅgamo samādapetā, ahañcamhi sīlesu aparipūrakārī, imāni ca pañca upāsakasatāni sīlesu aparipūrakārino.**‘I’m the helper, leader, and adviser of these five hundred lay followers, yet neither I nor they have fulfilled the precepts.*";
P_HTM[4348]="*Iccetaṃ samasamaṃ, natthi kiñci atirekaṃ;**We’re the same, I’m in no way better.*";
P_HTM[4349]="*handāhaṃ atirekāyā’ti.**So let me do better.’*";
P_HTM[4350]="*Atha kho, ānanda, gavesī upāsako yena tāni pañca upāsakasatāni tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā tāni pañca upāsakasatāni etadavoca:**Then Gavesī went to those five hundred lay followers and said to them:*";
P_HTM[4351]="*‘ajjatagge maṃ āyasmanto sīlesu paripūrakāriṃ dhārethā’ti.**‘From this day forth may the venerables remember me as one who has fulfilled the precepts.’*";
P_HTM[4352]="*Atha kho, ānanda, tesaṃ pañcannaṃ upāsakasatānaṃ etadahosi:**Then those five hundred lay followers thought:*";
P_HTM[4353]="*‘ayyo kho gavesī amhākaṃ bahūpakāro pubbaṅgamo samādapetā.**‘The venerable Gavesī is our helper, leader, and adviser,*";
P_HTM[4354]="*Ayyo hi nāma gavesī sīlesu paripūrakārī bhavissati.**and now he will fulfill the precepts.*";
P_HTM[4355]="*Kimaṅgaṃ pana mayan’ti.**Why don’t we do the same?’*";
P_HTM[4356]="*Atha kho, ānanda, tāni pañca upāsakasatāni yena gavesī upāsako tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā gavesiṃ upāsakaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then those five hundred lay followers went to Gavesī and said to him:*";
P_HTM[4357]="*‘ajjatagge ayyo gavesī imānipi pañca upāsakasatāni sīlesu paripūrakārino dhāretū’ti.**‘From this day forth may Venerable Gavesī remember these five hundred lay followers as having fulfilled the precepts.’*";
P_HTM[4358]="*Atha kho, ānanda, gavesissa upāsakassa etadahosi:**Then Gavesī thought:*";
P_HTM[4359]="*‘ahaṃ kho imesaṃ pañcannaṃ upāsakasatānaṃ bahūpakāro pubbaṅgamo samādapetā, ahañcamhi sīlesu paripūrakārī, imānipi pañca upāsakasatāni sīlesu paripūrakārino.**‘I’m the helper, leader, and adviser of these five hundred lay followers, and both I and they have fulfilled the precepts.*";
P_HTM[4360]="*Iccetaṃ samasamaṃ, natthi kiñci atirekaṃ;**We’re the same, I’m in no way better.*";
P_HTM[4361]="*handāhaṃ atirekāyā’ti.**So let me do better.’*";
P_HTM[4362]="*Atha kho, ānanda, gavesī upāsako yena tāni pañca upāsakasatāni tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā tāni pañca upāsakasatāni etadavoca:**Then Gavesī went to those five hundred lay followers and said to them:*";
P_HTM[4363]="*‘ajjatagge maṃ āyasmanto brahmacāriṃ dhāretha ārācāriṃ virataṃ methunā gāmadhammā’ti.**‘From this day forth may the venerables remember me as one who is celibate, set apart, avoiding the common practice of sex.’*";
P_HTM[4364]="*Atha kho, ānanda, tesaṃ pañcannaṃ upāsakasatānaṃ etadahosi:**Then those five hundred lay followers did the same. …*";
P_HTM[4365]="*‘ayyo kho gavesī amhākaṃ bahūpakāro pubbaṅgamo samādapetā.* **";
P_HTM[4366]="*Ayyo hi nāma gavesī brahmacārī bhavissati ārācārī virato methunā gāmadhammā.* **";
P_HTM[4367]="*Kimaṅgaṃ pana mayan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4368]="*Atha kho, ānanda, tāni pañca upāsakasatāni yena gavesī upāsako tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā gavesiṃ upāsakaṃ etadavocuṃ:* **";
P_HTM[4369]="*‘ajjatagge ayyo gavesī imānipi pañca upāsakasatāni brahmacārino dhāretu ārācārino viratā methunā gāmadhammā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4370]="*Atha kho, ānanda, gavesissa upāsakassa etadahosi:**Then Gavesī thought:*";
P_HTM[4371]="*‘ahaṃ kho imesaṃ pañcannaṃ upāsakasatānaṃ bahūpakāro pubbaṅgamo samādapetā.**‘These five hundred lay followers …*";
P_HTM[4372]="*Ahañcamhi sīlesu paripūrakārī.* **";
P_HTM[4373]="*Imānipi pañca upāsakasatāni sīlesu paripūrakārino.* **";
P_HTM[4374]="*Ahañcamhi brahmacārī ārācārī virato methunā gāmadhammā.* **";
P_HTM[4375]="*Imānipi pañca upāsakasatāni brahmacārino ārācārino viratā methunā gāmadhammā.**are celibate, set apart, avoiding the common practice of sex.*";
P_HTM[4376]="*Iccetaṃ samasamaṃ, natthi kiñci atirekaṃ;**We’re the same, I’m in no way better.*";
P_HTM[4377]="*handāhaṃ atirekāyā’ti.**So let me do better.’*";
P_HTM[4378]="*Atha kho, ānanda, gavesī upāsako yena tāni pañca upāsakasatāni tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā tāni pañca upāsakasatāni etadavoca:**Then Gavesī went to those five hundred lay followers and said to them:*";
P_HTM[4379]="*‘ajjatagge maṃ āyasmanto ekabhattikaṃ dhāretha rattūparataṃ virataṃ vikālabhojanā’ti.**‘From this day forth may the venerables remember me as one who eats in one part of the day, abstaining from eating at night, and from food at the wrong time.’*";
P_HTM[4380]="*Atha kho, ānanda, tesaṃ pañcannaṃ upāsakasatānaṃ etadahosi:**Then those five hundred lay followers did the same. …*";
P_HTM[4381]="*‘ayyo kho gavesī bahūpakāro pubbaṅgamo samādapetā.* **";
P_HTM[4382]="*Ayyo hi nāma gavesī ekabhattiko bhavissati rattūparato virato vikālabhojanā.* **";
P_HTM[4383]="*Kimaṅgaṃ pana mayan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4384]="*Atha kho, ānanda, tāni pañca upāsakasatāni yena gavesī upāsako tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā gavesiṃ upāsakaṃ etadavocuṃ:* **";
P_HTM[4385]="*‘ajjatagge ayyo gavesī imānipi pañca upāsakasatāni ekabhattike dhāretu rattūparate virate vikālabhojanā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4386]="*Atha kho, ānanda, gavesissa upāsakassa etadahosi:**Then Gavesī thought:*";
P_HTM[4387]="*‘ahaṃ kho imesaṃ pañcannaṃ upāsakasatānaṃ bahūpakāro pubbaṅgamo samādapetā.**‘These five hundred lay followers …*";
P_HTM[4388]="*Ahañcamhi sīlesu paripūrakārī.* **";
P_HTM[4389]="*Imānipi pañca upāsakasatāni sīlesu paripūrakārino.* **";
P_HTM[4390]="*Ahañcamhi brahmacārī ārācārī virato methunā gāmadhammā.* **";
P_HTM[4391]="*Imānipi pañca upāsakasatāni brahmacārino ārācārino viratā methunā gāmadhammā.* **";
P_HTM[4392]="*Ahañcamhi ekabhattiko rattūparato virato vikālabhojanā.* **";
P_HTM[4393]="*Imānipi pañca upāsakasatāni ekabhattikā rattūparatā viratā vikālabhojanā.**eat in one part of the day, abstaining from eating at night, and food at the wrong time.*";
P_HTM[4394]="*Iccetaṃ samasamaṃ, natthi kiñci atirekaṃ;**We’re the same, I’m in no way better.*";
P_HTM[4395]="*handāhaṃ atirekāyā’ti.**So let me do better.’*";
P_HTM[4396]="*Atha kho, ānanda, gavesī upāsako yena kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ etadavoca:**Then the lay follower Gavesī went up to the blessed one Kassapa, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha and said to him:*";
P_HTM[4397]="*‘labheyyāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ labheyyaṃ upasampadan’ti.**‘Sir, may I receive the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence?’*";
P_HTM[4398]="*Alattha kho, ānanda, gavesī upāsako kassapassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa santike pabbajjaṃ, alattha upasampadaṃ.**And he received the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence.*";
P_HTM[4399]="*Acirūpasampanno kho panānanda, gavesī bhikkhu eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi.**Not long after his ordination, the mendicant Gavesī, living alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, realized the supreme culmination of the spiritual path in this very life. He lived having achieved with his own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[4400]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti abbhaññāsi.**He understood: ‘Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of existence.’*";
P_HTM[4401]="*Aññataro ca panānanda, gavesī bhikkhu arahataṃ ahosi.**And the mendicant Gavesī became one of the perfected.*";
P_HTM[4402]="*Atha kho, ānanda, tesaṃ pañcannaṃ upāsakasatānaṃ etadahosi:**Then those five hundred lay followers thought:*";
P_HTM[4403]="*‘ayyo kho gavesī amhākaṃ bahūpakāro pubbaṅgamo samādapetā.**‘Venerable Gavesī is our helper, leader, and adviser,*";
P_HTM[4404]="*Ayyo hi nāma gavesī kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajissati.**He has shaved off his hair and beard, dressed in ocher robes, and gone forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[4405]="*Kimaṅgaṃ pana mayan’ti.**Why don’t we do the same?’*";
P_HTM[4406]="*Atha kho, ānanda, tāni pañca upāsakasatāni yena kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then those five hundred lay followers went up to the blessed one Kassapa, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha and said to him:*";
P_HTM[4407]="*‘labheyyāma mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, labheyyāma upasampadan’ti.**‘Sir, may we receive the going forth and ordination in the Buddha’s presence?’*";
P_HTM[4408]="*Alabhiṃsu kho, ānanda, tāni pañca upāsakasatāni kassapassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa santike pabbajjaṃ, alabhiṃsu upasampadaṃ.**And they did receive the going forth and ordination in the Buddha’s presence.*";
P_HTM[4409]="*Atha kho, ānanda, gavesissa bhikkhuno etadahosi:**Then the mendicant Gavesī thought:*";
P_HTM[4410]="*‘ahaṃ kho imassa anuttarassa vimuttisukhassa nikāmalābhī homi akicchalābhī akasiralābhī.**‘I get the supreme bliss of freedom whenever I want, without trouble or difficulty.*";
P_HTM[4411]="*Aho vatimānipi pañca bhikkhusatāni imassa anuttarassa vimuttisukhassa nikāmalābhino assu akicchalābhino akasiralābhino’ti.**Oh, may these five hundred mendicants do the same!’*";
P_HTM[4412]="*Atha kho, ānanda, tāni pañca bhikkhusatāni vūpakaṭṭhā appamattā ātāpino pahitattā viharantā nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—**Then those five hundred mendicants, living alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, soon realized the supreme culmination of the spiritual path in this very life. They lived having achieved with their own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[4413]="*brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihariṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[4414]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti abbhaññiṃsu.**They understood: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’*";
P_HTM[4415]="*Iti kho, ānanda, tāni pañca bhikkhusatāni gavesīpamukhāni uttaruttari paṇītapaṇītaṃ vāyamamānā anuttaraṃ vimuttiṃ sacchākaṃsu.**And so, Ānanda, those five hundred mendicants headed by Gavesī, trying to go higher and higher, better and better, realized the supreme bliss of freedom.*";
P_HTM[4416]="*Tasmātiha, ānanda, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**So you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[4417]="*‘uttaruttari paṇītapaṇītaṃ vāyamamānā anuttaraṃ vimuttiṃ sacchikarissāmā’ti.**‘Trying to go higher and higher, better and better, we will realize the supreme bliss of freedom.’*";
P_HTM[4418]="*Evañhi vo, ānanda, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[4419]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4420]="*Upāsakavaggo tatiyo.* **";
P_HTM[4421]="*Sārajjaṃ visārado nirayaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[4422]="*Veraṃ caṇḍālapañcamaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4423]="*Pīti vaṇijjā rājāno,* **";
P_HTM[4424]="*Gihī ceva gavesināti.* **";
P_HTM[4425]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**Wilderness Dwellers*";
P_HTM[4426]="*1. Āraññikasuttaṃ**Wilderness Dwellers*";
P_HTM[4427]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, āraññikā.**“Mendicants, there are these five kinds of wilderness dwellers.*";
P_HTM[4428]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4429]="*Mandattā momūhattā āraññiko hoti, pāpiccho icchāpakato āraññiko hoti, ummādā cittakkhepā āraññiko hoti, vaṇṇitaṃ buddhehi buddhasāvakehīti āraññiko hoti, appicchataṃyeva nissāya santuṭṭhiṃyeva nissāya sallekhaṃyeva nissāya pavivekaṃyeva nissāya idamatthitaṃyeva nissāya āraññiko hoti.**A person may be wilderness dweller because of stupidity and folly. Or because of wicked desires, being naturally full of desires. Or because of madness and mental disorder. Or because it is praised by the Buddhas and their disciples. Or for the sake of having few wishes, for the sake of contentment, self-effacement, seclusion, and simplicity.*";
P_HTM[4430]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca āraññikā.**These are the five kinds of wilderness dwellers.*";
P_HTM[4431]="*Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ āraññikānaṃ yvāyaṃ āraññiko appicchataṃyeva nissāya santuṭṭhiṃyeva nissāya sallekhaṃyeva nissāya pavivekaṃyeva nissāya idamatthitaṃyeva nissāya āraññiko hoti, ayaṃ imesaṃ pañcannaṃ āraññikānaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca mokkho ca uttamo ca pavaro ca.**But the person who dwells in the wilderness for the sake of having few wishes is the foremost, best, chief, highest, and finest of the five.*";
P_HTM[4432]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gavā khīraṃ, khīramhā dadhi, dadhimhā navanītaṃ, navanītamhā sappi, sappimhā sappimaṇḍo, sappimaṇḍo tattha aggamakkhāyati;**From a cow comes milk, from milk comes curds, from curds come butter, from butter comes ghee, and from ghee comes cream of ghee. And the cream of ghee is said to be the best of these.*";
P_HTM[4433]="*evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, imesaṃ pañcannaṃ āraññikānaṃ yvāyaṃ āraññiko appicchataṃyeva nissāya santuṭṭhiṃyeva nissāya sallekhaṃyeva nissāya pavivekaṃyeva nissāya idamatthitaṃyeva nissāya āraññiko hoti, ayaṃ imesaṃ pañcannaṃ āraññikānaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca mokkho ca uttamo ca pavaro cā”ti.**In the same way, the person who dwells in the wilderness for the sake of having few wishes is the foremost, best, chief, highest, and finest of the five.”*";
P_HTM[4434]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4435]="*2. Cīvarasuttaṃ**Robes*";
P_HTM[4436]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, paṃsukūlikā.**“Mendicants there are these five kinds of people who wear rag robes.*";
P_HTM[4437]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4438]="*Mandattā momūhattā paṃsukūliko hoti … pe … idamatthitaṃyeva nissāya paṃsukūliko hoti.**A person may wear rag robes because of stupidity … bad desires … madness … because it is praised by the Buddhas … or for the sake of having few wishes …*";
P_HTM[4439]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca paṃsukūlikā”ti.**These are the five kinds of people who wear rag robes.”*";
P_HTM[4440]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4441]="*3. Rukkhamūlikasuttaṃ**Dwelling at the Root of a Tree*";
P_HTM[4442]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, rukkhamūlikā.**“Mendicants, there are these five kinds of people who dwell at the root of a tree.*";
P_HTM[4443]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4444]="*Mandattā momūhattā rukkhamūliko hoti … pe … idamatthitaṃyeva nissāya rukkhamūliko hoti.**A person may dwell at the root of a tree because of stupidity … bad desires … madness … because it is praised by the Buddhas … or for the sake of having few wishes …*";
P_HTM[4445]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca rukkhamūlikā”ti.**These are the five kinds of people who dwell at the root of a tree.”*";
P_HTM[4446]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4447]="*4. Sosānikasuttaṃ**Charnel Ground Dwellers*";
P_HTM[4448]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, sosānikā.**“Mendicants, there are these five kinds of people who dwell in a charnel ground.*";
P_HTM[4449]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4450]="*Mandattā momūhattā sosāniko hoti … pe … idamatthitaṃyeva nissāya sosāniko hoti.**A person may dwell in a charnel ground because of stupidity … bad desires … madness … because it is praised by the Buddhas … or for the sake of having few wishes …*";
P_HTM[4451]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca sosānikā”ti.**These are the five kinds of people who dwell in a charnel ground.”*";
P_HTM[4452]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4453]="*5. Abbhokāsikasuttaṃ**Open Air Dwellers*";
P_HTM[4454]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, abbhokāsikā … pe ….**“There are these five kinds of people who dwell in the open air. …”*";
P_HTM[4455]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4456]="*6. Nesajjikasuttaṃ**Those Who Never Lie Down*";
P_HTM[4457]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, nesajjikā … pe ….**“There are these five kinds of people who never lie down. …”*";
P_HTM[4458]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4459]="*7. Yathāsanthatikasuttaṃ**Those Who Sleep Wherever a Mat is Laid*";
P_HTM[4460]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, yathāsanthatikā … pe ….**“There are these five kinds of people who sleep wherever they lay their mat. …”*";
P_HTM[4461]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4462]="*8. Ekāsanikasuttaṃ**Those Who Eat in One Sitting*";
P_HTM[4463]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ekāsanikā … pe ….**“There are these five kinds of people who eat in one sitting per day. …”*";
P_HTM[4464]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4465]="*9. Khalupacchābhattikasuttaṃ**Refusers of Late Food*";
P_HTM[4466]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, khalupacchābhattikā … pe ….**“There are these five kinds of people who refuse to accept food offered after the meal has begun. …”*";
P_HTM[4467]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4468]="*10. Pattapiṇḍikasuttaṃ**Those Who Eat Only From the Almsbowl*";
P_HTM[4469]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, pattapiṇḍikā.**“Mendicants, there are these five kinds of people who eat only from the almsbowl.*";
P_HTM[4470]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4471]="*Mandattā momūhattā pattapiṇḍiko hoti, pāpiccho icchāpakato pattapiṇḍiko hoti, ummādā cittakkhepā pattapiṇḍiko hoti, ‘vaṇṇitaṃ buddhehi buddhasāvakehī’ti pattapiṇḍiko hoti, appicchataṃyeva nissāya santuṭṭhiṃyeva nissāya sallekhaṃyeva nissāya pavivekaṃyeva nissāya idamatthitaṃyeva nissāya pattapiṇḍiko hoti.**A person may eat only from the almsbowl because of stupidity and folly. Or because of wicked desires, being naturally full of desires. Or because of madness and mental disorder. Or because it is praised by the Buddhas and their disciples. Or for the sake of having few wishes, for the sake of contentment, self-effacement, seclusion, and simplicity.*";
P_HTM[4472]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca pattapiṇḍikā.**These are the five kinds of people who eat only from the almsbowl.*";
P_HTM[4473]="*Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ pattapiṇḍikānaṃ yvāyaṃ pattapiṇḍiko appicchataṃyeva nissāya santuṭṭhiṃyeva nissāya sallekhaṃyeva nissāya pavivekaṃyeva nissāya idamatthitaṃyeva nissāya pattapiṇḍiko hoti, ayaṃ imesaṃ pañcannaṃ pattapiṇḍikānaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca mokkho ca uttamo ca pavaro ca.**But the person who eats only from the almsbowl for the sake of having few wishes is the foremost, best, chief, highest, and finest of the five.*";
P_HTM[4474]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gavā khīraṃ, khīramhā dadhi, dadhimhā navanītaṃ, navanītamhā sappi, sappimhā sappimaṇḍo, sappimaṇḍo tattha aggamakkhāyati;**From a cow comes milk, from milk comes curds, from curds come butter, from butter comes ghee, and from ghee comes cream of ghee. And the cream of ghee is said to be the best of these.*";
P_HTM[4475]="*evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, imesaṃ pañcannaṃ pattapiṇḍikānaṃ yvāyaṃ pattapiṇḍiko appicchataṃyeva nissāya santuṭṭhiṃyeva nissāya sallekhaṃyeva nissāya pavivekaṃyeva nissāya idamatthitaṃyeva nissāya pattapiṇḍiko hoti, ayaṃ imesaṃ pañcannaṃ pattapiṇḍikānaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca mokkho ca uttamo ca pavaro cā”ti.**In the same way, the person who eats only from the almsbowl for the sake of having few wishes is the foremost, best, chief, highest, and finest of the five.”*";
P_HTM[4476]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4477]="*Araññavaggo catuttho.* **";
P_HTM[4478]="*Araññaṃ cīvaraṃ rukkha,* **";
P_HTM[4479]="*Susānaṃ abbhokāsikaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4480]="*Nesajjaṃ santhataṃ ekāsanikaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[4481]="*Khalupacchāpiṇḍikena cāti.* **";
P_HTM[4482]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**Brahmins*";
P_HTM[4483]="*1. Soṇasuttaṃ**Dogs*";
P_HTM[4484]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, porāṇā brāhmaṇadhammā etarahi sunakhesu sandissanti, no brāhmaṇesu.**“Mendicants, these five traditions of the brahmins are seen these days among dogs, but not among brahmins.*";
P_HTM[4485]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4486]="*Pubbe sudaṃ, bhikkhave, brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇiṃyeva gacchanti, no abrāhmaṇiṃ.**In the past brahmins had sex only with brahmin women, not with others.*";
P_HTM[4487]="*Etarahi, bhikkhave, brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇimpi gacchanti, abrāhmaṇimpi gacchanti.**These days brahmins have sex with both brahmin women and others.*";
P_HTM[4488]="*Etarahi, bhikkhave, sunakhā sunakhiṃyeva gacchanti, no asunakhiṃ.**But these days dogs have sex only with female dogs, not with other species.*";
P_HTM[4489]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo porāṇo brāhmaṇadhammo etarahi sunakhesu sandissati, no brāhmaṇesu.**This is the first tradition of the brahmins seen these days among dogs, but not among brahmins.*";
P_HTM[4490]="*Pubbe sudaṃ, bhikkhave, brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇiṃ utuniṃyeva gacchanti, no anutuniṃ.**In the past brahmins had sex only with brahmin women in the fertile half of the month that starts with menstruation, not at other times.*";
P_HTM[4491]="*Etarahi, bhikkhave, brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇiṃ utunimpi gacchanti, anutunimpi gacchanti.**These days brahmins have sex with brahmin women both in the fertile half of the month and at other times.*";
P_HTM[4492]="*Etarahi, bhikkhave, sunakhā sunakhiṃ utuniṃyeva gacchanti, no anutuniṃ.**But these days dogs have sex only with female dogs when they are in heat, not at other times.*";
P_HTM[4493]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo porāṇo brāhmaṇadhammo etarahi sunakhesu sandissati, no brāhmaṇesu.**This is the second tradition of the brahmins seen these days among dogs, but not among brahmins.*";
P_HTM[4494]="*Pubbe sudaṃ, bhikkhave, brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇiṃ neva kiṇanti no vikkiṇanti, sampiyeneva saṃvāsaṃ sambandhāya sampavattenti.**In the past brahmins neither bought nor sold brahmin women. They lived together because they loved each other and wanted their family line to continue.*";
P_HTM[4495]="*Etarahi, bhikkhave, brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇiṃ kiṇantipi vikkiṇantipi, sampiyenapi saṃvāsaṃ sambandhāya sampavattenti.**These days brahmins both buy and sell brahmin women. They live together whether they love each other or not and they want their family line to continue.*";
P_HTM[4496]="*Etarahi, bhikkhave, sunakhā sunakhiṃ neva kiṇanti no vikkiṇanti, sampiyeneva saṃvāsaṃ sambandhāya sampavattenti.**But these days dogs neither buy nor sell female dogs. They live together because they’re attracted to each other and want their family line to continue.*";
P_HTM[4497]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo porāṇo brāhmaṇadhammo etarahi sunakhesu sandissati, no brāhmaṇesu.**This is the third tradition of the brahmins seen these days among dogs, but not among brahmins.*";
P_HTM[4498]="*Pubbe sudaṃ, bhikkhave, brāhmaṇā na sannidhiṃ karonti dhanassapi dhaññassapi rajatassapi jātarūpassapi.**In the past brahmins did not store up money, grain, silver, or gold.*";
P_HTM[4499]="*Etarahi, bhikkhave, brāhmaṇā sannidhiṃ karonti dhanassapi dhaññassapi rajatassapi jātarūpassapi.**These days brahmins do store up money, grain, silver, and gold.*";
P_HTM[4500]="*Etarahi, bhikkhave, sunakhā na sannidhiṃ karonti dhanassapi dhaññassapi rajatassapi jātarūpassapi.**But these days dogs don’t store up money, grain, silver, or gold.*";
P_HTM[4501]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho porāṇo brāhmaṇadhammo etarahi sunakhesu sandissati, no brāhmaṇesu.**This is the fourth tradition of the brahmins seen these days among dogs, but not among brahmins.*";
P_HTM[4502]="*Pubbe sudaṃ, bhikkhave, brāhmaṇā sāyaṃ sāyamāsāya pāto pātarāsāya bhikkhaṃ pariyesanti.**In the past brahmins went looking for almsfood for dinner in the evening, and for breakfast in the morning.*";
P_HTM[4503]="*Etarahi, bhikkhave, brāhmaṇā yāvadatthaṃ udarāvadehakaṃ bhuñjitvā avasesaṃ ādāya pakkamanti.**These days brahmins eat as much as they like until their bellies are full, then take away the leftovers.*";
P_HTM[4504]="*Etarahi, bhikkhave, sunakhā sāyaṃ sāyamāsāya pāto pātarāsāya bhikkhaṃ pariyesanti.**But these days dogs go looking for dinner in the evening, and for breakfast in the morning.*";
P_HTM[4505]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo porāṇo brāhmaṇadhammo etarahi sunakhesu sandissati, no brāhmaṇesu.**This is the fifth tradition of the brahmins seen these days among dogs, but not among brahmins.*";
P_HTM[4506]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca porāṇā brāhmaṇadhammā etarahi sunakhesu sandissanti, no brāhmaṇesū”ti.**These five traditions of the brahmins are seen these days among dogs, but not among brahmins.”*";
P_HTM[4507]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4508]="*2. Doṇabrāhmaṇasuttaṃ**With the Brahmin Doṇa*";
P_HTM[4509]="*Atha kho doṇo brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then Doṇa the brahmin went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[4510]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho doṇo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, Doṇa sat down to one side, and said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[4511]="*“Sutaṃ metaṃ, bho gotama:**“Master Gotama, I have heard that*";
P_HTM[4512]="*‘na samaṇo gotamo brāhmaṇe jiṇṇe vuḍḍhe mahallake addhagate vayoanuppatte abhivādeti vā paccuṭṭheti vā āsanena vā nimantetī’ti.**the ascetic Gotama doesn’t bow to old brahmins, the elderly and senior, who are advanced in years and have reached the final stage of life; nor does he rise in their presence or offer them a seat.*";
P_HTM[4513]="*Tayidaṃ, bho gotama, tatheva.**And this is indeed the case,*";
P_HTM[4514]="*Na hi bhavaṃ gotamo brāhmaṇe jiṇṇe vuḍḍhe mahallake addhagate vayoanuppatte abhivādeti vā paccuṭṭheti vā āsanena vā nimanteti.**for Master Gotama does not bow to old brahmins, elderly and senior, who are advanced in years and have reached the final stage of life; nor does he rise in their presence or offer them a seat.*";
P_HTM[4515]="*Tayidaṃ, bho gotama, na sampannamevā”ti.**This is not appropriate, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[4516]="*“Tvampi no, doṇa, brāhmaṇo paṭijānāsī”ti?**“Doṇa, do you too claim to be a brahmin?”*";
P_HTM[4517]="*“Yañhi taṃ, bho gotama, sammā vadamāno vadeyya:**“Master Gotama, if anyone should be rightly called*";
P_HTM[4518]="*‘brāhmaṇo ubhato sujāto—**a brahmin, it’s me.*";
P_HTM[4519]="*mātito ca pitito ca, saṃsuddhagahaṇiko, yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena, ajjhāyako mantadharo, tiṇṇaṃ vedānaṃ pāragū sanighaṇḍukeṭubhānaṃ sākkharappabhedānaṃ itihāsapañcamānaṃ, padako veyyākaraṇo lokāyatamahāpurisalakkhaṇesu anavayo’ti, mameva taṃ, bho gotama, sammā vadamāno vadeyya.* **";
P_HTM[4520]="*Ahañhi, bho gotama, brāhmaṇo ubhato sujāto—* **";
P_HTM[4521]="*mātito ca pitito ca, saṃsuddhagahaṇiko, yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena, ajjhāyako mantadharo, tiṇṇaṃ vedānaṃ pāragū sanighaṇḍukeṭubhānaṃ sākkharappabhedānaṃ itihāsapañcamānaṃ, padako veyyākaraṇo lokāyatamahāpurisalakkhaṇesu anavayo”ti.**For I am well born on both my mother’s and father’s side, of pure descent, irrefutable and impeccable in questions of ancestry back to the seventh paternal generation. I recite and remember the hymns, and have mastered the three Vedas, together with their vocabularies, ritual, phonology and etymology, and the testament as fifth. I know philology and grammar, and am well versed in cosmology and the marks of a great man.”*";
P_HTM[4522]="*“Ye kho te, doṇa, brāhmaṇānaṃ pubbakā isayo mantānaṃ kattāro mantānaṃ pavattāro, yesamidaṃ etarahi brāhmaṇā porāṇaṃ mantapadaṃ gītaṃ pavuttaṃ samihitaṃ tadanugāyanti tadanubhāsanti bhāsitamanubhāsanti sajjhāyitamanusajjhāyanti vācitamanuvācenti, seyyathidaṃ—aṭṭhako, vāmako, vāmadevo, vessāmitto, yamadaggi, aṅgīraso, bhāradvājo, vāseṭṭho, kassapo, bhagu;**“Doṇa, the brahmin hermits of the past were Aṭṭhaka, Vāmaka, Vāmadeva, Vessāmitta, Yamadaggi, Aṅgīrasa, Bhāradvāja, Vāseṭṭha, Kassapa, and Bhagu. They were the authors and propagators of the hymns, whose hymnal was sung and propagated and compiled in ancient times. These days, brahmins continue to sing and chant it. They continue chanting what was chanted, reciting what was recited, and teaching what was taught.*";
P_HTM[4523]="*tyāssume pañca brāhmaṇe paññāpenti—**Those seers described five kinds of brahmins.*";
P_HTM[4524]="*brahmasamaṃ, devasamaṃ, mariyādaṃ, sambhinnamariyādaṃ, brāhmaṇacaṇḍālaṃyeva pañcamaṃ.**A brahmin who is equal to Brahmā, one who is equal to a god, one who toes the line, one who crosses the line, and the fifth is a brahmin outcaste.*";
P_HTM[4525]="*Tesaṃ tvaṃ doṇa, katamo”ti?**Which one of these are you, Doṇa?”*";
P_HTM[4526]="*“Na kho mayaṃ, bho gotama, pañca brāhmaṇe jānāma, atha kho mayaṃ brāhmaṇātveva jānāma.**“Master Gotama, we don’t know about these five kinds of brahmins. We just know the word ‘brahmin’.*";
P_HTM[4527]="*Sādhu me bhavaṃ gotamo tathā dhammaṃ desetu yathā ahaṃ ime pañca brāhmaṇe jāneyyan”ti.**Master Gotama, please teach me this matter so I can learn about these five brahmins.”*";
P_HTM[4528]="*“Tena hi, brāhmaṇa, suṇohhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, brahmin, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[4529]="*“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho doṇo brāhmaṇo bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes sir,” Doṇa replied.*";
P_HTM[4530]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[4531]="*“Kathañca, doṇa, brāhmaṇo brahmasamo hoti?**“Doṇa, how is a brahmin equal to Brahmā?*";
P_HTM[4532]="*Idha, doṇa, brāhmaṇo ubhato sujāto hoti—**It’s when a brahmin is well born on both the mother’s and the father’s sides, coming from a clean womb back to the seventh paternal generation, incontestable and irreproachable in discussions about ancestry.*";
P_HTM[4533]="*mātito ca pitito ca, saṃsuddhagahaṇiko, yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena.* **";
P_HTM[4534]="*So aṭṭhacattālīsavassāni komārabrahmacariyaṃ carati mante adhīyamāno.**For forty-eight years he lives the spiritual life, from childhood, studying the hymns.*";
P_HTM[4535]="*Aṭṭhacattālīsavassāni komārabrahmacariyaṃ caritvā mante adhīyitvā ācariyassa ācariyadhanaṃ pariyesati dhammeneva, no adhammena.**Then he seeks a fee for his teacher, but only by legitimate means, not illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[4536]="*Tattha ca, doṇa, ko dhammo?**In this context, Doṇa, what is legitimate?*";
P_HTM[4537]="*Neva kasiyā na vaṇijjāya na gorakkhena na issatthena na rājaporisena na sippaññatarena, kevalaṃ bhikkhācariyāya kapālaṃ anatimaññamāno.**Not by farming, trade, raising cattle, archery, government service, or one of the professions, but solely by living on alms, not scorning the alms bowl.*";
P_HTM[4538]="*So ācariyassa ācariyadhanaṃ niyyādetvā kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati.**Having offered the fee to his teacher, he shaves off his hair and beard, dresses in ocher robes, and goes forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[4539]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ tathā tatiyaṃ tathā catutthaṃ, iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena pharitvā viharati.**Then they meditate spreading a heart full of love to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of love to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[4540]="*Karuṇā … pe …**They meditate spreading a heart full of compassion …*";
P_HTM[4541]="*muditā …**rejoicing …*";
P_HTM[4542]="*upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ tathā tatiyaṃ tathā catutthaṃ, iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena pharitvā viharati.**equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will.*";
P_HTM[4543]="*So ime cattāro brahmavihāre bhāvetvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ brahmalokaṃ upapajjati.**Having developed these four Brahmā meditations, when the body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a Brahmā realm.*";
P_HTM[4544]="*Evaṃ kho, doṇa, brāhmaṇo brahmasamo hoti. (1)**That’s how a brahmin is equal to Brahmā.*";
P_HTM[4545]="*Kathañca, doṇa, brāhmaṇo devasamo hoti?**And how is a brahmin equal to a god?*";
P_HTM[4546]="*Idha, doṇa, brāhmaṇo ubhato sujāto hoti—**It’s when a brahmin is well born on both the mother’s and the father’s sides …*";
P_HTM[4547]="*mātito ca pitito ca, saṃsuddhagahaṇiko, yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena.* **";
P_HTM[4548]="*So aṭṭhacattālīsavassāni komārabrahmacariyaṃ carati mante adhīyamāno.* **";
P_HTM[4549]="*Aṭṭhacattālīsavassāni komārabrahmacariyaṃ caritvā mante adhīyitvā ācariyassa ācariyadhanaṃ pariyesati dhammeneva, no adhammena.* **";
P_HTM[4550]="*Tattha ca, doṇa, ko dhammo?* **";
P_HTM[4551]="*Neva kasiyā na vaṇijjāya na gorakkhena na issatthena na rājaporisena na sippaññatarena, kevalaṃ bhikkhācariyāya kapālaṃ anatimaññamāno.* **";
P_HTM[4552]="*So ācariyassa ācariyadhanaṃ niyyādetvā dāraṃ pariyesati dhammeneva, no adhammena.**Having offered the fee to his teacher, he seeks a wife, but only by legitimate means, not illegitimate.*";
P_HTM[4553]="*Tattha ca, doṇa, ko dhammo?**In this context, Doṇa, what is legitimate?*";
P_HTM[4554]="*Neva kayena na vikkayena, brāhmaṇiṃyeva udakūpassaṭṭhaṃ.**Not by buying or selling, he only accepts a brahmin woman by the pouring of water.*";
P_HTM[4555]="*So brāhmaṇiṃyeva gacchati, na khattiyiṃ na vessiṃ na suddiṃ na caṇḍāliṃ na nesādiṃ na veniṃ na rathakāriṃ na pukkusiṃ gacchati, na gabbhiniṃ gacchati, na pāyamānaṃ gacchati, na anutuniṃ gacchati.**He has sex only with a brahmin woman. He does not have sex with a woman from a caste of aristocrats, merchants, workers, outcastes, hunters, bamboo workers, chariot-makers, or waste-collectors. Nor does he have sex with women who are pregnant, breastfeeding, or outside the fertile half of the month that starts with menstruation.*";
P_HTM[4556]="*Kasmā ca, doṇa, brāhmaṇo na gabbhiniṃ gacchati?**And why does the brahmin not have sex with a pregnant woman?*";
P_HTM[4557]="*Sace, doṇa, brāhmaṇo gabbhiniṃ gacchati, atimīḷhajo nāma so hoti māṇavako vā māṇavikā vā.**If a brahmin had sex with a pregnant woman, the boy or girl would be born in too much filth.*";
P_HTM[4558]="*Tasmā, doṇa, brāhmaṇo na gabbhiniṃ gacchati.**That’s why the brahmin doesn’t have sex with a pregnant woman.*";
P_HTM[4559]="*Kasmā ca, doṇa, brāhmaṇo na pāyamānaṃ gacchati?**And why does the brahmin not have sex with a breastfeeding woman?*";
P_HTM[4560]="*Sace, doṇa, brāhmaṇo pāyamānaṃ gacchati, asucipaṭipīḷito nāma so hoti māṇavako vā māṇavikā vā.**If a brahmin had sex with a breastfeeding woman, the boy or girl would drink back the semen.*";
P_HTM[4561]="*Tasmā, doṇa, brāhmaṇo na pāyamānaṃ gacchati.**That’s why the brahmin doesn’t have sex with a breastfeeding woman.*";
P_HTM[4562]="*Tassa sā hoti brāhmaṇī neva kāmatthā na davatthā na ratatthā, pajatthāva brāhmaṇassa brāhmaṇī hoti.**And why does the brahmin not have sex outside the fertile half of the month that starts with menstruation? Because his brahmin wife is not there for sensual pleasure, fun, and enjoyment, but only for procreation.*";
P_HTM[4563]="*So methunaṃ uppādetvā kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati.**Having ensured his progeny through sex, he shaves off his hair and beard, dresses in ocher robes, and goes forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[4564]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno vivicceva kāmehi … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**When he has gone forth, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, he enters and remains in the first absorption … second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption.*";
P_HTM[4565]="*So ime cattāro jhāne bhāvetvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati.**Having developed these four absorptions, when the body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[4566]="*Evaṃ kho, doṇa, brāhmaṇo devasamo hoti. (2)**That’s how a brahmin is equal to god.*";
P_HTM[4567]="*Kathañca, doṇa, brāhmaṇo mariyādo hoti?**And how does a brahmin toe the line?*";
P_HTM[4568]="*Idha, doṇa, brāhmaṇo ubhato sujāto hoti—**It’s when a brahmin is well born on both the mother’s and the father’s sides …*";
P_HTM[4569]="*mātito ca pitito ca, saṃsuddhagahaṇiko, yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena.* **";
P_HTM[4570]="*So aṭṭhacattālīsavassāni komārabrahmacariyaṃ carati mante adhīyamāno.* **";
P_HTM[4571]="*Aṭṭhacattālīsavassāni komārabrahmacariyaṃ caritvā mante adhīyitvā ācariyassa ācariyadhanaṃ pariyesati dhammeneva, no adhammena.* **";
P_HTM[4572]="*Tattha ca, doṇa, ko dhammo?* **";
P_HTM[4573]="*Neva kasiyā na vaṇijjāya na gorakkhena na issatthena na rājaporisena na sippaññatarena, kevalaṃ bhikkhācariyāya kapālaṃ anatimaññamāno.* **";
P_HTM[4574]="*So ācariyassa ācariyadhanaṃ niyyādetvā dāraṃ pariyesati dhammeneva, no adhammena.* **";
P_HTM[4575]="*Tattha ca, doṇa, ko dhammo?* **";
P_HTM[4576]="*Neva kayena na vikkayena, brāhmaṇiṃyeva udakūpassaṭṭhaṃ.**Not by buying or selling, he only accepts a brahmin woman by the pouring of water.*";
P_HTM[4577]="*So brāhmaṇiṃyeva gacchati, na khattiyiṃ na vessiṃ na suddiṃ na caṇḍāliṃ na nesādiṃ na veniṃ na rathakāriṃ na pukkusiṃ gacchati, na gabbhiniṃ gacchati, na pāyamānaṃ gacchati, na anutuniṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[4578]="*Kasmā ca, doṇa, brāhmaṇo na gabbhiniṃ gacchati?* **";
P_HTM[4579]="*Sace, doṇa, brāhmaṇo gabbhiniṃ gacchati, atimīḷhajo nāma so hoti māṇavako vā māṇavikā vā.* **";
P_HTM[4580]="*Tasmā, doṇa, brāhmaṇo na gabbhiniṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[4581]="*Kasmā ca, doṇa, brāhmaṇo na pāyamānaṃ gacchati?* **";
P_HTM[4582]="*Sace, doṇa, brāhmaṇo pāyamānaṃ gacchati, asucipaṭipīḷito nāma so hoti māṇavako vā māṇavikā vā.* **";
P_HTM[4583]="*Tasmā, doṇa, brāhmaṇo na pāyamānaṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[4584]="*Tassa sā hoti brāhmaṇī neva kāmatthā na davatthā na ratatthā, pajatthāva brāhmaṇassa brāhmaṇī hoti.* **";
P_HTM[4585]="*So methunaṃ uppādetvā tameva puttassādaṃ nikāmayamāno kuṭumbaṃ ajjhāvasati, na agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati.**Having ensured his progeny through sex, his child makes him happy. Because of this attachment he stays in his family property, and does not go forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[4586]="*Yāva porāṇānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ mariyādo tattha tiṭṭhati, taṃ na vītikkamati.**As far as the line of the ancient brahmins extends, he doesn’t cross over it.*";
P_HTM[4587]="*‘Yāva porāṇānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ mariyādo tattha brāhmaṇo ṭhito taṃ na vītikkamatī’ti, kho, doṇa, tasmā brāhmaṇo mariyādoti vuccati.**That’s why he’s called a brahmin who toes the line.*";
P_HTM[4588]="*Evaṃ kho, doṇa, brāhmaṇo mariyādo hoti. (3)**That’s how a brahmin toes the line.*";
P_HTM[4589]="*Kathañca, doṇa, brāhmaṇo sambhinnamariyādo hoti?**And how does a brahmin cross the line?*";
P_HTM[4590]="*Idha, doṇa, brāhmaṇo ubhato sujāto hoti—**It’s when a brahmin is well born on both the mother’s and the father’s sides …*";
P_HTM[4591]="*mātito ca pitito ca, saṃsuddhagahaṇiko, yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena.* **";
P_HTM[4592]="*So aṭṭhacattālīsavassāni komārabrahmacariyaṃ carati mante adhīyamāno.* **";
P_HTM[4593]="*Aṭṭhacattālīsavassāni komārabrahmacariyaṃ caritvā mante adhīyitvā ācariyassa ācariyadhanaṃ pariyesati dhammeneva, no adhammena.* **";
P_HTM[4594]="*Tattha ca, doṇa, ko dhammo?* **";
P_HTM[4595]="*Neva kasiyā na vaṇijjāya na gorakkhena na issatthena na rājaporisena na sippaññatarena, kevalaṃ bhikkhācariyāya kapālaṃ anatimaññamāno.* **";
P_HTM[4596]="*So ācariyassa ācariyadhanaṃ niyyādetvā dāraṃ pariyesati dhammenapi adhammenapi kayenapi vikkayenapi brāhmaṇimpi udakūpassaṭṭhaṃ.**Having offered a fee for his teacher, he seeks a wife by both legitimate and illegitimate means. That is, by buying or selling, as well as accepting a brahmin woman by the pouring of water.*";
P_HTM[4597]="*So brāhmaṇimpi gacchati khattiyimpi gacchati vessimpi gacchati suddimpi gacchati caṇḍālimpi gacchati nesādimpi gacchati venimpi gacchati rathakārimpi gacchati pukkusimpi gacchati gabbhinimpi gacchati pāyamānampi gacchati utunimpi gacchati anutunimpi gacchati.**He has sex with a brahmin woman, as well as with a woman from a caste of aristocrats, merchants, workers, outcastes, hunters, bamboo workers, chariot-makers, or waste-collectors. And he has sex with women who are pregnant, breastfeeding, or outside the fertile half of the month that starts with menstruation.*";
P_HTM[4598]="*Tassa sā hoti brāhmaṇī kāmatthāpi davatthāpi ratatthāpi pajatthāpi brāhmaṇassa brāhmaṇī hoti.**His brahmin wife is there for sensual pleasure, fun, and enjoyment, as well as for procreation.*";
P_HTM[4599]="*Yāva porāṇānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ mariyādo tattha na tiṭṭhati, taṃ vītikkamati.**As far as the line of the ancient brahmins extends, he crosses over it.*";
P_HTM[4600]="*‘Yāva porāṇānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ mariyādo tattha brāhmaṇo na ṭhito taṃ vītikkamatī’ti kho, doṇa, tasmā brāhmaṇo sambhinnamariyādoti vuccati.**That’s why he’s called a brahmin who crosses the line.*";
P_HTM[4601]="*Evaṃ kho, doṇa, brāhmaṇo sambhinnamariyādo hoti. (4)**That’s how a brahmin crosses the line.*";
P_HTM[4602]="*Kathañca, doṇa, brāhmaṇo brāhmaṇacaṇḍālo hoti?**And how is a brahmin a brahmin outcaste?*";
P_HTM[4603]="*Idha, doṇa, brāhmaṇo ubhato sujāto hoti—**It’s when a brahmin is well born on both the mother’s and the father’s sides, coming from a clean womb back to the seventh paternal generation, incontestable and irreproachable in discussions about ancestry.*";
P_HTM[4604]="*mātito ca pitito ca, saṃsuddhagahaṇiko, yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena.* **";
P_HTM[4605]="*So aṭṭhacattālīsavassāni komārabrahmacariyaṃ carati mante adhīyamāno.**For forty-eight years he lives the spiritual life, from childhood, studying the hymns.*";
P_HTM[4606]="*Aṭṭhacattālīsavassāni komārabrahmacariyaṃ caritvā mante adhīyitvā ācariyassa ācariyadhanaṃ pariyesati dhammenapi adhammenapi**Then he seeks a fee for his teacher by legitimate means and illegitimate means.*";
P_HTM[4607]="*kasiyāpi vaṇijjāyapi gorakkhenapi issatthenapi rājaporisenapi sippaññatarenapi, kevalampi bhikkhācariyāya, kapālaṃ anatimaññamāno.**By farming, trade, raising cattle, archery, government service, or one of the professions, not solely by living on alms, not scorning the alms bowl.*";
P_HTM[4608]="*So ācariyassa ācariyadhanaṃ niyyādetvā dāraṃ pariyesati dhammenapi adhammenapi kayenapi vikkayenapi brāhmaṇimpi udakūpassaṭṭhaṃ.**Having offered a fee for his teacher, he seeks a wife by both legitimate and illegitimate means. That is, by buying or selling, as well as accepting a brahmin woman by the pouring of water.*";
P_HTM[4609]="*So brāhmaṇimpi gacchati khattiyimpi gacchati vessimpi gacchati suddimpi gacchati caṇḍālimpi gacchati nesādimpi gacchati venimpi gacchati rathakārimpi gacchati pukkusimpi gacchati gabbhinimpi gacchati pāyamānampi gacchati utunimpi gacchati anutunimpi gacchati.**He has sex with a brahmin woman, as well as with a woman from a caste of aristocrats, merchants, workers, outcastes, hunters, bamboo workers, chariot-makers, or waste-collectors. And he has sex with women who are pregnant, breastfeeding, or outside the fertile half of the month that starts with menstruation.*";
P_HTM[4610]="*Tassa sā hoti brāhmaṇī kāmatthāpi davatthāpi ratatthāpi pajatthāpi brāhmaṇassa brāhmaṇī hoti.**His brahmin wife is there for sensual pleasure, fun, and enjoyment, as well as for procreation.*";
P_HTM[4611]="*So sabbakammehi jīvikaṃ kappeti.**He earns a living by any kind of work.*";
P_HTM[4612]="*Tamenaṃ brāhmaṇā evamāhaṃsu:**The brahmins say to him,*";
P_HTM[4613]="*‘kasmā bhavaṃ brāhmaṇo paṭijānamāno sabbakammehi jīvikaṃ kappetī’ti?**‘My good man, why is it that you claim to be a brahmin, but you earn a living by any kind of work?’*";
P_HTM[4614]="*So evamāha:**He says,*";
P_HTM[4615]="*‘seyyathāpi, bho, aggi sucimpi ḍahati asucimpi ḍahati, na ca tena aggi upalippati;**‘It’s like a fire that burns both pure and filthy substances, but doesn’t become corrupted by them.*";
P_HTM[4616]="*evamevaṃ kho, bho, sabbakammehi cepi brāhmaṇo jīvikaṃ kappeti, na ca tena brāhmaṇo upalippati.**In the same way, my good man, if a brahmin earns a living by any kind of work, he is not corrupted by that.’*";
P_HTM[4617]="*Sabbakammehi jīvikaṃ kappetī’ti kho, doṇa, tasmā brāhmaṇo brāhmaṇacaṇḍāloti vuccati.**A brahmin is called a brahmin outcaste because he earns a living by any kind of work.*";
P_HTM[4618]="*Evaṃ kho, doṇa, brāhmaṇo brāhmaṇacaṇḍālo hoti.**That’s how a brahmin is a brahmin outcaste.*";
P_HTM[4619]="*Ye kho te, doṇa, brāhmaṇānaṃ pubbakā isayo mantānaṃ kattāro mantānaṃ pavattāro yesamidaṃ etarahi brāhmaṇā porāṇaṃ mantapadaṃ gītaṃ pavuttaṃ samīhitaṃ tadanugāyanti tadanubhāsanti bhāsitamanubhāsanti sajjhāyitamanusajjhāyanti vācitamanuvācenti, seyyathidaṃ—aṭṭhako, vāmako, vāmadevo, vessāmitto, yamadaggi, aṅgīraso, bhāradvājo, vāseṭṭho, kassapo, bhagu;**Doṇa, the brahmin hermits of the past were Aṭṭhaka, Vāmaka, Vāmadeva, Vessāmitta, Yamadaggi, Aṅgīrasa, Bhāradvāja, Vāseṭṭha, Kassapa, and Bhagu. They were the authors and propagators of the hymns, whose hymnal was sung and propagated and compiled in ancient times. These days, brahmins continue to sing and chant it. They continue chanting what was chanted, reciting what was recited, and teaching what was taught.*";
P_HTM[4620]="*tyassume pañca brāhmaṇe paññāpenti—**Those hermits described five kinds of brahmins.*";
P_HTM[4621]="*brahmasamaṃ, devasamaṃ, mariyādaṃ, sambhinnamariyādaṃ, brāhmaṇacaṇḍālaṃyeva pañcamaṃ.**A brahmin who is equal to Brahmā, one who is equal to a god, one who toes the line, one who crosses the line, and the fifth is a brahmin outcaste.*";
P_HTM[4622]="*Tesaṃ tvaṃ, doṇa, katamoti?**Which one of these are you, Doṇa?”*";
P_HTM[4623]="*Evaṃ sante mayaṃ, bho gotama, brāhmaṇacaṇḍālampi na pūrema.**“This being so, Master Gotama, I don’t even qualify as a brahmin outcaste.*";
P_HTM[4624]="*Abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe … upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**Excellent, Master Gotama! … From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[4625]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4626]="*3. Saṅgāravasuttaṃ**With Saṅgārava*";
P_HTM[4627]="*Atha kho saṅgāravo brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then Saṅgārava the brahmin went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[4628]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho saṅgāravo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, Saṅgārava sat down to one side, and said to the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[4629]="*“ko nu kho, bho gotama, hetu ko paccayo, yena kadāci dīgharattaṃ sajjhāyakatāpi mantā nappaṭibhanti, pageva asajjhāyakatā?**“What is the cause, Master Gotama, what is the reason why sometimes even hymns that are long-practiced don’t spring to mind, let alone those that are not practiced?*";
P_HTM[4630]="*Ko pana, bho gotama, hetu ko paccayo, yena kadāci dīgharattaṃ asajjhāyakatāpi mantā paṭibhanti, pageva sajjhāyakatā”ti?**And why is it that sometimes even hymns that are long-unpracticed spring to mind, let alone those that are practiced?”*";
P_HTM[4631]="*Yasmiṃ, brāhmaṇa, samaye kāmarāgapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati kāmarāgaparetena, uppannassa ca kāmarāgassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, attatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, paratthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, ubhayatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, dīgharattaṃ sajjhāyakatāpi mantā nappaṭibhanti, pageva asajjhāyakatā.**“Brahmin, there’s a time when your heart is overcome and mired in sensual desire and you don’t truly understand the escape from sensual desire that has arisen. At that time you don’t truly know or see your own good, the good of another, or the good of both. Even hymns that are long-practiced don’t spring to mind, let alone those that are not practiced.*";
P_HTM[4632]="*Seyyathāpi, brāhmaṇa, udapatto saṃsaṭṭho lākhāya vā haliddiyā vā nīliyā vā mañjiṭṭhāya vā.**Suppose there was a bowl of water that was mixed with dye such as red lac, turmeric, indigo, or rose madder.*";
P_HTM[4633]="*Tattha cakkhumā puriso sakaṃ mukhanimittaṃ paccavekkhamāno yathābhūtaṃ nappajāneyya na passeyya.**Even a person with good eyesight checking their own reflection wouldn’t truly know it or see it.*";
P_HTM[4634]="*Evamevaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, yasmiṃ samaye kāmarāgapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati kāmarāgaparetena, uppannassa ca kāmarāgassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, attatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, paratthampi … pe … ubhayatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, dīgharattaṃ sajjhāyakatāpi mantā nappaṭibhanti, pageva asajjhāyakatā. (1)**In the same way, when your heart is overcome and mired in sensual desire … Even hymns that are long-practiced don’t spring to mind, let alone those that are not practiced.*";
P_HTM[4635]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, yasmiṃ samaye byāpādapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati byāpādaparetena, uppannassa ca byāpādassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, attatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, paratthampi … pe … ubhayatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, dīgharattaṃ sajjhāyakatāpi mantā nappaṭibhanti, pageva asajjhāyakatā.**Furthermore, when your heart is overcome and mired in ill will … Even hymns that are long-practiced don’t spring to mind, let alone those that are not practiced.*";
P_HTM[4636]="*Seyyathāpi, brāhmaṇa, udapatto agginā santatto ukkudhito ussadakajāto.**Suppose there was a bowl of water that was heated by fire, boiling and bubbling.*";
P_HTM[4637]="*Tattha cakkhumā puriso sakaṃ mukhanimittaṃ paccavekkhamāno yathābhūtaṃ nappajāneyya na passeyya.**Even a person with good eyesight checking their own reflection wouldn’t truly know it or see it.*";
P_HTM[4638]="*Evamevaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, yasmiṃ samaye byāpādapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati byāpādaparetena, uppannassa ca byāpādassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, attatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, paratthampi … pe … ubhayatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, dīgharattaṃ sajjhāyakatāpi mantā nappaṭibhanti, pageva asajjhāyakatā. (2)**In the same way, when your heart is overcome and mired in ill will … Even hymns that are long-practiced don’t spring to mind, let alone those that are not practiced.*";
P_HTM[4639]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, yasmiṃ samaye thinamiddhapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati thinamiddhaparetena, uppannassa ca thinamiddhassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, attatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, paratthampi … pe … ubhayatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, dīgharattaṃ sajjhāyakatāpi mantā nappaṭibhanti, pageva asajjhāyakatā.**Furthermore, when your heart is overcome and mired in dullness and drowsiness … Even hymns that are long-practiced don’t spring to mind, let alone those that are not practiced.*";
P_HTM[4640]="*Seyyathāpi, brāhmaṇa, udapatto sevālapaṇakapariyonaddho.**Suppose there was a bowl of water overgrown with moss and aquatic plants.*";
P_HTM[4641]="*Tattha cakkhumā puriso sakaṃ mukhanimittaṃ paccavekkhamāno yathābhūtaṃ nappajāneyya na passeyya.**Even a person with good eyesight checking their own reflection wouldn’t truly know it or see it.*";
P_HTM[4642]="*Evamevaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, yasmiṃ samaye thinamiddhapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati thinamiddhaparetena, uppannassa ca thinamiddhassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, attatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, paratthampi … pe … ubhayatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, dīgharattaṃ sajjhāyakatāpi mantā nappaṭibhanti, pageva asajjhāyakatā. (3)**In the same way, when your heart is overcome and mired in dullness and drowsiness … Even hymns that are long-practiced don’t spring to mind, let alone those that are not practiced.*";
P_HTM[4643]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, yasmiṃ samaye uddhaccakukkuccapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati uddhaccakukkuccaparetena, uppannassa ca uddhaccakukkuccassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, attatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, paratthampi … pe … ubhayatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, dīgharattaṃ sajjhāyakatāpi mantā nappaṭibhanti, pageva asajjhāyakatā.**Furthermore, when your heart is overcome and mired in restlessness and remorse … Even hymns that are long-practiced don’t spring to mind, let alone those that are not practiced.*";
P_HTM[4644]="*Seyyathāpi, brāhmaṇa, udapatto vāterito calito bhanto ūmijāto.**Suppose there was a bowl of water stirred by the wind, churning, swirling, and rippling.*";
P_HTM[4645]="*Tattha cakkhumā puriso sakaṃ mukhanimittaṃ paccavekkhamāno yathābhūtaṃ nappajāneyya na passeyya.**Even a person with good eyesight checking their own reflection wouldn’t truly know it or see it.*";
P_HTM[4646]="*Evamevaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, yasmiṃ samaye uddhaccakukkuccapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati uddhaccakukkuccaparetena, uppannassa ca uddhaccakukkuccassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, attatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, paratthampi … pe … ubhayatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, dīgharattaṃ sajjhāyakatāpi mantā nappaṭibhanti, pageva asajjhāyakatā. (4)**In the same way, when your heart is overcome and mired in restlessness and remorse … Even hymns that are long-practiced don’t spring to mind, let alone those that are not practiced.*";
P_HTM[4647]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, yasmiṃ samaye vicikicchāpariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati vicikicchāparetena, uppannāya ca vicikicchāya nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, attatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, paratthampi … pe … ubhayatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, dīgharattaṃ sajjhāyakatāpi mantā nappaṭibhanti, pageva asajjhāyakatā.**Furthermore, when your heart is overcome and mired in doubt … Even hymns that are long-practiced don’t spring to mind, let alone those that are not practiced.*";
P_HTM[4648]="*Seyyathāpi, brāhmaṇa, udapatto āvilo luḷito kalalībhūto andhakāre nikkhitto.**Suppose there was a bowl of water that was cloudy, murky, and muddy, hidden in the darkness.*";
P_HTM[4649]="*Tattha cakkhumā puriso sakaṃ mukhanimittaṃ paccavekkhamāno yathābhūtaṃ nappajāneyya na passeyya.**Even a person with good eyesight checking their own reflection wouldn’t truly know it or see it.*";
P_HTM[4650]="*Evamevaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, yasmiṃ samaye vicikicchāpariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati vicikicchāparetena, uppannāya ca vicikicchāya nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, attatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, paratthampi … pe … ubhayatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti na passati, dīgharattaṃ sajjhāyakatāpi mantā nappaṭibhanti, pageva asajjhāyakatā. (5)**In the same way, there’s a time when your heart is overcome and mired in doubt and you don’t truly understand the escape from doubt that has arisen. At that time you don’t truly know or see your own good, the good of another, or the good of both. Even hymns that are long-practiced don’t spring to mind, let alone those that are not practiced.*";
P_HTM[4651]="*Yasmiñca kho, brāhmaṇa, samaye na kāmarāgapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati na kāmarāgaparetena, uppannassa ca kāmarāgassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, attatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti passati, paratthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti passati, ubhayatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti passati, dīgharattaṃ asajjhāyakatāpi mantā paṭibhanti, pageva sajjhāyakatā.**There’s a time when your heart is not overcome and mired in sensual desire and you truly understand the escape from sensual desire that has arisen. At that time you truly know and see your own good, the good of another, and the good of both. Even hymns that are long-unpracticed spring to mind, let alone those that are practiced.*";
P_HTM[4652]="*Seyyathāpi, brāhmaṇa, udapatto asaṃsaṭṭho lākhāya vā haliddiyā vā nīliyā vā mañjiṭṭhāya vā.**Suppose there was a bowl of water that was not mixed with dye such as red lac, turmeric, indigo, or rose madder.*";
P_HTM[4653]="*Tattha cakkhumā puriso sakaṃ mukhanimittaṃ paccavekkhamāno yathābhūtaṃ pajāneyya passeyya.**A person with good eyesight checking their own reflection would truly know it and see it.*";
P_HTM[4654]="*Evamevaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, yasmiṃ samaye na kāmarāgapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati … pe …. (1)**In the same way, when your heart is not overcome and mired in sensual desire … Even hymns that are long-unpracticed spring to mind, let alone those that are practiced.*";
P_HTM[4655]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, yasmiṃ samaye na byāpādapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati … pe …**Furthermore, when your heart is not overcome and mired in ill will … Even hymns that are long-unpracticed spring to mind, let alone those that are practiced.*";
P_HTM[4656]="*seyyathāpi, brāhmaṇa, udapatto agginā asantatto anukkudhito anussadakajāto.**Suppose there was a bowl of water that’s not heated by a fire, boiling and bubbling.*";
P_HTM[4657]="*Tattha cakkhumā puriso sakaṃ mukhanimittaṃ paccavekkhamāno yathābhūtaṃ pajāneyya passeyya.**A person with good eyesight checking their own reflection would truly know it and see it.*";
P_HTM[4658]="*Evamevaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, yasmiṃ samaye na byāpādapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati … pe …. (2)**In the same way, when your heart is not overcome and mired in ill will … Even hymns that are long-unpracticed spring to mind, let alone those that are practiced.*";
P_HTM[4659]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, yasmiṃ samaye na thinamiddhapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati … pe …**Furthermore, when your heart is not overcome and mired in dullness and drowsiness … Even hymns that are long-unpracticed spring to mind, let alone those that are practiced.*";
P_HTM[4660]="*seyyathāpi, brāhmaṇa, udapatto na sevālapaṇakapariyonaddho.**Suppose there was a bowl of water that’s not overgrown with moss and aquatic plants.*";
P_HTM[4661]="*Tattha cakkhumā puriso sakaṃ mukhanimittaṃ paccavekkhamāno yathābhūtaṃ pajāneyya passeyya.**A person with good eyesight checking their own reflection would truly know it and see it.*";
P_HTM[4662]="*Evamevaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, yasmiṃ samaye na thinamiddhapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati … pe …. (3)**In the same way, when your heart is not overcome and mired in dullness and drowsiness … Even hymns that are long-unpracticed spring to mind, let alone those that are practiced.*";
P_HTM[4663]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, yasmiṃ samaye na uddhaccakukkuccapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati … pe …**Furthermore, when your heart is not overcome and mired in restlessness and remorse … Even hymns that are long-unpracticed spring to mind, let alone those that are practiced.*";
P_HTM[4664]="*seyyathāpi, brāhmaṇa, udapatto na vāterito na calito na bhanto na ūmijāto.**Suppose there was a bowl of water that’s not stirred by the wind, churning, swirling, and rippling.*";
P_HTM[4665]="*Tattha cakkhumā puriso sakaṃ mukhanimittaṃ paccavekkhamāno yathābhūtaṃ pajāneyya passeyya.**A person with good eyesight checking their own reflection would truly know it and see it.*";
P_HTM[4666]="*Evamevaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, yasmiṃ samaye na uddhaccakukkuccapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati … pe …. (4)**In the same way, when your heart is not overcome and mired in restlessness and remorse … Even hymns that are long-unpracticed spring to mind, let alone those that are practiced.*";
P_HTM[4667]="*Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇa, yasmiṃ samaye na vicikicchāpariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati na vicikicchāparetena, uppannāya ca vicikicchāya nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, attatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti passati, paratthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti passati, ubhayatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti passati, dīgharattaṃ asajjhāyakatāpi mantā paṭibhanti, pageva sajjhāyakatā.**Furthermore, when your heart is not overcome and mired in doubt … Even hymns that are long-unpracticed spring to mind, let alone those that are practiced.*";
P_HTM[4668]="*Seyyathāpi, brāhmaṇa, udapatto accho vippasanno anāvilo āloke nikkhitto.**Suppose there was a bowl of water that’s transparent, clear, and unclouded, brought into the light.*";
P_HTM[4669]="*Tattha cakkhumā puriso sakaṃ mukhanimittaṃ paccavekkhamāno yathābhūtaṃ pajāneyya passeyya.**A person with good eyesight checking their own reflection would truly know it and see it.*";
P_HTM[4670]="*Evamevaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, yasmiṃ samaye na vicikicchāpariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati na vicikicchāparetena, uppannāya ca vicikicchāya nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, attatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti passati, paratthampi … pe … ubhayatthampi tasmiṃ samaye yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti passati, dīgharattaṃ asajjhāyakatāpi mantā paṭibhanti, pageva sajjhāyakatā. (5)**In the same way, there’s a time when your heart is not overcome and mired in doubt and you truly understand the escape from doubt that has arisen. At that time you truly know and see your own good, the good of another, and the good of both. Even hymns that are long-unpracticed spring to mind, let alone those that are practiced.*";
P_HTM[4671]="*Ayaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, hetu ayaṃ paccayo, yena kadāci dīgharattaṃ sajjhāyakatāpi mantā nappaṭibhanti, pageva asajjhāyakatā.**This is the cause, brahmin, this is the reason why sometimes even hymns that are long-practiced don’t spring to mind, let alone those that are not practiced.*";
P_HTM[4672]="*Ayaṃ pana, brāhmaṇa, hetu ayaṃ paccayo, yena kadāci dīgharattaṃ asajjhāyakatāpi mantā paṭibhanti, pageva sajjhāyakatā”ti.**And this is why sometimes even hymns that are long-unpracticed spring to mind, let alone those that are practiced.”*";
P_HTM[4673]="*“Abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe … upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**“Excellent, Master Gotama! … From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[4674]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4675]="*4. Kāraṇapālīsuttaṃ**With Kāraṇapālī*";
P_HTM[4676]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof.*";
P_HTM[4677]="*Tena kho pana samayena kāraṇapālī brāhmaṇo licchavīnaṃ kammantaṃ kāreti.**Now at that time the brahmin Kāraṇapālī was working for the Licchavis.*";
P_HTM[4678]="*Addasā kho kāraṇapālī brāhmaṇo piṅgiyāniṃ brāhmaṇaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ;**He saw the brahmin Piṅgiyānī coming off in the distance*";
P_HTM[4679]="*disvā piṅgiyāniṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca:**and said to him,*";
P_HTM[4680]="*“Handa kuto nu bhavaṃ piṅgiyānī āgacchati divā divassā”ti?**“So, Piṅgiyānī, where are you coming from in the middle of the day?”*";
P_HTM[4681]="*“Itohaṃ, bho, āgacchāmi samaṇassa gotamassa santikā”ti.**“I’m coming, my good man, from the presence of the ascetic Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[4682]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññati bhavaṃ piṅgiyānī samaṇassa gotamassa paññāveyyattiyaṃ? Paṇḍito maññe”ti?**“What do you think of the ascetic Gotama’s lucidity of wisdom? Do you think he’s astute?”*";
P_HTM[4683]="*“Ko cāhaṃ, bho, ko ca samaṇassa gotamassa paññāveyyattiyaṃ jānissāmi.**“My good man, who am I to judge the ascetic Gotama’s lucidity of wisdom?*";
P_HTM[4684]="*Sopi nūnassa tādisova yo samaṇassa gotamassa paññāveyyattiyaṃ jāneyyā”ti.**You’d really have to be on the same level to judge his lucidity of wisdom.”*";
P_HTM[4685]="*“Uḷārāya khalu bhavaṃ piṅgiyānī samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ pasaṃsāya pasaṃsatī”ti.**“Master Piṅgiyānī praises the ascetic Gotama with magnificent praise indeed.”*";
P_HTM[4686]="*“Ko cāhaṃ, bho, ko ca samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ pasaṃsissāmi.**“Who am I to praise the ascetic Gotama?*";
P_HTM[4687]="*Pasatthappasatthova so bhavaṃ gotamo seṭṭho devamanussānan”ti.**He is praised by the praised as the best of gods and humans.”*";
P_HTM[4688]="*“Kiṃ pana bhavaṃ piṅgiyānī atthavasaṃ sampassamāno samaṇe gotame evaṃ abhippasanno”ti?**“But for what reason are you so devoted to the ascetic Gotama?”*";
P_HTM[4689]="*“Seyyathāpi, bho, puriso aggarasaparititto na aññesaṃ hīnānaṃ rasānaṃ piheti;**“Suppose a person was completely satisfied by the best tasting food. They wouldn’t be attracted to anything that tasted inferior.*";
P_HTM[4690]="*evamevaṃ kho, bho, yato yato tassa bhoto gotamassa dhammaṃ suṇāti—**In the same way, when you hear the ascetic Gotama’s teaching—*";
P_HTM[4691]="*yadi suttaso, yadi geyyaso, yadi veyyākaraṇaso, yadi abbhutadhammaso—**whatever it may be, whether statements, songs, discussions, or amazing stories—*";
P_HTM[4692]="*tato tato na aññesaṃ puthusamaṇabrāhmaṇappavādānaṃ piheti.**then you’re not attracted to the doctrines of the various ascetics and brahmins.*";
P_HTM[4693]="*Seyyathāpi, bho, puriso jighacchādubbalyapareto madhupiṇḍikaṃ adhigaccheyya.**Suppose a person who was weak with hunger was to obtain a honey-cake.*";
P_HTM[4694]="*So yato yato sāyetha, labhateva sādurasaṃ asecanakaṃ;**Wherever they taste it, they would enjoy a sweet, delicious flavor.*";
P_HTM[4695]="*evamevaṃ kho, bho, yato yato tassa bhoto gotamassa dhammaṃ suṇāti—**In the same way, when you hear the ascetic Gotama’s teaching—*";
P_HTM[4696]="*yadi suttaso, yadi geyyaso, yadi veyyākaraṇaso, yadi abbhutadhammaso—**whatever it may be, whether statements, songs, discussions, or amazing stories—*";
P_HTM[4697]="*tato tato labhateva attamanataṃ, labhati cetaso pasādaṃ.**then you get a sense of uplift, a confidence of the heart.*";
P_HTM[4698]="*Seyyathāpi, bho, puriso candanaghaṭikaṃ adhigaccheyya—**Suppose a person were to obtain a piece of sandalwood,*";
P_HTM[4699]="*haricandanassa vā lohitacandanassa vā.**whether yellow or red.*";
P_HTM[4700]="*So yato yato ghāyetha—**Wherever they smelled it—*";
P_HTM[4701]="*yadi mūlato, yadi majjhato, yadi aggato—**whether at the root, the middle, or the top—*";
P_HTM[4702]="*adhigacchateva surabhigandhaṃ asecanakaṃ;**they’d enjoy a delicious fragrance.*";
P_HTM[4703]="*evamevaṃ kho, bho, yato yato tassa bhoto gotamassa dhammaṃ suṇāti—**In the same way, when you hear the ascetic Gotama’s teaching—*";
P_HTM[4704]="*yadi suttaso, yadi geyyaso, yadi veyyākaraṇaso, yadi abbhutadhammaso—**whatever it may be, whether statements, songs, discussions, or amazing stories—*";
P_HTM[4705]="*tato tato adhigacchati pāmojjaṃ adhigacchati somanassaṃ.**then you become filled with joy and happiness.*";
P_HTM[4706]="*Seyyathāpi, bho, puriso ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno.**Suppose there was a person who was sick, suffering, gravely ill.*";
P_HTM[4707]="*Tassa kusalo bhisakko ṭhānaso ābādhaṃ nīhareyya;**A good doctor would cure them on the spot.*";
P_HTM[4708]="*evamevaṃ kho, bho, yato yato tassa bhoto gotamassa dhammaṃ suṇāti—**In the same way, when you hear the ascetic Gotama’s teaching—*";
P_HTM[4709]="*yadi suttaso, yadi geyyaso, yadi veyyākaraṇaso, yadi abbhutadhammaso—**whatever it may be, whether statements, songs, discussions, or amazing stories—*";
P_HTM[4710]="*tato tato sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā abbhatthaṃ gacchanti.**then you make an end of sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress.*";
P_HTM[4711]="*Seyyathāpi, bho, pokkharaṇī acchodakā sātodakā sītodakā setakā supatitthā ramaṇīyā.**Suppose there was a lotus pond with clear, sweet, cool water, clean, with smooth banks, delightful.*";
P_HTM[4712]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya ghammābhitatto ghammapareto kilanto tasito pipāsito.**Then along comes a person struggling in the oppressive heat, weary, thirsty, and parched.*";
P_HTM[4713]="*So taṃ pokkharaṇiṃ ogāhetvā nhātvā ca pivitvā ca sabbadarathakilamathapariḷāhaṃ paṭippassambheyya.**They’d plunge into the lotus pond to bathe and drink. And all their stress, weariness, and heat exhaustion would die down.*";
P_HTM[4714]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bho, yato yato tassa bhoto gotamassa dhammaṃ suṇāti—**In the same way, when you hear the ascetic Gotama’s teaching—*";
P_HTM[4715]="*yadi suttaso, yadi geyyaso, yadi veyyākaraṇaso, yadi abbhutadhammaso—**whatever it may be, whether statements, songs, discussions, or amazing stories—*";
P_HTM[4716]="*tato tato sabbadarathakilamathapariḷāhā paṭippassambhantī”ti.**then all your stress, weariness, and exhaustion die down.”*";
P_HTM[4717]="*Evaṃ vutte, kāraṇapālī brāhmaṇo uṭṭhāyāsanā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā dakkhiṇaṃ jāṇumaṇḍalaṃ pathaviyaṃ nihantvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā tikkhattuṃ udānaṃ udānesi:**When this was said, the brahmin Kāraṇapālī got up from his seat, arranged his robe over one shoulder, knelt on his right knee, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and was inspired to exclaim three times:*";
P_HTM[4718]="*“Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa.**“Homage to that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!*";
P_HTM[4719]="*Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa.**Homage to that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!*";
P_HTM[4720]="*Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassāti.**Homage to that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!*";
P_HTM[4721]="*Abhikkantaṃ, bho piṅgiyāni, abhikkantaṃ, bho piṅgiyāni.**Excellent, Master Piṅgiyānī! Excellent!*";
P_HTM[4722]="*Seyyathāpi, bho piṅgiyāni, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā piṅgiyāninā anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito.**As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, Master Piṅgiyānī has made the teaching clear in many ways.*";
P_HTM[4723]="*Esāhaṃ, bho piṅgiyāni, taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṃghañca.**I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[4724]="*Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ piṅgiyānī dhāretu, ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Piṅgiyānī remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[4725]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4726]="*5. Piṅgiyānīsuttaṃ**Piṅgiyānī*";
P_HTM[4727]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof.*";
P_HTM[4728]="*Tena kho pana samayena pañcamattāni licchavisatāni bhagavantaṃ payirupāsanti.**Now at that time around five hundred Licchavis were visiting the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4729]="*Appekacce licchavī nīlā honti nīlavaṇṇā nīlavatthā nīlālaṅkārā, appekacce licchavī pītā honti pītavaṇṇā pītavatthā pītālaṅkārā, appekacce licchavī lohitakā honti lohitakavaṇṇā lohitakavatthā lohitakālaṅkārā, appekacce licchavī odātā honti odātavaṇṇā odātavatthā odātālaṅkārā.**Some of the Licchavis were in blue, of blue color, clad in blue, adorned with blue. And some were similarly colored in yellow, red, or white.*";
P_HTM[4730]="*Tyassudaṃ bhagavā atirocati vaṇṇena ceva yasasā ca.**But the Buddha outshone them all in beauty and glory.*";
P_HTM[4731]="*Atha kho piṅgiyānī brāhmaṇo uṭṭhāyāsanā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then the brahmin Piṅgīyānī got up from his seat, arranged his robe over one shoulder, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and said,*";
P_HTM[4732]="*“paṭibhāti maṃ, bhagavā, paṭibhāti maṃ, sugatā”ti.**“I feel inspired to speak, Blessed One! I feel inspired to speak, Holy One!”*";
P_HTM[4733]="*“Paṭibhātu taṃ piṅgiyānī”ti bhagavā avoca.**“Then speak as you feel inspired,” said the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4734]="*Atha kho piṅgiyānī brāhmaṇo bhagavato sammukhā sāruppāya gāthāya abhitthavi:**So the brahmin Piṅgīyānī extolled the Buddha in his presence with a fitting verse.*";
P_HTM[4735]="*“Padmaṃ yathā kokanadaṃ sugandhaṃ,**“Like a fragrant pink lotus*";
P_HTM[4736]="*Pāto siyā phullamavītagandhaṃ;**that blooms in the morning, its fragrance unfaded—*";
P_HTM[4737]="*Aṅgīrasaṃ passa virocamānaṃ,**see Aṅgīrasa shine,*";
P_HTM[4738]="*Tapantamādiccamivantalikkhe”ti.**bright as the sun in the sky!”*";
P_HTM[4739]="*Atha kho te licchavī pañcahi uttarāsaṅgasatehi piṅgiyāniṃ brāhmaṇaṃ acchādesuṃ.**Then those Licchavis clothed Piṅgiyānī with five hundred upper robes.*";
P_HTM[4740]="*Atha kho piṅgiyānī brāhmaṇo tehi pañcahi uttarāsaṅgasatehi bhagavantaṃ acchādesi.**And Piṅgiyānī clothed the Buddha with them.*";
P_HTM[4741]="*Atha kho bhagavā te licchavī etadavoca:**Then the Buddha said to the Licchavis:*";
P_HTM[4742]="*“pañcannaṃ, licchavī, ratanānaṃ pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ.**“Licchavis, the appearance of five treasures is rare in the world.*";
P_HTM[4743]="*Katamesaṃ pañcannaṃ?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4744]="*Tathāgatassa arahato sammāsambuddhassa pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmiṃ.**A Realized One, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4745]="*Tathāgatappaveditassa dhammavinayassa desetā puggalo dullabho lokasmiṃ.**A person who explains the teaching and training proclaimed by a Realized One.*";
P_HTM[4746]="*Tathāgatappaveditassa dhammavinayassa desitassa viññātā puggalo dullabho lokasmiṃ.**A person who understands the teaching and training proclaimed by a Realized One.*";
P_HTM[4747]="*Tathāgatappaveditassa dhammavinayassa desitassa viññātā dhammānudhammappaṭipanno puggalo dullabho lokasmiṃ.**A person who practices in line with the teaching.*";
P_HTM[4748]="*Kataññū katavedī puggalo dullabho lokasmiṃ.**A person who is grateful and thankful.*";
P_HTM[4749]="*Imesaṃ kho, licchavī, pañcannaṃ ratanānaṃ pātubhāvo dullabho lokasmin”ti.**The appearance of these five treasures is rare in the world.”*";
P_HTM[4750]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4751]="*6. Mahāsupinasuttaṃ**The Great Dreams*";
P_HTM[4752]="*“Tathāgatassa, bhikkhave, arahato sammāsambuddhassa pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato pañca mahāsupinā pāturahesuṃ.**“Mendicants, before his awakening five great dreams appeared to the Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, when he was still not awake but intent on awakening.*";
P_HTM[4753]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4754]="*Tathāgatassa, bhikkhave, arahato sammāsambuddhassa pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato ayaṃ mahāpathavī mahāsayanaṃ ahosi, himavā pabbatarājā bibbohanaṃ ahosi, puratthime samudde vāmo hattho ohito ahosi, pacchime samudde dakkhiṇo hattho ohito ahosi, dakkhiṇe samudde ubho pādā ohitā ahesuṃ.**This great earth was his bed. Himalaya, king of mountains, was his pillow. His left hand was laid down in the eastern sea. His right hand was laid down in the western sea. And both his feet were laid down in the southern sea.*";
P_HTM[4755]="*Tathāgatassa, bhikkhave, arahato sammāsambuddhassa pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato ayaṃ paṭhamo mahāsupino pāturahosi.**This is the first great dream that appeared to the Realized One before his awakening.*";
P_HTM[4756]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa arahato sammāsambuddhassa pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato tiriyā nāma tiṇajāti nābhiyā uggantvā nabhaṃ āhacca ṭhitā ahosi.**Next, a kind of grass called ‘the crosser’ grew up from his navel and stood pressing against the cloudy sky.*";
P_HTM[4757]="*Tathāgatassa, bhikkhave, arahato sammāsambuddhassa pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato ayaṃ dutiyo mahāsupino pāturahosi.**This is the second great dream that appeared to the Realized One before his awakening.*";
P_HTM[4758]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa arahato sammāsambuddhassa pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato setā kimī kaṇhasīsā pādehi ussakkitvā () yāva jāṇumaṇḍalā paṭicchādesuṃ.**Next, white caterpillars with black heads crawled up from his feet and covered his knees.*";
P_HTM[4759]="*Tathāgatassa, bhikkhave, arahato sammāsambuddhassa pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato ayaṃ tatiyo mahāsupino pāturahosi.**This is the third great dream that appeared to the Realized One before his awakening.*";
P_HTM[4760]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa arahato sammāsambuddhassa pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato cattāro sakuṇā nānāvaṇṇā catūhi disāhi āgantvā pādamūle nipatitvā sabbasetā sampajjiṃsu.**Next, four birds of different colors came from the four directions. They fell at his feet, turning pure white.*";
P_HTM[4761]="*Tathāgatassa, bhikkhave, arahato sammāsambuddhassa pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato ayaṃ catuttho mahāsupino pāturahosi.**This is the fourth great dream that appeared to the Realized One before his awakening.*";
P_HTM[4762]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato arahaṃ sammāsambuddho pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddho bodhisattova samāno mahato mīḷhapabbatassa uparūpari caṅkamati alippamāno mīḷhena.**Next, he walked back and forth on top of a huge mountain of filth while remaining unsoiled.*";
P_HTM[4763]="*Tathāgatassa, bhikkhave, arahato sammāsambuddhassa pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato ayaṃ pañcamo mahāsupino pāturahosi.**This is the fifth great dream that appeared to the Realized One before his awakening.*";
P_HTM[4764]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa arahato sammāsambuddhassa pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato ayaṃ mahāpathavī mahāsayanaṃ ahosi, himavā pabbatarājā bibbohanaṃ ahosi, puratthime samudde vāmo hattho ohito ahosi, pacchime samudde dakkhiṇo hattho ohito ahosi, dakkhiṇe samudde ubho pādā ohitā ahesuṃ;**Now, as to when, before his awakening, the Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha was still not awake but intent on awakening. This great earth was his bed. Himalaya, king of mountains, was his pillow. His left hand was laid down in the eastern sea. His right hand was laid down in the western sea. And both his feet were laid down in the southern sea.*";
P_HTM[4765]="*tathāgatena, bhikkhave, arahatā sammāsambuddhena anuttarā sammāsambodhi abhisambuddhā.**This was fulfilled when the Buddha awakened to the perfect awakening.*";
P_HTM[4766]="*Tassā abhisambodhāya ayaṃ paṭhamo mahāsupino pāturahosi.**This was the first great dream that appeared to him while he was still not awakened.*";
P_HTM[4767]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa arahato sammāsambuddhassa pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato tiriyā nāma tiṇajāti nābhiyā uggantvā nabhaṃ āhacca ṭhitā ahosi;**As to when a kind of grass called ‘the crosser’ grew up from his navel and stood pressing against the cloudy sky.*";
P_HTM[4768]="*tathāgatena, bhikkhave, arahatā sammāsambuddhena ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo abhisambujjhitvā yāva devamanussehi suppakāsito.**This was fulfilled when, after the Buddha had awakened to the noble eightfold path, it was well proclaimed wherever there are gods and humans.*";
P_HTM[4769]="*Tassa abhisambodhāya ayaṃ dutiyo mahāsupino pāturahosi.**This was the second great dream that appeared to him while he was still not awakened.*";
P_HTM[4770]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa arahato sammāsambuddhassa pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato setā kimī kaṇhasīsā pādehi ussakkitvā yāva jāṇumaṇḍalā paṭicchādesuṃ;**As to when white caterpillars with black heads crawled up from his feet and covered his knees.*";
P_HTM[4771]="*bahū, bhikkhave, gihī odātavasanā tathāgataṃ pāṇupetā saraṇaṃ gatā.**This was fulfilled when many white-clothed laypeople went for refuge to him for life.*";
P_HTM[4772]="*Tassa abhisambodhāya ayaṃ tatiyo mahāsupino pāturahosi.**This was the third great dream that appeared to him while he was still not awakened.*";
P_HTM[4773]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa arahato sammāsambuddhassa pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato cattāro sakuṇā nānāvaṇṇā catūhi disāhi āgantvā pādamūle nipatitvā sabbasetā sampajjiṃsu;**As to when four birds of different colors came from the four directions. They fell at his feet, turning pure white.*";
P_HTM[4774]="*cattārome, bhikkhave, vaṇṇā khattiyā brāhmaṇā vessā suddā te tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitvā anuttaraṃ vimuttiṃ sacchikaronti.**This was fulfilled when members of the four castes—aristocrats, brahmins, merchants, and workers—went forth from the lay life to homelessness in the teaching and training proclaimed by the Realized One and realized supreme freedom.*";
P_HTM[4775]="*Tassa abhisambodhāya ayaṃ catuttho mahāsupino pāturahosi.**This was the fourth great dream that appeared to him while he was still not awakened.*";
P_HTM[4776]="*Yampi, bhikkhave, tathāgato arahaṃ sammāsambuddho pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddho bodhisattova samāno mahato mīḷhapabbatassa uparūpari caṅkamati alippamāno mīḷhena;**As to when he walked back and forth on top of a huge mountain of filth while remaining unsoiled.*";
P_HTM[4777]="*lābhī, bhikkhave, tathāgato cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ, taṃ tathāgato agathito amucchito anajjhosanno ādīnavadassāvī nissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati.**This was fulfilled when the Realized One received robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick. And he used them untied, uninfatuated, unattached, seeing the drawbacks, and understanding the escape.*";
P_HTM[4778]="*Tassa abhisambodhāya ayaṃ pañcamo mahāsupino pāturahosi.**This was the fifth great dream that appeared to him while he was still not awakened.*";
P_HTM[4779]="*Tathāgatassa, bhikkhave, arahato sammāsambuddhassa pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato ime pañca mahāsupinā pāturahesun”ti.**Before his awakening these five great dreams appeared to the Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, when he was still not awake but intent on awakening.”*";
P_HTM[4780]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4781]="*7. Vassasuttaṃ**Obstacles to Rain*";
P_HTM[4782]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, vassassa antarāyā, yaṃ nemittā na jānanti, yattha nemittānaṃ cakkhu na kamati.**“Mendicants, there are these five obstacles to rain, which the forecasters don’t know, and which their vision does not traverse.*";
P_HTM[4783]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4784]="*Upari, bhikkhave, ākāse tejodhātu pakuppati.**In the upper atmosphere the fire element flares up,*";
P_HTM[4785]="*Tena uppannā meghā paṭivigacchanti.**which disperses the clouds.*";
P_HTM[4786]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo vassassa antarāyo, yaṃ nemittā na jānanti, yattha nemittānaṃ cakkhu na kamati.**This is the first obstacle to rain, which the forecasters don’t know, and which their vision does not traverse.*";
P_HTM[4787]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, upari ākāse vāyodhātu pakuppati.**Furthermore, in the upper atmosphere the air element flares up,*";
P_HTM[4788]="*Tena uppannā meghā paṭivigacchanti.**which disperses the clouds.*";
P_HTM[4789]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo vassassa antarāyo, yaṃ nemittā na jānanti, yattha nemittānaṃ cakkhu na kamati.**This is the second obstacle to rain …*";
P_HTM[4790]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, rāhu asurindo pāṇinā udakaṃ sampaṭicchitvā mahāsamudde chaḍḍeti.**Furthermore, Rāhu, lord of demons, receives water in his hand and tosses it in the ocean.*";
P_HTM[4791]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo vassassa antarāyo, yaṃ nemittā na jānanti, yattha nemittānaṃ cakkhu na kamati.**This is the third obstacle to rain …*";
P_HTM[4792]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, vassavalāhakā devā pamattā honti.**Furthermore, the gods of the rain clouds become negligent.*";
P_HTM[4793]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho vassassa antarāyo, yaṃ nemittā na jānanti, yattha nemittānaṃ cakkhu na kamati.**This is the fourth obstacle to rain …*";
P_HTM[4794]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, manussā adhammikā honti.**Furthermore, humans become unprincipled.*";
P_HTM[4795]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo vassassa antarāyo, yaṃ nemittā na jānanti, yattha nemittānaṃ cakkhu na kamati.**This is the fifth obstacle to rain, which the forecasters don’t know, and which their vision does not traverse.*";
P_HTM[4796]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca vassassa antarāyā, yaṃ nemittā na jānanti, yattha nemittānaṃ cakkhu na kamatī”ti.**These are the five obstacles to rain, which the forecasters don’t know, and which their vision does not traverse.”*";
P_HTM[4797]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4798]="*8. Vācāsuttaṃ**Well*";
P_HTM[4799]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatā vācā subhāsitā hoti, no dubbhāsitā, anavajjā ca ananuvajjā ca viññūnaṃ.**“Mendicants, speech that has five factors is well spoken, not poorly spoken. It’s blameless and is not criticized by sensible people.*";
P_HTM[4800]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4801]="*Kālena ca bhāsitā hoti, saccā ca bhāsitā hoti, saṇhā ca bhāsitā hoti, atthasaṃhitā ca bhāsitā hoti, mettacittena ca bhāsitā hoti.**It is speech that is timely, true, gentle, beneficial, and loving.*";
P_HTM[4802]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi aṅgehi samannāgatā vācā subhāsitā hoti, no dubbhāsitā, anavajjā ca ananuvajjā ca viññūnan”ti.**Speech with these five factors is well spoken, not poorly spoken. It’s blameless and is not criticized by sensible people.”*";
P_HTM[4803]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4804]="*9. Kulasuttaṃ**Families*";
P_HTM[4805]="*“Yaṃ, bhikkhave, sīlavanto pabbajitā kulaṃ upasaṅkamanti, tattha manussā pañcahi ṭhānehi bahuṃ puññaṃ pasavanti.**“When ethical renunciates come to a family, the people make much merit for five reasons.*";
P_HTM[4806]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4807]="*Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye sīlavante pabbajite kulaṃ upasaṅkamante manussā disvā cittāni pasādenti, saggasaṃvattanikaṃ, bhikkhave, taṃ kulaṃ tasmiṃ samaye paṭipadaṃ paṭipannaṃ hoti.**When they see ethical renunciates coming to their family, the people bring up confidence in their hearts. At that time the family is practicing a path leading to heaven.*";
P_HTM[4808]="*Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye sīlavante pabbajite kulaṃ upasaṅkamante manussā paccuṭṭhenti abhivādenti āsanaṃ denti, uccākulīnasaṃvattanikaṃ, bhikkhave, taṃ kulaṃ tasmiṃ samaye paṭipadaṃ paṭipannaṃ hoti.**When ethical renunciates come to their family, the people rise from their seats, bow down, and offer them a seat. At that time the family is practicing a path leading to a birth in an eminent family.*";
P_HTM[4809]="*Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye sīlavante pabbajite kulaṃ upasaṅkamante manussā maccheramalaṃ paṭivinenti, mahesakkhasaṃvattanikaṃ, bhikkhave, taṃ kulaṃ tasmiṃ samaye paṭipadaṃ paṭipannaṃ hoti.**When ethical renunciates come to their family, the people get rid of the stain of stinginess. At that time the family is practicing a path leading to being illustrious.*";
P_HTM[4810]="*Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye sīlavante pabbajite kulaṃ upasaṅkamante manussā yathāsatti yathābalaṃ saṃvibhajanti, mahābhogasaṃvattanikaṃ, bhikkhave, taṃ kulaṃ tasmiṃ samaye paṭipadaṃ paṭipannaṃ hoti.**When ethical renunciates come to their family, the people share what they have as best they can. At that time the family is practicing a path leading to great wealth.*";
P_HTM[4811]="*Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye sīlavante pabbajite kulaṃ upasaṅkamante manussā paripucchanti paripañhanti dhammaṃ suṇanti, mahāpaññāsaṃvattanikaṃ, bhikkhave, taṃ kulaṃ tasmiṃ samaye paṭipadaṃ paṭipannaṃ hoti.**When ethical renunciates come to their family, the people ask questions and listen to the teachings. At that time the family is practicing a path leading to great wisdom.*";
P_HTM[4812]="*Yaṃ, bhikkhave, sīlavanto pabbajitā kulaṃ upasaṅkamanti, tattha manussā imehi pañcahi ṭhānehi bahuṃ puññaṃ pasavantī”ti.**When ethical renunciates come to a family, the people make much merit for these five reasons.”*";
P_HTM[4813]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4814]="*10. Nissāraṇīyasuttaṃ**Elements of Escape*";
P_HTM[4815]="*“Pañcimā, bhikkhave, nissāraṇīyā dhātuyo.**“Mendicants, there are these five elements of escape.*";
P_HTM[4816]="*Katamā pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4817]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno kāmaṃ manasikaroto kāmesu cittaṃ na pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati.**Take a case where a mendicant focuses on sensual pleasures, but their mind isn’t eager, confident, settled, and decided about them.*";
P_HTM[4818]="*Nekkhammaṃ kho panassa manasikaroto nekkhamme cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati santiṭṭhati vimuccati.**But when they focus on renunciation, their mind is eager, confident, settled, and decided about it.*";
P_HTM[4819]="*Tassa taṃ cittaṃ sugataṃ subhāvitaṃ suvuṭṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ suvisaṃyuttaṃ kāmehi;**Their mind is in a good state, well developed, well risen, well freed, and well detached from sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[4820]="*ye ca kāmapaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, mutto so tehi, na so taṃ vedanaṃ vediyati.**They’re freed from the distressing and feverish defilements that arise because of sensual pleasures, so they don’t experience that kind of feeling.*";
P_HTM[4821]="*Idamakkhātaṃ kāmānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ. (1)**This is how the escape from sensual pleasures is explained.*";
P_HTM[4822]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno byāpādaṃ manasikaroto byāpāde cittaṃ na pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati.**Take another case where a mendicant focuses on ill will, but their mind isn’t eager …*";
P_HTM[4823]="*Abyāpādaṃ kho panassa manasikaroto abyāpāde cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati santiṭṭhati vimuccati.**But when they focus on good will, their mind is eager …*";
P_HTM[4824]="*Tassa taṃ cittaṃ sugataṃ subhāvitaṃ suvuṭṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ suvisaṃyuttaṃ byāpādena;**Their mind is in a good state … well detached from ill will.*";
P_HTM[4825]="*ye ca byāpādapaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, mutto so tehi, na so taṃ vedanaṃ vediyati.**They’re freed from the distressing and feverish defilements that arise because of ill will, so they don’t experience that kind of feeling.*";
P_HTM[4826]="*Idamakkhātaṃ byāpādassa nissaraṇaṃ. (2)**This is how the escape from ill will is explained.*";
P_HTM[4827]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno vihesaṃ manasikaroto vihesāya cittaṃ na pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati.**Take another case where a mendicant focuses on harming, but their mind isn’t eager …*";
P_HTM[4828]="*Avihesaṃ kho panassa manasikaroto avihesāya cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati santiṭṭhati vimuccati.**But when they focus on compassion, their mind is eager …*";
P_HTM[4829]="*Tassa taṃ cittaṃ sugataṃ subhāvitaṃ suvuṭṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ suvisaṃyuttaṃ vihesāya;**Their mind is in a good state … well detached from harming.*";
P_HTM[4830]="*ye ca vihesāpaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, mutto so tehi, na so taṃ vedanaṃ vediyati.**They’re freed from the distressing and feverish defilements that arise because of harming, so they don’t experience that kind of feeling.*";
P_HTM[4831]="*Idamakkhātaṃ vihesāya nissaraṇaṃ. (3)**This is how the escape from harming is explained.*";
P_HTM[4832]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno rūpaṃ manasikaroto rūpe cittaṃ na pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati.**Take another case where a mendicant focuses on form, but their mind isn’t eager …*";
P_HTM[4833]="*Arūpaṃ kho panassa manasikaroto arūpe cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati santiṭṭhati vimuccati.**But when they focus on the formless, their mind is eager …*";
P_HTM[4834]="*Tassa taṃ cittaṃ sugataṃ subhāvitaṃ suvuṭṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ suvisaṃyuttaṃ rūpehi;**Their mind is in a good state … well detached from forms.*";
P_HTM[4835]="*ye ca rūpapaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, mutto so tehi, na so taṃ vedanaṃ vediyati.**They’re freed from the distressing and feverish defilements that arise because of form, so they don’t experience that kind of feeling.*";
P_HTM[4836]="*Idamakkhātaṃ rūpānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ. (4)**This is how the escape from forms is explained.*";
P_HTM[4837]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno sakkāyaṃ manasikaroto sakkāye cittaṃ na pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati.**Take a case where a mendicant focuses on identity, but their mind isn’t eager, confident, settled, and decided about it.*";
P_HTM[4838]="*Sakkāyanirodhaṃ kho panassa manasikaroto sakkāyanirodhe cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati santiṭṭhati vimuccati.**But when they focus on the ending of identity, their mind is eager, confident, settled, and decided about it.*";
P_HTM[4839]="*Tassa taṃ cittaṃ sugataṃ subhāvitaṃ suvuṭṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ suvisaṃyuttaṃ sakkāyena;**Their mind is in a good state, well developed, well risen, well freed, and well detached from identity.*";
P_HTM[4840]="*ye ca sakkāyapaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, mutto so tehi, na so taṃ vedanaṃ vediyati.**They’re freed from the distressing and feverish defilements that arise because of identity, so they don’t experience that kind of feeling.*";
P_HTM[4841]="*Idamakkhātaṃ sakkāyassa nissaraṇaṃ. (5)**This is how the escape from identity is explained.*";
P_HTM[4842]="*Tassa kāmanandīpi nānuseti, byāpādanandīpi nānuseti, vihesānandīpi nānuseti, rūpanandīpi nānuseti, sakkāyanandīpi nānuseti so kāmanandiyāpi ananusayā, byāpādanandiyāpi ananusayā, vihesānandiyāpi ananusayā, rūpanandiyāpi ananusayā, sakkāyanandiyāpi ananusayā.**Delight in sensual pleasures, ill will, harming, form, and identity don’t linger within them.*";
P_HTM[4843]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu niranusayo, acchecchi taṇhaṃ, vivattayi saṃyojanaṃ, sammā mānābhisamayā antamakāsi dukkhassa.**That’s why they’re called a mendicant who is without underlying tendencies, who has cut off craving, untied the fetters, and by rightly comprehending conceit has made an end of suffering.*";
P_HTM[4844]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, pañca nissāraṇīyā dhātuyo”ti.**These are the five elements of escape.”*";
P_HTM[4845]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4846]="*Brāhmaṇavaggo pañcamo.* **";
P_HTM[4847]="*Soṇo doṇo saṅgāravo,* **";
P_HTM[4848]="*Kāraṇapālī ca piṅgiyānī;* **";
P_HTM[4849]="*Supinā ca vassā vācā,* **";
P_HTM[4850]="*Kulaṃ nissāraṇīyena cāti.* **";
P_HTM[4851]="*Catuttho paṇṇāsako samatto.* **";
P_HTM[4852]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**With Kimbila*";
P_HTM[4853]="*1. Kimilasuttaṃ**With Kimbila*";
P_HTM[4854]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kimilāyaṃ viharati veḷuvane.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Kimbilā in the Freshwater Mangrove Wood.*";
P_HTM[4855]="*Atha kho āyasmā kimilo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā kimilo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Venerable Kimbila went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[4856]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu ko paccayo, yena tathāgate parinibbute saddhammo na ciraṭṭhitiko hotī”ti?**“What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why the true teaching does not last long after the final extinguishment of the Realized One?”*";
P_HTM[4857]="*“Idha, kimila, tathāgate parinibbute bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo upāsakā upāsikāyo satthari agāravā viharanti appatissā, dhamme agāravā viharanti appatissā, saṃghe agāravā viharanti appatissā, sikkhāya agāravā viharanti appatissā, aññamaññaṃ agāravā viharanti appatissā.**“Kimbila, it’s when the monks, nuns, laymen, and laywomen lack respect and reverence for the Teacher, the teaching, the Saṅgha, the training, and each other after the final extinguishment of the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[4858]="*Ayaṃ kho, kimila, hetu ayaṃ paccayo, yena tathāgate parinibbute saddhammo na ciraṭṭhitiko hotī”ti.**This is the cause, this is the reason why the true teaching does not last long after the final extinguishment of the Realized One.”*";
P_HTM[4859]="*“Ko pana, bhante, hetu ko paccayo, yena tathāgate parinibbute saddhammo ciraṭṭhitiko hotī”ti?**“What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why the true teaching does last long after the final extinguishment of the Realized One?”*";
P_HTM[4860]="*“Idha, kimila, tathāgate parinibbute bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo upāsakā upāsikāyo satthari sagāravā viharanti sappatissā, dhamme sagāravā viharanti sappatissā, saṅghe sagāravā viharanti sappatissā, sikkhāya sagāravā viharanti sappatissā, aññamaññaṃ sagāravā viharanti sappatissā.**“Kimbila, it’s when the monks, nuns, laymen, and laywomen maintain respect and reverence for the Teacher, the teaching, the Saṅgha, the training, and each other after the final extinguishment of the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[4861]="*Ayaṃ kho, kimila, hetu ayaṃ paccayo, yena tathāgate parinibbute saddhammo ciraṭṭhitiko hotī”ti.**This is the cause, this is the reason why the true teaching does last long after the final extinguishment of the Realized One.”*";
P_HTM[4862]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4863]="*2. Dhammassavanasuttaṃ**Listening to the Teaching*";
P_HTM[4864]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ānisaṃsā dhammassavane.**“Mendicants, there are these five benefits of listening to the teaching.*";
P_HTM[4865]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4866]="*Assutaṃ suṇāti, sutaṃ pariyodāpeti, kaṅkhaṃ vitarati, diṭṭhiṃ ujuṃ karoti, cittamassa pasīdati.**You learn new things, clarify what you’ve learned, get over uncertainty, correct your views, and inspire confidence in your mind.*";
P_HTM[4867]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā dhammassavane”ti.**These are the five benefits of listening to the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[4868]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4869]="*3. Assājānīyasuttaṃ**A Thoroughbred*";
P_HTM[4870]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato rañño bhadro assājānīyo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅgantveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**“Mendicants, a fine royal thoroughbred with five factors is worthy of a king, fit to serve a king, and is considered a factor of kingship.*";
P_HTM[4871]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4872]="*Ajjavena, javena, maddavena, khantiyā, soraccena—**Integrity, speed, gentleness, patience, and sweetness.*";
P_HTM[4873]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi aṅgehi samannāgato rañño bhadro assājānīyo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅgantveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati.**A fine royal thoroughbred with these five factors is worthy of a king. …*";
P_HTM[4874]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa.**In the same way, a mendicant with five qualities is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.*";
P_HTM[4875]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4876]="*Ajjavena, javena, maddavena, khantiyā, soraccena—**Integrity, speed, gentleness, patience, and sweetness.*";
P_HTM[4877]="*imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti.**A mendicant with these five qualities is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.”*";
P_HTM[4878]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4879]="*4. Balasuttaṃ**Powers*";
P_HTM[4880]="*“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, balāni.**“Mendicants, there are these five powers.*";
P_HTM[4881]="*Katamāni pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4882]="*Saddhābalaṃ, hiribalaṃ, ottappabalaṃ, vīriyabalaṃ, paññābalaṃ—**Faith, conscience, prudence, energy, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[4883]="*imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca balānī”ti.**These are the five powers.”*";
P_HTM[4884]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4885]="*5. Cetokhilasuttaṃ**Emotional Barrenness*";
P_HTM[4886]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, cetokhilā.**“Mendicants, there are these five kinds of emotional barrenness.*";
P_HTM[4887]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4888]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu satthari kaṅkhati vicikicchati nādhimuccati na sampasīdati.**Firstly, a mendicant has doubts about the Teacher. They’re uncertain, undecided, and lacking confidence.*";
P_HTM[4889]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu satthari kaṅkhati vicikicchati nādhimuccati na sampasīdati, tassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya.**This being so, their mind doesn’t incline toward keenness, commitment, persistence, and striving.*";
P_HTM[4890]="*Yassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya, ayaṃ paṭhamo cetokhilo.**This is the first kind of emotional barrenness.*";
P_HTM[4891]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhamme kaṅkhati … pe …**Furthermore, a mendicant has doubts about the teaching …*";
P_HTM[4892]="*saṅghe kaṅkhati … pe …**the Saṅgha …*";
P_HTM[4893]="*sikkhāya kaṅkhati … pe …**the training …*";
P_HTM[4894]="*sabrahmacārīsu kupito hoti anattamano āhatacitto khilajāto.**A mendicant is angry and upset with their spiritual companions, resentful and closed off.*";
P_HTM[4895]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabrahmacārīsu kupito hoti anattamano āhatacitto khilajāto, tassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya.**This being so, their mind doesn’t incline toward keenness, commitment, persistence, and striving.*";
P_HTM[4896]="*Yassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya, ayaṃ pañcamo cetokhilo.**This is the fifth kind of emotional barrenness.*";
P_HTM[4897]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca cetokhilā”ti.**These are the five kinds of emotional barrenness.”*";
P_HTM[4898]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4899]="*6. Vinibandhasuttaṃ**Shackles*";
P_HTM[4900]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, cetasovinibandhā.**“Mendicants, there are these five emotional shackles.*";
P_HTM[4901]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4902]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāmesu avītarāgo hoti avigatacchando avigatapemo avigatapipāso avigatapariḷāho avigatataṇho.**Firstly, a mendicant isn’t free of greed, desire, fondness, thirst, passion, and craving for sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[4903]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāmesu avītarāgo hoti avigatacchando avigatapemo avigatapipāso avigatapariḷāho avigatataṇho, tassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya.**This being so, their mind doesn’t incline toward keenness, commitment, persistence, and striving.*";
P_HTM[4904]="*Yassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya, ayaṃ paṭhamo cetasovinibandho.**This is the first emotional shackle.*";
P_HTM[4905]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye avītarāgo hoti … pe …**Furthermore, a mendicant isn’t free of greed for the body …*";
P_HTM[4906]="*rūpe avītarāgo hoti … pe …**They’re not free of greed for form …*";
P_HTM[4907]="*yāvadatthaṃ udarāvadehakaṃ bhuñjitvā seyyasukhaṃ passasukhaṃ middhasukhaṃ anuyutto viharati … pe …**They eat as much as they like until their belly is full, then indulge in the pleasures of sleeping, lying, and drowsing …*";
P_HTM[4908]="*aññataraṃ devanikāyaṃ paṇidhāya brahmacariyaṃ carati: ‘imināhaṃ sīlena vā vatena vā tapena vā brahmacariyena vā devo vā bhavissāmi devaññataro vā’ti.**They live the spiritual life hoping to be reborn in one of the orders of gods, thinking: ‘By this precept or observance or mortification or spiritual life, may I become one of the gods!’*";
P_HTM[4909]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ devanikāyaṃ paṇidhāya brahmacariyaṃ carati: ‘imināhaṃ sīlena vā vatena vā tapena vā brahmacariyena vā devo vā bhavissāmi devaññataro vā’ti, tassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya.**This being so, their mind doesn’t incline toward keenness, commitment, persistence, and striving.*";
P_HTM[4910]="*Yassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya, ayaṃ pañcamo cetasovinibandho.**This is the fifth emotional shackle.*";
P_HTM[4911]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca cetasovinibandhā”ti.**These are the five emotional shackles.”*";
P_HTM[4912]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4913]="*7. Yāgusuttaṃ**Porridge*";
P_HTM[4914]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ānisaṃsā yāguyā.**“Mendicants, there are these five benefits of porridge.*";
P_HTM[4915]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4916]="*Khuddaṃ paṭihanati, pipāsaṃ paṭivineti, vātaṃ anulometi, vatthiṃ sodheti, āmāvasesaṃ pāceti.**It wards off hunger, quenches thirst, settles the wind, cleans the bladder, and helps digestion.*";
P_HTM[4917]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā yāguyā”ti.**These are the five benefits of porridge.”*";
P_HTM[4918]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4919]="*8. Dantakaṭṭhasuttaṃ**Chew Sticks*";
P_HTM[4920]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā dantakaṭṭhassa akhādane.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks of not using chew sticks.*";
P_HTM[4921]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4922]="*Acakkhussaṃ, mukhaṃ duggandhaṃ hoti, rasaharaṇiyo na visujjhanti, pittaṃ semhaṃ bhattaṃ pariyonandhati, bhattamassa nacchādeti.**It’s not good for your eyes, you get bad breath, your taste-buds aren’t cleaned, bile and phlegm cover your food, and you lose your appetite.*";
P_HTM[4923]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā dantakaṭṭhassa akhādane.**These are the five drawbacks of not using chew sticks.*";
P_HTM[4924]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, ānisaṃsā dantakaṭṭhassa khādane.**There are these five benefits of using chew sticks.*";
P_HTM[4925]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4926]="*Cakkhussaṃ, mukhaṃ na duggandhaṃ hoti, rasaharaṇiyo visujjhanti, pittaṃ semhaṃ bhattaṃ na pariyonandhati, bhattamassa chādeti.**It’s good for your eyes, you don’t get bad breath, your taste-buds are cleaned, bile and phlegm don’t cover your food, and food agrees with you.*";
P_HTM[4927]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā dantakaṭṭhassa khādane”ti.**These are the five benefits of using chew sticks.”*";
P_HTM[4928]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4929]="*9. Gītassarasuttaṃ**The Sound of Singing*";
P_HTM[4930]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā āyatakena gītassarena dhammaṃ bhaṇantassa.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks in reciting with a drawn-out singing sound.*";
P_HTM[4931]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4932]="*Attanāpi tasmiṃ sare sārajjati, parepi tasmiṃ sare sārajjanti, gahapatikāpi ujjhāyanti:**You relish the sound of your own voice. Others relish the sound of your voice. Householders complain:*";
P_HTM[4933]="*‘yatheva mayaṃ gāyāma, evamevaṃ kho samaṇā sakyaputtiyā gāyantī’ti, sarakuttimpi nikāmayamānassa samādhissa bhaṅgo hoti, pacchimā janatā diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjati.**‘These ascetics, followers of the Sakyan, sing just like us!’ When you’re enjoying the melody, your immersion breaks up. Those who come after follow your example.*";
P_HTM[4934]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā āyatakena gītassarena dhammaṃ bhaṇantassā”ti.**These are the five drawbacks in reciting with a drawn-out singing sound.”*";
P_HTM[4935]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4936]="*10. Muṭṭhassatisuttaṃ**Unmindful*";
P_HTM[4937]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā muṭṭhassatissa asampajānassa niddaṃ okkamayato.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks of falling asleep unmindful and unaware.*";
P_HTM[4938]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4939]="*Dukkhaṃ supati, dukkhaṃ paṭibujjhati, pāpakaṃ supinaṃ passati, devatā na rakkhanti, asuci muccati.**You sleep badly and wake miserably. You have bad dreams. The deities don’t protect you. And you emit semen.*";
P_HTM[4940]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā muṭṭhassatissa asampajānassa niddaṃ okkamayato.**These are the five drawbacks of falling asleep unmindful and unaware.*";
P_HTM[4941]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, ānisaṃsā upaṭṭhitassatissa sampajānassa niddaṃ okkamayato.**There are these five benefits of falling asleep mindful and aware.*";
P_HTM[4942]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4943]="*Sukhaṃ supati, sukhaṃ paṭibujjhati, na pāpakaṃ supinaṃ passati, devatā rakkhanti, asuci na muccati.**You sleep well and wake happily. You don’t have bad dreams. The deities protect you. And you don’t emit semen.*";
P_HTM[4944]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā upaṭṭhitassatissa sampajānassa niddaṃ okkamayato”ti.**These are the five benefits of falling asleep mindful and aware.”*";
P_HTM[4945]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4946]="*Kimilavaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[4947]="*Kimilo dhammassavanaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[4948]="*ājānīyo balaṃ khilaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4949]="*Vinibandhaṃ yāgu kaṭṭhaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[4950]="*gītaṃ muṭṭhassatinā cāti.* **";
P_HTM[4951]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**Abuse*";
P_HTM[4952]="*1. Akkosakasuttaṃ**An Abuser*";
P_HTM[4953]="*“Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkosakaparibhāsako ariyūpavādī sabrahmacārīnaṃ, tassa pañca ādīnavā pāṭikaṅkhā.**“Mendicants, a mendicant who abuses and insults their spiritual companions, speaking ill of the noble ones, can expect these five drawbacks.*";
P_HTM[4954]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4955]="*Pārājiko vā hoti chinnaparipantho, aññataraṃ vā saṃkiliṭṭhaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati, bāḷhaṃ vā rogātaṅkaṃ phusati, sammūḷho kālaṃ karoti, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati.**They’re expelled, cut off, shut out; or they commit a corrupt offense; or they contract a severe illness. They die confused. And when their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[4956]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu akkosakaparibhāsako ariyūpavādī sabrahmacārīnaṃ, tassa ime pañca ādīnavā pāṭikaṅkhā”ti.**A mendicant who abuses and insults their spiritual companions, speaking ill of the noble ones, can expect these five drawbacks.”*";
P_HTM[4957]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4958]="*2. Bhaṇḍanakārakasuttaṃ**Starting Arguments*";
P_HTM[4959]="*“Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bhaṇḍanakārako kalahakārako vivādakārako bhassakārako saṃghe adhikaraṇakārako, tassa pañca ādīnavā pāṭikaṅkhā.**“Mendicants, a mendicant who starts arguments, quarrels, fights, debates, and disciplinary issues in the Saṅgha can expect five drawbacks.*";
P_HTM[4960]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4961]="*Anadhigataṃ nādhigacchati, adhigatā parihāyati, pāpako kittisaddo abbhuggacchati, sammūḷho kālaṃ karoti, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati.**They don’t achieve the unachieved. What they have achieved falls away. They get a bad reputation. They feel lost when they die. And when their body breaks up, after death, they are reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[4962]="*Yo so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bhaṇḍanakārako kalahakārako vivādakārako bhassakārako saṃghe adhikaraṇakārako, tassa ime pañca ādīnavā pāṭikaṅkhā”ti.**A mendicant who starts arguments, quarrels, fights, debates, and disciplinary issues in the Saṅgha can expect these five drawbacks.”*";
P_HTM[4963]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4964]="*3. Sīlasuttaṃ**Ethics*";
P_HTM[4965]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks for an unethical person because of their failure in ethics.*";
P_HTM[4966]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4967]="*Idha, bhikkhave, dussīlo sīlavipanno pamādādhikaraṇaṃ mahatiṃ bhogajāniṃ nigacchati.**Firstly, an unethical person loses substantial wealth on account of negligence.*";
P_HTM[4968]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo ādīnavo dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā.**This is the first drawback.*";
P_HTM[4969]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, dussīlassa sīlavipannassa pāpako kittisaddo abbhuggacchati.**Furthermore, an unethical person gets a bad reputation.*";
P_HTM[4970]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo ādīnavo dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā.**This is the second drawback.*";
P_HTM[4971]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, dussīlo sīlavipanno yaññadeva parisaṃ upasaṅkamati—yadi khattiyaparisaṃ, yadi brāhmaṇaparisaṃ, yadi gahapatiparisaṃ, yadi samaṇaparisaṃ—avisārado upasaṅkamati maṅkubhūto.**Furthermore, an unethical person enters any kind of assembly timid and embarrassed, whether it’s an assembly of aristocrats, brahmins, householders, or ascetics.*";
P_HTM[4972]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo ādīnavo dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā.**This is the third drawback.*";
P_HTM[4973]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, dussīlo sīlavipanno sammūḷho kālaṃ karoti.**Furthermore, an unethical person dies feeling lost.*";
P_HTM[4974]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho ādīnavo dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā.**This is the fourth drawback.*";
P_HTM[4975]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, dussīlo sīlavipanno kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati.**Furthermore, an unethical person, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[4976]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo ādīnavo dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā.**This is the fifth drawback.*";
P_HTM[4977]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā.**These are the five drawbacks for an unethical person because of their failure in ethics.*";
P_HTM[4978]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, ānisaṃsā sīlavato sīlasampadāya.**There are these five benefits for an ethical person because of their accomplishment in ethics.*";
P_HTM[4979]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4980]="*Idha, bhikkhave, sīlavā sīlasampanno appamādādhikaraṇaṃ mahantaṃ bhogakkhandhaṃ adhigacchati.**Firstly, an ethical person gains substantial wealth on account of diligence.*";
P_HTM[4981]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo ānisaṃso sīlavato sīlasampadāya.**This is the first benefit.*";
P_HTM[4982]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sīlavato sīlasampannassa kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggacchati.**Furthermore, an ethical person gets a good reputation.*";
P_HTM[4983]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo ānisaṃso sīlavato sīlasampadāya.**This is the second benefit.*";
P_HTM[4984]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sīlavā sīlasampanno yaññadeva parisaṃ upasaṅkamati—yadi khattiyaparisaṃ, yadi brāhmaṇaparisaṃ, yadi gahapatiparisaṃ, yadi samaṇaparisaṃ—visārado upasaṅkamati amaṅkubhūto.**Furthermore, an ethical person enters any kind of assembly bold and self-assured, whether it’s an assembly of aristocrats, brahmins, householders, or ascetics.*";
P_HTM[4985]="*Ayaṃ bhikkhave, tatiyo ānisaṃso sīlavato sīlasampadāya.**This is the third benefit.*";
P_HTM[4986]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sīlavā sīlasampanno asammūḷho kālaṃ karoti.**Furthermore, an ethical person dies not feeling lost.*";
P_HTM[4987]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho ānisaṃso sīlavato sīlasampadāya.**This is the fourth benefit.*";
P_HTM[4988]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sīlavā sīlasampanno kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati.**Furthermore, when an ethical person’s body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[4989]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo ānisaṃso sīlavato sīlasampadāya.**This is the fifth benefit.*";
P_HTM[4990]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā sīlavato sīlasampadāyā”ti.**These are the five benefits for an ethical person because of their accomplishment in ethics.”*";
P_HTM[4991]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4992]="*4. Bahubhāṇisuttaṃ**Someone Who Talks a Lot*";
P_HTM[4993]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā bahubhāṇismiṃ puggale.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks for a person who talks a lot.*";
P_HTM[4994]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4995]="*Musā bhaṇati, pisuṇaṃ bhaṇati, pharusaṃ bhaṇati, samphappalāpaṃ bhaṇati, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati.**They use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, and nonsensical. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[4996]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā bahubhāṇismiṃ puggale.**These are the five drawbacks for a person who talks a lot.*";
P_HTM[4997]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, ānisaṃsā mantabhāṇismiṃ puggale.**There are these five benefits for a person who talks thoughtfully.*";
P_HTM[4998]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4999]="*Na musā bhaṇati, na pisuṇaṃ bhaṇati, na pharusaṃ bhaṇati, na samphappalāpaṃ bhaṇati, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati.**They don’t use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, and nonsensical. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[5000]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā mantabhāṇismiṃ puggale”ti.**These are the five benefits for a person who talks thoughtfully.”*";
P_HTM[5001]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5002]="*5. Paṭhamaakkhantisuttaṃ**Intolerance (1st)*";
P_HTM[5003]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā akkhantiyā.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks of intolerance.*";
P_HTM[5004]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5005]="*Bahuno janassa appiyo hoti amanāpo, verabahulo ca hoti, vajjabahulo ca, sammūḷho kālaṃ karoti, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati.**Most people find you unlikable and unloveable. You have lots of enmity and many faults. You feel lost when you die. And when your body breaks up, after death, you’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[5006]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā akkhantiyā.**These are the five drawbacks to intolerance.*";
P_HTM[5007]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, ānisaṃsā khantiyā.**There are these five benefits of tolerance.*";
P_HTM[5008]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5009]="*Bahuno janassa piyo hoti manāpo, na verabahulo hoti, na vajjabahulo, asammūḷho kālaṃ karoti, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati.**Most people find you dear and lovable. You have little enmity and few faults. You don’t feel lost when you die. And when your body breaks up, after death, you’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[5010]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā khantiyā”ti.**These are the five benefits of tolerance.”*";
P_HTM[5011]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5012]="*6. Dutiyaakkhantisuttaṃ**Intolerance (2nd)*";
P_HTM[5013]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā akkhantiyā.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks of intolerance.*";
P_HTM[5014]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5015]="*Bahuno janassa appiyo hoti amanāpo, luddo ca hoti, vippaṭisārī ca, sammūḷho kālaṃ karoti, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati.**Most people find you unlikable and unlovable. You’re cruel and remorseful. You feel lost when you die. And when your body breaks up, after death, you’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[5016]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā akkhantiyā.**These are the five drawbacks to intolerance.*";
P_HTM[5017]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, ānisaṃsā khantiyā.**There are these five benefits of tolerance.*";
P_HTM[5018]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5019]="*Bahuno janassa piyo hoti manāpo, aluddo ca hoti, avippaṭisārī ca, asammūḷho kālaṃ karoti, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati.**Most people find you likable and lovable. You’re neither cruel nor remorseful. You don’t feel lost when you die. And when your body breaks up, after death, you’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[5020]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā khantiyā”ti.**These are the five benefits of tolerance.”*";
P_HTM[5021]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5022]="*7. Paṭhamaapāsādikasuttaṃ**Uninspiring Conduct (1st)*";
P_HTM[5023]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā apāsādike.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks of uninspiring conduct.*";
P_HTM[5024]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5025]="*Attāpi attānaṃ upavadati,**You blame yourself.*";
P_HTM[5026]="*anuvicca viññū garahanti,**After examination, sensible people criticize you.*";
P_HTM[5027]="*pāpako kittisaddo abbhuggacchati,**You get a bad reputation.*";
P_HTM[5028]="*sammūḷho kālaṃ karoti,**You feel lost when you die.*";
P_HTM[5029]="*kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati.**And when your body breaks up, after death, you’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[5030]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā apāsādike.**These are the five drawbacks of uninspiring conduct.*";
P_HTM[5031]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, ānisaṃsā pāsādike.**There are these five benefits of inspiring conduct.*";
P_HTM[5032]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5033]="*Attāpi attānaṃ na upavadati,**You don’t blame yourself.*";
P_HTM[5034]="*anuvicca viññū pasaṃsanti,**After examination, sensible people praise you.*";
P_HTM[5035]="*kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggacchati,**You get a good reputation.*";
P_HTM[5036]="*asammūḷho kālaṃ karoti,**You don’t feel lost when you die.*";
P_HTM[5037]="*kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati.**And when the body breaks up, after death, you’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[5038]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā pāsādike”ti.**These are the five benefits of inspiring conduct.”*";
P_HTM[5039]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5040]="*8. Dutiyaapāsādikasuttaṃ**Uninspiring Conduct (2nd)*";
P_HTM[5041]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā apāsādike.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks of uninspiring conduct.*";
P_HTM[5042]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5043]="*Appasannā nappasīdanti, pasannānañca ekaccānaṃ aññathattaṃ hoti, satthusāsanaṃ akataṃ hoti, pacchimā janatā diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjati, cittamassa nappasīdati.**You don’t inspire confidence in those without it. You cause some with confidence to change their minds. You don’t follow the Teacher’s instructions. Those who come after you follow your example. And your mind doesn’t become clear.*";
P_HTM[5044]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā apāsādike.**These are the five drawbacks of uninspiring conduct.*";
P_HTM[5045]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, ānisaṃsā pāsādike.**There are these five benefits of inspiring conduct.*";
P_HTM[5046]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5047]="*Appasannā pasīdanti, pasannānañca bhiyyobhāvo hoti, satthusāsanaṃ kataṃ hoti, pacchimā janatā diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjati, cittamassa pasīdati.**You inspire confidence in those without it. You increase confidence in those who have it. You follow the Teacher’s instructions. Those who come after you follow your example. And your mind becomes clear.*";
P_HTM[5048]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā pāsādike”ti.**These are the five benefits of inspiring conduct.”*";
P_HTM[5049]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5050]="*9. Aggisuttaṃ**Fire*";
P_HTM[5051]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā aggismiṃ.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks of a fire.*";
P_HTM[5052]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5053]="*Acakkhusso, dubbaṇṇakaraṇo, dubbalakaraṇo, saṅgaṇikāpavaḍḍhano, tiracchānakathāpavattaniko hoti.**It’s bad for your eyes. It’s bad for your complexion. It makes you weak. It draws in groups. And it encourages unworthy talk.*";
P_HTM[5054]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā aggismin”ti.**These are the five drawbacks of a fire.”*";
P_HTM[5055]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5056]="*10. Madhurāsuttaṃ**About Madhurā*";
P_HTM[5057]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā madhurāyaṃ.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks of Madhurā.*";
P_HTM[5058]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5059]="*Visamā, bahurajā, caṇḍasunakhā, vāḷayakkhā, dullabhapiṇḍā.**The ground is uneven and dusty, the dogs are fierce, the native spirits are vicious, and it’s hard to get almsfood.*";
P_HTM[5060]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā madhurāyan”ti.**These are the five drawbacks of Madhurā.”*";
P_HTM[5061]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5062]="*Akkosakavaggo dutiyo.* **";
P_HTM[5063]="*Akkosabhaṇḍanasīlaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[5064]="*bahubhāṇī dve akhantiyo;* **";
P_HTM[5065]="*Apāsādikā dve vuttā,* **";
P_HTM[5066]="*aggismiṃ madhurena cāti.* **";
P_HTM[5067]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**Long Wandering*";
P_HTM[5068]="*1. Paṭhamadīghacārikasuttaṃ**Long Wandering (1st)*";
P_HTM[5069]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā dīghacārikaṃ anavatthacārikaṃ anuyuttassa viharato.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks for someone who likes long and aimless wandering.*";
P_HTM[5070]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5071]="*Assutaṃ na suṇāti, sutaṃ na pariyodāpeti, sutenekaccena avisārado hoti, gāḷhaṃ rogātaṅkaṃ phusati, na ca mittavā hoti.**You don’t learn new things. You don’t clarify what you’ve learned. You lack confidence in some things you have learned. You contract a severe illness. You don’t have any friends.*";
P_HTM[5072]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā dīghacārikaṃ anavatthacārikaṃ anuyuttassa viharato.**These are the five drawbacks for someone who likes long and aimless wandering.*";
P_HTM[5073]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, ānisaṃsā samavatthacāre.**There are these five benefits of a reasonable amount of wandering.*";
P_HTM[5074]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5075]="*Assutaṃ suṇāti, sutaṃ pariyodāpeti, sutenekaccena visārado hoti, na gāḷhaṃ rogātaṅkaṃ phusati, mittavā ca hoti.**You learn new things. You clarify what you’ve learned. You have confidence in some things you have learned. You don’t contract severe illness. You have friends.*";
P_HTM[5076]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā samavatthacāre”ti.**These are the five benefits of a reasonable amount of wandering.”*";
P_HTM[5077]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5078]="*2. Dutiyadīghacārikasuttaṃ**Long Wandering (2nd)*";
P_HTM[5079]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā dīghacārikaṃ anavatthacārikaṃ anuyuttassa viharato.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks for someone who likes long and aimless wandering.*";
P_HTM[5080]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5081]="*Anadhigataṃ nādhigacchati, adhigatā parihāyati, adhigatenekaccena avisārado hoti, gāḷhaṃ rogātaṅkaṃ phusati, na ca mittavā hoti.**You don’t achieve the unachieved. What you have achieved falls away. You lose confidence in some things you’ve achieved. You contract a severe illness. You don’t have any friends.*";
P_HTM[5082]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā dīghacārikaṃ anavatthacārikaṃ anuyuttassa viharato.**These are the five drawbacks for someone who likes long and aimless wandering.*";
P_HTM[5083]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, ānisaṃsā samavatthacāre.**There are these five benefits of a reasonable amount of wandering.*";
P_HTM[5084]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5085]="*Anadhigataṃ adhigacchati, adhigatā na parihāyati, adhigatenekaccena visārado hoti, na gāḷhaṃ rogātaṅkaṃ phusati, mittavā ca hoti.**You achieve the unachieved. What you have achieved doesn’t fall away. You’re confident in some things you’ve achieved. You don’t contract severe illness. You have friends.*";
P_HTM[5086]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā samavatthacāre”ti.**These are the five benefits of a reasonable amount of wandering.”*";
P_HTM[5087]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5088]="*3. Atinivāsasuttaṃ**Overstaying*";
P_HTM[5089]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā atinivāse.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks of overstaying.*";
P_HTM[5090]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5091]="*Bahubhaṇḍo hoti bahubhaṇḍasannicayo, bahubhesajjo hoti bahubhesajjasannicayo, bahukicco hoti bahukaraṇīyo byatto kiṅkaraṇīyesu, saṃsaṭṭho viharati gahaṭṭhapabbajitehi ananulomikena gihisaṃsaggena, tamhā ca āvāsā pakkamanto sāpekkho pakkamati.**You have a lot of stuff and store it up. You have a lot of medicine and store it up. You have a lot of duties and responsibilities, and become capable in whatever needs to be done. You mix closely with laypeople and renunciates, socializing inappropriately like a layperson. And when you leave that monastery, you miss it.*";
P_HTM[5092]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā atinivāse.**These are the five drawbacks of overstaying.*";
P_HTM[5093]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, ānisaṃsā samavatthavāse.**There are these five benefits of staying for a reasonable length of time.*";
P_HTM[5094]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5095]="*Na bahubhaṇḍo hoti na bahubhaṇḍasannicayo, na bahubhesajjo hoti na bahubhesajjasannicayo, na bahukicco hoti na bahukaraṇīyo na byatto kiṅkaraṇīyesu, asaṃsaṭṭho viharati gahaṭṭhapabbajitehi ananulomikena gihisaṃsaggena, tamhā ca āvāsā pakkamanto anapekkho pakkamati.**You don’t have a lot of stuff and store it up. You don’t have a lot of medicine and store it up. You don’t have a lot of duties and responsibilities, or become capable in whatever needs to be done. You don’t mix closely with laypeople and renunciates, socializing inappropriately like a layperson. And when you leave that monastery, you don’t miss it.*";
P_HTM[5096]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā samavatthavāse”ti.**These are the five benefits of staying for a reasonable length of time.”*";
P_HTM[5097]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5098]="*4. Maccharīsuttaṃ**Stingy*";
P_HTM[5099]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā atinivāse.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks of overstaying.*";
P_HTM[5100]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5101]="*Āvāsamaccharī hoti, kulamaccharī hoti, lābhamaccharī hoti, vaṇṇamaccharī hoti, dhammamaccharī hoti.**You become stingy with dwellings, families, material possessions, praise, and the teaching.*";
P_HTM[5102]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā atinivāse.**These are the five drawbacks of overstaying.*";
P_HTM[5103]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, ānisaṃsā samavatthavāse.**There are these five benefits of staying for a reasonable length of time.*";
P_HTM[5104]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5105]="*Na āvāsamaccharī hoti, na kulamaccharī hoti, na lābhamaccharī hoti, na vaṇṇamaccharī hoti, na dhammamaccharī hoti.**You’re not stingy with dwellings, families, material possessions, praise, and the teaching.*";
P_HTM[5106]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā samavatthavāse”ti.**These are the five benefits of staying for a reasonable length of time.”*";
P_HTM[5107]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5108]="*5. Paṭhamakulūpakasuttaṃ**Visiting Families (1st)*";
P_HTM[5109]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā kulūpake.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks of visiting families.*";
P_HTM[5110]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5111]="*Anāmantacāre āpajjati, raho nisajjāya āpajjati, paṭicchanne āsane āpajjati, mātugāmassa uttari chappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ desento āpajjati, kāmasaṅkappabahulo viharati.**You fall into an offense for wandering without leave. You fall into an offense for sitting in a private place with someone of the opposite sex. You fall into an offense for sitting in a hidden place with someone of the opposite sex. You fall into an offense for teaching more than five or six sentences to someone of the opposite sex. You have a lot of sensual thoughts.*";
P_HTM[5112]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā kulūpake”ti.**These are the five drawbacks of visiting families.”*";
P_HTM[5113]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5114]="*6. Dutiyakulūpakasuttaṃ**Visiting Families (2nd)*";
P_HTM[5115]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā kulūpakassa bhikkhuno ativelaṃ kulesu saṃsaṭṭhassa viharato.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks for a mendicant who visits families for too long, mixing closely with them.*";
P_HTM[5116]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5117]="*Mātugāmassa abhiṇhadassanaṃ,**You often see members of the opposite sex.*";
P_HTM[5118]="*dassane sati saṃsaggo,**Seeing them, you become close.*";
P_HTM[5119]="*saṃsagge sati vissāso,**Being so close, you become intimate.*";
P_HTM[5120]="*vissāse sati otāro,**Being intimate, lust overcomes you.*";
P_HTM[5121]="*otiṇṇacittassetaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ: ‘anabhirato vā brahmacariyaṃ carissati aññataraṃ vā saṅkiliṭṭhaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjissati sikkhaṃ vā paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattissati’.**When your mind is swamped by lust, you can expect that you will live the spiritual life dissatisfied, or commit one of the corrupt offenses, or reject the training and return to a lesser life.*";
P_HTM[5122]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā kulūpakassa bhikkhuno ativelaṃ kulesu saṃsaṭṭhassa viharato”ti.**These are the five drawbacks for a mendicant who visits families for too long, mixing closely with them.”*";
P_HTM[5123]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5124]="*7. Bhogasuttaṃ**Riches*";
P_HTM[5125]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā bhogesu.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks of riches.*";
P_HTM[5126]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5127]="*Aggisādhāraṇā bhogā, udakasādhāraṇā bhogā, rājasādhāraṇā bhogā, corasādhāraṇā bhogā, appiyehi dāyādehi sādhāraṇā bhogā.**Fire, water, kings, thieves, and unloved heirs all take a share.*";
P_HTM[5128]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā bhogesu.**These are the five drawbacks of riches.*";
P_HTM[5129]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, ānisaṃsā bhogesu.**There are these five benefits of riches.*";
P_HTM[5130]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5131]="*Bhoge nissāya attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti sammā sukhaṃ pariharati, mātāpitaro sukheti pīṇeti sammā sukhaṃ pariharati, puttadāradāsakammakaraporise sukheti pīṇeti sammā sukhaṃ pariharati, mittāmacce sukheti pīṇeti sammā sukhaṃ pariharati, samaṇabrāhmaṇesu uddhaggikaṃ dakkhiṇaṃ patiṭṭhāpeti sovaggikaṃ sukhavipākaṃ saggasaṃvattanikaṃ.**Riches enable you to bring pleasure and joy to yourself; your mother and father; your children, partners, bondservants, workers, and staff; and your friends and colleagues; and to keep them all happy. And they enable you to establish an uplifting religious donation for ascetics and brahmins that’s conducive to heaven, ripens in happiness, and leads to heaven.*";
P_HTM[5132]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā bhogesū”ti.**These are the five benefits of riches.”*";
P_HTM[5133]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5134]="*8. Ussūrabhattasuttaṃ**Eating Late*";
P_HTM[5135]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā ussūrabhatte kule.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks for a family who takes their meals late in the day.*";
P_HTM[5136]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5137]="*Ye te atithī pāhunā, te na kālena paṭipūjenti;**When guests visit, they are not served on time.*";
P_HTM[5138]="*yā tā balipaṭiggāhikā devatā, tā na kālena paṭipūjenti;**The deities who accept spirit-offerings are not served on time.*";
P_HTM[5139]="*ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā ekabhattikā rattūparatā viratā vikālabhojanā, te na kālena paṭipūjenti;**Ascetics and brahmins who eat in one part of the day, abstaining from eating at night, and from food at the wrong time are not served on time.*";
P_HTM[5140]="*dāsakammakaraporisā vimukhā kammaṃ karonti;**Bondservants, workers, and staff do their duties neglectfully.*";
P_HTM[5141]="*tāvatakaṃyeva asamayena bhuttaṃ anojavantaṃ hoti.**A meal eaten during the wrong period is not nutritious.*";
P_HTM[5142]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā ussūrabhatte kule.**These are the five drawbacks for a family who takes their meals late in the day.*";
P_HTM[5143]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, ānisaṃsā samayabhatte kule.**There are these five benefits for a family who takes their meals at a proper time.*";
P_HTM[5144]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5145]="*Ye te atithī pāhunā, te kālena paṭipūjenti;**When guests visit, they are served on time.*";
P_HTM[5146]="*yā tā balipaṭiggāhikā devatā, tā kālena paṭipūjenti;**The deities who accept spirit-offerings are served on time.*";
P_HTM[5147]="*ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā ekabhattikā rattūparatā viratā vikālabhojanā, te kālena paṭipūjenti;**Ascetics and brahmins who eat in one part of the day, abstaining from eating at night, and from food at the wrong time are served on time.*";
P_HTM[5148]="*dāsakammakaraporisā avimukhā kammaṃ karonti;**Bondservants, workers, and staff do their duties attentively.*";
P_HTM[5149]="*tāvatakaṃyeva samayena bhuttaṃ ojavantaṃ hoti.**A meal eaten during the proper period is nutritious.*";
P_HTM[5150]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā samayabhatte kule”ti.**These are the five benefits for a family who takes their meals at a proper time.”*";
P_HTM[5151]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5152]="*9. Paṭhamakaṇhasappasuttaṃ**Black Snakes (1st)*";
P_HTM[5153]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā kaṇhasappe.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks of a black snake.*";
P_HTM[5154]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5155]="*Asuci, duggandho, sabhīru, sappaṭibhayo, mittadubbhī.**It’s filthy, stinking, cowardly, frightening, and treacherous.*";
P_HTM[5156]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā kaṇhasappe.**These are the five dangers of a black snake.*";
P_HTM[5157]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcime ādīnavā mātugāme.**In the same way there are five drawbacks of a female.*";
P_HTM[5158]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5159]="*Asuci, duggandho, sabhīru, sappaṭibhayo, mittadubbhī.**She’s filthy, stinking, cowardly, frightening, and treacherous.*";
P_HTM[5160]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā mātugāme”ti.**These are the five drawbacks of a female.”*";
P_HTM[5161]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5162]="*10. Dutiyakaṇhasappasuttaṃ**Black Snakes (2nd)*";
P_HTM[5163]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā kaṇhasappe.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks of a black snake.*";
P_HTM[5164]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5165]="*Kodhano, upanāhī, ghoraviso, dujjivho, mittadubbhī.**It’s irritable, hostile, venomous, fork-tongued, and treacherous.*";
P_HTM[5166]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā kaṇhasappe.**These are the five dangers of a black snake.*";
P_HTM[5167]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcime ādīnavā mātugāme.**In the same way there are five drawbacks of a female.*";
P_HTM[5168]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5169]="*Kodhano, upanāhī, ghoraviso, dujjivho, mittadubbhī.**She’s irritable, hostile, venomous, fork-tongued, and treacherous.*";
P_HTM[5170]="*Tatridaṃ, bhikkhave, mātugāmassa ghoravisatā—**This is a female’s venom:*";
P_HTM[5171]="*yebhuyyena, bhikkhave, mātugāmo tibbarāgo.**usually she’s very lustful.*";
P_HTM[5172]="*Tatridaṃ, bhikkhave, mātugāmassa dujjivhatā—**This is a female’s forked tongue:*";
P_HTM[5173]="*yebhuyyena, bhikkhave, mātugāmo pisuṇavāco.**usually she speaks divisively.*";
P_HTM[5174]="*Tatridaṃ, bhikkhave, mātugāmassa mittadubbhitā—**This is a female’s treachery:*";
P_HTM[5175]="*yebhuyyena, bhikkhave, mātugāmo aticārinī.**usually she’s an adulteress.*";
P_HTM[5176]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā mātugāme”ti.**These are the five drawbacks of a female.”*";
P_HTM[5177]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5178]="*Dīghacārikavaggo tatiyo.* **";
P_HTM[5179]="*Dve dīghacārikā vuttā,* **";
P_HTM[5180]="*atinivāsamaccharī;* **";
P_HTM[5181]="*Dve ca kulūpakā bhogā,* **";
P_HTM[5182]="*bhattaṃ sappāpare duveti.* **";
P_HTM[5183]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**A Resident Mendicant*";
P_HTM[5184]="*1. Āvāsikasuttaṃ**A Resident Mendicant*";
P_HTM[5185]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu abhāvanīyo hoti.**“Mendicants, a resident mendicant with five qualities is not admirable.*";
P_HTM[5186]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5187]="*Na ākappasampanno hoti na vattasampanno;**They’re not accomplished in being well-presented and doing their duties.*";
P_HTM[5188]="*na bahussuto hoti na sutadharo;**They’re not very learned and don’t remember what they’ve learned.*";
P_HTM[5189]="*na paṭisallekhitā hoti na paṭisallānārāmo;**They’re not self-effacing and don’t enjoy self-effacement.*";
P_HTM[5190]="*na kalyāṇavāco hoti na kalyāṇavākkaraṇo;**They’re not a good speaker and don’t speak well.*";
P_HTM[5191]="*duppañño hoti jaḷo eḷamūgo.**They’re witless, dull, and stupid.*";
P_HTM[5192]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu abhāvanīyo hoti.**A resident mendicant with these five qualities is not admirable.*";
P_HTM[5193]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu bhāvanīyo hoti.**A resident mendicant with these five qualities is admirable.*";
P_HTM[5194]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5195]="*Ākappasampanno hoti vattasampanno;**They’re accomplished in being well-presented and doing their duties.*";
P_HTM[5196]="*bahussuto hoti sutadharo;**They’re very learned and remember what they’ve learned.*";
P_HTM[5197]="*paṭisallekhitā hoti paṭisallānārāmo;**They’re self-effacing and enjoy self-effacement.*";
P_HTM[5198]="*kalyāṇavāco hoti kalyāṇavākkaraṇo;**They’re a good speaker and speak well.*";
P_HTM[5199]="*paññavā hoti ajaḷo aneḷamūgo.**They’re wise, bright, and clever.*";
P_HTM[5200]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu bhāvanīyo hotī”ti.**A resident mendicant with these five qualities is admirable.”*";
P_HTM[5201]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5202]="*2. Piyasuttaṃ**Liked*";
P_HTM[5203]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo ca.**“Mendicants, a resident mendicant with five qualities is dear and beloved to their spiritual companions, respected and admired.*";
P_HTM[5204]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5205]="*Sīlavā hoti, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati ācāragocarasampanno aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu;**They’re ethical, restrained in the monastic code, conducting themselves well and seeking alms in suitable places. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken.*";
P_HTM[5206]="*bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo, ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpāssa dhammā bahussutā honti dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā;**They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering them, reinforcing them by recitation, mentally scrutinizing them, and comprehending them theoretically.*";
P_HTM[5207]="*kalyāṇavāco hoti kalyāṇavākkaraṇo poriyā vācāya samannāgato vissaṭṭhāya anelagalāya atthassa viññāpaniyā;**They’re a good speaker, with a polished, clear, and articulate voice that expresses the meaning.*";
P_HTM[5208]="*catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī;**They get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that belong to the higher mind—when they want, without trouble or difficulty.*";
P_HTM[5209]="*āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati.**They realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[5210]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu sabrahmacārīnaṃ piyo ca hoti manāpo ca garu ca bhāvanīyo cā”ti.**A resident mendicant with these five qualities is dear and beloved to their spiritual companions, respected and admired.”*";
P_HTM[5211]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5212]="*3. Sobhanasuttaṃ**Beautification*";
P_HTM[5213]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu āvāsaṃ sobheti.**“Mendicants, a resident mendicant with five qualities beautifies the monastery.*";
P_HTM[5214]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5215]="*Sīlavā hoti … pe … samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu;**They’re ethical, restrained in the code of conduct, with good behavior and supporters. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken.*";
P_HTM[5216]="*bahussuto hoti … pe … diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā;**They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s totally full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering them, reciting them, mentally scrutinizing them, and understanding them with right view.*";
P_HTM[5217]="*kalyāṇavāco hoti kalyāṇavākkaraṇo poriyā vācāya samannāgato vissaṭṭhāya anelagalāya atthassa viññāpaniyā;**They’re a good speaker, with a polished, clear, and articulate voice that expresses the meaning.*";
P_HTM[5218]="*paṭibalo hoti upasaṅkamante dhammiyā kathāya sandassetuṃ samādapetuṃ samuttejetuṃ sampahaṃsetuṃ;**They’re able to educate, encourage, fire up, and inspire those who approach them with a Dhamma talk.*";
P_HTM[5219]="*catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī.**They get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that belong to the higher mind—when they want, without trouble or difficulty.*";
P_HTM[5220]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu āvāsaṃ sobhetī”ti.**A resident mendicant with these five qualities beautifies the monastery.”*";
P_HTM[5221]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5222]="*4. Bahūpakārasuttaṃ**Very Helpful*";
P_HTM[5223]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu āvāsassa bahūpakāro hoti.**“Mendicants, a resident mendicant with five qualities is very helpful to the monastery.*";
P_HTM[5224]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5225]="*Sīlavā hoti … pe … samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu;**They’re ethical, restrained in the code of conduct, with good behavior and supporters. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken.*";
P_HTM[5226]="*bahussuto hoti … pe … diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā;**They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s totally full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering them, reciting them, mentally scrutinizing them, and understanding them with right view.*";
P_HTM[5227]="*khaṇḍaphullaṃ paṭisaṅkharoti;**They repair what is decayed and damaged.*";
P_HTM[5228]="*mahā kho pana bhikkhusaṅgho abhikkanto nānāverajjakā bhikkhū gihīnaṃ upasaṅkamitvā āroceti:**When a large mendicant Saṅgha is arriving with mendicants from abroad, they go to the lay people and announce:*";
P_HTM[5229]="*‘mahā kho, āvuso, bhikkhusaṅgho abhikkanto nānāverajjakā bhikkhū, karotha puññāni, samayo puññāni kātun’ti;**‘A large mendicant Saṅgha is arriving with mendicants from abroad. Make merit! Now is the time to make merit!’*";
P_HTM[5230]="*catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī.**They get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that belong to the higher mind—when they want, without trouble or difficulty.*";
P_HTM[5231]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu āvāsassa bahūpakāro hotī”ti.**A resident mendicant with these five qualities is very helpful to the monastery.”*";
P_HTM[5232]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5233]="*5. Anukampasuttaṃ**A Compassionate Mendicant*";
P_HTM[5234]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu gihīnaṃ anukampati.**“Mendicants, a resident mendicant with five qualities shows compassion to the lay people.*";
P_HTM[5235]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5236]="*Adhisīle samādapeti;**They encourage them in higher ethics.*";
P_HTM[5237]="*dhammadassane niveseti;**They equip them to see the truth of the teachings.*";
P_HTM[5238]="*gilānake upasaṅkamitvā satiṃ uppādeti:**When they are sick, they go to them and prompt their mindfulness, saying:*";
P_HTM[5239]="*‘arahaggataṃ āyasmanto satiṃ upaṭṭhāpethā’ti;**‘Establish your mindfulness, good sirs, in what is worthy.’*";
P_HTM[5240]="*mahā kho pana bhikkhusaṃgho abhikkanto nānāverajjakā bhikkhū gihīnaṃ upasaṅkamitvā āroceti:**When a large mendicant Saṅgha is arriving with mendicants from abroad, they go to the lay people and announce:*";
P_HTM[5241]="*‘mahā kho, āvuso, bhikkhusaṃgho abhikkanto nānāverajjakā bhikkhū, karotha puññāni, samayo puññāni kātun’ti;**‘A large mendicant Saṅgha is arriving with mendicants from abroad. Make merit! Now is the time to make merit!’*";
P_HTM[5242]="*yaṃ kho panassa bhojanaṃ denti lūkhaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā taṃ attanā paribhuñjati, saddhādeyyaṃ na vinipāteti.**And they eat whatever food they give them, coarse or fine, not wasting a gift given in faith.*";
P_HTM[5243]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu gihīnaṃ anukampatī”ti.**A resident mendicant with these five qualities shows compassion to the lay people.”*";
P_HTM[5244]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5245]="*6. Paṭhamaavaṇṇārahasuttaṃ**Deserving Criticism (1st)*";
P_HTM[5246]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, a resident mendicant with five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[5247]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5248]="*Ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā avaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;**Without examining or scrutinizing, they praise those deserving of criticism,*";
P_HTM[5249]="*ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā vaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;**and they criticize those deserving of praise.*";
P_HTM[5250]="*ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā appasādanīye ṭhāne pasādaṃ upadaṃseti;**Without examining or scrutinizing, they arouse faith in things that are dubious,*";
P_HTM[5251]="*ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā pasādanīye ṭhāne appasādaṃ upadaṃseti;**and they don’t arouse faith in things that are inspiring.*";
P_HTM[5252]="*saddhādeyyaṃ vinipāteti.**And they waste a gift given in faith.*";
P_HTM[5253]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**A resident mendicant with these five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[5254]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.**A resident mendicant with five qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[5255]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5256]="*Anuvicca pariyogāhetvā avaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;**After examining and scrutinizing, they criticize those deserving of criticism,*";
P_HTM[5257]="*anuvicca pariyogāhetvā vaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;**and they praise those deserving of praise.*";
P_HTM[5258]="*anuvicca pariyogāhetvā appasādanīye ṭhāne appasādaṃ upadaṃseti;**They don’t arouse faith in things that are dubious,*";
P_HTM[5259]="*anuvicca pariyogāhetvā pasādanīye ṭhāne pasādaṃ upadaṃseti;**and they do arouse faith in things that are inspiring.*";
P_HTM[5260]="*saddhādeyyaṃ na vinipāteti.**And they don’t waste a gift given in faith.*";
P_HTM[5261]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.**A resident mendicant with these five qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[5262]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5263]="*7. Dutiyaavaṇṇārahasuttaṃ**Deserving Criticism (2nd)*";
P_HTM[5264]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, a resident mendicant with five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[5265]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5266]="*Ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā avaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;**Without examining or scrutinizing, they praise those deserving of criticism,*";
P_HTM[5267]="*ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā vaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;**and they criticize those deserving of praise.*";
P_HTM[5268]="*āvāsamaccharī hoti āvāsapaligedhī;**They’re stingy and avaricious regarding monasteries.*";
P_HTM[5269]="*kulamaccharī hoti kulapaligedhī;**They’re stingy and avaricious regarding families.*";
P_HTM[5270]="*saddhādeyyaṃ vinipāteti.**And they waste a gift given in faith.*";
P_HTM[5271]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**A resident mendicant with these five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[5272]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.**A resident mendicant with five qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[5273]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5274]="*Anuvicca pariyogāhetvā avaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;**After examining and scrutinizing, they criticize those deserving of criticism,*";
P_HTM[5275]="*anuvicca pariyogāhetvā vaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;**and they praise those deserving of praise.*";
P_HTM[5276]="*na āvāsamaccharī hoti na āvāsapaligedhī;**They’re not stingy and avaricious regarding monasteries.*";
P_HTM[5277]="*na kulamaccharī hoti na kulapaligedhī;**They’re not stingy and avaricious regarding families.*";
P_HTM[5278]="*saddhādeyyaṃ na vinipāteti.**And they don’t waste a gift given in faith.*";
P_HTM[5279]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.**A resident mendicant with these five qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[5280]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5281]="*8. Tatiyaavaṇṇārahasuttaṃ**Deserving Criticism (3rd)*";
P_HTM[5282]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato āvāsiko bhikkhu yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, a resident mendicant with five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[5283]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5284]="*Ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā avaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;**Without examining or scrutinizing, they praise those deserving of criticism,*";
