P_HTM[5335]="*Āvāsikavaggo catuttho.* **";
P_HTM[5336]="*Āvāsiko piyo ca sobhano,* **";
P_HTM[5337]="*Bahūpakāro anukampako ca;* **";
P_HTM[5338]="*Tayo avaṇṇārahā ceva,* **";
P_HTM[5339]="*Macchariyā duvepi cāti.* **";
P_HTM[5340]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**Bad Conduct*";
P_HTM[5341]="*1. Paṭhamaduccaritasuttaṃ**Bad Conduct (1st)*";
P_HTM[5342]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā duccarite.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks of bad conduct.*";
P_HTM[5343]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5344]="*Attāpi attānaṃ upavadati;**You blame yourself.*";
P_HTM[5345]="*anuvicca viññū garahanti;**After examination, sensible people criticize you.*";
P_HTM[5346]="*pāpako kittisaddo abbhuggacchati;**You get a bad reputation.*";
P_HTM[5347]="*sammūḷho kālaṃ karoti;**You feel lost when you die.*";
P_HTM[5348]="*kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati.**And when your body breaks up, after death, you’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[5349]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā duccarite.**These are the five drawbacks of bad conduct.*";
P_HTM[5350]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, ānisaṃsā sucarite.**There are these five benefits of good conduct.*";
P_HTM[5351]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5352]="*Attāpi attānaṃ na upavadati;**You don’t blame yourself.*";
P_HTM[5353]="*anuvicca viññū pasaṃsanti;**After examination, sensible people praise you.*";
P_HTM[5354]="*kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggacchati;**You get a good reputation.*";
P_HTM[5355]="*asammūḷho kālaṃ karoti;**You don’t feel lost when you die.*";
P_HTM[5356]="*kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati.**When your body breaks up, after death, you’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.*";
P_HTM[5357]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā sucarite”ti.**These are the five benefits of good conduct.”*";
P_HTM[5358]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5359]="*2. Paṭhamakāyaduccaritasuttaṃ**Bad Bodily Conduct (1st)*";
P_HTM[5360]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā kāyaduccarite … pe … ānisaṃsā kāyasucarite … pe ….**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks in bad bodily conduct … benefits in good bodily conduct …”*";
P_HTM[5361]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5362]="*3. Paṭhamavacīduccaritasuttaṃ**Bad Verbal Conduct (1st)*";
P_HTM[5363]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā vacīduccarite … pe … ānisaṃsā vacīsucarite … pe ….**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks in bad verbal conduct … benefits in good verbal conduct …”*";
P_HTM[5364]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5365]="*4. Paṭhamamanoduccaritasuttaṃ**Bad Mental Conduct (1st)*";
P_HTM[5366]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā manoduccarite … pe … ānisaṃsā manosucarite.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks in bad mental conduct … benefits in good mental conduct …”*";
P_HTM[5367]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[5368]="*Attāpi attānaṃ na upavadati;* **";
P_HTM[5369]="*anuvicca viññū pasaṃsanti;* **";
P_HTM[5370]="*kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggacchati;* **";
P_HTM[5371]="*asammūḷho kālaṃ karoti;* **";
P_HTM[5372]="*kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati.* **";
P_HTM[5373]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā manosucarite”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5374]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5375]="*5. Dutiyaduccaritasuttaṃ**Bad Conduct (2nd)*";
P_HTM[5376]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā duccarite.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks of bad conduct.*";
P_HTM[5377]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5378]="*Attāpi attānaṃ upavadati;**You blame yourself.*";
P_HTM[5379]="*anuvicca viññū garahanti;**After examination, sensible people criticize you.*";
P_HTM[5380]="*pāpako kittisaddo abbhuggacchati;**You get a bad reputation.*";
P_HTM[5381]="*saddhammā vuṭṭhāti;**You drift away from true teachings.*";
P_HTM[5382]="*asaddhamme patiṭṭhāti.**You settle on untrue teachings.*";
P_HTM[5383]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā duccarite.**These are the five drawbacks of bad conduct.*";
P_HTM[5384]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, ānisaṃsā sucarite.**There are these five benefits of good conduct.*";
P_HTM[5385]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5386]="*Attāpi attānaṃ na upavadati;**You don’t blame yourself.*";
P_HTM[5387]="*anuvicca viññū pasaṃsanti;**After examination, sensible people praise you.*";
P_HTM[5388]="*kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggacchati;**You get a good reputation.*";
P_HTM[5389]="*asaddhammā vuṭṭhāti;**You drift away from untrue teachings.*";
P_HTM[5390]="*saddhamme patiṭṭhāti.**You settle on true teachings.*";
P_HTM[5391]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā sucarite”ti.**These are the five benefits of good conduct.”*";
P_HTM[5392]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5393]="*6. Dutiyakāyaduccaritasuttaṃ**Bad Bodily Conduct (2nd)*";
P_HTM[5394]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā kāyaduccarite … pe … ānisaṃsā kāyasucarite … pe ….**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks in bad bodily conduct … benefits in good bodily conduct …”*";
P_HTM[5395]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5396]="*7. Dutiyavacīduccaritasuttaṃ**Bad Verbal Conduct (2nd)*";
P_HTM[5397]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā vacīduccarite … pe … ānisaṃsā vacīsucarite … pe ….**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks in bad verbal conduct … benefits in good verbal conduct …”*";
P_HTM[5398]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5399]="*8. Dutiyamanoduccaritasuttaṃ**Bad Mental Conduct (2nd)*";
P_HTM[5400]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā manoduccarite … pe … ānisaṃsā manosucarite.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks in bad mental conduct … benefits in good mental conduct …”*";
P_HTM[5401]="*Katame pañca?* **";
P_HTM[5402]="*Attāpi attānaṃ na upavadati;* **";
P_HTM[5403]="*anuvicca viññū pasaṃsanti;* **";
P_HTM[5404]="*kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggacchati;* **";
P_HTM[5405]="*asaddhammā vuṭṭhāti;* **";
P_HTM[5406]="*saddhamme patiṭṭhāti.* **";
P_HTM[5407]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā manosucarite”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5408]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5409]="*9. Sivathikasuttaṃ**A Charnel Ground*";
P_HTM[5410]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā sivathikāya.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks to a charnel ground.*";
P_HTM[5411]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5412]="*Asuci, duggandhā, sappaṭibhayā, vāḷānaṃ amanussānaṃ āvāso, bahuno janassa ārodanā—**It’s filthy, stinking, frightening, a gathering place for savage monsters, and a weeping place for many people.*";
P_HTM[5413]="*ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā sivathikāya.**These are the five drawbacks of a charnel ground.*";
P_HTM[5414]="*Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcime ādīnavā sivathikūpame puggale.**In the same way there are five drawbacks of a person like a charnel ground.*";
P_HTM[5415]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5416]="*Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo asucinā kāyakammena samannāgato hoti;**To start with, some person has filthy conduct by way of body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[5417]="*asucinā vacīkammena samannāgato hoti;* **";
P_HTM[5418]="*asucinā manokammena samannāgato hoti.* **";
P_HTM[5419]="*Idamassa asucitāya vadāmi.**This is how they’re filthy, I say.*";
P_HTM[5420]="*Seyyathāpi sā, bhikkhave, sivathikā asuci;**That person is just as filthy as a charnel ground.*";
P_HTM[5421]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[5422]="*Tassa asucinā kāyakammena samannāgatassa, asucinā vacīkammena samannāgatassa, asucinā manokammena samannāgatassa pāpako kittisaddo abbhuggacchati.**Because of their filthy conduct, they get a bad reputation.*";
P_HTM[5423]="*Idamassa duggandhatāya vadāmi.**This is how they’re stinky, I say.*";
P_HTM[5424]="*Seyyathāpi sā, bhikkhave, sivathikā duggandhā;**That person is just as stinky as a charnel ground.*";
P_HTM[5425]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[5426]="*Tamenaṃ asucinā kāyakammena samannāgataṃ, asucinā vacīkammena samannāgataṃ, asucinā manokammena samannāgataṃ pesalā sabrahmacārī ārakā parivajjanti.**Because of their filthy conduct, good-hearted spiritual companions avoid them from afar.*";
P_HTM[5427]="*Idamassa sappaṭibhayasmiṃ vadāmi.**That’s how they’re frightening, I say.*";
P_HTM[5428]="*Seyyathāpi sā, bhikkhave, sivathikā sappaṭibhayā;**That person is just as frightening as a charnel ground.*";
P_HTM[5429]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[5430]="*So asucinā kāyakammena samannāgato, asucinā vacīkammena samannāgato, asucinā manokammena samannāgato sabhāgehi puggalehi saddhiṃ saṃvasati.**Because of their filthy conduct, they live together with people of a similar character.*";
P_HTM[5431]="*Idamassa vāḷāvāsasmiṃ vadāmi.**This is how they gather with savage monsters, I say.*";
P_HTM[5432]="*Seyyathāpi sā, bhikkhave, sivathikā vāḷānaṃ amanussānaṃ āvāso;**That person is just as much a gathering place of savage monsters as a charnel ground.*";
P_HTM[5433]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[5434]="*Tamenaṃ asucinā kāyakammena samannāgataṃ, asucinā vacīkammena samannāgataṃ, asucinā manokammena samannāgataṃ pesalā sabrahmacārī disvā khīyadhammaṃ āpajjanti:**Because of their filthy conduct, when good-hearted spiritual companions see them they complain:*";
P_HTM[5435]="*‘aho vata no dukkhaṃ ye mayaṃ evarūpehi puggalehi saddhiṃ saṃvasāmā’ti.**‘Oh, it’s so painful for us to have to live together with such as these.’*";
P_HTM[5436]="*Idamassa ārodanāya vadāmi.**This is how there’s weeping, I say.*";
P_HTM[5437]="*Seyyathāpi sā, bhikkhave, sivathikā bahuno janassa ārodanā;**This person is just as much a weeping place for many people as a charnel ground.*";
P_HTM[5438]="*tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[5439]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā sivathikūpame puggale”ti.**These are the five drawbacks of a person like a charnel ground.”*";
P_HTM[5440]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5441]="*10. Puggalappasādasuttaṃ**Faith in Individuals*";
P_HTM[5442]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā puggalappasāde.**“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks of placing faith in an individual.*";
P_HTM[5443]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5444]="*Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, puggale puggalo abhippasanno hoti, so tathārūpaṃ āpattiṃ āpanno hoti yathārūpāya āpattiyā saṅgho ukkhipati.**The individual to whom a person is devoted falls into an offense such that the Saṅgha suspends them.*";
P_HTM[5445]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**It occurs to them:*";
P_HTM[5446]="*‘yo kho myāyaṃ puggalo piyo manāpo so saṅghena ukkhitto’ti.**‘This person dear and beloved to me has been suspended by the Saṅgha.’*";
P_HTM[5447]="*Bhikkhūsu appasādabahulo hoti.**They lose much of their faith in mendicants.*";
P_HTM[5448]="*Bhikkhūsu appasādabahulo samāno aññe bhikkhū na bhajati.**So they don’t frequent other mendicants,*";
P_HTM[5449]="*Aññe bhikkhū abhajanto saddhammaṃ na suṇāti.**they don’t hear the true teaching,*";
P_HTM[5450]="*Saddhammaṃ asuṇanto saddhammā parihāyati.**and they fall away from the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[5451]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo ādīnavo puggalappasāde.**This is the first drawback in placing faith in an individual.*";
P_HTM[5452]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, yasmiṃ puggale puggalo abhippasanno hoti, so tathārūpaṃ āpattiṃ āpanno hoti yathārūpāya āpattiyā saṅgho ante nisīdāpeti.**Furthermore, the individual to whom a person is devoted falls into an offense such that the Saṅgha makes them sit at the end of the line. …*";
P_HTM[5453]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:* **";
P_HTM[5454]="*‘yo kho myāyaṃ puggalo piyo manāpo so saṅghena ante nisīdāpito’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5455]="*Bhikkhūsu appasādabahulo hoti.* **";
P_HTM[5456]="*Bhikkhūsu appasādabahulo samāno aññe bhikkhū na bhajati.* **";
P_HTM[5457]="*Aññe bhikkhū abhajanto saddhammaṃ na suṇāti.* **";
P_HTM[5458]="*Saddhammaṃ asuṇanto saddhammā parihāyati.* **";
P_HTM[5459]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo ādīnavo puggalappasāde.**This is the second drawback in placing faith in an individual.*";
P_HTM[5460]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, yasmiṃ puggale puggalo abhippasanno hoti, so disāpakkanto hoti … pe … so vibbhanto hoti … pe … so kālaṅkato hoti.**Furthermore, the individual to whom a person is devoted departs for another region … disrobes … passes away.*";
P_HTM[5461]="*Tassa evaṃ hoti:**It occurs to them:*";
P_HTM[5462]="*‘yo kho myāyaṃ puggalo piyo manāpo so kālaṅkato’ti.**‘This person dear and beloved to me has passed away.’*";
P_HTM[5463]="*Aññe bhikkhū na bhajati.**So they don’t frequent other mendicants,*";
P_HTM[5464]="*Aññe bhikkhū abhajanto saddhammaṃ na suṇāti.**they don’t hear the true teaching,*";
P_HTM[5465]="*Saddhammaṃ asuṇanto saddhammā parihāyati.**and they fall away from the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[5466]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo ādīnavo puggalappasāde.**This is the fifth drawback in placing faith in an individual.*";
P_HTM[5467]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā puggalappasāde”ti.**These are the five drawbacks of placing faith in an individual.”*";
P_HTM[5468]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5469]="*Duccaritavaggo pañcamo.* **";
P_HTM[5470]="*Duccaritaṃ kāyaduccaritaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[5471]="*Vacīduccaritaṃ manoduccaritaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[5472]="*Catūhi pare dve sivathikā,* **";
P_HTM[5473]="*Puggalappasādena cāti.* **";
P_HTM[5474]="*Pañcamo paṇṇāsako samatto.* **";
P_HTM[5475]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**Ordination*";
P_HTM[5476]="*1. Upasampādetabbasuttaṃ**Who Should Give Ordination*";
P_HTM[5477]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā upasampādetabbaṃ.**“Mendicants, ordination should be given by a mendicant with five qualities.*";
P_HTM[5478]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5479]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu asekhena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato hoti;**It’s a mendicant who has the entire spectrum of an adept’s ethics,*";
P_HTM[5480]="*asekhena samādhikkhandhena samannāgato hoti;**immersion,*";
P_HTM[5481]="*asekhena paññākkhandhena samannāgato hoti;**wisdom,*";
P_HTM[5482]="*asekhena vimuttikkhandhena samannāgato hoti;**freedom,*";
P_HTM[5483]="*asekhena vimuttiñāṇadassanakkhandhena samannāgato hoti.**and the knowledge and vision of freedom.*";
P_HTM[5484]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā upasampādetabban”ti.**Ordination should be given by a mendicant with these five qualities.”*";
P_HTM[5485]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5486]="*2. Nissayasuttaṃ**Who Should Give Dependence*";
P_HTM[5487]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā nissayo dātabbo.**“Mendicants, dependence should be given by a mendicant with five qualities.*";
P_HTM[5488]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5489]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu asekhena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato hoti … pe … asekhena vimuttiñāṇadassanakkhandhena samannāgato hoti.**It’s a mendicant who has the entire spectrum of an adept’s ethics, immersion, wisdom, freedom, and the knowledge and vision of freedom.*";
P_HTM[5490]="*Imehi … pe … nissayo dātabbo”ti.**Dependence should be given by a mendicant with these five qualities.”*";
P_HTM[5491]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5492]="*3. Sāmaṇerasuttaṃ**Who Should Have a Novice as Attendant*";
P_HTM[5493]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo.**“Mendicants, a novice should attend on a mendicant with five qualities.*";
P_HTM[5494]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5495]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu asekhena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato hoti; asekhena samādhikkhandhena … asekhena paññākkhandhena … asekhena vimuttikkhandhena … asekhena vimuttiñāṇadassanakkhandhena samannāgato hoti.**It’s a mendicant who has the entire spectrum of an adept’s ethics, immersion, wisdom, freedom, and the knowledge and vision of freedom.*";
P_HTM[5496]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgatena bhikkhunā sāmaṇero upaṭṭhāpetabbo”ti.**A novice should attend on a mendicant with these five qualities.”*";
P_HTM[5497]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5498]="*4. Pañcamacchariyasuttaṃ**Five Kinds of Stinginess*";
P_HTM[5499]="*“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, macchariyāni.**“Mendicants, there are these five kinds of stinginess.*";
P_HTM[5500]="*Katamāni pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5501]="*Āvāsamacchariyaṃ, kulamacchariyaṃ, lābhamacchariyaṃ, vaṇṇamacchariyaṃ, dhammamacchariyaṃ—**Stinginess with dwellings, families, material possessions, praise, and the teachings.*";
P_HTM[5502]="*imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca macchariyāni.**These are the five kinds of stinginess.*";
P_HTM[5503]="*Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ macchariyānaṃ etaṃ paṭikuṭṭhaṃ, yadidaṃ dhammamacchariyan”ti.**The most contemptible of these five kinds of stinginess is stinginess with the teachings.”*";
P_HTM[5504]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5505]="*5. Macchariyappahānasuttaṃ**Giving Up Stinginess*";
P_HTM[5506]="*“Pañcannaṃ, bhikkhave, macchariyānaṃ pahānāya samucchedāya brahmacariyaṃ vussati.**“Mendicants, the spiritual life is lived to give up and cut out these five kinds of stinginess.*";
P_HTM[5507]="*Katamesaṃ pañcannaṃ?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5508]="*Āvāsamacchariyassa pahānāya samucchedāya brahmacariyaṃ vussati;**Stinginess with dwellings, families, material possessions, praise, and the teachings.*";
P_HTM[5509]="*kulamacchariyassa … lābhamacchariyassa … vaṇṇamacchariyassa … dhammamacchariyassa pahānāya samucchedāya brahmacariyaṃ vussati.* **";
P_HTM[5510]="*Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ macchariyānaṃ pahānāya samucchedāya brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti.**The spiritual life is lived to give up and cut out these five kinds of stinginess.”*";
P_HTM[5511]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5512]="*6. Paṭhamajhānasuttaṃ**The First Absorption*";
P_HTM[5513]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhamme appahāya abhabbo paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharituṃ.**“Mendicants, without giving up these five qualities you can’t enter and remain in the first absorption.*";
P_HTM[5514]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5515]="*Āvāsamacchariyaṃ, kulamacchariyaṃ, lābhamacchariyaṃ, vaṇṇamacchariyaṃ, dhammamacchariyaṃ.**Stinginess with dwellings, families, material possessions, praise, and the teachings.*";
P_HTM[5516]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhamme appahāya abhabbo paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharituṃ.**Without giving up these five qualities you can’t enter and remain in the first absorption.*";
P_HTM[5517]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhamme pahāya bhabbo paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharituṃ.**But after giving up these five qualities you can enter and remain in the first absorption.*";
P_HTM[5518]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5519]="*Āvāsamacchariyaṃ, kulamacchariyaṃ, lābhamacchariyaṃ, vaṇṇamacchariyaṃ, dhammamacchariyaṃ.**Stinginess with dwellings, families, material possessions, praise, and the teachings.*";
P_HTM[5520]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhamme pahāya bhabbo paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharitun”ti.**After giving up these five qualities you can enter and remain in the first absorption.”*";
P_HTM[5521]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5522]="*7-13. Dutiyajhānasuttādisattakaṃ**257–263. Dutiyajhānasuttādisattaka*";
P_HTM[5523]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhamme appahāya abhabbo dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … abhabbo tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … abhabbo catutthaṃ jhānaṃ … abhabbo sotāpattiphalaṃ … abhabbo sakadāgāmiphalaṃ … abhabbo anāgāmiphalaṃ … abhabbo arahattaṃ sacchikātuṃ.**“Mendicants, without giving up these five qualities you can’t enter and remain in the second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption … or realize the fruit of stream-entry … the fruit of once-return … the fruit of non-return … perfection.*";
P_HTM[5524]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5525]="*Āvāsamacchariyaṃ, kulamacchariyaṃ, lābhamacchariyaṃ, vaṇṇamacchariyaṃ, dhammamacchariyaṃ.**Stinginess with dwellings, families, material possessions, praise, and the teachings.*";
P_HTM[5526]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhamme appahāya abhabbo arahattaṃ sacchikātuṃ.**Without giving up these five qualities you can’t realize perfection.*";
P_HTM[5527]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhamme pahāya bhabbo dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … bhabbo tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … bhabbo catutthaṃ jhānaṃ … bhabbo sotāpattiphalaṃ … bhabbo sakadāgāmiphalaṃ … bhabbo anāgāmiphalaṃ … bhabbo arahattaṃ sacchikātuṃ.**But after giving up these five qualities you can enter and remain in the second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption … and realize the fruit of stream-entry … the fruit of once-return … the fruit of non-return … perfection.*";
P_HTM[5528]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5529]="*Āvāsamacchariyaṃ, kulamacchariyaṃ, lābhamacchariyaṃ, vaṇṇamacchariyaṃ, dhammamacchariyaṃ.**Stinginess with dwellings, families, material possessions, praise, and the teachings.*";
P_HTM[5530]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhamme pahāya bhabbo arahattaṃ sacchikātun”ti.**After giving up these five qualities you can realize perfection.”*";
P_HTM[5531]="*Terasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5532]="*14. Aparapaṭhamajhānasuttaṃ**Another Discourse on the First Absorption*";
P_HTM[5533]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhamme appahāya abhabbo paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharituṃ.**“Mendicants, without giving up these five qualities you can’t enter and remain in the first absorption.*";
P_HTM[5534]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5535]="*Āvāsamacchariyaṃ, kulamacchariyaṃ, lābhamacchariyaṃ, vaṇṇamacchariyaṃ, akataññutaṃ akataveditaṃ.**Stinginess with dwellings, families, material possessions, praise, and lack of gratitude and thankfulness.*";
P_HTM[5536]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhamme appahāya abhabbo paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharituṃ.**Without giving up these five qualities you can’t enter and remain in the first absorption.*";
P_HTM[5537]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhamme pahāya bhabbo paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharituṃ.**But after giving up these five qualities you can enter and remain in the first absorption.*";
P_HTM[5538]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5539]="*Āvāsamacchariyaṃ, kulamacchariyaṃ, lābhamacchariyaṃ, vaṇṇamacchariyaṃ, akataññutaṃ akataveditaṃ.**Stinginess with dwellings, families, material possessions, praise, and lack of gratitude and thankfulness.*";
P_HTM[5540]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhamme pahāya bhabbo paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharitun”ti.**After giving up these five qualities you can enter and remain in the first absorption.”*";
P_HTM[5541]="*Cuddasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5542]="*15-21. Aparadutiyajhānasuttādisattakaṃ**265–271. Aparadutiyajhānasuttādi*";
P_HTM[5543]="*“Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhamme appahāya abhabbo dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ … sotāpattiphalaṃ … sakadāgāmiphalaṃ … anāgāmiphalaṃ … arahattaṃ sacchikātuṃ.**“Mendicants, without giving up these five qualities you can’t enter and remain in the second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption … or realize the fruit of stream-entry … the fruit of once-return … the fruit of non-return … perfection.*";
P_HTM[5544]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5545]="*Āvāsamacchariyaṃ, kulamacchariyaṃ, lābhamacchariyaṃ, vaṇṇamacchariyaṃ, akataññutaṃ akataveditaṃ.**Stinginess with dwellings, families, material possessions, praise, and lack of gratitude and thankfulness.*";
P_HTM[5546]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhamme appahāya abhabbo arahattaṃ sacchikātuṃ.**Without giving up these five qualities you can’t realize perfection.*";
P_HTM[5547]="*Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhamme pahāya bhabbo dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ … sotāpattiphalaṃ … sakadāgāmiphalaṃ … anāgāmiphalaṃ … arahattaṃ sacchikātuṃ.**But after giving up these five qualities you can enter and remain in the second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption … and realize the fruit of stream-entry … the fruit of once-return … the fruit of non-return … perfection.*";
P_HTM[5548]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5549]="*Āvāsamacchariyaṃ, kulamacchariyaṃ, lābhamacchariyaṃ, vaṇṇamacchariyaṃ, akataññutaṃ akataveditaṃ.**Stinginess with dwellings, families, material possessions, praise, and lack of gratitude and thankfulness.*";
P_HTM[5550]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhamme pahāya bhabbo arahattaṃ sacchikātun”ti.**After giving up these five qualities you can realize perfection.”*";
P_HTM[5551]="*Ekavīsatimaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5552]="*Upasampadāvaggo chaṭṭho.* **";
P_HTM[5553]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**Abbreviated Texts on Appointments*";
P_HTM[5554]="*1. Bhattuddesakasuttaṃ**A Meal Assigner*";
P_HTM[5555]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhattuddesako na sammannitabbo.**“Mendicants, a person with five qualities should not be appointed as meal assigner.*";
P_HTM[5556]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5557]="*Chandāgatiṃ gacchati, dosāgatiṃ gacchati, mohāgatiṃ gacchati, bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, uddiṭṭhānuddiṭṭhaṃ na jānāti.**They make decisions prejudiced by favoritism, hostility, stupidity, and cowardice. And they don’t know if a meal has been assigned or not.*";
P_HTM[5558]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhattuddesako na sammannitabbo.**A person with these five qualities should not be appointed as meal assigner.*";
P_HTM[5559]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhattuddesako sammannitabbo.**A person with five qualities should be appointed as meal assigner.*";
P_HTM[5560]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5561]="*Na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, na dosāgatiṃ gacchati, na mohāgatiṃ gacchati, na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, uddiṭṭhānuddiṭṭhaṃ jānāti.**They don’t make decisions prejudiced by favoritism, hostility, stupidity, and cowardice. And they know if a meal has been assigned or not.*";
P_HTM[5562]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhattuddesako sammannitabboti.**A person with these five qualities should be appointed as meal assigner.*";
P_HTM[5563]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhattuddesako sammato na pesetabbo … pe … sammato pesetabbo … bālo veditabbo … paṇḍito veditabbo … khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati … akkhataṃ anupahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati … yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye … yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.**A person with five qualities who has been appointed as meal assigner should not be called upon … should be called upon … should be known as a fool … should be known as astute … they keep themselves broken and damaged … they keep themselves unbroken and undamaged … is cast down to hell … is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[5564]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5565]="*Na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, na dosāgatiṃ gacchati, na mohāgatiṃ gacchati, na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, uddiṭṭhānuddiṭṭhaṃ jānāti.**They don’t make decisions prejudiced by favoritism, hostility, stupidity, and cowardice. And they know if a meal has been assigned or not.*";
P_HTM[5566]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhattuddesako yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.**A meal assigner with these five qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[5567]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5568]="*2-14. Senāsanapaññāpakasuttāditerasakaṃ**273–285. Senāsanapaññāpakasuttādi*";
P_HTM[5569]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato senāsanapaññāpako na sammannitabbo … pe … paññattāpaññattaṃ na jānāti … pe … senāsanapaññāpako sammannitabbo … pe … paññattāpaññattaṃ jānāti … pe ….**“Mendicants, a person with five qualities should not be appointed as lodgings assigner … they don’t know if a lodging has been assigned or not … A person with five qualities should be appointed as lodgings assigner … they know if a lodging has been assigned or not …*";
P_HTM[5570]="*Senāsanagāhāpako na sammannitabbo … pe … gahitāgahitaṃ na jānāti … pe … senāsanagāhāpako sammannitabbo … pe … gahitāgahitaṃ jānāti … pe ….**A person should not be appointed as lodgings allocator … they don’t know if a lodging has been allocated or not … A person should be appointed as lodgings allocator … they know if a lodging has been allocated or not …*";
P_HTM[5571]="*Bhaṇḍāgāriko na sammannitabbo … pe … guttāguttaṃ na jānāti … bhaṇḍāgāriko sammannitabbo … pe … guttāguttaṃ jānāti ….**A person should not be appointed as storeperson … they don’t know if stores are protected or not … A person should be appointed as storeperson … they know if stores are protected or not …*";
P_HTM[5572]="*Cīvarapaṭiggāhako na sammannitabbo … pe … gahitāgahitaṃ na jānāti … cīvarapaṭiggāhako sammannitabbo … pe … gahitāgahitaṃ jānāti ….**… robe receiver …*";
P_HTM[5573]="*Cīvarabhājako na sammannitabbo … pe … bhājitābhājitaṃ na jānāti … cīvarabhājako sammannitabbo … pe … bhājitābhājitaṃ jānāti ….**… robe distributor …*";
P_HTM[5574]="*Yāgubhājako na sammannitabbo … pe … yāgubhājako sammannitabbo … pe ….**… porridge distributor …*";
P_HTM[5575]="*Phalabhājako na sammannitabbo … pe … phalabhājako sammannitabbo … pe ….**… fruit distributor …*";
P_HTM[5576]="*Khajjakabhājako na sammannitabbo … pe … bhājitābhājitaṃ na jānāti … khajjakabhājako sammannitabbo … pe … bhājitābhājitaṃ jānāti ….**… cake distributor …*";
P_HTM[5577]="*Appamattakavissajjako na sammannitabbo … pe … vissajjitāvissajjitaṃ na jānāti … appamattakavissajjako sammannitabbo … pe … vissajjitāvissajjitaṃ jānāti ….**… dispenser of minor accessories …*";
P_HTM[5578]="*Sāṭiyaggāhāpako na sammannitabbo … pe … gahitāgahitaṃ na jānāti … sāṭiyaggāhāpako sammannitabbo … pe … gahitāgahitaṃ jānāti ….**… allocator of bathing cloths …*";
P_HTM[5579]="*Pattaggāhāpako na sammannitabbo … pe … gahitāgahitaṃ na jānāti … pattaggāhāpako sammannitabbo … pe … gahitāgahitaṃ jānāti ….**… bowl allocator …*";
P_HTM[5580]="*Ārāmikapesako na sammannitabbo … pe … ārāmikapesako sammannitabbo … pe ….**… supervisor of monastery staff …*";
P_HTM[5581]="*Sāmaṇerapesako na sammannitabbo … pe … sāmaṇerapesako sammannitabbo … pe …. Sammato na pesetabbo … pe … sammato pesetabbo … pe ….**… supervisor of novices …*";
P_HTM[5582]="*Sāmaṇerapesako bālo veditabbo … pe … paṇḍito veditabbo … khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati … akkhataṃ anupahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati … yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye … yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.* **";
P_HTM[5583]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5584]="*Na chandāgatiṃ gacchati, na dosāgatiṃ gacchati, na mohāgatiṃ gacchati, na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati, pesitāpesitaṃ jānāti.**They don’t make decisions prejudiced by favoritism, hostility, stupidity, and cowardice. And they know if a novice has been supervised or not.*";
P_HTM[5585]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato sāmaṇerapesako yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.**A supervisor of novices with these five qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[5586]="*Cuddasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5587]="*Sammutipeyyālaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5588]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**Abbreviated Texts on Training Rules*";
P_HTM[5589]="*1. Bhikkhusuttaṃ**A Monk*";
P_HTM[5590]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, a monk with five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[5591]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5592]="*Pāṇātipātī hoti, adinnādāyī hoti, abrahmacārī hoti, musāvādī hoti, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhāyī hoti.**He kills living creatures, steals, has sex, lies, and uses alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[5593]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**A monk with these five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[5594]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge.**A monk with five qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[5595]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5596]="*Pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, abrahmacariyā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti.**He doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, have sex, lie, or use alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[5597]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge”ti.**A monk with these five qualities is raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[5598]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5599]="*2-7. Bhikkhunīsuttādichakkaṃ**287–292. Bhikkhunīsuttādi*";
P_HTM[5600]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgatā bhikkhunī … pe … sikkhamānā … sāmaṇero … sāmaṇerī … upāsako … upāsikā yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ niraye.**“A nun … trainee nun … novice monk … novice nun … layman … laywoman … with five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[5601]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5602]="*Pāṇātipātinī hoti, adinnādāyinī hoti, kāmesumicchācārinī hoti, musāvādinī hoti, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhāyinī hoti.**They kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, lie, and use alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[5603]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgatā upāsikā yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ niraye.**With these five qualities they’re cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[5604]="*Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgatā upāsikā yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ sagge.**A nun … female intern … novice monk … novice nun … layman … laywoman … with five qualities is raised up to heaven.*";
P_HTM[5605]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5606]="*Pāṇātipātā paṭiviratā hoti, adinnādānā paṭiviratā hoti, kāmesumicchācārā paṭiviratā hoti, musāvādā paṭiviratā hoti, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭiviratā hoti.**They don’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, lie, or use alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[5607]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgatā upāsikā yathābhataṃ nikkhittā evaṃ sagge”ti.**With these five qualities they’re raised up to heaven.”*";
P_HTM[5608]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5609]="*8. Ājīvakasuttaṃ**An Ājīvaka*";
P_HTM[5610]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato ājīvako yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**“Mendicants, an Ājīvaka ascetic with five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[5611]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5612]="*Pāṇātipātī hoti, adinnādāyī hoti, abrahmacārī hoti, musāvādī hoti, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhāyī hoti.**They kill living creatures, steal, have sex, lie, and use alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[5613]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato ājīvako yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye”ti.**An Ājīvaka ascetic with these five qualities is cast down to hell.”*";
P_HTM[5614]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5615]="*9-17. Nigaṇṭhasuttādinavakaṃ**294–302. Nigaṇṭhasuttādi*";
P_HTM[5616]="*“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato nigaṇṭho … muṇḍasāvako … jaṭilako … paribbājako … māgaṇḍiko … tedaṇḍiko … āruddhako … gotamako … devadhammiko yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye.**A Jain … disciple of the shavelings … a matted-hair ascetic … a wanderer … a follower of Māgaṇḍiya … a trident-bearing ascetic … a follower of the unobstructed … a follower of Gotama … one who performs rituals for the gods … with five qualities is cast down to hell.*";
P_HTM[5617]="*Katamehi pañcahi?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5618]="*Pāṇātipātī hoti, adinnādāyī hoti … pe … surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhāyī hoti.**They kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, lie, and use alcoholic drinks that cause negligence.*";
P_HTM[5619]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato devadhammiko yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye”ti.**With these five qualities they’re cast down to hell.”*";
P_HTM[5620]="*Sattarasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5621]="*Sikkhāpadapeyyālaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5622]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**303*";
P_HTM[5623]="*“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya pañca dhammā bhāvetabbā.**“For insight into greed, five things should be developed.*";
P_HTM[5624]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5625]="*Asubhasaññā, maraṇasaññā, ādīnavasaññā, āhāre paṭikūlasaññā, sabbaloke anabhiratasaññā—**The perceptions of ugliness, death, drawbacks, repulsiveness of food, and dissatisfaction with the whole world.*";
P_HTM[5626]="*rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya ime pañca dhammā bhāvetabbā”ti. (1)**For insight into greed, these five things should be developed.”*";
P_HTM[5627]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**304*";
P_HTM[5628]="*“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya pañca dhammā bhāvetabbā.**“For insight into greed, five things should be developed.*";
P_HTM[5629]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5630]="*Aniccasaññā, anattasaññā, maraṇasaññā, āhāre paṭikūlasaññā, sabbaloke anabhiratasaññā—**The perceptions of impermanence, not-self, death, repulsiveness of food, and dissatisfaction with the whole world.*";
P_HTM[5631]="*rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya ime pañca dhammā bhāvetabbā”ti. (2)**For insight into greed, these five things should be developed.”*";
P_HTM[5632]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**305*";
P_HTM[5633]="*“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya pañca dhammā bhāvetabbā.**“For insight into greed, five things should be developed.*";
P_HTM[5634]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5635]="*Aniccasaññā, anicce dukkhasaññā, dukkhe anattasaññā, pahānasaññā, virāgasaññā—**The perception of impermanence, the perception of suffering in impermanence, the perception of not-self in suffering, the perception of giving up, and the perception of fading away.*";
P_HTM[5636]="*rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya ime pañca dhammā bhāvetabbā”ti. (3)**For insight into greed, these five things should be developed.”*";
P_HTM[5637]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**306*";
P_HTM[5638]="*“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya pañca dhammā bhāvetabbā.**“For insight into greed, five things should be developed.*";
P_HTM[5639]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5640]="*Saddhindriyaṃ, vīriyindriyaṃ, satindriyaṃ, samādhindriyaṃ, paññindriyaṃ—**The faculties of faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[5641]="*rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya ime pañca dhammā bhāvetabbā”ti. (4)**For insight into greed, these five things should be developed.”*";
P_HTM[5642]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**307*";
P_HTM[5643]="*“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya pañca dhammā bhāvetabbā.**“For insight into greed, five things should be developed.*";
P_HTM[5644]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5645]="*Saddhābalaṃ, vīriyabalaṃ, satibalaṃ, samādhibalaṃ, paññābalaṃ—**The powers of faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[5646]="*rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya ime pañca dhammā bhāvetabbā”ti. (5)**For insight into greed, these five things should be developed.”*";
P_HTM[5647]="*13. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**308–1152*";
P_HTM[5648]="*“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, pariññāya … parikkhayāya … pahānāya … khayāya … vayāya … virāgāya … nirodhāya … cāgāya … paṭinissaggāya pañca dhammā bhāvetabbā.**“For the complete understanding … finishing … giving up … ending … vanishing … fading away … cessation … giving away … letting go of greed, five things should be developed.”*";
P_HTM[5649]="*Dosassa … mohassa … kodhassa … upanāhassa … makkhassa … paḷāsassa … issāya … macchariyassa … māyāya … sāṭheyyassa … thambhassa … sārambhassa … mānassa … atimānassa … madassa … pamādassa abhiññāya … pariññāya … parikkhayāya … pahānāya … khayāya … vayāya … virāgāya … nirodhāya … cāgāya … paṭinissaggāya pañca dhammā bhāvetabbā. (6–849.)**“Of hate … delusion … anger … hostility … offensiveness … contempt … jealousy … stinginess … deceit … deviousness … obstinacy … aggression … conceit … arrogance … vanity … negligence … for insight … complete understanding … finishing … giving up … ending … vanishing … fading away … cessation … giving away … letting go … five things should be developed.*";
P_HTM[5650]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[5651]="*Saddhābalaṃ, vīriyabalaṃ, satibalaṃ, samādhibalaṃ, paññābalaṃ—**The powers of faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[5652]="*pamādassa, bhikkhave, paṭinissaggāya ime pañca dhammā bhāvetabbā”ti. (850)**For the letting go of negligence, these five things should be developed.”*";
P_HTM[5653]="*Rāgapeyyālaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5654]="*Abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya,* **";
P_HTM[5655]="*Pahānāya khayāya vayena ca;* **";
P_HTM[5656]="*Virāganirodhā cāgañca,* **";
P_HTM[5657]="*Paṭinissaggo ime dasāti.* **";
P_HTM[5658]="*Pañcakanipāto niṭṭhito.* **";
P_HTM[5659]="*Sekhabalaṃ balañceva,* **";
P_HTM[5660]="*Pañcaṅgikañca sumanaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[5661]="*Muṇḍanīvaraṇañca saññañca,* **";
P_HTM[5662]="*Yodhājīvañca aṭṭhamaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[5663]="*Theraṃ kakudhaphāsuñca,* **";
P_HTM[5664]="*Andhakavindadvādasaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[5665]="*Gilānarājatikaṇḍaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[5666]="*Saddhammāghātupāsakaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[5667]="*Araññabrāhmaṇañceva,* **";
P_HTM[5668]="*Kimilakkosakaṃ tathā;* **";
P_HTM[5669]="*Dīghācārāvāsikañca,* **";
P_HTM[5670]="*Duccaritūpasampadanti.* **";
P_HTM[5671]="*Pañcakanipātapāḷi niṭṭhitā.**The Book of the Fives is finished.*";
